565897489
00:10:06.598 --> 00:10:07.048
Speaker.

62120317
00:10:07.049 --> 00:10:09.607
I welcome the announcement
of a record 100 million

1230576297
00:10:09.752 --> 00:10:12.058
expansion of GPS tagging
for domestic abusers

405973222
00:10:12.059 --> 00:10:14.568
following a pilot by
Greater London Authority,

3572287682
00:10:14.569 --> 00:10:18.307
which saw reoffending fall by up to 63%.

658222036
00:10:18.308 --> 00:10:19.711
The current plans, however,

662201353
00:10:19.712 --> 00:10:22.303
will only apply to
the highest risk offenders,

1539512508
00:10:22.304 --> 00:10:25.463
given that all domestic abuse is
serious and many perpetrators

3566752760
00:10:25.464 --> 00:10:27.368
escalate their violence upon release,

801399831
00:10:27.369 --> 00:10:30.529
I'm concerned this will allow
abusers to slip through the net.

3971896976
00:10:30.530 --> 00:10:33.537
Will the Ministers therefore
consider extending GPS tagging

2688483318
00:10:33.538 --> 00:10:35.844
to all convicted offenders
of domestic abuse,

2009972624
00:10:35.845 --> 00:10:38.654
not just those deemed high risk?

2063152773
00:10:38.655 --> 00:10:39.356
>> Ministers.

2052735609
00:10:39.357 --> 00:10:41.005
>> I thank my hon.

428942048
00:10:41.006 --> 00:10:43.011
Friend for her consistent and proactive

3229534799
00:10:43.712 --> 00:10:45.516
support for domestic abuse victims,

3785343502
00:10:45.517 --> 00:10:48.959
ensuring that it is perpetrators and not

825199826
00:10:48.960 --> 00:10:51.503
victims who are punished and restricted

1923120523
00:10:51.503 --> 00:10:55.313
is key to the domestic abuse
perpetrators on licence pilot.

89378789
00:10:55.314 --> 00:10:58.811
The pilot that will be rolled
out nationally from September.

2502777989
00:10:58.813 --> 00:11:03.064
Offenders are tagged on release
and subjected to strict

2920282656
00:11:03.756 --> 00:11:06.011
conditions like exclusion
zones and curfews.

453405927
00:11:06.012 --> 00:11:10.960
Dapol allow probation to tag
any and all offenders who are

4050119115
00:11:10.961 --> 00:11:14.514
considered to be at risk of
perpetrating domestic abuse,

3541540036
00:11:14.515 --> 00:11:18.959
but I would be happy to meet
with her about her concerns.

2483664474
00:11:18.960 --> 00:11:19.712
>> Roger Gale.

3858882848
00:11:19.713 --> 00:11:21.207
>> Thank you, Mr.

4230809523
00:11:21.208 --> 00:11:21.657
Speaker.

1914904155
00:11:21.659 --> 00:11:23.465
Further to her response to the hon.

461073853
00:11:23.466 --> 00:11:25.320
Gentleman, the Member for Lichfield,

2375169386
00:11:25.320 --> 00:11:30.429
and on the basis that justice
delayed is justice denied,

3117159428
00:11:30.430 --> 00:11:34.614
will seek to use her good office
with the Home Office to ensure

711945224
00:11:34.615 --> 00:11:38.258
that the Metropolitan Police
expedites its investigations,

3425816832
00:11:38.259 --> 00:11:41.762
so that those hundreds of women
who have suffered at the hands

1261430693
00:11:41.764 --> 00:11:44.574
of fate can at last have
the justice that they deserve.

145925162
00:11:44.575 --> 00:11:48.310
>> Ministers.

1668272786
00:11:48.311 --> 00:11:49.616
>> I thank the right hon.

278607064
00:11:49.617 --> 00:11:54.933
Member for his his question,
and he is absolutely

550533461
00:11:54.934 --> 00:11:57.761
right that justice delayed
is justice denied,

3851845015
00:11:57.762 --> 00:12:01.314
which is why this government
is taking such proactive steps

1243967415
00:12:01.315 --> 00:12:05.314
to try and reduce the delays
that victims are seeing,

2600825123
00:12:05.315 --> 00:12:09.056
and I would be happy to
meet with him and other

568966510
00:12:09.057 --> 00:12:11.063
members who I know are hugely concerned

822987316
00:12:11.064 --> 00:12:16.507
about the impact that these cases
have had on victims and survivors.

3749634668
00:12:16.508 --> 00:12:17.913
>> Katie Lam thank you, Mr.

3817150545
00:12:17.914 --> 00:12:20.867
Speaker, and I welcome
the Ministers to her place.

564275422
00:12:20.868 --> 00:12:23.325
Almost the first thing
that the Prime Minister's

2414254563
00:12:23.326 --> 00:12:24.881
new adviser on women and girls

1374313394
00:12:24.882 --> 00:12:26.839
did after she was appointed was to say

3553839292
00:12:26.840 --> 00:12:28.596
on social media that a Rouge Shah,

3802245287
00:12:28.597 --> 00:12:31.003
the recently defeated
leader of Oldham Council,

1285061594
00:12:31.003 --> 00:12:32.358
should be given a peerage.

4068388567
00:12:32.358 --> 00:12:35.662
This is despite the fact that
Shah spent years trying to block

2788170972
00:12:35.663 --> 00:12:39.165
a full inquiry into rape
and grooming gangs in Oldham.

1627282578
00:12:39.166 --> 00:12:42.476
What does the Ministers think that
says to victims and survivors,

933178576
00:12:42.477 --> 00:12:44.836
and how can they and
the public trust her now?

4033481451
00:12:44.837 --> 00:12:47.897
And I would also be interested
to know whether the Ministers

3984062549
00:12:47.898 --> 00:12:51.660
agrees that Shah should
be made a life peer.

2749904634
00:12:51.661 --> 00:12:55.510
>> Ministers Baroness Harman's
record speaks for itself.

4176741769
00:12:55.511 --> 00:12:58.514
She has spent decades
turning words into action,

2602530905
00:12:58.515 --> 00:13:00.857
whether through landmark legislation,

2790620238
00:13:00.858 --> 00:13:04.560
strengthening protections
or relentlessly pushing this issue up.

1794641337
00:13:04.561 --> 00:13:06.717
The political agenda which should never be

1720857982
00:13:06.718 --> 00:13:09.008
used for party political point scoring.

727101069
00:13:09.009 --> 00:13:11.718
It is this Prime Minister
and this government who are

1772670886
00:13:11.719 --> 00:13:14.425
determined to halve violence
against women and girls.

2311560348
00:13:14.427 --> 00:13:17.162
Our Vawg strategy sets
out the plan to do so,

1249635029
00:13:17.163 --> 00:13:19.672
and we are getting on
the job with delivering it.

3343527631
00:13:19.673 --> 00:13:20.424
>> Cheltenham.

2607894779
00:13:20.760 --> 00:13:22.213
Ministers dot Kieran Mullan.

1360456174
00:13:22.214 --> 00:13:23.117
>> Thank you, Mr.

120623411
00:13:23.756 --> 00:13:24.206
Speaker.

2767878769
00:13:24.207 --> 00:13:26.817
Can I welcome the new
Ministers to her post and for

3009936532
00:13:26.818 --> 00:13:29.175
all the policies she might
be glad to inherit,

899260351
00:13:29.177 --> 00:13:32.588
she's also inheriting a plan later
this year to let out potentially

3884543532
00:13:32.589 --> 00:13:35.519
thousands of the worst offenders
against women and girls,

1778005382
00:13:35.520 --> 00:13:38.527
including rapists and those
responsible for sexual assault.

1165016604
00:13:38.528 --> 00:13:41.587
And the government is refusing
to be transparent about this,

983361263
00:13:41.588 --> 00:13:44.998
not answering for wise and written
questions about how many rapists

339130628
00:13:44.999 --> 00:13:48.409
and sexual assault offenders will
be allowed out of prison earlier.

241096158
00:13:48.410 --> 00:13:51.070
Can this new Ministers open
a new leaf in this book,

128233865
00:13:51.761 --> 00:13:55.021
and at least be transparent about
how many rapists they're going

2512872499
00:13:55.022 --> 00:13:57.731
to be letting out of prison
earlier, later this year?

3298159568
00:13:57.732 --> 00:13:58.433
>> Ministers.

711140123
00:13:58.434 --> 00:14:01.961
>> The Conservatives
left a criminal justice

1354719633
00:14:01.962 --> 00:14:04.912
system where victims
wait years for trials,

3350130747
00:14:04.913 --> 00:14:09.861
where victims feel traumatised
by their experiences in court

3514230261
00:14:09.862 --> 00:14:13.469
and where our prisons were full
and the system at risk of collapse,

672190866
00:14:13.470 --> 00:14:15.675
not to mention
the probation service which,

859600132
00:14:15.756 --> 00:14:19.307
after their failed privatisation
attempts, was on its knees.

3943855378
00:14:19.308 --> 00:14:21.866
It is this Labour government
that is taking action

3002398958
00:14:21.867 --> 00:14:24.311
to halve violence against women and girls,

3347992937
00:14:24.311 --> 00:14:26.168
to reduce the time that victims wait

2029048283
00:14:26.169 --> 00:14:29.469
to see justice and to better support

3551118889
00:14:29.470 --> 00:14:33.070
victims with record investment
in victim support services.

682094996
00:14:33.070 --> 00:14:33.371
Here.

154058032
00:14:33.372 --> 00:14:34.675
>> Pam Cox Kieran Mullan.

3637275130
00:14:34.677 --> 00:14:38.188
>> I'd ask the Ministers to think
about perhaps having a constituency

4056892145
00:14:38.189 --> 00:14:40.598
surgery and a victim of
rape coming to see her,

138016480
00:14:40.599 --> 00:14:42.854
perhaps their offenders
currently in prison,

3373908710
00:14:42.855 --> 00:14:45.967
and that that rapist is now going
to get out of prison early.

743893892
00:14:45.968 --> 00:14:48.978
And I wonder what that victim
would think about the answer.

2512156812
00:14:48.979 --> 00:14:52.038
She's just given to a serious
question about serious issues.

3307045792
00:14:52.039 --> 00:14:54.849
If she is refusing to tell
the House at the very least.

3709385930
00:14:54.851 --> 00:14:57.560
Will the Ministers commit
to writing to all the women

1864503989
00:14:57.561 --> 00:15:00.169
and girls who currently
have an offender in prison,

213233881
00:15:00.170 --> 00:15:03.382
perhaps due to go out two years
from now, three years from now?

1631651473
00:15:03.383 --> 00:15:06.545
That's going to get out this year,
and at least doing the good

2818672764
00:15:06.546 --> 00:15:09.706
grace of telling them the victims
when that's going to happen.

1547013726
00:15:09.707 --> 00:15:10.407
>> Ministers.

1415268833
00:15:10.409 --> 00:15:12.365
>> I meet with constituents every week

1220273680
00:15:12.366 --> 00:15:14.524
and victims will always be my priority.

4157692214
00:15:14.525 --> 00:15:14.976
The hon.

2388914197
00:15:14.977 --> 00:15:17.466
Member comes to this House time and time

75678966
00:15:17.467 --> 00:15:19.711
again listing horrific offences,

1790028601
00:15:19.712 --> 00:15:22.516
but not once has he
apologised for the damage

3598433635
00:15:22.517 --> 00:15:25.160
that his party did to our justice system.

3169146381
00:15:25.161 --> 00:15:28.213
Victims will not forget
the mess that they created.

3826933462
00:15:28.214 --> 00:15:31.411
Victims won't forgive their
failures to take action.

2390458351
00:15:31.412 --> 00:15:34.766
Victims will not be fooled
by their claims to care now.

3987850804
00:15:34.767 --> 00:15:36.824
And it is this Labour government that is

2937941782
00:15:36.825 --> 00:15:38.779
committed to halving against violence,

3733366829
00:15:38.780 --> 00:15:40.885
against women, and this Labour government

1430605648
00:15:41.719 --> 00:15:43.576
that has the plan to make it happen.

1684670646
00:15:43.577 --> 00:15:44.579
>> Richard Quigley.

2016750221
00:15:45.762 --> 00:15:47.217
>> Question number five, Mr.

3370627789
00:15:47.218 --> 00:15:47.668
Speaker.

1843685845
00:15:47.669 --> 00:15:52.461
>> Who wants it?

3625551431
00:15:52.462 --> 00:15:53.413
Ministers Malcolm.

2370303284
00:15:53.414 --> 00:15:54.317
>> Thank you, Mr.

167226667
00:15:59.760 --> 00:16:00.210
Speaker.

1630359318
00:16:00.211 --> 00:16:02.217
Perpetrators must not be allowed to use

2025185823
00:16:02.760 --> 00:16:04.866
the family courts to further their abuse.

4128666198
00:16:04.867 --> 00:16:07.716
While the family courts
already have a range

657876123
00:16:07.717 --> 00:16:10.514
of tools designed to protect victims,

2990345008
00:16:10.515 --> 00:16:12.469
we are going further by rolling out

3809666244
00:16:12.470 --> 00:16:15.526
the child focussed
courts model nationally.

2108104450
00:16:15.527 --> 00:16:16.430
>> Thank you, Mr.

1316655499
00:16:16.431 --> 00:16:19.139
Speaker, and while I welcome
the steps the Department

2693739028
00:16:19.140 --> 00:16:21.396
has already taken to
prevent perpetrators of

2882100374
00:16:21.397 --> 00:16:25.318
domestic abuse from using
the family courts to continue coercive,

2815192120
00:16:25.319 --> 00:16:26.721
coercive, coercive control.

2944559723
00:16:26.722 --> 00:16:29.180
Will the Ministers look
at ensuring legal aid is

2989866831
00:16:29.181 --> 00:16:31.386
accessible to victims
in pathfinder courts,

2496194213
00:16:31.387 --> 00:16:33.140
particularly at decision hearings?

3140896440
00:16:33.141 --> 00:16:35.347
Given worrying reports
that this has become

4095074611
00:16:35.348 --> 00:16:37.403
nearly impossible to access in practice,

320782140
00:16:37.404 --> 00:16:39.710
so that perpetrators can
exploit this process

1898323798
00:16:39.711 --> 00:16:41.916
and continue their
campaigns of harassment.

1972650207
00:16:41.916 --> 00:16:45.069
>> We're all too ready.

3351594200
00:16:45.070 --> 00:16:46.224
>> Can I thank my hon.

1120366593
00:16:46.226 --> 00:16:50.217
Friend for, again, speaking up on
behalf of domestic abuse victims?

3078399624
00:16:50.218 --> 00:16:54.815
I remember the powerful debate that
he secured on protecting children,

495809736
00:16:54.816 --> 00:16:58.364
children from domestic abuse
government recognises the vital

1805891916
00:16:58.365 --> 00:17:01.870
role that legal aid plays in
supporting victims of abuse.

2762400386
00:17:01.871 --> 00:17:06.163
Child focussed courts, otherwise
known as Pathfinder courts,

690983470
00:17:06.164 --> 00:17:08.221
have been rolled out to ten court areas,

2601487937
00:17:08.222 --> 00:17:10.771
most recently the Isle
of Wight, in January.

2416937817
00:17:10.772 --> 00:17:14.226
Legal aid is available in child
focussed courts for victims

2230360434
00:17:14.227 --> 00:17:16.635
of domestic violence
or those at risk of abuse,

2943887494
00:17:16.786 --> 00:17:22.012
but we are aware that there are
challenges affecting timely access.

2316899573
00:17:22.012 --> 00:17:23.620
I am happy to meet with my hon.

2267985160
00:17:23.621 --> 00:17:26.230
Friend on this issue,
and can assure the House that

2993199635
00:17:26.231 --> 00:17:31.216
we are working to resolve
this matter swiftly.

404549659
00:17:31.217 --> 00:17:32.721
Rachel Gilmour thank you, Mr.

2250522597
00:17:32.722 --> 00:17:33.172
Speaker.

285377026
00:17:33.173 --> 00:17:33.976
Around 1 in 20.

2706908919
00:17:33.977 --> 00:17:37.035
>> Rural households experienced
some form of domestic abuse,

1429901258
00:17:37.036 --> 00:17:41.214
although experts believe
this figure is significantly

225802524
00:17:41.215 --> 00:17:43.519
understated owing to
chronic under-reporting,

34389841
00:17:43.520 --> 00:17:47.069
evidence shows that financial
control and exclusion from business

2824537479
00:17:47.070 --> 00:17:49.770
decisions is a particular
feature in rural areas.

3413579189
00:17:49.771 --> 00:17:51.974
The pressures of
multi-generational living,

794193188
00:17:51.976 --> 00:17:54.063
the unique stresses of farming life,

2006284042
00:17:54.064 --> 00:17:56.912
and the combination of
geographic and digital

2966638049
00:17:56.913 --> 00:17:59.017
isolation can all heighten vulnerability.

2743894923
00:17:59.018 --> 00:18:02.177
Would the Ministers set out what
specific steps the government

1545460567
00:18:02.178 --> 00:18:05.067
is taking to address these
rural risk factors,

699245256
00:18:05.068 --> 00:18:08.813
improve reporting pathways
and consider setting

1421828130
00:18:08.814 --> 00:18:15.521
up a special committee to look into this.

3185656492
00:18:15.522 --> 00:18:15.923
>> Sir.

2487751027
00:18:15.924 --> 00:18:16.928
>> I thank the hon.

3028755106
00:18:19.761 --> 00:18:21.766
Member issues and alongside the rollout

996693917
00:18:21.767 --> 00:18:24.170
of child focussed courts, there, do.

2600055908
00:18:24.171 --> 00:18:27.622
There does need to be more work
on looking at coercive control.

2016942448
00:18:27.623 --> 00:18:30.521
I know that it's an issue that is of real

1913594412
00:18:30.522 --> 00:18:32.327
interest to many across this House,

4055788392
00:18:32.328 --> 00:18:35.428
and something that this
government takes very seriously.

1796631743
00:18:35.429 --> 00:18:38.716
>> Gregory Stafford question.

1458364259
00:18:38.717 --> 00:18:39.319
>> Six sir.

380991501
00:18:39.320 --> 00:18:40.373
>> Sarah Bool state.

3891807266
00:18:40.765 --> 00:18:41.216
>> With.

1528303780
00:18:41.217 --> 00:18:41.668
Yes, Mr.

84142333
00:18:41.669 --> 00:18:44.327
Speaker, I'll answer question six and 20.

3847281672
00:18:44.328 --> 00:18:47.114
Together, we inherited a justice system

1120454483
00:18:47.115 --> 00:18:49.122
in crisis with a backlog of over 80,000

3967276649
00:18:49.123 --> 00:18:52.625
cases, a double as it
was in pre-COVID era.

2311959749
00:18:52.626 --> 00:18:56.216
Victims, witnesses and defendants
waiting years for justice.

750188820
00:18:56.217 --> 00:18:59.627
And that is what truly undermines
confidence in our justice system.

322558917
00:18:59.628 --> 00:19:01.771
Justice delayed is justice denied only

1493506591
00:19:01.772 --> 00:19:03.526
by pulling every lever investment,

3096564072
00:19:03.764 --> 00:19:07.163
efficiency and reform can
we turn the tide around.

4249917988
00:19:07.164 --> 00:19:08.517
>> Gregory Stafford thank.

4001679965
00:19:08.518 --> 00:19:08.919
>> You.

2166673368
00:19:08.920 --> 00:19:09.271
>> Mr.

2839243171
00:19:09.272 --> 00:19:09.722
Speaker.

954419074
00:19:09.723 --> 00:19:11.628
>> On the Secretary of State's watch,

1482272210
00:19:11.630 --> 00:19:13.936
the courts backlog has
reached record levels,

374285564
00:19:13.936 --> 00:19:16.246
yet his answer is to
weaken one of the oldest

1430746186
00:19:16.764 --> 00:19:19.021
rights in our justice
system, trial by jury.

908735832
00:19:19.022 --> 00:19:20.928
The backlog was not caused by juries,

600235053
00:19:20.929 --> 00:19:23.287
and it will not be solved
by scrapping juries.

1398992263
00:19:23.288 --> 00:19:25.395
The Bar Council says there is very little

2674945652
00:19:25.396 --> 00:19:27.400
evidence for the government's approach.

1538072695
00:19:27.401 --> 00:19:29.907
While the Institute for
government estimates that

2551233679
00:19:29.907 --> 00:19:32.267
it would save at most
around 2% of court time.

2600524146
00:19:32.268 --> 00:19:33.823
And even that may be generous.

4225134021
00:19:33.824 --> 00:19:36.017
So why will the government not drop this

2390877091
00:19:36.018 --> 00:19:38.820
ill judged proposal and focus instead on

1760287155
00:19:38.822 --> 00:19:41.565
the serious reforms
needed to cut the backlog

3704629636
00:19:41.566 --> 00:19:43.271
and speed up justice for victims?

1392748516
00:19:43.272 --> 00:19:43.723
>> Yeah.

4083455621
00:19:43.724 --> 00:19:45.331
>> I've got to say, if the hon.

867216322
00:19:45.764 --> 00:19:48.372
Gentleman were serious, he
would get on the detail.

412255897
00:19:49.764 --> 00:19:51.166
We're not scrapping juries.

3943333007
00:19:51.168 --> 00:19:54.121
Juries remain a cornerstone of our system.

3768968270
00:19:54.122 --> 00:19:57.870
Just as Margaret Thatcher made
changes to the jury system,

3188220868
00:19:57.871 --> 00:20:01.271
just as the Blair government
made changes to the jury system,

4053236129
00:20:02.769 --> 00:20:05.227
we are making changes to
