3319258167
00:30:33.083 --> 00:30:34.136
>> Order, order, Mr.

3995113917
00:30:34.137 --> 00:30:37.235
Timothy, you're going to
come in on two questions.

844927600
00:30:37.236 --> 00:30:41.034
Can you not just at least wait
half a minute before you jump in?

2692696179
00:30:41.035 --> 00:30:44.741
>> It's a serious subject, and I'm pleased

2438227373
00:30:44.742 --> 00:30:50.134
that just after 22 months in office,

4198695655
00:30:50.135 --> 00:30:52.984
knife crime has seen
falls in the last year,

2974469298
00:30:52.985 --> 00:30:56.084
and we will continue with
our knife crime strategy.

2947230194
00:30:56.085 --> 00:30:57.388
>> Nick Timothy secondly.

3324838863
00:30:57.389 --> 00:30:58.292
>> Thank you, Mr.

312091876
00:30:58.293 --> 00:30:58.743
Speaker.

1095271631
00:30:58.744 --> 00:31:02.033
What the Justice Secretary
just said about the record

4243964830
00:31:02.034 --> 00:31:04.290
of the last government
was factually untrue,

1852691157
00:31:04.291 --> 00:31:05.645
and he should withdraw it.

3616422402
00:31:05.646 --> 00:31:06.549
It is his policy.

678196489
00:31:06.550 --> 00:31:07.955
He didn't want to admit it,

2842165831
00:31:07.956 --> 00:31:10.615
but it's his policy to send
knife criminals to jail.

2372894890
00:31:10.616 --> 00:31:12.423
That's why he just said what he did

3562654122
00:31:12.424 --> 00:31:14.480
and buried in his white paper yesterday.

913786813
00:31:14.481 --> 00:31:15.334
It's on page 46.

3489046774
00:31:15.335 --> 00:31:16.489
You can read it again.

2755816382
00:31:16.490 --> 00:31:20.641
Was his plan not just to go soft on
young criminals, but make others?

2391272980
00:31:20.642 --> 00:31:23.751
This is a quote including
vulnerable adults and young adults,

3611345260
00:31:23.752 --> 00:31:26.232
subject to a different process.

2262700091
00:31:26.233 --> 00:31:26.985
That is wrong.

2134041059
00:31:26.986 --> 00:31:30.692
So can the Justice Secretary rule
out weaker sentences and targets

2404431061
00:31:30.693 --> 00:31:34.990
to reduce imprisonment rates
for any adult criminals?

4047016355
00:31:34.991 --> 00:31:36.093
>> Justice Secretary.

2381908393
00:31:36.094 --> 00:31:41.486
>> I've got to tell him he left
us with a prison capacity crisis,

1639503914
00:31:41.487 --> 00:31:45.493
and the last government
had success in reducing

3035157022
00:31:45.494 --> 00:31:48.983
the amount of young people in prison.

321930202
00:31:48.984 --> 00:31:49.636
He knows it.

4118706284
00:31:49.637 --> 00:31:51.281
The record is there.

2301466205
00:31:51.282 --> 00:31:54.180
And I worked with Michael
Gove and David Cameron

3923511809
00:31:54.181 --> 00:31:55.937
as they set about on that mission.

3284639935
00:31:55.938 --> 00:31:58.981
The strategy we published
yesterday, of course,

461092759
00:31:58.982 --> 00:32:01.036
puts public protection first.

4287984682
00:32:01.037 --> 00:32:04.148
There will always be young people
that have to be in custody,

3996632911
00:32:04.149 --> 00:32:06.079
but working with the most vulnerable,

2947813979
00:32:06.080 --> 00:32:08.889
we are determined to reduce
the amount of young people,

1051266909
00:32:08.890 --> 00:32:10.180
particularly on remand.

3944101194
00:32:10.181 --> 00:32:11.735
>> Patrick Hurley number nine.

2610589834
00:32:11.736 --> 00:32:14.387
>> Please, sir.

1547335168
00:32:14.388 --> 00:32:15.089
>> Ministers.

3754777444
00:32:15.090 --> 00:32:19.835
>> The victim will deliver
a new strengthened victims code.

1452336262
00:32:19.836 --> 00:32:22.935
We've engaged with victims
support services and criminal

3536259728
00:32:24.781 --> 00:32:26.785
justice professionals in a consultation

1069733800
00:32:26.786 --> 00:32:28.898
that closed on the 30th of April,

1396797722
00:32:28.899 --> 00:32:32.290
and we are now taking time to
consider nearly 200 responses.

351814565
00:32:32.291 --> 00:32:35.584
We will issue a public
response ahead of finalising

1083994857
00:32:35.585 --> 00:32:38.184
the new code and bringing it into force.

3968410345
00:32:38.185 --> 00:32:41.532
>> Patrick Hurley thank you, Mr.

2730088934
00:32:41.533 --> 00:32:44.787
Speaker, in my constituency,
an acknowledged victim.

1287802770
00:32:44.788 --> 00:32:45.391
>> Of a of.

475231153
00:32:45.392 --> 00:32:48.589
>> A violent crime is being
alleged to be contributory

1947060122
00:32:48.590 --> 00:32:51.682
negligent in the civil courts.

2648106642
00:32:51.683 --> 00:32:55.940
This is retraumatising and appears
to be contrary to natural justice.

1188348363
00:32:55.941 --> 00:32:59.620
So will the Ministers agree to
meet with me and my constituents,

1555433728
00:32:59.621 --> 00:33:00.623
to discuss further,

3429500121
00:33:00.624 --> 00:33:03.886
and to see what measures can be
put in place to address concerns

484874328
00:33:03.887 --> 00:33:08.281
about how the civil law system
deals with cases such as these.

183753636
00:33:08.282 --> 00:33:08.983
>> Ministers.

1476048849
00:33:08.984 --> 00:33:13.192
>> The new Victims Code will ensure
that victims know the service,

2895056502
00:33:13.740 --> 00:33:16.045
support and information
that they're entitled

4222988741
00:33:16.046 --> 00:33:17.801
to in the criminal justice system,

2711073161
00:33:17.802 --> 00:33:20.535
but our civil and family
courts should never be used

2419847903
00:33:20.536 --> 00:33:23.534
to perpetuate the trauma
that victims have suffered.

224230511
00:33:23.535 --> 00:33:25.443
I would be happy to meet with my hon.

26518907
00:33:25.444 --> 00:33:28.083
Friend, or arrange
a meeting with the relevant

2826492390
00:33:28.084 --> 00:33:29.637
Ministers to better understand

2294555822
00:33:29.638 --> 00:33:33.936
the case that he is raising,
and what his constituent is facing.

769359489
00:33:33.937 --> 00:33:34.739
>> Rishi Sunak.

3284671177
00:33:34.740 --> 00:33:37.537
>> Thank you, Mr.

2683375205
00:33:37.538 --> 00:33:37.988
Speaker.

3016974982
00:33:37.989 --> 00:33:38.591
>> In 1990.

1404314470
00:33:38.592 --> 00:33:41.739
>> Doctor David Birkett
was brutally murdered in

1060055573
00:33:41.740 --> 00:33:43.996
a crime that shocked
the Teesside community.

3511360378
00:33:43.997 --> 00:33:48.085
He was discovered by his young daughter,
who was a constituent of mine.

350340597
00:33:48.086 --> 00:33:52.785
Despite the deputy Prime Minister's
very welcome opposition,

2690839473
00:33:52.786 --> 00:33:54.590
the murderer was recently released.

2356047700
00:33:54.785 --> 00:33:56.691
Can I thank the Ministry for agreeing

2307687097
00:33:56.692 --> 00:33:58.599
to a request from myself and the hon.

893002529
00:33:58.600 --> 00:34:01.157
Member for Middlesbrough
and Thornaby East to meet

496227944
00:34:01.158 --> 00:34:03.739
with my constituent to
hear about her concerns

801990550
00:34:03.740 --> 00:34:06.147
about the process
and interactions she had with

3404664916
00:34:06.148 --> 00:34:08.355
the parole board leading
up to his release.

830286251
00:34:08.356 --> 00:34:11.138
Now, I know this is subject
to an ongoing J.R.

403171780
00:34:11.139 --> 00:34:13.196
but could I thank the Ministry for their

967290815
00:34:13.197 --> 00:34:14.851
continued attention to this case

2495073106
00:34:14.852 --> 00:34:18.937
and urge them to learn what we can
to support victims in the future?

3226165144
00:34:18.938 --> 00:34:19.639
>> Ministers.

1816631109
00:34:19.640 --> 00:34:22.138
>> I'm grateful to the right hon.

2224780041
00:34:22.139 --> 00:34:25.034
Member for raising this
deeply distressing case,

1062082348
00:34:25.035 --> 00:34:28.134
and I would like to pay
tribute to Doctor Birkett,

61132890
00:34:28.135 --> 00:34:31.435
daughter, for the courage
in continuing to engage,

1385833133
00:34:31.436 --> 00:34:34.738
which I think is truly commendable.

3150715391
00:34:34.739 --> 00:34:34.989
The.

4119820066
00:34:34.990 --> 00:34:37.836
It is right that the Parole
Board is independent

3353417552
00:34:37.837 --> 00:34:40.986
of government and
the Deputy Prime Minister's

3324577673
00:34:40.987 --> 00:34:43.490
application for reconsideration
was considered

3362729654
00:34:43.491 --> 00:34:45.245
not sufficient to reach threshold,

3515833355
00:34:45.780 --> 00:34:47.836
but the Deputy Prime Minister decided to

875141814
00:34:47.837 --> 00:34:50.484
seek permission for judicial review of

943562581
00:34:50.484 --> 00:34:55.287
the Parole Board's decision not
to set aside their decision,

481124894
00:34:55.288 --> 00:34:57.833
and this has been Fylde.

2741215043
00:34:57.834 --> 00:35:00.743
I await the response and hope
that permission is granted,

4112211807
00:35:00.743 --> 00:35:03.987
but I do want to reassure the right hon.

4087973166
00:35:03.988 --> 00:35:07.939
Member and Doctor Burkett's
family that this department will

3973346686
00:35:07.940 --> 00:35:11.242
continue to seek to mitigate
the hurt that they are feeling.

3466627208
00:35:11.243 --> 00:35:14.246
>> John Whitby the question, Mr.

4184345827
00:35:14.247 --> 00:35:14.697
Speaker.

3151900734
00:35:14.698 --> 00:35:15.248
Ministers.

382065812
00:35:15.249 --> 00:35:15.600
>> Mr.

3864445759
00:35:15.601 --> 00:35:17.907
Speaker, far too many
care experienced people

3811144536
00:35:17.908 --> 00:35:19.864
end up in the criminal justice system.

3041513846
00:35:19.865 --> 00:35:23.426
In November last year, the Deputy
Prime Minister announced a review of

2576096697
00:35:23.426 --> 00:35:26.986
the National Protocol for reducing
the criminalisation of this cohort.

621954633
00:35:26.987 --> 00:35:28.992
Officials are actively working on this,

377540196
00:35:28.993 --> 00:35:32.051
and we will publish a strengthened
protocol later this year.

3688193864
00:35:32.053 --> 00:35:33.558
>> John Whitby thank you, Mr.

3887950025
00:35:33.559 --> 00:35:34.009
Speaker.

674550595
00:35:34.010 --> 00:35:35.816
I refer to my register of interest.

2030488993
00:35:35.817 --> 00:35:40.087
Children in care have often
faced significant trauma,

398782594
00:35:40.087 --> 00:35:41.641
instability, neglect or abuse.

3838108960
00:35:41.642 --> 00:35:43.649
As a result, many of these children end

272026800
00:35:43.650 --> 00:35:45.405
up in the criminal justice system,

3435342596
00:35:45.406 --> 00:35:48.938
with care leavers being ten times
more likely to end up in prison.

3429073686
00:35:48.939 --> 00:35:52.551
Counselling has been shown to help
keep children in care out of prison,

1202582840
00:35:52.551 --> 00:35:54.909
which obviously is better
for the young people

3379840505
00:35:54.910 --> 00:35:57.118
and saves the state
money in the long term.

1683586181
00:35:57.118 --> 00:35:59.073
Would the Ministers therefore consider

3007106156
00:35:59.074 --> 00:36:00.977
changing national protocol guidelines

665477538
00:36:00.978 --> 00:36:04.087
to ensure trauma counselling is
provided to children in care,

3177629259
00:36:04.087 --> 00:36:08.585
who are identified as being at
risk of engaging in criminality?

621084004
00:36:08.586 --> 00:36:08.987
>> Hey.

3720727525
00:36:08.988 --> 00:36:09.689
>> Ministers.

104193627
00:36:09.784 --> 00:36:10.336
>> My hon.

2135638758
00:36:10.337 --> 00:36:12.694
Friend is right to raise
this important issue.

3559061921
00:36:12.694 --> 00:36:16.033
The disproportionality of care
leavers and children who've been

2499571302
00:36:16.034 --> 00:36:19.194
in care in our criminal justice
system is a national disgrace.

3381096015
00:36:19.194 --> 00:36:21.501
And just yesterday,
the Deputy Prime Minister

4001516065
00:36:21.502 --> 00:36:23.256
met with the Ministers responsible

872584935
00:36:23.257 --> 00:36:26.518
for children's social care to look
at these issues in the round.

117427915
00:36:26.519 --> 00:36:29.278
As I said before, we are
looking at strengthening that

2033457089
00:36:29.279 --> 00:36:31.937
protocol and we'll be
publishing that in due course.

2599536876
00:36:31.938 --> 00:36:33.041
>> Great Yarmouth Mr.

3753384865
00:36:33.042 --> 00:36:33.492
Speaker.

949666409
00:36:33.493 --> 00:36:35.700
>> Of course,
the youngest children in care

295413357
00:36:35.701 --> 00:36:37.636
are babies who might shock the house.

2665518016
00:36:37.638 --> 00:36:40.312
There are 36 babies currently residing,

98790353
00:36:40.313 --> 00:36:44.095
no fault of their own in mother
and baby units around this country.

3687253553
00:36:44.096 --> 00:36:48.790
And I just wonder, as part of
the wider sentencing review,

1206405356
00:36:48.791 --> 00:36:51.399
given that babies are taken
away from their mothers

2109001859
00:36:51.400 --> 00:36:54.340
on a case by case basis after 18 months,

337846136
00:36:54.341 --> 00:36:57.341
whether part of that
review should be apart

1993666964
00:36:57.342 --> 00:36:59.986
from the most serious criminal cases,

449013932
00:36:59.987 --> 00:37:03.840
whether it's appropriate at all for
mothers and babies to be imprisoned,

535399181
00:37:04.788 --> 00:37:06.040
particularly the babies.

3537610932
00:37:06.041 --> 00:37:06.742
>> Ministers.

1954860897
00:37:06.743 --> 00:37:07.747
>> I thank the hon.

1938775209
00:37:07.748 --> 00:37:10.104
Member's question,
and he's raised this issue.

1520538636
00:37:10.105 --> 00:37:12.060
Indeed, just yesterday in the Commons,

2465824208
00:37:12.060 --> 00:37:14.169
a similar theme, and he's right to do so.

1726073733
00:37:14.170 --> 00:37:16.729
I know that Lord Timpson
has a particular focus on

1164857211
00:37:16.730 --> 00:37:19.238
female offenders
and women inmates in prison,

3184179763
00:37:19.239 --> 00:37:21.747
and will be making
an announcement in due course.

2445207724
00:37:21.748 --> 00:37:25.259
But he's right to raise these issues
and they're very important ones.

903583560
00:37:25.260 --> 00:37:27.115
>> Alistair Strathern thank you, Mr.

3183255091
00:37:27.116 --> 00:37:27.566
Speaker.

2345798139
00:37:27.567 --> 00:37:28.118
Number 12.

1718251112
00:37:28.118 --> 00:37:29.623
>> Well, with permission, Mr.

2215032459
00:37:29.624 --> 00:37:30.074
Speaker.

3388200425
00:37:30.075 --> 00:37:31.428
I'll answer the questions.

3580441912
00:37:31.429 --> 00:37:34.490
12 and 14 together, the Prime
Minister asked me to lead work

1082689898
00:37:34.491 --> 00:37:37.299
across government to improve
outcomes for boys and men.

51882803
00:37:37.300 --> 00:37:40.358
This includes a specific focus
on convening and coordinating

2751109138
00:37:40.359 --> 00:37:42.764
the brilliant existing
work across departments,

1318169838
00:37:42.765 --> 00:37:44.368
including health and wellbeing,

2598843531
00:37:44.780 --> 00:37:47.736
education and employment
and masculinities and connection.

2609787707
00:37:47.737 --> 00:37:51.097
Furthermore, yesterday we set out
a plan for youth justice reform,

1060018733
00:37:51.098 --> 00:37:53.134
the first in many, many years.

4148499020
00:37:53.135 --> 00:37:54.038
>> Thank you, Mr.

3020793428
00:37:54.039 --> 00:37:54.489
Speaker.

1160052922
00:37:54.490 --> 00:37:58.239
>> The Anti-Slavery Commissioner
recently called out the targeted

3418321799
00:37:58.240 --> 00:38:01.440
online grooming of young men
online by county lines gangs.

3815944972
00:38:01.441 --> 00:38:04.801
This is far from an isolated targeting
we know from the manosphere

3819915688
00:38:04.803 --> 00:38:07.810
to predatory gambling companies
and get rich quick schemes.

1453421233
00:38:07.812 --> 00:38:10.622
Young men growing up in Britain
today are all too often

868767250
00:38:10.623 --> 00:38:12.980
targeted by the worst
corners of the internet.

26129156
00:38:12.981 --> 00:38:15.537
However, while Ofcom rightly
has specific guidance

840509788
00:38:15.538 --> 00:38:17.243
for platforms about how to better

3941324177
00:38:17.243 --> 00:38:20.856
protect women and girls from
the specific harms they can be exposed to,

3563833778
00:38:20.857 --> 00:38:23.514
no such parallel guidance
currently exists for young

3702885020
00:38:23.515 --> 00:38:25.622
men and boys growing up in Britain today,

3268254033
00:38:25.623 --> 00:38:27.933
and we are all worse off
as a result of that.

3660560136
00:38:27.934 --> 00:38:30.192
We recently convened
over 60 MPs to write to

3930555942
00:38:30.193 --> 00:38:32.200
Ofcom and urged them to put this right,

960913630
00:38:32.201 --> 00:38:34.408
with the Deputy Prime
Minister like to join

3353818133
00:38:34.409 --> 00:38:36.467
us today in calling on Ofcom to step up.

2490857927
00:38:36.468 --> 00:38:37.421
Its in their gift.

2368815492
00:38:37.422 --> 00:38:38.375
Let's get it done.

859883894
00:38:38.376 --> 00:38:40.332
>> Christy knows what the question is.

3570633279
00:38:40.333 --> 00:38:43.395
>> Well, it's an excellent
question and he's quite right.

1411462788
00:38:43.397 --> 00:38:48.440
There are a lot of concerns
about the online space

936476816
00:38:48.441 --> 00:38:52.843
and what it means for men
and boys in a modern society.

3613658991
00:38:52.844 --> 00:38:55.140
There's an important role for Ofcom.

4110482366
00:38:55.141 --> 00:38:58.790
I'd encourage him to write
to the Secretary of State,

905693119
00:38:58.791 --> 00:39:00.594
science, Innovation and Technology.

3817748552
00:39:00.595 --> 00:39:02.702
And of course, I'll take a close interest

3416938270
00:39:02.703 --> 00:39:05.162
and I hope he gets a meeting
with the Ministers.

859684384
00:39:05.163 --> 00:39:06.768
>> Amanda Martin thank you, Mr.

2028980027
00:39:06.769 --> 00:39:07.219
Speaker.

817129078
00:39:07.220 --> 00:39:10.281
As the founding member of
the Labour Group for Men and Boys,

812049193
00:39:10.282 --> 00:39:13.490
I welcome the government's focus
and on prevention opportunity,

3421696906
00:39:13.491 --> 00:39:16.602
because supporting men and boys
Mr Speaker is not a zero sum.

1438265565
00:39:16.603 --> 00:39:19.410
It benefits women, girls,
families and communities too.

2154158868
00:39:19.411 --> 00:39:21.568
But in Portsmouth, too many boys and young

2474334012
00:39:21.569 --> 00:39:23.323
men are struggling with education,

346526305
00:39:23.324 --> 00:39:25.229
mental health and pathways into work.

126142688
00:39:25.230 --> 00:39:28.339
While many older men tell me
increasingly they feel isolated,

3702820944
00:39:28.340 --> 00:39:31.145
overlooked and mistrustful
of institution and politics.

2282237196
00:39:31.147 --> 00:39:33.654
What discussions is
the Secretary of State having

485265565
00:39:33.655 --> 00:39:36.160
with Cabinet colleagues
about rebuilding purpose,

1061216991
00:39:36.161 --> 00:39:39.319
trust and opportunity for men
and boys across our communities?

2377583421
00:39:39.321 --> 00:39:42.131
And we work with me to turn
this ambition to meaningful

1592108685
00:39:42.132 --> 00:39:44.087
action for men and boys in Portsmouth.

1206160877
00:39:44.089 --> 00:39:46.097
>> Well, very keen to work with my hon.

896874614
00:39:46.098 --> 00:39:48.707
Friend on this issue and
I recognise that there are

2742697458
00:39:48.708 --> 00:39:51.115
real issues in her
constituency in this regard.

1299657877
00:39:51.116 --> 00:39:53.373
She'll be pleased that
last month I attended

1502825286
00:39:53.374 --> 00:39:55.732
a round table with some
of the leading figures

860326856
