00:49:46.799 --> 00:49:50.002
the harrowing journey they
face rebuilding their lives.

329046070
00:49:50.002 --> 00:49:53.264
For many, the one thing that gives
them comfort is the knowledge

3344923710
00:49:53.265 --> 00:49:56.252
that their abuser cannot
reach them from behind bars.

17855896
00:49:56.254 --> 00:49:58.855
But government changes
to category D prisons

3491463269
00:49:58.856 --> 00:50:00.902
can now allow these offenders

3959923482
00:50:00.903 --> 00:50:03.761
to be moved to open conditions
much earlier than before,

17641403
00:50:03.763 --> 00:50:06.069
despite their crimes
being exempt from SDS 40

175890212
00:50:06.071 --> 00:50:09.006
because of their recognised higher risk.

3130877761
00:50:09.007 --> 00:50:11.547
So will the Ministers
meet with me to discuss,

1115013348
00:50:11.548 --> 00:50:14.258
excluding domestic abusers and stalkers,

1803246569
00:50:14.259 --> 00:50:16.114
from early transfer to open prisons,

2179794456
00:50:16.115 --> 00:50:20.513
so that their peace of mind
and victims can be retained?

3926247850
00:50:20.800 --> 00:50:22.203
>> Ministers all prisoners?

999553696
00:50:22.203 --> 00:50:24.460
As I said earlier,
including those convicted

531583546
00:50:24.461 --> 00:50:26.666
of domestic violence
and stalking offences,

1203432383
00:50:26.667 --> 00:50:29.277
will only be allowed to
move to an open prison when

185485610
00:50:29.278 --> 00:50:31.434
they have been assessed and risk assessed.

1021367005
00:50:31.435 --> 00:50:33.944
I'm very happy to organise
a meeting for him with

1891545338
00:50:33.944 --> 00:50:36.752
the relevant Ministers to
discuss this particular case.

2323335501
00:50:36.752 --> 00:50:37.705
>> Jill, Scotland.

1545899176
00:50:37.706 --> 00:50:38.609
>> Thank you, Mr.

1724652261
00:50:38.609 --> 00:50:39.060
Speaker.

2302904552
00:50:39.060 --> 00:50:41.799
I welcome the Youth Justice
White Paper and its

334979335
00:50:41.800 --> 00:50:44.852
focus on tackling
the root causes of offending.

1934757522
00:50:44.853 --> 00:50:48.113
Like many of my colleagues, I've
seen tragic cases of vulnerable

440314290
00:50:48.114 --> 00:50:52.208
young people being exploited by
adults and drawn into crime.

2483629698
00:50:52.209 --> 00:50:55.170
Can I urge the Ministers to
ensure that the new offence of

1061841430
00:50:55.171 --> 00:50:57.977
child criminal exploitation
is brought forward swiftly,

1444043842
00:50:57.978 --> 00:51:02.203
and that it's robust enough to
go after those responsible?

1238692718
00:51:02.203 --> 00:51:04.803
>> So I'm very grateful to my hon.

2824922866
00:51:04.804 --> 00:51:05.203
Friend.

2030380927
00:51:05.205 --> 00:51:09.106
There's nothing more tragic
than seeing young people,

1662572357
00:51:09.107 --> 00:51:12.409
often from deprived backgrounds,

1262521254
00:51:12.410 --> 00:51:14.468
preyed on by adults to run drugs and all

566041830
00:51:14.469 --> 00:51:16.474
sorts of contraband across the country.

399783106
00:51:16.475 --> 00:51:20.358
We will be bringing this
forward as soon as possible.

4262163717
00:51:20.805 --> 00:51:21.708
>> Tim Farron Mr.

3166561255
00:51:21.709 --> 00:51:24.952
Speaker, Kendal Magistrates
Court was outrageously

1324794453
00:51:24.953 --> 00:51:26.508
closed in 2017 on the promise,

338542407
00:51:26.509 --> 00:51:29.366
though, that sittings would
continue in other locations.

1091109695
00:51:29.367 --> 00:51:32.251
Public buildings in Kendal after closure.

2051905479
00:51:32.252 --> 00:51:35.905
Yet there has not been a single
sitting in Kendal since 2020.

893046823
00:51:35.906 --> 00:51:39.807
Will the Deputy Prime Minister put
this right urgently so that promise

637483052
00:51:39.808 --> 00:51:44.255
can be kept and local people can
have reasonable access to justice?

3431155911
00:51:44.256 --> 00:51:45.962
>> I'm grateful to the right hon.

442281234
00:51:46.804 --> 00:51:47.354
Gentleman.

275223039
00:51:47.355 --> 00:51:50.551
He knows that the government
inherited a justice system

3061718330
00:51:50.553 --> 00:51:53.301
in crisis with record and rising caseload.

448777284
00:51:53.301 --> 00:51:57.154
He also knows that
the last government closed

1861721427
00:51:57.155 --> 00:51:58.809
courts right across the country.

1973817454
00:51:58.810 --> 00:52:02.554
We are legislating for structural reform.

2426402252
00:52:02.555 --> 00:52:06.261
I've invested 2.78 billion in
investment to bring down the backlog.

2080886070
00:52:06.805 --> 00:52:09.564
We'll continue to look closely
at the needs in Kendal,

1064613247
00:52:09.565 --> 00:52:11.672
but he recognises that it's going to take

3656941324
00:52:11.761 --> 00:52:13.767
some time to address what we inherited.

3438168537
00:52:13.768 --> 00:52:15.858
>> Liz Twist thank you, Mr.

1421826973
00:52:15.859 --> 00:52:16.309
Speaker.

3829866557
00:52:16.310 --> 00:52:17.312
The latest Women's.

2886530568
00:52:17.801 --> 00:52:22.402
>> Aid annual audit highlights
that nearly 80% of domestic

3022838520
00:52:22.403 --> 00:52:24.558
abuse survivors now face devastating tech,

542803972
00:52:25.804 --> 00:52:27.758
facilitated abuse and online stalking.

1540443483
00:52:27.759 --> 00:52:30.805
How will the Justice
Department collaborate

1728120895
00:52:30.806 --> 00:52:33.104
across government to ensure that

377682113
00:52:33.105 --> 00:52:37.301
our courts and prosecutors are fully

1778075305
00:52:37.301 --> 00:52:39.156
equipped to tackle digital violence?

1452128446
00:52:39.157 --> 00:52:40.351
>> Ministers.

3467869021
00:52:40.352 --> 00:52:41.306
>> I thank my hon.

222000207
00:52:41.307 --> 00:52:44.209
Friend for her question and her consistent

3104488924
00:52:44.210 --> 00:52:46.506
efforts on to raise online harms,

72159507
00:52:46.507 --> 00:52:49.607
whether it's physical, oral
or online abuse is abuse,

588696924
00:52:49.608 --> 00:52:53.307
and this government is
determined to tackle violence

1893979548
00:52:53.308 --> 00:52:55.960
against women and girls
online as well as off.

1459810221
00:52:55.961 --> 00:52:58.453
We are making it illegal to take or make

854717194
00:52:58.455 --> 00:53:00.108
intimate images without consent,

567056520
00:53:00.804 --> 00:53:01.906
including deep fakes.

2834642973
00:53:01.907 --> 00:53:03.962
Our new deletion orders will ensure that

3803118132
00:53:03.964 --> 00:53:05.918
courts can require offenders convicted

1762066866
00:53:05.919 --> 00:53:09.557
of intimate image offences to
delete images of their victims.

4019823817
00:53:09.558 --> 00:53:13.767
The Vawg strategy sets out
our plan to tackle digitally

1776555046
00:53:13.768 --> 00:53:15.770
facilitated violence across government.

3419903579
00:53:15.772 --> 00:53:17.277
>> John Lamont thank you, Mr.

3251412883
00:53:17.278 --> 00:53:17.728
Speaker.

4042825303
00:53:17.809 --> 00:53:21.156
We know how grooming gangs
regularly trafficked young,

2540577946
00:53:21.157 --> 00:53:23.011
vulnerable girls across the borders,

1937412173
00:53:23.011 --> 00:53:26.069
but survivors of these appalling
crimes are deeply concerned

4161800411
00:53:26.071 --> 00:53:28.426
that the UK Government
and Scottish Government

2110231488
00:53:28.428 --> 00:53:30.834
inquiries are doing
separate inquiries and will

1984256766
00:53:30.835 --> 00:53:33.089
not investigate cross-border
grooming gangs.

2205835971
00:53:33.090 --> 00:53:36.300
So what is the Ministers doing
to ensure that the perpetrators,

172198469
00:53:36.301 --> 00:53:38.707
both the perpetrators of
these horrific crimes,

1300425196
00:53:38.708 --> 00:53:40.663
are also the institutions that failed.

2168182629
00:53:40.664 --> 00:53:43.171
Their victims are being
properly held to account.

3885895906
00:53:43.172 --> 00:53:43.873
>> Ministers.

1858452978
00:53:43.874 --> 00:53:44.476
>> The hon.

2956450212
00:53:44.477 --> 00:53:47.687
Member is right to raise this
and has consistently raised this.

3038173004
00:53:47.688 --> 00:53:49.593
I meet with justice counterparts from

3529953567
00:53:49.594 --> 00:53:51.397
the devolved governments regularly,

640223955
00:53:51.398 --> 00:53:54.962
and I'll make sure this is high up
on the agenda for our next meeting.

3457285245
00:53:54.962 --> 00:53:56.417
It's a very important issue.

1506675101
00:53:56.418 --> 00:53:58.977
There is a lot of good work
happening in Scotland,

550116543
00:53:58.978 --> 00:54:01.285
in Wales and Northern
Ireland and in England.

2725624348
00:54:01.286 --> 00:54:03.193
We need to make sure that's joined up

3317189230
00:54:03.194 --> 00:54:05.048
to address that particular mischief,

3783452537
00:54:05.049 --> 00:54:06.502
which is incredibly serious.

3150980682
00:54:06.502 --> 00:54:07.506
>> Adam Jogee very.

2827224859
00:54:07.507 --> 00:54:08.159
>> Much, Mr.

1478878462
00:54:08.160 --> 00:54:08.609
Speaker.

1650726890
00:54:08.611 --> 00:54:10.971
>> Can I ask the Ministers
to assure me and my

2624637259
00:54:10.972 --> 00:54:13.326
constituents back home
in Newcastle-under-Lyme

2531145005
00:54:13.327 --> 00:54:16.085
that the changes to the unduly
lenient sentence scheme

2556520462
00:54:16.086 --> 00:54:19.597
will ensure that victims of crime
in Newcastle and across the Kingdom

1337557823
00:54:19.598 --> 00:54:23.008
are better supported at every stage
of the criminal justice system.

4007970157
00:54:23.009 --> 00:54:23.710
>> Ministers.

4081440686
00:54:23.711 --> 00:54:24.263
>> My hon.

792008238
00:54:24.264 --> 00:54:25.819
Friend is right to raise this.

3314650108
00:54:25.819 --> 00:54:28.879
I'm very proud that this government
has listened to victims.

3012174000
00:54:28.880 --> 00:54:32.241
I've met with the victims Commissioner
and an array of victims who

3134937814
00:54:32.242 --> 00:54:35.349
have been complaining about
unduly lenient sentencing scheme.

1418483875
00:54:35.350 --> 00:54:37.407
We've been able to modernise it to allow

2402760622
00:54:37.408 --> 00:54:39.064
an out of time route for victims

1779806527
00:54:39.065 --> 00:54:41.421
and bereaved family members
to refer sentences

2162582532
00:54:41.422 --> 00:54:43.127
outside of the 28 day time limit.

2676301838
00:54:43.129 --> 00:54:45.636
Clearly, 28 days is sometimes
not appropriate for

1861210406
00:54:45.636 --> 00:54:48.142
families who are deeply
distressed circumstances.

3780503656
00:54:48.143 --> 00:54:50.150
We've been able to make changes of that

3747477916
00:54:50.151 --> 00:54:52.157
working on a cross-party basis as well.

3138022039
00:54:52.158 --> 00:54:54.665
I'm proud that this
government is putting victims

1626089547
00:54:54.666 --> 00:54:56.923
at the heart of
the criminal justice system.

2702513277
00:54:56.924 --> 00:54:58.277
Neil Shastri- Hurst thank.

61119849
00:54:58.278 --> 00:54:59.382
>> You very much, Mr.

1988522099
00:54:59.383 --> 00:54:59.833
Speaker.

323643173
00:54:59.834 --> 00:55:03.249
I think it would be fair to say
the government and I do not see eye

1740467786
00:55:03.250 --> 00:55:06.462
to eye when it comes to the policy
of curtailing trial by jury.

1372931485
00:55:06.462 --> 00:55:09.673
However, if the government is
determined to go down this route,

1454592390
00:55:09.674 --> 00:55:12.482
their own impact assessment
sets out that a significant

4243241971
00:55:12.483 --> 00:55:14.689
number of magistrates
need to be recruited.

3603833240
00:55:14.690 --> 00:55:17.401
The MoJ has set this out to
be 7000 over three years.

2004017191
00:55:17.402 --> 00:55:19.810
In order for the government's
own plan to work,

2769164887
00:55:19.810 --> 00:55:22.872
will they commit not to change
any of the rules around trial

3315307331
00:55:22.873 --> 00:55:25.759
by jury until they have
recruited those magistrates?

674248761
00:55:25.760 --> 00:55:29.321
>> Secretary I think magistrates
play a hugely important role.

36381390
00:55:29.322 --> 00:55:32.809
I was sad that under the last
government they were cut back.

3588969467
00:55:32.810 --> 00:55:35.808
They used to be about 29,000.

4203726260
00:55:35.809 --> 00:55:40.160
He will see the recruitment
campaign right across the country.

2805733290
00:55:40.161 --> 00:55:42.569
I think we need a new
generation of magistrates

3548694112
00:55:42.569 --> 00:55:44.877
and I want them to come
from all backgrounds.

3115488547
00:55:44.879 --> 00:55:45.982
>> Gurinder Josan Mr.

481493648
00:55:45.983 --> 00:55:46.584
>> Speaker.

2015447895
00:55:46.585 --> 00:55:47.889
>> Half of all prisoners.

242147321
00:55:47.890 --> 00:55:52.002
>> Lack the basic literacy skills
needed to navigate everyday life.

952368447
00:55:52.002 --> 00:55:54.706
Only 1 in 3 secure
employment within six months

2393106727
00:55:54.707 --> 00:55:58.053
of release and a third
re-offend within a year.

2139503720
00:55:58.054 --> 00:56:01.109
So rehabilitation, reducing
reoffending and improving public

2903432831
00:56:01.111 --> 00:56:04.121
safety must be at the heart of
our criminal justice system.

3302555321
00:56:04.122 --> 00:56:06.729
Will the Secretary of State
please therefore commit

3751676647
00:56:06.730 --> 00:56:08.885
to increasing funding for prison education

461250428
00:56:08.886 --> 00:56:11.193
so that offenders can
access the basic skills

2747648422
00:56:11.194 --> 00:56:13.501
and support they need
to rebuild their lives,

3517339686
00:56:13.502 --> 00:56:16.152
and so that they can
reintegrate and contribute

3554250646
00:56:16.153 --> 00:56:19.005
positively to society
when they leave prison.

4139762458
00:56:19.006 --> 00:56:19.707
>> Ministers.

1637509699
00:56:19.708 --> 00:56:21.205
>> My hon.

2456280158
00:56:21.206 --> 00:56:24.214
Friend has been consistent in
raising this important issue.

1658456074
00:56:24.215 --> 00:56:27.024
We are committed to ensuring
that there is a sufficient

1678737141
00:56:27.025 --> 00:56:28.778
education provision for prisoners.

3163175219
00:56:28.779 --> 00:56:32.139
I would gently stress, however, we
can only provide that education

980647558
00:56:32.140 --> 00:56:34.749
if we are able to get
prisoners into the classroom.

1372734637
00:56:34.750 --> 00:56:36.907
So we need to stabilise the prison system,

2050220875
00:56:36.908 --> 00:56:40.470
get order back into the prison system
off the chaos that we inherited.

2481177174
00:56:40.471 --> 00:56:43.578
But absolutely, this government
is committed to ensuring that

779800170
00:56:43.580 --> 00:56:46.687
prisoners have education
and work opportunities upon leaving.

2242236600
00:56:46.688 --> 00:56:47.440
>> Tessa Munt.

3784456902
00:56:47.441 --> 00:56:48.344
>> Thank you, Mr.

472776237
00:56:48.345 --> 00:56:48.795
Speaker.

1839157693
00:56:48.796 --> 00:56:50.351
I represent a very rural area,

1525169511
00:56:50.352 --> 00:56:52.913
and we have to drive many
miles to get to a court.

1908255294
00:56:52.914 --> 00:56:54.921
With fuel prices so high at the moment,

3071906650
00:56:54.922 --> 00:56:57.429
I wonder why ordinary
citizens are reimbursed for

4171095586
00:56:57.430 --> 00:57:00.063
jury service at the rate of only 31.4

514911513
00:57:00.064 --> 00:57:04.158
pence per mile for their
travel by car costs.

1798391762
00:57:04.159 --> 00:57:08.714
And yet the standard HMRC
approved rate is £0.45 per mile.

2558658858
00:57:08.715 --> 00:57:11.223
It doesn't cover the cost
of travel and penalises

980915304
00:57:11.224 --> 00:57:13.564
those who live in rural areas.

323815972
00:57:13.565 --> 00:57:13.916
>> Mr.

2530872103
00:57:13.917 --> 00:57:14.618
>> Well, the.

1120390166
00:57:14.620 --> 00:57:15.020
>> Hon.

2805650768
00:57:15.022 --> 00:57:17.630
Member is a member of
the Justice Select Committee.

1962765653
00:57:17.631 --> 00:57:19.786
Raises an important, very practical point.

2600223999
00:57:19.787 --> 00:57:22.694
The government recognises
the hugely important civic duty

175696301
00:57:22.694 --> 00:57:25.354
that jurors play day in, day
out across the country.

3550305196
00:57:25.355 --> 00:57:28.564
We always will keep renumeration
and travel costs under review.

1989172960
00:57:28.565 --> 00:57:30.314
And we've heard the question.

2633702991
00:57:30.315 --> 00:57:32.069
>> Samantha Niblett thank you, Mr.

3413927791
00:57:32.071 --> 00:57:32.520
Speaker.

266049725
00:57:32.522 --> 00:57:35.381
I'm sure it's not missed
anybody's radar that I recently

2017751038
00:57:35.382 --> 00:57:38.556
launched a campaign for
lifelong sex education,

2200613474
00:57:38.557 --> 00:57:41.417
and as of last week, I met
with some parish councillors,

1844243948
00:57:41.418 --> 00:57:43.913
one of which works within
the probation service,

3839936049
00:57:43.914 --> 00:57:46.975
and she thanked me for
the campaign because of the amount of

2188252655
00:57:46.976 --> 00:57:49.835
re-education they have to do
of young men in particular,

3254916600
00:57:49.836 --> 00:57:53.669
when it comes to what is acceptable
within sexual relationships.

4271883529
00:57:53.670 --> 00:57:55.928
So I wonder if
the Secretary of State would,

1748266880
00:57:55.929 --> 00:57:58.638
and the relevant Ministers
would meet with me to talk

1524135856
00:57:58.639 --> 00:58:01.455
about the importance of
lifelong sex education in

1791395411
00:58:01.456 --> 00:58:03.759
re-educating potential
offenders reoffending.

2672372397
00:58:05.806 --> 00:58:10.958
>> Well, can I thank her for her
campaign and her work in this area?

1871709233
00:58:10.959 --> 00:58:14.519
It is important that prisoners
and those on probation are re-educated.

4077303747
00:58:15.804 --> 00:58:16.203
Really?

2750599397
00:58:16.205 --> 00:58:17.409
As to codes of conduct.

483288037
00:58:17.410 --> 00:58:19.518
I'm very happy for her to arrange to have

1681926460
00:58:19.519 --> 00:58:21.424
a meeting with the Prisons Ministers.

3286864954
00:58:21.425 --> 00:58:22.176
>> Adam Dance.

289812255
00:58:22.178 --> 00:58:23.081
>> Thank you, Mr.

4290922336
00:58:23.082 --> 00:58:23.532
Speaker.

3254571251
00:58:23.533 --> 00:58:27.159
Can the Secretary of State outline
what steps he is taking through

416451103
00:58:27.160 --> 00:58:29.115
the criminal justice system to support

866164729
00:58:29.116 --> 00:58:30.870
victims of violence against women,

1085917639
00:58:30.871 --> 00:58:34.308
particularly those that report
historic cases of sexual violence?

4057378056
00:58:34.309 --> 00:58:37.005
Like several of my young constituents who

2652119754
00:58:37.006 --> 00:58:38.759
have faced terrible communication,

3994325356
00:58:38.760 --> 00:58:40.766
years of delays, and ultimately the CPS

741500415
00:58:40.767 --> 00:58:45.465
not procrastinating with prosecution.

851731441
00:58:45.466 --> 00:58:48.274
>> Ministers those of us
who've spent years campaigning

1606258408
00:58:48.275 --> 00:58:50.481
to address violence
against women and girls

3233235089
00:58:50.482 --> 00:58:53.041
know that we are building
on the work of pioneers,

1329240679
00:58:53.042 --> 00:58:55.399
and Baroness Harman was
one of those pioneers.

1858439263
00:58:55.400 --> 00:58:57.807
I'm looking forward to
working closely with her

1457357401
00:58:57.808 --> 00:59:00.214
across government to
deliver our Vawg strategy.

4026650287
00:59:00.215 --> 00:59:03.276
As part of that, we will be
delivering the new Victims Code,

3128765587
00:59:03.277 --> 00:59:05.656
which will set out the service,

3504697882
00:59:05.657 --> 00:59:08.364
support and information that
victims are entitled to,

857442898
00:59:08.365 --> 00:59:13.170
and we're supporting victims
with the largest ever investment

526199129
00:59:13.171 --> 00:59:15.377
of £550 million in
victim support services.

1900531594
00:59:15.377 --> 00:59:16.280
Sarah Coombes Mr.

3048307413
00:59:16.281 --> 00:59:18.187
Speaker, in the past six months, the.

480192264
00:59:18.188 --> 00:59:21.549
>> Community in the Black Country
was rocked by two horrific cases

2149429321
00:59:21.550 --> 00:59:24.508
of Sikh women being raped in
racially aggravated assaults.

312030548
00:59:24.509 --> 00:59:27.460
These two attacks shook
the entire community to our core,

3105988524
00:59:27.461 --> 00:59:30.421
but it recently came to light
that a Reform Party election

94631488
00:59:30.422 --> 00:59:32.726
candidate celebrated
these appalling attacks.

3729572352
00:59:32.727 --> 00:59:36.339
He is thankfully now stood down after
being elected just two weeks ago.

3075882777
00:59:36.340 --> 00:59:38.497
Can the Ministers say more about how women

3872034625
00:59:38.498 --> 00:59:40.203
will be supported in these cases,

683083238
00:59:40.203 --> 00:59:43.263
where not only were they victims
of horrific sexual attacks,

958028365
00:59:43.264 --> 00:59:45.571
but there was racial
hatred involved as well?

588928846
00:59:45.572 --> 00:59:46.273
>> Ministers.

4005311876
00:59:46.274 --> 00:59:48.659
>> What is unsurprising that yet again,

4160443627
00:59:48.660 --> 00:59:51.609
we do not have any reform
MPs in the chamber.

1363227533
00:59:51.611 --> 00:59:56.663
People will be shocked to
hear about these cases

1903493292
00:59:56.664 --> 01:00:00.210
of racially aggravated sexual violence.

4228012867
01:00:00.211 --> 01:00:03.812
And any comments celebrating
that are utterly repugnant.

2874897819
01:00:03.813 --> 01:00:08.013
This government is determined
to support victims

569012938
01:00:08.014 --> 01:00:11.060
of violence against women and girls,

4062522727
01:00:11.062 --> 01:00:15.219
and we are committed to not
only supporting the victims.

1530999397
01:00:15.220 --> 01:00:20.219
With the £550 for victim support,
but we are also introducing

344332558
01:00:20.808 --> 01:00:23.364
independent legal advisers
for adult rape victims.

2798198586
01:00:23.365 --> 01:00:24.509
>> Shockat Adam.

553006808
01:00:24.510 --> 01:00:24.861
>> Mr.

1499263167
01:00:24.862 --> 01:00:26.768
speaker, can I ask the Ministers what

3185696774
01:00:26.769 --> 01:00:28.675
assessment he has made of the reports

906356445
01:00:28.676 --> 01:00:31.832
concerning communication between
the former Foreign Secretary,

1098261467
01:00:31.833 --> 01:00:34.413
Lord Cameron, and the ICC
prosecutor, Karim Khan,

3718479377
01:00:34.414 --> 01:00:38.058
regarding the court's investigation
into war crimes in Gaza?

1890582062
01:00:38.059 --> 01:00:41.161
And what steps is he taking
to uphold the independence

2066912246
01:00:41.162 --> 01:00:43.923
of the international
judicial institutions,

661077647
01:00:43.924 --> 01:00:45.377
institutions that we set up?

2382913102
01:00:46.116 --> 01:00:46.817
>> Ministers.

2368934249
01:00:46.818 --> 01:00:50.420
>> Well, clearly, some of those
matters raised by the hon.

1378849795
01:00:50.421 --> 01:00:53.913
Member are perhaps matters
for the Foreign Secretary

2795166197
01:00:53.914 --> 01:00:55.759
rather than the Justice Secretary.

238659536
01:00:55.760 --> 01:00:59.109
As he said, we clearly always
respect international law

517858440
01:00:59.111 --> 01:01:01.819
and the principles of
the rule of law more generally.

4145923347
01:01:01.821 --> 01:01:03.426
>> Baggy Shanker thank you, Mr.

3727539213
01:01:03.426 --> 01:01:03.877
Speaker.

798935526
01:01:03.877 --> 01:01:07.412
Sexual assaults and harassment
on trains have risen

388316722
01:01:07.413 --> 01:01:10.609
more than a third over the last ten years,

2564826048
01:01:10.611 --> 01:01:16.069
yet too many trains and stations
still lack adequate CCTV.

3182905871
01:01:16.069 --> 01:01:19.962
This evidence gap lets criminals
evade justice and fails victims.

1472289766
01:01:19.964 --> 01:01:24.660
Can the Secretary of State outline
what steps he is taking alongside

3700840365
01:01:24.661 --> 01:01:28.363
colleagues to improve CCTV coverage
across the whole rail network,

3862221122
01:01:28.364 --> 01:01:30.769
so that perpetrators of
violence against women

524172573
01:01:30.770 --> 01:01:33.810
and girls can be brought to justice?

2820909865
01:01:33.812 --> 01:01:34.513
>> Ministers.

2707581239
01:01:34.514 --> 01:01:35.066
>> My hon.

3837800113
01:01:36.808 --> 01:01:38.964
Friend and neighbour share a keen interest

3665507747
01:01:38.965 --> 01:01:40.965
in rail as we represent a city

458227351
01:01:40.966 --> 01:01:45.020
at the centre of the largest cluster
of rail companies in Europe,

2068184906
01:01:45.022 --> 01:01:47.715
and we have launched
a new campaign to drive

3218949546
01:01:47.716 --> 01:01:50.065
up reporting of harassment on trains.

1439143394
01:01:50.066 --> 01:01:53.910
The new safer Railway scheme,
where train operators

1543541027
01:01:53.911 --> 01:01:56.460
must show what they are doing to

3089264830
01:01:56.461 --> 01:01:58.617
tackle violence against women and girls so

214665094
01:01:58.618 --> 01:02:00.523
that they can travel with confidence,

1087236983
01:02:00.524 --> 01:02:04.465
and I look forward to working
with him on this initiative.

2408217049
01:02:04.813 --> 01:02:05.565
>> Ashley Fox.

1919043686
01:02:05.566 --> 01:02:05.766
Mr.

3702574153
01:02:05.767 --> 01:02:10.816
speaker, the former Ministers
for Safeguarding and Violence

3640851828
01:02:10.817 --> 01:02:13.373
against Women and Girls
said that real change

3044393406
01:02:13.374 --> 01:02:16.863
in combating violence usually
came only after threats

2510840229
01:02:16.864 --> 01:02:20.464
from her following catastrophic mistakes.

1367787400
01:02:20.465 --> 01:02:24.112
Doesn't this confirm that the government
is unwilling to take the tough

2110401198
01:02:24.113 --> 01:02:30.062
decisions necessary to tackle
violence against women and girls?

1420276630
01:02:30.063 --> 01:02:32.769
>> I am honoured to take
up the role and build

3173433442
01:02:32.770 --> 01:02:35.511
upon the incredible work that the hon.

2523781537
01:02:35.511 --> 01:02:40.008
Member for Pontypridd
undertook, and she was

606983614
01:02:40.009 --> 01:02:42.164
absolutely essential in the Vawg strategy.

3811179185
01:02:43.766 --> 01:02:46.023
Freedom from violence
and abuse so that this

3397781775
01:02:46.816 --> 01:02:48.972
government has a plan to prevent violence,

3035457512
01:02:48.973 --> 01:02:53.212
pursue and prosecute perpetrators
and support victims.

3777055676
01:02:53.214 --> 01:02:59.215
And we will be working
across government to deliver

754964349
01:02:59.216 --> 01:03:01.421
the strongest crackdown
in British history.

1863535850
01:03:01.422 --> 01:03:03.077
>> Alison Bennett thank you, Mr.

1827014005
01:03:03.078 --> 01:03:03.528
Speaker.

12993061
01:03:03.529 --> 01:03:07.265
My constituent is a mental health
legal aid lawyer who has seen

2339812541
01:03:07.266 --> 01:03:10.912
demand in the sector rise while
fees keep fail to keep up.

1420115540
01:03:10.913 --> 01:03:14.522
As a result, many have left this
work despite the government's

1384418977
01:03:14.523 --> 01:03:17.613
2025 Mental Health Act
increasing the workload.

3817172477
01:03:17.614 --> 01:03:21.214
This is unacceptable when
people's liberty is at stake.

4261898256
01:03:21.215 --> 01:03:24.721
So I ask, what specific assessments
has the department made of

2408667202
01:03:24.722 --> 01:03:28.031
the current sustainability of
the mental health legal aid sector,

998888417
01:03:28.032 --> 01:03:30.038
and what concrete steps are they taking

4184063298
01:03:30.039 --> 01:03:31.793
to ensure its financial viability?

3655686509
01:03:32.808 --> 01:03:33.108
Yeah.

1877701301
01:03:33.109 --> 01:03:33.460
>> So.

37154093
01:03:33.461 --> 01:03:34.866
>> I'm grateful to the hon.

604661277
01:03:34.867 --> 01:03:35.167
Lady.

3850965798
01:03:36.001 --> 01:03:39.319
We've announced additional
funding of up to 34 million

1003471967
01:03:39.319 --> 01:03:41.376
a year for criminal legal aid advocates,

3845506725
01:03:41.773 --> 01:03:43.980
and up an additional
92 million beyond that

603402278
01:03:44.809 --> 01:03:46.563
for criminal legal aid solicitors.

1101064196
01:03:46.564 --> 01:03:51.118
She raised the important area of mental.

524977999
01:03:51.120 --> 01:03:54.011
Legal aid in relation
to mental health cases,

1240908379
01:03:54.011 --> 01:03:57.469
and we'll look closely at that
in the next funding period.

4074823058
01:03:57.470 --> 01:03:58.925
>> Anna Dixon thank you, Mr.

145631626
01:03:58.926 --> 01:04:01.233
Speaker, and I'd like
to congratulate my hon.

3159514603
01:04:01.234 --> 01:04:04.513
Friend for her first outing
at the despatch box.

1408244179
01:04:04.514 --> 01:04:07.023
On Friday I met Jimmy,
an IPP prisoner whose case

1715572292
01:04:07.024 --> 01:04:09.611
I've previously raised
with the Prime Minister,

3305087843
01:04:09.612 --> 01:04:12.318
the Justice Secretary
and the Prisons Ministers.

1704812782
01:04:12.319 --> 01:04:16.314
Despite good progress, he still
does not have a firm release date.

1606607692
01:04:16.315 --> 01:04:20.212
After more than 20 years
in prison and over

3718851901
01:04:20.214 --> 01:04:23.122
a decade since IPP
sentences were abolished,

1163242793
01:04:23.123 --> 01:04:26.316
so will the Justice Secretary
urge his department

585696970
01:04:26.317 --> 01:04:29.117
to do all it can to
expedite Jimmy's release,

1766356227
01:04:29.118 --> 01:04:33.914
and that of the other
estimated 2800 people

2092243228
01:04:33.915 --> 01:04:37.366
who remain in prison on IPP sentences.

1922645418
01:04:37.367 --> 01:04:41.668
>> So will I recognise the real
issues that exist for IPP prisoners,

656743273
01:04:41.669 --> 01:04:46.430
and we have discussed this at
length and will continue to do so.

3368649369
01:04:46.812 --> 01:04:50.363
The Prisons Ministers has done
a lot of work in this area,

254671652
01:04:50.364 --> 01:04:51.718
engaged with all of those,

3982121042
01:04:51.719 --> 01:04:53.122
including in Another place,

216863793
01:04:53.123 --> 01:04:56.515
who raised these issues
on almost a weekly basis.

377511924
01:04:56.516 --> 01:05:00.016
And of course, we want to do
more and see those prisoners

974272936
01:05:00.017 --> 01:05:02.914
who are not going to cause
public harm released.

309326233
01:05:02.915 --> 01:05:04.368
>> That completes questions.

824753881
01:05:26.814 --> 01:05:28.317
>> The frontbench changeover.

4139627906
01:05:28.318 --> 01:05:28.970
We now come.

2898448929
01:05:30.813 --> 01:05:32.418
>> To the urgent question, sir.

1227009656
01:05:32.419 --> 01:05:34.564
>> Jeremy Wright thank you, Mr.

1087621523
01:05:34.565 --> 01:05:35.015
Speaker.

3961284173
01:05:35.016 --> 01:05:37.977
To ask the Chancellor of
the Duchy of Lancaster if he will

186699127
01:05:37.978 --> 01:05:41.418
make a statement on
the government's approach to redacting

3240727299
01:05:41.419 --> 01:05:45.174
or withholding documents within
scope of the Humble Address

1118236828
01:05:45.175 --> 01:05:47.935
agreed by this House on
the 4th of February this year.

502788544
01:05:47.935 --> 01:05:48.938
>> Secretary Jones.

2141878208
01:05:48.939 --> 01:05:51.013
>> Thank you, Mr.

2175302541
01:05:51.014 --> 01:05:51.464
Speaker.

3654099934
01:05:51.465 --> 01:05:54.124
As I've set out to this House
on previous occasions,

3131071445
01:05:54.125 --> 01:05:57.968
the government is working to comply
with the motion passed in February.

1200399411
01:05:57.969 --> 01:06:01.123
I can reassure the House
that this remains the case

3659913643
01:06:01.124 --> 01:06:03.817
and can provide
the following update today.

3213004427
01:06:03.818 --> 01:06:08.261
The government confirmed before
prorogation that it had referred

2664932578
01:06:08.263 --> 01:06:11.797
over 300 documents to
the Intelligence and Security Committee,

98226800
01:06:11.798 --> 01:06:14.976
which at the time represented
all of the documents in

3669338252
01:06:14.977 --> 01:06:17.484
scope of the motion where
the government believed

1615613363
01:06:17.484 --> 01:06:20.169
that publication would be
prejudicial to UK national

2670404973
01:06:20.170 --> 01:06:23.063
security or international relations.

4157437335
01:06:23.064 --> 01:06:26.316
The government has repeatedly
assessed all of the documents

1800270262
01:06:26.317 --> 01:06:29.230
it has collected to make
sure that all of those

2850808188
01:06:29.231 --> 01:06:32.167
that need to be referred
to the ISC are referred to

1089586172
01:06:32.168 --> 01:06:35.466
the committee as part of this
quality control process.

52365780
01:06:35.467 --> 01:06:37.673
The government identified
a small number of

2606498841
01:06:37.674 --> 01:06:39.730
further documents that it felt should be

3476573238
01:06:39.731 --> 01:06:42.037
reviewed by the ISC
and immediately submitted

4021386640
01:06:42.038 --> 01:06:43.742
these documents to the committee.

1484359161
01:06:43.743 --> 01:06:47.066
As Friday's statement from
the committee set out,

2223213989
01:06:47.067 --> 01:06:49.374
it has now considered
all of these documents.

301591135
01:06:49.375 --> 01:06:51.382
As I have previously said to the House,

719941344
01:06:51.383 --> 01:06:54.592
the government will be publishing
a second tranche of material.

2703626386
01:06:54.593 --> 01:06:57.252
This is currently being
finalised and will be one of

4144784695
01:06:57.252 --> 01:07:01.069
the largest government publications
ever laid in this House.

1771814546
01:07:01.071 --> 01:07:03.529
This is reflective of
the breadth of the motion,

12526122
01:07:03.530 --> 01:07:05.384
and also the government's commitment

559241237
01:07:05.385 --> 01:07:07.240
to transparency in responding to it.

559963975
01:07:08.817 --> 01:07:12.220
It constitutes a very
significant disclosure exercise

394231352
01:07:12.221 --> 01:07:14.876
involving sensitive material
from across government.

3001918235
01:07:14.877 --> 01:07:17.433
The government has taken
seriously its obligations

2217488687
01:07:17.434 --> 01:07:19.591
to comply with the Humble Address in full,

3439009851
01:07:19.816 --> 01:07:23.212
while also upholding other
public interest issues,

4279608586
01:07:23.212 --> 01:07:25.321
such as our duty of care to junior staff.

2367099342
01:07:25.322 --> 01:07:28.933
The government has carried out this
work according to a robust process,

1673626185
01:07:28.934 --> 01:07:32.617
with assurance from an independent KC,

3952816843
01:07:32.618 --> 01:07:35.514
given the House is due
to rise on Thursday, Mr.

488767620
01:07:35.515 --> 01:07:38.022
Speaker, and given
the length of the publication.

702486428
01:07:38.023 --> 01:07:41.014
The second tranche will now
be published after Whitsun

3887347793
01:07:41.015 --> 01:07:43.222
recess to give to give
the House sufficient

1286141489
01:07:43.223 --> 01:07:45.532
time to review
the material and to be able to

4036329083
01:07:45.533 --> 01:07:47.589
ask me and the government questions, Mr.

3824158547
01:07:47.590 --> 01:07:48.040
Speaker.

2050343191
01:07:48.041 --> 01:07:50.522
It could have been published
this Thursday, Mr.

1037605732
01:07:50.523 --> 01:07:54.135
Speaker, but I felt that the House
would deem that to be inappropriate,

867738710
01:07:54.136 --> 01:07:58.415
given it will be such
a significant publication.

1785706478
01:07:58.416 --> 01:07:58.616
Mr.

1735400350
01:07:58.617 --> 01:08:01.225
speaker, I just refer back
to my previous comments.

734052114
01:08:01.226 --> 01:08:04.185
This will be the largest
publication, other than, I think,

2018290139
01:08:04.185 --> 01:08:06.993
the Chilcot inquiry report
ever published to the House.

2381688461
01:08:06.995 --> 01:08:10.153
When the government publishes
the second tranche of documents,

3895500139
01:08:10.154 --> 01:08:12.460
we will also publish
a methodology confirming

2114801740
01:08:12.461 --> 01:08:13.965
the process we have followed,

212891900
01:08:13.966 --> 01:08:16.574
and it will be clear from
the published information

1147144570
01:08:16.816 --> 01:08:19.123
the basis on which content
has been redacted,

2532135232
01:08:19.124 --> 01:08:22.032
the targeted redactions made
to the material beyond those

703517194
01:08:22.033 --> 01:08:24.639
made relevant to national
security or international

2852200426
01:08:24.640 --> 01:08:26.847
relations have been
made in line with clear

142990611
01:08:26.848 --> 01:08:29.002
precedent set by previous administrations.

3953862136
01:08:29.002 --> 01:08:30.757
In responding to humble addresses.

2047646739
01:08:30.758 --> 01:08:33.376
As I set out to the House
on the 23rd of February,

319820167
01:08:33.377 --> 01:08:35.684
and again when we published
the first tranche

54023089
01:08:35.685 --> 01:08:37.573
of material on the 11th of March.

3737955637
01:08:37.574 --> 01:08:41.134
We have taken the normal approach to
redacting junior officials names,

989266998
01:08:41.135 --> 01:08:45.381
contact details like telephone
numbers and email addresses,

2501407224
01:08:45.382 --> 01:08:47.187
the personal data of third parties,

674972846
01:08:47.188 --> 01:08:50.249
where this is not in scope of
the motion and where relevant,

2362217364
01:08:50.250 --> 01:08:51.752
legal professional privilege.

3353427019
01:08:51.752 --> 01:08:54.069
This has been done using
the principles set

761137012
01:08:54.069 --> 01:08:56.026
out in the Freedom of Information Act,

404292506
01:08:56.027 --> 01:08:59.087
and in line with the Ministerial
Code and the resolutions on

131730141
01:08:59.087 --> 01:09:03.124
ministerial accountability
passed by both houses in 1997,

3694363998
01:09:03.125 --> 01:09:06.073
which state that Ministers
should be as open as possible

2754289000
01:09:06.074 --> 01:09:08.781
with Parliament and not
provide information only when

337683089
01:09:08.819 --> 01:09:11.227
disclosure would not be
in the public interest,

66821759
01:09:11.228 --> 01:09:14.336
which should be decided in
accordance with relevant statutes.

987054618
01:09:14.337 --> 01:09:17.145
I am sure members across
the House will recognise there

2029052946
01:09:17.147 --> 01:09:19.703
is no public interest in
the government publishing

1794527975
01:09:19.705 --> 01:09:22.212
the names and contact
details of junior officials

789080692
01:09:22.212 --> 01:09:24.218
or their telephone numbers, Mr Speaker.

1384510056
01:09:24.219 --> 01:09:24.921
>> Or Maldon.

1775068494
01:09:24.922 --> 01:09:25.624
I don't know.

908389647
01:09:25.625 --> 01:09:28.736
I know you've been here quite
a time, but it's three minutes.

587843512
01:09:29.818 --> 01:09:31.825
We're over 3.5 minutes now and I wasn't

4194381397
01:09:31.826 --> 01:09:34.270
given notice of extra time needed,

552947827
01:09:34.270 --> 01:09:37.421
and obviously other people
would need to know that.

507248387
01:09:37.422 --> 01:09:37.822
Please.

1374127860
01:09:37.823 --> 01:09:39.530
I did set out rules of the House.

1343285397
01:09:39.531 --> 01:09:41.398
We should adhere to them once again.

881095235
01:09:41.399 --> 01:09:42.351
We've broken them.

2657013852
01:09:42.352 --> 01:09:44.008
We've only been back a few days.

1383927364
01:09:44.009 --> 01:09:45.564
