02:13:03.569 --> 02:13:08.540
to cancel the line in the Midlands.

731180835
02:13:08.541 --> 02:13:09.595
>> My right, my hon.

3784272948
02:13:09.596 --> 02:13:13.496
Friend, has been a great
advocate for his constituents

1430148824
02:13:13.497 --> 02:13:15.504
and I totally agree that the focus now,

3209824120
02:13:15.505 --> 02:13:17.292
as it should have been all along,

1556723999
02:13:17.293 --> 02:13:21.895
is about delivering more seats
and trains that run on time.

760146527
02:13:21.896 --> 02:13:24.989
We will be conducting
a further feasibility study

3896439496
02:13:24.990 --> 02:13:27.588
into connectivity north of Birmingham,

2675960754
02:13:27.589 --> 02:13:31.245
which will consider all
options and the impact

2182036872
02:13:31.246 --> 02:13:33.743
of each option on economic growth,

2381804337
02:13:33.744 --> 02:13:37.423
housing capacity on the rail network,
journey times and resilience,

4292881870
02:13:37.424 --> 02:13:41.890
as well as looking at how
we might design consent,

2022655255
02:13:41.891 --> 02:13:45.255
fund the scheme, the specification
of any future scheme.

3015791835
02:13:45.256 --> 02:13:50.890
So I'm willing to continue a dialogue
with him about those issues.

1371211117
02:13:50.891 --> 02:13:51.693
>> Smith thank.

3425718398
02:13:51.694 --> 02:13:53.198
>> You, Madam Deputy Speaker.

3086366084
02:13:53.199 --> 02:13:56.360
>> The Secretary of State in her
statement said she was angry,

2161960957
02:13:56.361 --> 02:13:58.568
and I can assure her
I've been consistently

516152396
02:13:58.569 --> 02:14:00.122
angry about this unaffordable,

915740031
02:14:00.123 --> 02:14:02.430
unwanted railway since
it was ever green lit,

818207850
02:14:02.431 --> 02:14:05.089
angry on behalf of my
constituents that have to live

1445853437
02:14:05.091 --> 02:14:07.546
under hellish conditions
while it's constructed,

1886700119
02:14:07.547 --> 02:14:10.485
landowners still waiting for
payment for land taken,

344810250
02:14:10.486 --> 02:14:13.995
our roads churned up by construction,
traffic going unfixed.

2147454255
02:14:13.996 --> 02:14:16.652
Mitigation projects promised
a decade ago that still

702540618
02:14:16.654 --> 02:14:19.243
don't actually have
the money to deliver them.

2530232247
02:14:19.244 --> 02:14:22.087
I heard nothing about
any of those challenges

2758654404
02:14:22.088 --> 02:14:24.043
in the Secretary of State's statement,

159097337
02:14:24.044 --> 02:14:28.341
but can I ask a very specifically
about noise modelling in Wendover?

2920379498
02:14:28.342 --> 02:14:30.749
Hundreds of homes
and trains were already going

3464583816
02:14:30.750 --> 02:14:34.241
to come through Wendover at 320km an hour.

1954297236
02:14:34.243 --> 02:14:38.643
Already, hundreds of homes
under modelling are found to

3722595347
02:14:38.643 --> 02:14:41.895
be above the permitted decibel
limit that the W.H.O.

1187408851
02:14:41.896 --> 02:14:42.447
sets down.

1747402887
02:14:42.448 --> 02:14:45.156
So, under the new speed
that she has set for HS2,

1242694034
02:14:45.157 --> 02:14:48.294
will she commit to
the government fully remodelling,

610680728
02:14:48.889 --> 02:14:50.641
certainly through Buckinghamshire,

2099122584
02:14:50.642 --> 02:14:53.953
the noise impacts of this railway
on real people once it's built,

1611050778
02:14:53.954 --> 02:14:57.096
and come back to the House
with a commitment that

3304243570
02:14:57.097 --> 02:15:01.388
those levels will not be
above the WHO guidance.

3523639780
02:15:01.389 --> 02:15:02.542
>> Secretary of State.

663838877
02:15:02.543 --> 02:15:05.302
>> Madam Deputy Speaker,
I do appreciate that the hon.

2341840981
02:15:07.889 --> 02:15:10.092
Gentleman's constituents
in Buckinghamshire

614795601
02:15:10.093 --> 02:15:13.097
will have experienced considerable

1009615799
02:15:13.098 --> 02:15:16.508
disruption to their lives as
a result of this construction project,

4127032023
02:15:16.509 --> 02:15:19.297
and I know that it is
the case that some of the time,

3028676025
02:15:19.298 --> 02:15:23.039
those who live nearest by
infrastructure infrastructure schemes

962835064
02:15:23.040 --> 02:15:26.396
tend to take more of the pain
before the gain is delivered.

101336546
02:15:26.397 --> 02:15:32.000
In terms of the new service,
I will look into the matter that

3625114502
02:15:32.000 --> 02:15:38.339
he raises around the noise impacts
of a lower speed railway.

2639327967
02:15:38.339 --> 02:15:41.363
My instinct is that
the noise is likely to be less,

1016878496
02:15:41.364 --> 02:15:43.271
but if it is any different from that,

2175321945
02:15:43.272 --> 02:15:45.279
I will certainly write back to the hon.

727444681
02:15:45.280 --> 02:15:47.589
Gentleman and let him know.

2162233114
02:15:47.591 --> 02:15:50.689
>> Dave Robertson thank
you, Madam Deputy Speaker.

1644426939
02:15:50.690 --> 02:15:53.539
The Secretary of State
will not be surprised to

3063614516
02:15:53.540 --> 02:15:57.640
see me rise to raise
issues with HS2 yet again,

4158714247
02:15:57.641 --> 02:16:00.302
and she is very right to be
angry about the scale of

707880420
02:16:00.303 --> 02:16:03.263
the failings that have been
laid out in the reports today.

4055832606
02:16:03.264 --> 02:16:08.548
She is angry, I am angry, but that
absolutely pales into insignificance

924978239
02:16:08.892 --> 02:16:11.249
when compared to the anger
of my constituents,

3746910341
02:16:11.848 --> 02:16:13.957
who have had to fight through 17 years of

181303946
02:16:13.958 --> 02:16:16.597
dealing with the failures of HS2 limited.

377388192
02:16:16.598 --> 02:16:19.207
Part of the announcement
today is that we will face

3295374249
02:16:19.208 --> 02:16:21.594
potentially another 13
years before they even

4119116565
02:16:21.595 --> 02:16:24.643
continue to carry on with
work north of Curzon

242217537
02:16:24.645 --> 02:16:27.000
Street and connecting
into Handsacre Junction.

2573187975
02:16:27.000 --> 02:16:29.546
All of which, by the way,
is north of Birmingham.

1519243960
02:16:29.547 --> 02:16:31.495
The community is furious.

2149787925
02:16:31.496 --> 02:16:35.188
My constituents are potentially the most,

3677091511
02:16:35.189 --> 02:16:37.497
or certainly one of
the most impacted by HS2.

622185755
02:16:37.892 --> 02:16:42.252
Just last month they closed the A38
going past Lichfield, forcing 70,000

2232477803
02:16:42.253 --> 02:16:46.104
vehicles a day onto local
roads in the city.

1653071178
02:16:46.105 --> 02:16:49.197
Constituents are fed up,
so can she give some reassurance

8786756
02:16:49.198 --> 02:16:51.906
that the works at Streethay,
which are still ongoing,

3204860232
02:16:51.907 --> 02:16:56.491
one of only two places north of Curzon
Street where work is continuing,

2400670981
02:16:56.493 --> 02:16:58.348
will be completed on time by October

2241050783
02:16:58.350 --> 02:17:00.356
and that the department will look very,

1658345056
02:17:00.357 --> 02:17:02.864
very closely at what
mitigations they are putting

414979636
02:17:02.865 --> 02:17:04.871
in place for communities like mine who,

1250004684
02:17:04.872 --> 02:17:07.031
by the sounds of it, could face a third of

1060511152
02:17:07.032 --> 02:17:09.139
a century from the start of this process,

2814962437
02:17:09.140 --> 02:17:12.148
before trains actually start
travelling through our part of

3717987404
02:17:12.149 --> 02:17:17.157
the world and the significant
impact it's had on our community.

647066892
02:17:17.158 --> 02:17:17.458
Yeah.

2060717821
02:17:17.887 --> 02:17:18.841
>> I thank my hon.

1240723327
02:17:18.842 --> 02:17:20.145
Friend for that question.

4101358457
02:17:20.146 --> 02:17:25.643
And he has been a fierce advocate
for his constituents on this issue,

1609345719
02:17:25.645 --> 02:17:28.606
and I know that he will be
meeting with the Rail Ministers

4276398722
02:17:28.607 --> 02:17:32.295
later today to talk about
constituency impacts.

690915624
02:17:32.296 --> 02:17:36.598
I have heard nothing to
suggest that the works

368015729
02:17:36.598 --> 02:17:39.844
at Street will not be delivered on time.

2360103341
02:17:39.845 --> 02:17:43.256
If there is any latest information
that I haven't been apprised of,

32491337
02:17:43.257 --> 02:17:46.447
I will certainly come back to my hon.

346715941
02:17:46.448 --> 02:17:49.192
Friend and let him know.

3750444268
02:17:49.193 --> 02:17:52.347
Of course, it is important
that we do continue

2392943246
02:17:52.348 --> 02:17:54.152
with the works north of Birmingham,

3409939476
02:17:54.154 --> 02:17:56.008
Birmingham up to Handsacre Junction,

2015279963
02:17:56.009 --> 02:18:00.950
because this is the way that HS2
will connect into the wider

3267096486
02:18:00.951 --> 02:18:05.301
rail network and whilst in
the short term this will.

3842178872
02:18:05.302 --> 02:18:10.694
This project will improve connections
between London and Birmingham.

382655735
02:18:10.695 --> 02:18:14.102
In the longer term, this is
about improving the frequency,

1893618242
02:18:14.103 --> 02:18:16.258
capacity and reliability of connections to

2383883507
02:18:16.259 --> 02:18:19.798
the North West and beyond
to Scotland as well,

2040903140
02:18:19.799 --> 02:18:22.848
so I appreciate his constituents
patience on this project,

1807103245
02:18:22.848 --> 02:18:25.246
but it is important for
the national interest.

1582139628
02:18:25.247 --> 02:18:26.199
So, Jeremy Wright.

2053914616
02:18:26.200 --> 02:18:28.507
>> Thank you very much,
Madam Deputy Speaker.

2710903524
02:18:28.508 --> 02:18:30.767
>> I have to say I share a good deal of

1430247154
02:18:30.768 --> 02:18:32.672
the Secretary of State's frustration,

3677284792
02:18:32.673 --> 02:18:35.951
not least because I was one of
those who argued at the time that

2741261214
02:18:35.952 --> 02:18:39.463
if the speed of the railways reduced
to roughly what she's proposing,

3970868011
02:18:39.464 --> 02:18:42.273
it would open up a number of
alternative route options,

1358972565
02:18:42.274 --> 02:18:45.333
avoiding the open countryside
that the line now cuts across.

4030343927
02:18:45.334 --> 02:18:49.801
But can I counterintuitively ask
her to be a little more ambitious?

1634699772
02:18:49.802 --> 02:18:52.459
Despite everything she's
said about high speed rail,

226649834
02:18:52.460 --> 02:18:55.451
she will recognise that
the strategic benefits of high

765378672
02:18:55.452 --> 02:18:58.493
speed rail as they were put
to this House originally,

4254201280
02:18:58.494 --> 02:19:00.148
were about a network nationwide,

3229487052
02:19:00.149 --> 02:19:03.148
not simply a line between
London and Birmingham.

1678986268
02:19:03.149 --> 02:19:05.901
So can I ask her to state,
hopefully at least,

3915641642
02:19:05.902 --> 02:19:09.049
that this and future governments
will seek to expand

16292490
02:19:09.050 --> 02:19:11.898
that network so that
what we're focussed on,

1922720574
02:19:11.899 --> 02:19:19.342
on high speed rail is not going
faster, but on going further.

2821646588
02:19:19.343 --> 02:19:19.945
>> The hon.

1774091134
02:19:19.946 --> 02:19:22.843
Gentleman makes a very interesting point.

3190555037
02:19:22.844 --> 02:19:26.461
And I would say to him that one of
the things I'm most keen to do is to

3907855351
02:19:26.462 --> 02:19:33.293
ensure that this huge investment
that we are putting into HS2 between

758063222
02:19:33.294 --> 02:19:35.248
London and Birmingham actually results

103070988
02:19:35.249 --> 02:19:37.395
in an improved passenger experience

2111699366
02:19:37.396 --> 02:19:40.898
for people more broadly across
the rest of the country.

1287259610
02:19:40.899 --> 02:19:43.959
That's one of the reasons why,
when we made the announcement

343885381
02:19:43.960 --> 02:19:46.466
about Northern Powerhouse
Rail earlier this year,

532261382
02:19:46.893 --> 02:19:51.191
that we also announced
a feasibility study about

2743094687
02:19:51.192 --> 02:19:56.491
a new connection between
Birmingham and Manchester.

994609687
02:19:56.493 --> 02:19:58.801
And whilst it's slightly
too soon to get into

1383376116
02:19:58.892 --> 02:20:02.191
the specifics of exactly
what that would look like,

1265890141
02:20:02.192 --> 02:20:04.149
I can assure him that the thinking and

2724320502
02:20:04.150 --> 02:20:06.507
the planning is happening
in the department at

3850649368
02:20:06.508 --> 02:20:09.350
the moment to make sure that
this investment unlocks

2081299563
02:20:09.351 --> 02:20:11.700
the maximum benefit across the country.

4191764550
02:20:11.701 --> 02:20:14.400
>> John McDonnell.

2005868570
02:20:14.401 --> 02:20:15.354
>> Given the huge.

3927678574
02:20:15.355 --> 02:20:17.663
>> Sums she's talking
about, what what I want

1131704192
02:20:17.664 --> 02:20:19.768
to raise might appear relatively trivial,

2537983753
02:20:19.770 --> 02:20:23.098
but actually for my community,
it's quite significant.

965556848
02:20:23.098 --> 02:20:25.457
It is that we have
a charity called Hillingdon

3320172370
02:20:25.458 --> 02:20:28.095
Outdoor Activity Centre that ran

3599010119
02:20:28.096 --> 02:20:30.254
a lake for to enable local young people in

428249579
02:20:30.888 --> 02:20:32.844
particular to learn to sail and canoe.

2350796288
02:20:32.845 --> 02:20:37.352
That lake has been taken over
by HS2 as part of the route.

2310931853
02:20:37.353 --> 02:20:41.154
Therefore, it's not been
available for six years now.

2149381465
02:20:41.155 --> 02:20:45.149
An alternative has not been identified
until very recently and again,

2465356808
02:20:45.150 --> 02:20:49.003
part of the decision making with
regard to HS2 itself as well.

2393709951
02:20:49.004 --> 02:20:51.902
It's meant that charity,
now all its reserves have

1405468144
02:20:51.902 --> 02:20:54.061
now gone and the staff are being laid off.

3165103368
02:20:54.062 --> 02:20:58.299
And I just wonder, could the Secretary
of State arrange for a meeting

3768627064
02:20:58.300 --> 02:21:02.698
with her officials and HS2 that
I can meet them to talk through

3963482602
02:21:02.699 --> 02:21:05.859
the opportunities that there might
be to assist the charity to

2788876761
02:21:05.860 --> 02:21:10.102
continue providing such an excellent
service to our community?

1211741386
02:21:11.854 --> 02:21:14.161
>> I'd be very happy to
ask relevant officers

2918826807
02:21:16.897 --> 02:21:18.402
from HS2 to meet with my hon.

2476168287
02:21:18.404 --> 02:21:21.249
Friend and to look at
options for the Hillingdon

2613358633
02:21:21.250 --> 02:21:25.848
Outdoor Activity Centre that he mentioned.

3772707594
02:21:25.850 --> 02:21:29.163
When I look at the scale of some
of the structures that are being

3806740856
02:21:29.164 --> 02:21:32.054
built on the outskirts of
London at the moment, the 2.1

2632912572
02:21:32.055 --> 02:21:37.650
mile Colne Valley viaduct, for example,

1775836454
02:21:37.651 --> 02:21:43.096
it's evident what a a huge and ambitious
construction project this is,

3098050717
02:21:43.097 --> 02:21:49.348
and I'm sorry that there will have
been some impacts on communities,

2617331757
02:21:49.350 --> 02:21:50.802
individual community groups,

3028763406
02:21:50.902 --> 02:21:57.049
and I would be happy to look at
what the alternatives might be.

4165340345
02:21:57.050 --> 02:21:59.457
>> Sarah Green thank you,
Madam Deputy Speaker.

1415813522
02:21:59.458 --> 02:22:02.316
My constituents in Chesham
and Amersham didn't want HS2,

3337620340
02:22:02.317 --> 02:22:07.049
and they've been putting
up with the disruption

3143241042
02:22:07.050 --> 02:22:08.402
of construction for years.

2502579027
02:22:09.898 --> 02:22:13.657
Some of them warned that this would
be a colossal waste of money.

3975085304
02:22:13.658 --> 02:22:14.711
And they were right.

2124544753
02:22:14.712 --> 02:22:19.152
This railway is costing
nearly £1 billion a mile.

3039891899
02:22:19.154 --> 02:22:22.552
Every pound of cost overrun is a pound

2634262764
02:22:22.553 --> 02:22:24.997
not spent on the local infrastructure.

3962849082
02:22:24.998 --> 02:22:27.844
My constituents actually
use and actually need.

2008558611
02:22:27.845 --> 02:22:32.748
So given the department's complete failure

117596776
02:22:32.749 --> 02:22:34.756
to date to hold HS2 limited to account,

2507437552
02:22:34.757 --> 02:22:38.398
what commitment can
the Secretary of State give that

1523128420
02:22:38.399 --> 02:22:40.607
we won't be here again
in a few years time?

34864674
02:22:41.896 --> 02:22:43.348
Talking about HS2 overspend?

133968933
02:22:43.350 --> 02:22:43.600
Yes.

1206250508
02:22:43.601 --> 02:22:50.056
>> We have taken a different
approach this time.

1821925521
02:22:50.057 --> 02:22:53.604
Our estimates are based on
prices that have been informed

3173960580
02:22:53.897 --> 02:22:58.246
by the work that has been done
over the last five years.

4103984476
02:22:58.247 --> 02:23:02.098
I am committed to ensuring that
the scope remains the same,

3512078573
02:23:02.100 --> 02:23:05.259
and we don't have the chopping
and changing that characterised

662441236
02:23:05.259 --> 02:23:07.866
the previous government's
approach to this project.

4067170305
02:23:07.866 --> 02:23:10.498
But I would also say to her,

866365597
02:23:10.499 --> 02:23:15.559
whilst recognising there will be
some impacts in her constituency,

4182026320
02:23:15.560 --> 02:23:18.048
that this is a great engineering feat

2683259963
02:23:18.049 --> 02:23:21.652
that we are involved in delivering.

1492821810
02:23:21.652 --> 02:23:27.758
The first new terminus Station that
this country has built in 125 years.

2521898351
02:23:27.759 --> 02:23:31.552
New stations at Birmingham
Interchange, Old Oak, Common,

3624334133
02:23:32.897 --> 02:23:34.954
Euston and so whilst I'm always happy to

3416476997
02:23:34.955 --> 02:23:38.354
talk to her about the local impacts,

4249530189
02:23:38.355 --> 02:23:41.906
I think in terms of the improvements to

61344394
02:23:41.907 --> 02:23:43.863
the rail network that HS2 can provide,

2154277793
02:23:43.864 --> 02:23:48.348
it is very significant and I think
this government is entirely right

2102345329
02:23:48.350 --> 02:23:52.056
to be committed to delivering
this project to its completion.

4115628949
02:23:52.057 --> 02:23:53.661
>> Toby Perkins thank you very.

4183373571
02:23:53.663 --> 02:23:55.217
>> Much, Madam Deputy Speaker.

3566172949
02:23:55.218 --> 02:23:57.524
Is the Member of Parliament
for Chesterfield.

3319002965
02:23:57.525 --> 02:24:01.149
My constituents at one time hoped
they might be beneficiaries of HS2.

652151013
02:24:01.150 --> 02:24:07.007
That seems so many years ago,
but I share the Secretary of State's

415295023
02:24:07.008 --> 02:24:10.304
fury at the incompetence that
has got us to this stage.

1049341537
02:24:10.305 --> 02:24:13.109
We wouldn't have supported
a program like this if we'd

3533960312
02:24:13.110 --> 02:24:15.720
known it was only going to
be a line to Birmingham.

2966714250
02:24:15.721 --> 02:24:18.229
It should be going, as any
serious country would,

3242160307
02:24:18.230 --> 02:24:21.141
to have high speed rail up to
Manchester and up to Leeds.

2019634580
02:24:21.142 --> 02:24:23.802
At the very least, I'm very
glad that she's laid out

1867797619
02:24:23.803 --> 02:24:26.705
today how she's going to try
and get a grip of this,

1464113264
02:24:26.707 --> 02:24:29.366
but can I add to what we've
heard from the gentleman

1233330460
02:24:29.368 --> 02:24:31.223
from Kenilworth and Southam and say,

1606881680
02:24:31.223 --> 02:24:34.383
once the government has managed
to demonstrate that under this

1577258921
02:24:34.384 --> 02:24:37.295
government we have got a grip
of the costs and the times,

2340081591
02:24:37.296 --> 02:24:40.756
can we start to be more ambitious
about reopening discussions around

3517975286
