little environmental gain.

2658577012
02:53:47.285 --> 02:53:50.579
Is he fighting it?

3615622030
02:53:50.580 --> 02:53:50.780
No.

1548667791
02:53:50.781 --> 02:53:52.335
He's defending the status quo.

431360149
02:53:52.336 --> 02:53:54.482
But by the end of this Parliament,

2182378713
02:53:54.484 --> 02:53:56.541
we'll still be waiting for a decision as

3707291666
02:53:56.542 --> 02:53:59.684
to whether SMS will go ahead by 2030.

296008339
02:53:59.685 --> 02:54:04.636
There will be less nuclear
online than there is now.

1488807150
02:54:04.637 --> 02:54:09.739
And in 2035, which is ten years
away, they still won't have started

2698662826
02:54:09.740 --> 02:54:13.118
any new large scale nuclear
power plants in this country.

1759327689
02:54:13.119 --> 02:54:15.734
This is the same old stop start approach

1879554047
02:54:15.735 --> 02:54:18.336
that killed the industry to begin with,

1666482091
02:54:18.337 --> 02:54:22.384
if that's what he calls being
ambitious for nuclear,

2429473912
02:54:22.386 --> 02:54:25.881
he needs to give his head a wobble.

941408984
02:54:25.882 --> 02:54:26.585
>> I thank I.

3164774690
02:54:26.586 --> 02:54:29.190
>> Thank the hon.

1474518460
02:54:29.191 --> 02:54:30.244
Lady for giving way.

2318580613
02:54:30.245 --> 02:54:32.601
In my constituency of
Morecambe and Lunesdale,

924756267
02:54:32.602 --> 02:54:34.709
we have Heysham one and two power plants.

726521303
02:54:34.710 --> 02:54:37.469
The reason that nuclear power
will possibly go down is

3460397170
02:54:37.470 --> 02:54:40.129
because plants are coming
to the end of their lives.

3168948526
02:54:40.130 --> 02:54:42.087
Plants come to the end of their lives,

624230465
02:54:42.088 --> 02:54:44.044
and you and the honourable, right hon.

1777016120
02:54:44.045 --> 02:54:47.433
Lady's government did nothing
about it for 14 years.

1088443358
02:54:47.434 --> 02:54:47.884
>> Yeah.

3282307563
02:54:47.886 --> 02:54:48.136
Yes.

712784113
02:54:48.137 --> 02:54:50.143
>> Why did she not deliver Madam Deputy

855587973
02:54:50.145 --> 02:54:53.533
Speaker when she was in government?

2688585532
02:54:53.534 --> 02:54:53.985
>> Yeah.

2368160177
02:54:53.986 --> 02:54:55.793
>> Well, look, let me tell the hon.

2357122604
02:54:55.794 --> 02:54:57.749
Lady under the last Labour government,

2373202572
02:54:57.930 --> 02:55:00.639
which the Energy Secretary
was part of, not a single.

3217443172
02:55:03.929 --> 02:55:04.731
Let me explain.

4027219981
02:55:04.732 --> 02:55:08.586
Not a single, not a single new
nuclear power plant was started.

2176168161
02:55:08.587 --> 02:55:10.685
So when we came into power in 2015,

3923337529
02:55:10.686 --> 02:55:14.589
when we got control of the energy brief,

1944393434
02:55:14.589 --> 02:55:18.382
there was one nuclear
welder left in the country.

422915109
02:55:18.383 --> 02:55:22.034
It is the stop start approach
which kills the nuclear industry.

350927369
02:55:22.035 --> 02:55:23.238
And here's the problem.

2021026997
02:55:23.239 --> 02:55:25.234
They have killed the pipeline.

618673728
02:55:25.235 --> 02:55:27.884
Again, these are the same old mistakes.

3387155015
02:55:27.886 --> 02:55:29.592
And that is why I'm raising them,

3381638222
02:55:29.593 --> 02:55:32.150
because we're getting into
the same trouble again.

2594140149
02:55:32.933 --> 02:55:35.841
Now, Madam Deputy Speaker, he
says they weren't mistakes.

2545035415
02:55:35.842 --> 02:55:38.853
It wasn't a mistake not to start
a new nuclear power plant.

3390037833
02:55:38.854 --> 02:55:40.710
That's what he thinks on the record.

1406040941
02:55:40.711 --> 02:55:44.439
Now, Madam Deputy Speaker,
on to the North Sea.

214316746
02:55:44.440 --> 02:55:47.683
Andy Burnham, who is hoping
to be Labour leader,

1830629238
02:55:47.684 --> 02:55:50.978
talked yesterday about
Reindustrialisation.

1964083012
02:55:50.979 --> 02:55:54.433
But meanwhile, today
the Secretary of State is asking

1828307107
02:55:54.434 --> 02:55:58.931
his backbenchers to vote to
shut down the North Sea.

3950218221
02:55:58.932 --> 02:56:01.629
This is the single
greatest act of industrial

3313417751
02:56:01.630 --> 02:56:04.527
self-harm we have seen in a generation.

3119018013
02:56:04.529 --> 02:56:07.729
Only a complete wacko would
respond to a supply shortage

2956490286
02:56:07.730 --> 02:56:12.789
by shutting down their own
oil and gas industry.

3662383636
02:56:12.790 --> 02:56:16.084
We are in the absurd position
of the Labour Chancellor,

1973841786
02:56:16.085 --> 02:56:21.493
thanking Canada and Norway for
increasing their oil and gas production

717417935
02:56:21.934 --> 02:56:26.783
