shutting British production down.

2249018757
02:56:26.784 --> 02:56:27.235
And why?

283991277
02:56:27.236 --> 02:56:32.049
So we can be more reliant on higher
emission gas from Qatar or the US,

3419572645
02:56:32.050 --> 02:56:35.212
so we can send billions of pounds
to Norway to import gas from

3473465789
02:56:35.213 --> 02:56:39.929
the very same basin that we
could be drilling ourselves.

1000552223
02:56:39.930 --> 02:56:42.591
And they're calling this
energy independence.

610794568
02:56:42.592 --> 02:56:43.996
Have they lost their minds?

2086328528
02:56:43.997 --> 02:56:44.398
>> Yes.

224304172
02:56:44.399 --> 02:56:46.406
>> I'll happily give way on that point.

765501470
02:56:46.407 --> 02:56:48.163
>> Very grateful to the right hon.

2471853082
02:56:48.164 --> 02:56:48.464
Lady.

1080913616
02:56:48.464 --> 02:56:50.018
She talks of absurd positions.

1705506914
02:56:50.020 --> 02:56:53.766
I did a little bit of research
before the speech today.

1487908013
02:56:53.767 --> 02:56:55.625
I went back to the 21st of May 2024,

3756403764
02:56:55.625 --> 02:56:57.580
just before the last general election,

3626584724
02:56:57.582 --> 02:56:59.388
and in this House, in her capacity,

130209135
02:56:59.389 --> 02:57:02.348
then as the Secretary of State,
she said that she believed

3971737661
02:57:02.350 --> 02:57:04.759
in net zero and that we
will get there in 2050.

2149430739
02:57:04.761 --> 02:57:06.417
And with the public on our side,

1251269977
02:57:06.418 --> 02:57:09.328
her position now is that she
doesn't believe in net zero,

3655850656
02:57:09.932 --> 02:57:12.237
doesn't believe it's
desirable or achievable.

1720635885
02:57:12.238 --> 02:57:15.290
Is that not absurd?

369703571
02:57:15.291 --> 02:57:15.741
>> Yeah.

2974808279
02:57:15.743 --> 02:57:16.996
>> Madam Deputy Speaker,

2253899869
02:57:16.997 --> 02:57:19.555
people change their minds
when they look at facts.

1472681006
02:57:20.932 --> 02:57:23.089
I'm not you know, I'm not hiding for this.

3680440382
02:57:23.091 --> 02:57:24.345
I'm not hiding for this.

1074136795
02:57:24.346 --> 02:57:25.900
>> It takes actually thinking.

300568074
02:57:25.901 --> 02:57:26.753
>> For yourself.

3183926987
02:57:26.754 --> 02:57:28.109
>> Though I think the hon.

2828278537
02:57:28.110 --> 02:57:30.066
Gentleman needs to look at the overall

3556811811
02:57:30.067 --> 02:57:32.023
record of things I said in government.

592221475
02:57:32.024 --> 02:57:35.236
The key thing, the first thing
I said when I went into position

462998525
02:57:35.237 --> 02:57:38.197
is we cannot impoverish ourselves
in the name of net zero.

4171064450
02:57:38.198 --> 02:57:41.408
You know, I started a true costing
of renewables and department

797292628
02:57:41.409 --> 02:57:43.967
because we didn't have
a proper costing of energy.

3458057805
02:57:43.968 --> 02:57:45.171
Who councils that work?

2592856123
02:57:45.172 --> 02:57:47.580
The Secretary of State,
I backed the North Sea.

224026604
02:57:47.580 --> 02:57:49.984
I signed off Rosebank.

2630433616
02:57:49.985 --> 02:57:53.934
I legislated to protect
those North Sea licences.

396251444
02:57:53.935 --> 02:57:55.741
Who was turning all of that around?

713331649
02:57:55.937 --> 02:57:57.140
The Secretary of State.

4137598489
02:57:57.141 --> 02:57:57.994
And we all know.

4265343959
02:57:57.995 --> 02:58:02.190
We all know the real
reason that he's doing it.

1015094725
02:58:02.191 --> 02:58:06.041
He's shutting down British oil
and gas to show climate leadership.

3212790900
02:58:06.042 --> 02:58:07.748
He put that in the King's Speech.

2305112658
02:58:07.933 --> 02:58:09.536
Let's be crystal clear, though.

3674294327
02:58:09.538 --> 02:58:11.812
What he's saying is that he's willing

2180719025
02:58:11.813 --> 02:58:15.436
to turn his back on British industry,

84562586
02:58:15.437 --> 02:58:17.243
even though we won't need any less.

2493054772
02:58:17.244 --> 02:58:22.788
We'll just rely on higher emission
imports from abroad because he cares

266834172
02:58:22.789 --> 02:58:26.637
more about the climate bureaucrats
than the jobs of British workers.

222525230
02:58:26.638 --> 02:58:29.838
That is what climate
leadership means to him.

347620578
02:58:29.839 --> 02:58:31.495
But the question I would ask is,

1052939408
02:58:31.496 --> 02:58:35.386
where exactly is this meant to
be leading us to bankruptcy?

3468147312
02:58:35.387 --> 02:58:36.339
Where does it end?

37445068
02:58:36.933 --> 02:58:40.888
Cheering as the lights go out as
the last factory in Britain closes.

2250786061
02:58:40.889 --> 02:58:45.447
That's what his North Sea
and carbon tax policies are doing.

245877414
02:58:45.448 --> 02:58:48.388
They are simply offshoring
British emissions

3774074100
02:58:48.389 --> 02:58:50.984
to the coal powered refineries of India.

4234934111
02:58:50.985 --> 02:58:54.187
The diesel tankers bring US
gas from the US and Qatar to

536148269
02:58:54.188 --> 02:58:57.837
the factories we are now getting
our ammonia from in Trinidad.

3423104570
02:58:57.838 --> 02:59:02.189
That doesn't help
the climate and it doesn't help

3615233374
02:59:02.190 --> 02:59:04.447
British workers give way
to the middle lady.

2220772210
02:59:04.448 --> 02:59:04.999
Thank you.

4152428303
02:59:05.000 --> 02:59:05.753
>> I thank my.

4052531580
02:59:05.754 --> 02:59:06.455
>> Right hon.

650808976
02:59:06.457 --> 02:59:10.388
Friend for giving way and businesses
in Bognor Regis and Littlehampton

812220615
02:59:11.893 --> 02:59:17.332
need stable and affordable
energy to grow and invest.

3898232925
02:59:17.333 --> 02:59:21.386
So would she agree that with
our Get Britain drilling

4037407395
02:59:21.387 --> 02:59:25.435
Bill is vital not just
for energy security,

777319674
02:59:25.436 --> 02:59:27.341
but for our future economic security?

3669258704
02:59:27.342 --> 02:59:29.236
>> Here?

1779128912
02:59:29.237 --> 02:59:30.241
>> I thank the hon.

801039746
02:59:30.241 --> 02:59:31.395
Lady for her question.

1799359750
02:59:31.934 --> 02:59:34.293
The North Sea is a vital
part of our industry.

445941417
02:59:34.294 --> 02:59:38.988
It not only provides us with the gas
that we need for energy security,

859099434
02:59:38.989 --> 02:59:42.248
but it provides feedstock that
feeds into our chemical industry,

311864521
02:59:42.249 --> 02:59:43.351
our plastic industry.

350044869
02:59:43.352 --> 02:59:46.763
There's a whole supply chain,
a whole set of other industries which

3270697732
02:59:46.764 --> 02:59:51.142
rely on the North Sea and us having
a successful industrial base.

83741029
02:59:51.143 --> 02:59:52.297
You lose one of those.

2014778685
02:59:52.298 --> 02:59:54.431
I'll just make a bit more progress.

3632208021
02:59:54.432 --> 02:59:58.690
You lose one of those foundational
industries and it's like dominoes.

2044339055
02:59:58.691 --> 02:59:59.343
The rest go.

781648577
02:59:59.344 --> 03:00:01.890
And this is the point.

3659938661
03:00:01.891 --> 03:00:03.946
If we keep offshoring British emissions,

4176369401
03:00:03.947 --> 03:00:07.207
it doesn't help the climate
and it doesn't help British workers.

1707375907
03:00:07.208 --> 03:00:09.115
And the question I would ask them is,

326468114
03:00:09.116 --> 03:00:11.173
do they understand how bad it looks when

2354689955
03:00:11.174 --> 03:00:14.734
they make speeches patting themselves
on the back here in Westminster,

2287005382
03:00:14.735 --> 03:00:18.801
whilst hard working Brits out
there lose their jobs so we

4141203849
03:00:18.802 --> 03:00:22.991
can import more goods with
higher emissions from abroad.

4079584408
03:00:22.993 --> 03:00:25.743
That's why the vote on the North Sea today

2854968306
03:00:25.744 --> 03:00:30.041
should be a litmus test for them.

3115956533
03:00:30.042 --> 03:00:35.296
Do they reject decarbonisation
by deindustrialisation or not?

3768541401
03:00:35.297 --> 03:00:37.000
Now let's talk about electricity.

3601752590
03:00:37.002 --> 03:00:38.708
I'll just make a bit of progress.

2498769992
03:00:38.709 --> 03:00:42.447
A key part of the Secretary
of State's plan is to

682006907
03:00:42.448 --> 03:00:44.704
make us more reliant on
electricity imports.

443484302
03:00:44.705 --> 03:00:47.866
He doesn't like to talk about it,
but at the height of winter,

75265172
03:00:47.868 --> 03:00:48.972
when we need it most,

652606217
03:00:48.973 --> 03:00:53.042
will be importing twice
as much electricity by

4069047184
03:00:53.043 --> 03:00:55.541
2030 as we did when they came into office.

2569571856
03:00:55.542 --> 03:00:57.240
What does that mean?

3399144962
03:00:57.241 --> 03:00:59.398
It means relying on the goodwill of France

3256708604
03:00:59.399 --> 03:01:01.999
and Norway to keep
the lights on in Britain.

2253439356
03:01:02.936 --> 03:01:05.345
I'll remind the House we
are now in a situation

278179049
03:01:05.346 --> 03:01:08.945
where France is on
the edge of a debt crisis,

3772489925
03:01:08.946 --> 03:01:11.102
with the National Rally topping the polls.

2420545728
03:01:11.103 --> 03:01:13.848
Does the House really think
it's prudent to hand over

3327747048
03:01:13.848 --> 03:01:18.239
the keys to our electricity
security to Marine Le Pen?

3795808436
03:01:18.936 --> 03:01:21.393
Because, let's be honest,
that is the right hon.

924637351
03:01:21.936 --> 03:01:22.687
Member's plan.

1261701624
03:01:22.688 --> 03:01:28.686
Whichever way you look at it, this
isn't an energy independence bill.

2557087408
03:01:28.687 --> 03:01:31.690
This is an energy dependence
bill that makes Britain

1428912160
03:01:31.691 --> 03:01:34.699
beholden to Marine Le Pen
for our electricity,

4177159626
03:01:34.700 --> 03:01:41.701
to Xi Jinping, for our solar panels,
and to Donald Trump for our gas.

2675061967
03:01:41.702 --> 03:01:43.457
Their plan is for energy scarcity.

2663557709
03:01:43.458 --> 03:01:46.389
But what we need is energy abundance.

3135949599
03:01:46.390 --> 03:01:49.741
That's why our plan would be
to double down on nuclear,

860300916
03:01:49.743 --> 03:01:51.536
to axe the carbon tax,

2725776451
03:01:51.538 --> 03:01:53.594
to save British industry, to get Britain

2581762588
03:01:53.595 --> 03:01:55.600
drilling and to make electricity cheap.

162969806
03:01:55.601 --> 03:01:56.536
>> To give me.

3140220276
03:01:56.538 --> 03:01:58.445
>> This time I will happily give way.

2253478661
03:01:58.446 --> 03:01:58.998
>> To the.

2898042934
03:01:58.999 --> 03:02:00.102
>> I'm very grateful.

3236447258
03:02:00.103 --> 03:02:06.893
She paints in her speech a very stark
consequence of the Labour Party's

4198720918
03:02:06.893 --> 03:02:11.042
policy of a total proscription
on new oil and gas licences.

3684647818
03:02:11.043 --> 03:02:12.446
What can she advise us?

1229048834
03:02:12.447 --> 03:02:15.487
What will that look like
without access to future oil

2244024523
03:02:15.488 --> 03:02:19.939
and gas from the North Sea
basin for the United Kingdom?

390018152
03:02:19.940 --> 03:02:21.245
>> Well, I thank the hon.

2270297720
03:02:21.246 --> 03:02:24.838
Gentleman, and I know his party has
changed position on this recently,

2306669692
03:02:24.839 --> 03:02:26.193
and I welcome that change.

3838187403
03:02:26.194 --> 03:02:30.446
Like I said before, the North
Sea is a foundational industry.

1324323796
03:02:30.447 --> 03:02:32.605
It's not just the oil and gas it provides.

1947201601
03:02:32.606 --> 03:02:34.211
It's not just the tax revenues.

859438852
03:02:34.212 --> 03:02:37.841
It's not just the jobs that
exist within that industry.

4078438465
03:02:37.842 --> 03:02:39.647
It's all of those other industries.

1983954308
03:02:39.648 --> 03:02:43.166
It supports the chemicals industry,
the plastics industries,

442801915
03:02:43.167 --> 03:02:45.223
even the renewable industry, by the way,

3759186908
03:02:45.223 --> 03:02:47.431
they support more
drilling in the North Sea

1410737111
03:02:47.432 --> 03:02:49.791
because they need the specialist rigs,

2719551868
03:02:49.792 --> 03:02:51.646
they need the undersea technologies.

420023979
03:02:51.944 --> 03:02:53.649
They need the exact same workers.

2837528891
03:02:53.650 --> 03:02:58.339
There are so many industries and wider
economies that they are killing

2011759542
03:02:58.341 --> 03:03:02.189
just because of the ideological
bent of this Secretary of State.

701127874
03:03:02.190 --> 03:03:04.449
And here is I will make
a bit more progress.

3069191915
03:03:04.450 --> 03:03:07.642
And here's the fundamental bind
that the Labour Party is in.

1659994746
03:03:07.643 --> 03:03:13.196
It doesn't matter who their next
leader is, they will all fail.

1709543485
03:03:13.197 --> 03:03:18.038
Their supposedly popular leadership
contenders will become unpopular

3767990907
03:03:18.039 --> 03:03:21.289
very quickly when they
can't keep their promises.

2778710821
03:03:21.290 --> 03:03:22.945
It happened to us in government.

1419428382
03:03:22.946 --> 03:03:24.450
It's happening to Labour now.

2348958765
03:03:24.451 --> 03:03:27.047
It's happening to reform
at the council level.

2940014603
03:03:27.048 --> 03:03:30.997
It'll happen to whoever
is in government next.

516138589
03:03:30.998 --> 03:03:33.445
Unless you actually face up to the trade

1734500660
03:03:33.446 --> 03:03:35.692
offs that get you better growth.

2565019020
03:03:35.693 --> 03:03:39.641
Growth is the antidote to
so many of our problems.

2862578050
03:03:39.642 --> 03:03:43.598
But to deliver it, you
need two things cheap,

4091535877
03:03:43.598 --> 03:03:45.503
abundant energy and economic freedom.

2756288268
03:03:45.504 --> 03:03:50.391
But by shutting down the North
Sea, cancelling nuclear projects,

1601699283
03:03:50.392 --> 03:03:52.848
keeping a distorted
electricity market in place,

205427298
03:03:52.848 --> 03:03:57.389
what they are doing is making
energy scarce and expensive.

3690984584
03:03:57.390 --> 03:04:00.098
Now, being part of the EU
doesn't solve that problem.

2602518802
03:04:00.100 --> 03:04:05.801
The EU leaders themselves rail
against their own energy policy.

2254438556
03:04:05.802 --> 03:04:09.250
Reindustrialisation is
just a meaningless slogan

4180282041
03:04:09.250 --> 03:04:11.057
unless you back the North Sea acts,

3069385322
03:04:11.058 --> 03:04:13.164
the carbon taxes that are killing British

2495208010
03:04:13.165 --> 03:04:15.021
industry and cut the cost of energy.

3878704180
03:04:15.022 --> 03:04:17.793
If none of their contenders
have the courage

418586963
03:04:17.794 --> 03:04:21.336
to say anything about these issues,

3239928553
03:04:21.337 --> 03:04:22.640
then nothing will change.

1686917208
03:04:22.641 --> 03:04:25.138
And along side cheap, abundant energy,

1258001984
03:04:25.139 --> 03:04:30.096
the most important ingredient
for growth is economic freedom.

2484966379
03:04:30.097 --> 03:04:33.147
But the Labour Party openly
stands for more state control,

2994521169
03:04:33.148 --> 03:04:37.393
more tax and spend more red
tape on employing people,

3975519647
03:04:37.935 --> 03:04:41.915
more expensive energy, less AI,
fewer profits and more subsidies.

795121532
03:04:41.916 --> 03:04:44.375
But they've been on this
path for two years now.

687841471
03:04:44.375 --> 03:04:47.140
And what do we have to show for it?

4085370504
03:04:47.141 --> 03:04:50.640
Higher inflation, weaker
growth, soaring unemployment.

2586543786
03:04:50.641 --> 03:04:52.447
Why would anyone want more of this?

3384850966
03:04:52.941 --> 03:04:54.946
Families are working harder and harder,

2794054614
03:04:54.947 --> 03:04:57.306
getting less and less at
the end of the month.

3075445942
03:04:57.307 --> 03:05:00.695
And if what people want
is full fat socialism,

1426861160
03:05:00.696 --> 03:05:02.401
why would they choose labour when

4126309982
03:05:02.402 --> 03:05:04.508
they've got the boob whisperer over there

2462116808
03:05:04.509 --> 03:05:08.341
who's offering them bigger and better,

3981527788
03:05:08.342 --> 03:05:12.600
our whole system, a whole
system is flooded with caution.

4053644038
03:05:12.601 --> 03:05:17.290
Nobody's incentivised to take any risks.

3595051124
03:05:17.291 --> 03:05:18.946
That is what's making us poorer.

1265814834
03:05:18.947 --> 03:05:21.551
And the truth is, the personalities and

3463065140
03:05:21.552 --> 03:05:24.494
the Labour leadership race do not matter.

2284267309
03:05:24.495 --> 03:05:26.792
Unless we get cheap, abundant energy.

3315684422
03:05:26.793 --> 03:05:29.893
We remove the legal
straitjackets, the onerous taxes,

2688126172
03:05:29.893 --> 03:05:32.451
fix the broken regulators
and the sluggish machine

2696962147
03:05:32.452 --> 03:05:36.637
of government to set the economy free.

56391577
03:05:36.638 --> 03:05:38.042
Nothing is going to change.

1966228467
03:05:38.043 --> 03:05:40.201
And look, if people think on their side of

684607205
03:05:40.202 --> 03:05:42.459
the House that Andy
Burnham has the answers.

3147117565
03:05:42.460 --> 03:05:44.669
Let me tell you, Andy
is like the fun uncle

1236252882
03:05:44.670 --> 03:05:46.443
who's got to sit on the sidelines

2090318426
03:05:46.444 --> 03:05:49.752
saying whatever he wants without
anybody holding him accountable.

3472354422
03:05:49.753 --> 03:05:51.408
Let's have ice cream for dinner.

2302958221
03:05:51.409 --> 03:05:52.964
Let's go to the zoo next week.

3103370828
03:05:52.966 --> 03:05:54.468
Let's nationalise everything.

2808560676
03:05:54.469 --> 03:05:56.174
Who cares about the bond markets?

1762555910
03:05:56.175 --> 03:05:57.228
Let's rejoin the EU.

1366297493
03:05:57.229 --> 03:05:59.185
He just said whatever he likes because

2635048346
03:05:59.186 --> 03:06:00.993
he's never had to pick up the bill.

3162848360
03:06:00.994 --> 03:06:03.301
Now he's actually looking
at being in charge.

1915280035
03:06:03.302 --> 03:06:05.761
He's having to go back on
all of these promises.

3533977061
03:06:05.762 --> 03:06:06.615
So ask him this.

2869942686
03:06:06.616 --> 03:06:09.525
Ask him how he's going to fund
his nationalisation plans.

1014196338
03:06:09.526 --> 03:06:11.482
He wants to stick to the fiscal rules.

470153932
03:06:11.484 --> 03:06:14.093
So is he really saying he's
going back to taxpayers

89310581
03:06:14.094 --> 03:06:16.702
who already face the highest
tax burden in history?

1076793958
03:06:16.703 --> 03:06:20.145
When he talks about Reindustrialisation,
ask him if he supports

2268366549
03:06:20.146 --> 03:06:24.444
the secretary of State's plans to
shut down the oil and gas industry.

887115194
03:06:24.445 --> 03:06:28.243
The biggest act of industrial
self-harm committed in generations.

3712696127
03:06:28.244 --> 03:06:30.598
If we want more powers at a local level.

1981885176
03:06:30.600 --> 03:06:31.302
Amen to that.

2883745005
03:06:31.303 --> 03:06:32.455
I couldn't agree more.

1132635947
03:06:32.937 --> 03:06:36.497
But ask him how can he argue
for economic freedom in

2486025085
03:06:36.498 --> 03:06:38.955
one breath whilst with
another dictate to people

1324942523
03:06:38.955 --> 03:06:43.652
what tumble dryers or cars
they have to buy if they

1114004231
03:06:43.654 --> 03:06:46.994
really care about growth
and reindustrialisation,

505679772
03:06:46.995 --> 03:06:50.845
they would axe carbon taxes,
get Britain drilling,

3789599049
03:06:50.846 --> 03:06:53.402
double down on nuclear
and make electricity cheap.

1284347273
03:06:53.404 --> 03:06:56.213
In short, they would put
the national interest ahead of

3595449949
03:06:56.214 --> 03:07:01.100
the Secretary of State's ideology
and vote with us tonight.

2158059030
03:07:01.101 --> 03:07:01.552
>> They.

540224801
03:07:01.944 --> 03:07:05.393
>> The original question
was that a Humble Address.

4038847239
03:07:05.395 --> 03:07:07.954
Be presented to His Majesty
as on the Order Paper.

4119015543
03:07:07.955 --> 03:07:11.216
Since when an amendment has been
proposed as on the Order Paper.

3663396756
03:07:11.217 --> 03:07:13.424
The question is that
the amendment be made,

3567644710
03:07:13.425 --> 03:07:15.181
and I call the Secretary of State.

1606763217
03:07:16.945 --> 03:07:18.951
>> Ed Miliband thank you, privilege to.

2745054952
03:07:18.952 --> 03:07:21.750
>> Speak in support of
this Gracious Speech,

2186253557
03:07:21.750 --> 03:07:24.498
Madam Deputy Speaker
and fossil fuel shock.

816035885
03:07:24.499 --> 03:07:26.805
In four years, families
and businesses across

189418340
03:07:26.806 --> 03:07:28.460
the country are deeply concerned

2546007866
03:07:28.461 --> 03:07:32.249
about the impact of the Iran war
on the cost of living a war.

474259782
03:07:32.250 --> 03:07:33.955
This country did not start a war.

3519971542
03:07:33.957 --> 03:07:36.866
This government, a war this
government chose not to join,

811979187
03:07:36.866 --> 03:07:39.575
but which is having significant
effects here at home.

1130223910
03:07:39.576 --> 03:07:44.058
Just like when Russia invaded Ukraine
in 2022 and energy bills rocketed,

679932276
03:07:44.059 --> 03:07:47.201
and the British people
and firms paid the price.

3932160751
03:07:47.202 --> 03:07:50.713
And the argument, Madam Deputy
Speaker, at the heart of this Gracious

2491184824
03:07:50.714 --> 03:07:54.598
Speech is there is one overriding
lesson of these two crises that,

2118976
03:07:54.600 --> 03:07:57.559
while we remain exposed to
the fossil fuel roller coaster,

3043220016
03:07:57.560 --> 03:07:59.749
we are deeply vulnerable as a country.

2710221145
03:07:59.750 --> 03:08:01.648
Our sovereignty, our security,

2832173934
03:08:01.649 --> 03:08:04.495
and the British people's living standards.

3787920297
03:08:04.496 --> 03:08:06.701
Undermined by this
dependence and exposure.

2597732326
03:08:06.702 --> 03:08:08.255
Because, Madam Deputy Speaker,

1588495574
03:08:08.256 --> 03:08:11.504
for a simple reason we do not
control the price of oil and gas,

2007558201
03:08:11.505 --> 03:08:13.460
which is set on international markets.

2044767244
03:08:13.461 --> 03:08:14.665
And there is an answer.

1295212581
03:08:14.666 --> 03:08:17.025
And this is different
from what it was like in

2596512794
03:08:17.026 --> 03:08:19.133
the 1970s when we had fossil fuel shocks.

2143566801
03:08:19.134 --> 03:08:21.292
There is an answer staring us in the face.

96190108
