03:49:00.551 --> 03:49:01.805
He played all the wages.

483360746
03:49:01.806 --> 03:49:04.365
So I personally not neither
for nor opposed to it,

1768097342
03:49:04.366 --> 03:49:06.388
but actually just nationalised.

2819862750
03:49:06.389 --> 03:49:08.846
British Steel won't make
a difference when we're

554406348
03:49:08.847 --> 03:49:11.003
paying the highest energy costs in Europe.

91185747
03:49:11.004 --> 03:49:12.257
That's the real problem.

3566619165
03:49:12.258 --> 03:49:16.803
So that's the problem that
the government needs to address.

3972419638
03:49:16.804 --> 03:49:18.006
Nationalisation or not.

2733454066
03:49:18.007 --> 03:49:20.314
Let's not get bogged
down in these arguments.

967281510
03:49:20.315 --> 03:49:22.070
Let's find a private sector buyer.

108339627
03:49:22.071 --> 03:49:24.227
Let's get the workers back into operation,

1497937510
03:49:24.228 --> 03:49:26.033
get our blast blast furnaces moving

811416379
03:49:26.034 --> 03:49:30.849
and not be over worried about
ideologies, about the blast furnaces.

3992956694
03:49:30.850 --> 03:49:32.505
We want to create British Steel.

1335945862
03:49:32.506 --> 03:49:33.761
>> I thank my right hon.

2386139704
03:49:33.762 --> 03:49:34.915
Friend for giving way.

2118316938
03:49:34.916 --> 03:49:38.277
And he's making an excellent point
in respect of of British Steel,

4213245464
03:49:38.278 --> 03:49:42.498
where hundreds of my
constituents also work.

192508863
03:49:42.499 --> 03:49:45.257
Would you agree that in
the short term nationalisation

3542228953
03:49:45.258 --> 03:49:46.462
may be the way forward,

2207837199
03:49:46.463 --> 03:49:48.420
but longer term we need to get private

4142368019
03:49:48.421 --> 03:49:50.275
sector investment into the industry.

1675543817
03:49:50.276 --> 03:49:53.193
And the way to achieve that
is to reduce energy costs.

4031190665
03:49:53.194 --> 03:49:55.852
And that is absolutely
critical, not just for steel,

4065217270
03:49:55.853 --> 03:49:58.044
but for so many of our heavy industries.

606274519
03:49:58.045 --> 03:49:58.345
Yeah.

952610966
03:49:58.346 --> 03:49:58.898
>> My hon.

3957356497
03:49:58.899 --> 03:50:04.490
Friend is so well respected
in the area for the fantastic

702555227
03:50:04.491 --> 03:50:06.497
amount of work he's done in Scunthorpe,

1217363906
03:50:06.498 --> 03:50:09.806
constantly holding the government
to working with the government.

2598624908
03:50:09.807 --> 03:50:13.199
And we've got to do this together
to protect our steel making

2372422339
03:50:13.200 --> 03:50:16.493
capacity for the sake of our
industrial, you know, wealth.

1165461600
03:50:16.494 --> 03:50:22.191
Now, the Energy independence Bill,
I agree it provides a framework for

1085839513
03:50:22.192 --> 03:50:26.207
trans transitioning the UK energy
market away from fossil fuels.

3636554143
03:50:26.208 --> 03:50:29.217
We all agree with that towards
alternative forms of energy.

3307577961
03:50:29.218 --> 03:50:31.291
No problem with that.

694568372
03:50:31.292 --> 03:50:33.447
This is sensible regarding nuclear energy,

658590618
03:50:34.991 --> 03:50:38.234
but the ideological pursuit
of renewables is doing harm

2906054454
03:50:38.235 --> 03:50:41.450
and is at odds with
achieving energy security.

3762733021
03:50:41.451 --> 03:50:44.893
When we have our own fossil fuel
resources in the North Sea,

3467069592
03:50:44.894 --> 03:50:46.199
it's not a zero sum game.

18061991
03:50:46.200 --> 03:50:51.839
I don't see the I'm sorry, I don't
see the ideological virtue of simply

2184532748
03:50:51.840 --> 03:50:55.344
exporting your carbon emissions,
which we're doing to Nova.

3107029608
03:50:55.345 --> 03:50:57.753
I've got to make some
progress, I do apologise.

3012864415
03:50:57.754 --> 03:51:01.197
So again, I would have thought we
could have a compromise on that.

171161691
03:51:01.198 --> 03:51:03.644
We could have a policy which is sensible,

3444844413
03:51:03.645 --> 03:51:06.544
gradually moving away from fossil fuels,

742462275
03:51:06.545 --> 03:51:10.343
gradually becoming a more
green energy economy,

3996707952
03:51:10.344 --> 03:51:14.551
but not simply exporting our emissions
by setting arbitrary dates.

1244628936
03:51:14.552 --> 03:51:17.146
Now, will you forgive me,
Madam Deputy Speaker,

553988456
03:51:17.147 --> 03:51:19.305
as this is a debate on the Queen's Speech,

3852768424
03:51:19.306 --> 03:51:23.543
if I mention another subject in
the short time available to me now,

701549325
03:51:23.544 --> 03:51:25.201
when you when you get to my age,

63648529
03:51:25.202 --> 03:51:27.810
you can say unpopular things
because I haven't got.

3208373125
03:51:30.992 --> 03:51:32.697
I haven't got much longer anyway.

3381975984
03:51:32.698 --> 03:51:33.099
So let.

1682545825
03:51:33.100 --> 03:51:39.184
I've got The problem with two minutes and.

1405194331
03:51:39.185 --> 03:51:43.004
The problem with our country is that
we're governing by focus groups.

1191755677
03:51:43.005 --> 03:51:45.142
And what are focus groups want.

1261678562
03:51:45.143 --> 03:51:46.146
They want less tax.

1789177116
03:51:46.990 --> 03:51:49.397
And of course they want
better public services.

1739566318
03:51:49.398 --> 03:51:53.749
Their debt is already 100% of
GDP within 50 years because of

1467079091
03:51:53.750 --> 03:51:59.399
the triple lock and other benefit
increases, it will be 170%.

3378027365
03:51:59.400 --> 03:52:01.608
Now, of course, the old
vote, the old vote.

3861888391
03:52:01.609 --> 03:52:03.915
But they all have children
and grandchildren.

1297536046
03:52:03.916 --> 03:52:07.026
We do have a responsibility to
younger people in our country.

2069353840
03:52:07.027 --> 03:52:10.247
They know the present
system is unsustainable.

909127805
03:52:10.248 --> 03:52:13.207
So whilst the average increase
of the triple lock measures

3271008424
03:52:13.208 --> 03:52:15.849
over the past 13 years,
and we brought it in,

1820582284
03:52:15.850 --> 03:52:18.007
it was supposed to be a temporary measure,

1059768769
03:52:18.008 --> 03:52:20.166
but no party has the courage to change it.

2403838894
03:52:20.167 --> 03:52:23.343
The average increase over 13
years has been around 40%.

2438545568
03:52:23.344 --> 03:52:26.492
Pensions have gone up over 60%,

1239677681
03:52:26.493 --> 03:52:30.242
nearly £20 billion of annual
additional costs so far.

1353937884
03:52:30.243 --> 03:52:33.546
This will get bigger every year
and more unaffordable by 2050.

1015122655
03:52:33.547 --> 03:52:39.049
The gap is likely to have grown
to £120 billion, if not more,

820211343
03:52:39.050 --> 03:52:43.152
to exacerbate the economic crisis
and whoever becomes Prime Minister,

3163883147
03:52:43.153 --> 03:52:44.708
they've got to cope with this.

3797548582
03:52:44.709 --> 03:52:47.891
It's really important.

1573805046
03:52:47.892 --> 03:52:50.844
By that time, there will
be 20 to 25% fewer tax

935758804
03:52:50.845 --> 03:52:53.442
paying workers for pensioners in Britain,

2279849911
03:52:53.443 --> 03:52:55.247
our children and our grandchildren.

1726927621
03:52:55.248 --> 03:52:57.506
Of course, we've got to
care for old people,

2069217287
03:52:57.992 --> 03:52:59.796
particularly old people in poverty,

3646545018
03:52:59.797 --> 03:53:02.355
and divert resources to
the old people in poverty.

882571941
03:53:02.356 --> 03:53:04.964
But you've got to remember
the younger people, too.

3279616222
03:53:04.965 --> 03:53:07.191
This is entirely unsustainable.

1688434277
03:53:07.192 --> 03:53:08.647
So let me finish this point.

2672248983
03:53:08.991 --> 03:53:11.852
Yes, we want to keep a triple
lock, not the triple lock.

201762078
03:53:11.853 --> 03:53:12.957
We want to have lock.

3881720160
03:53:12.958 --> 03:53:15.646
We want to have the average
of the three indices

557061101
03:53:15.647 --> 03:53:18.292
so it doesn't go up
exponentially every year.

765308345
03:53:18.293 --> 03:53:22.502
The government should do the right
thing by the nation and bring it in.

1132399974
03:53:22.503 --> 03:53:26.093
They should bring it in, make our
fantasy our fantasies affordable,

4208027470
03:53:26.094 --> 03:53:28.645
and my frontbench should not oppose them.

4128193015
03:53:28.646 --> 03:53:31.491
We should govern in the national interest.

3786318640
03:53:31.492 --> 03:53:33.547
We should make our finances sustainable,

4237971448
03:53:33.548 --> 03:53:36.453
and then we can really help
the people most in need.

1936079546
03:53:37.992 --> 03:53:38.543
Thank you.

1255147025
03:53:38.544 --> 03:53:39.245
Toby Perkins.

1050264706
03:53:39.246 --> 03:53:40.299
Thank you very much.

1182181070
03:53:40.950 --> 03:53:42.604
>> Indeed, Madam Deputy Speaker.

779479038
03:53:42.605 --> 03:53:45.696
His Majesty's Gracious
Speech set out a forward

317705292
03:53:45.697 --> 03:53:47.944
legislative programme for the government

2200418273
03:53:47.945 --> 03:53:50.942
with plans to build our national security,

1431443480
03:53:50.943 --> 03:53:53.098
our economic security and energy security.

3006625443
03:53:53.099 --> 03:53:54.453
And I welcome this agenda.

3814533599
03:53:54.454 --> 03:53:57.163
It's consistent with
the manifesto that I and my hon.

118621077
03:53:57.164 --> 03:53:59.346
Friends were elected on, and I urge all

510234782
03:53:59.347 --> 03:54:02.104
members of the government to exhibit

2551130859
03:54:02.105 --> 03:54:05.394
a relentless focus and urgency
on delivery of that programme,

3630636882
03:54:05.395 --> 03:54:08.747
to ensure that that ambition
is matched by its impact.

2826407286
03:54:08.748 --> 03:54:12.406
Now, we were elected in 2024 on a mandate

2980428237
03:54:12.407 --> 03:54:15.452
of change for national renewal.

3545537202
03:54:15.453 --> 03:54:17.660
After 14 years of decline
under the Tories,

1018812271
03:54:17.661 --> 03:54:20.222
and there is a great deal
that I could focus on in

3206293441
03:54:20.223 --> 03:54:25.296
terms of those achievements
if I had more time,

676806756
03:54:25.297 --> 03:54:28.713
but specifically on the National
Health Service, on migration,

1264776058
03:54:28.714 --> 03:54:32.143
where we saw the recent
very positive announcements

267508485
03:54:32.144 --> 03:54:33.648
on the minimum wage increase,

2590180279
03:54:33.992 --> 03:54:35.697
on workers and on renters rights.

322901121
03:54:35.698 --> 03:54:38.757
This is a government that is
delivering against that agenda.

4118858921
03:54:38.758 --> 03:54:40.900
And we also saw that despite the prophets

2679048424
03:54:40.901 --> 03:54:42.556
of doom on the benches opposite.

3591915191
03:54:42.557 --> 03:54:44.844
The most recent figures show once again,

251328009
03:54:44.845 --> 03:54:47.795
unemployment continuing
to fall and the fastest

704955383
03:54:47.796 --> 03:54:51.446
growth in the G7 in the last quarter.

3074579464
03:54:51.447 --> 03:54:54.557
So many of the fundamentals are
going in the right direction.

341517082
03:54:54.558 --> 03:54:57.768
But anyone who spent time attempting
to persuade voters to vote

2244363378
03:54:57.769 --> 03:55:00.930
Labour in the recent elections
will have been left in no doubt

1501838430
03:55:00.931 --> 03:55:03.991
that our voters remain unconvinced
that we are going fast or

3500787885
03:55:03.992 --> 03:55:07.146
far enough to bring about
the change that they want to see.

1440181234
03:55:07.147 --> 03:55:10.696
So I would like to focus on some
specific measures within His

1610489352
03:55:10.697 --> 03:55:13.453
Majesty's Gracious Speech
that I particularly welcome.

4169987682
03:55:13.454 --> 03:55:15.649
Firstly, on the Energy Independence Bill,

3222012575
03:55:15.650 --> 03:55:18.748
I very much welcome
the government's action to

3474228866
03:55:18.749 --> 03:55:21.247
protect households
and industry from global

2530438397
03:55:21.248 --> 03:55:24.448
instability by powering
forward with clean,

2472605552
03:55:24.449 --> 03:55:26.854
home-grown energy to
create energy independence

1301311688
03:55:26.855 --> 03:55:29.062
and get off the fossil
fuel roller coaster.

207889875
03:55:29.063 --> 03:55:31.844
Both the Energy Independence
Bill and the National

1690579935
03:55:31.845 --> 03:55:34.999
Nuclear Regulation Bill
will also strengthen our

3017371837
03:55:35.000 --> 03:55:38.250
resilience to energy price
shocks for the long term

2914982075
03:55:38.251 --> 03:55:40.996
and bring down the cost
of bills for families.

2309550255
03:55:40.997 --> 03:55:44.002
The Ukraine crisis, as
we referred to earlier,

997321323
03:55:44.003 --> 03:55:46.194
saw the government of the time pay

2172422362
03:55:46.195 --> 03:55:48.451
to subsidise customers
bills because we were

723297888
03:55:48.452 --> 03:55:51.648
so dependent on the global markets.

206256360
03:55:51.649 --> 03:55:54.000
That intervention that
that government made,

2724060889
03:55:54.001 --> 03:55:56.509
that I think politically
they had to make because

258092320
03:55:56.510 --> 03:55:59.801
of the impact it would have
had on the on the number

2646719412
03:55:59.802 --> 03:56:01.909
of people who would have gone under cost.

2455134234
03:56:01.910 --> 03:56:07.949
The British taxpayer £44
billion in a single year.

2996751040
03:56:07.950 --> 03:56:12.654
The idea that the response to
that further global insecurity of

2050750837
03:56:12.655 --> 03:56:16.249
the Iran war is to reduce investment
in renewables is quite mad.

2039506112
03:56:16.250 --> 03:56:18.957
And so I welcome
the government's further legislation

2899773214
03:56:18.958 --> 03:56:20.663
on these two bills and absolutely

1981690455
03:56:20.664 --> 03:56:24.800
support the increase in nuclear that
this government is getting on with.

3449533606
03:56:24.801 --> 03:56:27.559
After the dither and delay
of the previous government.

382152
03:56:27.560 --> 03:56:31.125
It was quite remarkable
to hear the contribution

3863287437
03:56:31.126 --> 03:56:33.354
of the shadow Secretary of State,

3139323997
03:56:33.355 --> 03:56:35.295
who on the one hand said, well,

4197476875
03:56:35.296 --> 03:56:37.754
you haven't done enough
in two years on nuclear,

731308031
03:56:37.755 --> 03:56:41.269
and on the other hand said, well,
you can't blame us for the 14 years

391770671
03:56:41.270 --> 03:56:44.581
of inaction because the previous
government got in the way of it.

3221992950
03:56:44.582 --> 03:56:46.599
It was just absolutely incoherent.

3524262601
03:56:46.600 --> 03:56:49.910
And the exchange of letters between
the shadow Secretary of State

4254244367
03:56:49.911 --> 03:56:53.070
and encourage everyone to look
at between the shadow Secretary

3473264027
03:56:53.071 --> 03:56:56.081
of State and the chair of
the Climate Change Committee made

1916598175
03:56:56.082 --> 03:57:00.552
absolutely clear that when she
voted against the auction,

914649278
03:57:00.553 --> 03:57:03.295
auction seven, she simply
did not understand

2225503188
03:57:03.296 --> 03:57:07.698
what she was talking
about in terms of the.

2192057304
03:57:07.699 --> 03:57:11.296
The difference between Elko
and contracts for difference.

3387826852
03:57:11.297 --> 03:57:14.812
So when she says that we should
follow her advice on this,

4078419019
03:57:14.813 --> 03:57:17.521
we should treat that with
the greatest of scepticism.

2976695286
03:57:17.522 --> 03:57:21.303
Now, I should also say that
I echo the contribution.

1764885225
03:57:21.304 --> 03:57:23.247
My hon.

4031617431
03:57:23.248 --> 03:57:28.450
Friend from Sefton Central on
the need to reduce energy bills far more

2957423596
03:57:28.451 --> 03:57:31.613
to help with the cost of living,
but also to ease the current.

3457880180
03:57:31.614 --> 03:57:34.903
The green transition to benefit consumers

3292409337
03:57:34.904 --> 03:57:39.700
and to support industry in this country.

1629287923
03:57:39.701 --> 03:57:46.295
Alongside that, we also see in this
King's Speech, the Clean Water Bill,

1071204696
03:57:46.296 --> 03:57:50.149
which alongside climate action,
we do need action on nature.

2324935179
03:57:50.150 --> 03:57:53.599
Nature is the foundation of our
national economic security,

2562465258
03:57:53.600 --> 03:57:56.708
and we cannot tackle climate
change without restoring nature.

2257532138
03:57:56.709 --> 03:58:00.170
The government made a promise to
clean up Britain's rivers and seas,

1808130981
03:58:00.171 --> 03:58:02.597
and I am delighted to see this clean water

3080770060
03:58:02.598 --> 03:58:04.655
bill there as part of the King's Speech.

3746368583
03:58:04.999 --> 03:58:08.661
Not only tackling the water
industry reform, which is crucial,

3845059298
03:58:08.662 --> 03:58:11.955
but also recognising
the need to tackle agricultural

1801679349
03:58:11.956 --> 03:58:16.048
water pollution and road
based water pollution too.

1311344705
03:58:16.049 --> 03:58:18.104
I welcome the European Partnership Bill.

2500006971
03:58:18.105 --> 03:58:21.314
It's important we work more closely
with our European partners,

4122343243
03:58:21.315 --> 03:58:23.747
and I fully support what the government

854156376
03:58:23.748 --> 03:58:25.452
is also doing on apprenticeships,

3267569197
03:58:25.996 --> 03:58:27.949
apprenticeships and greater investment

1972747376
03:58:27.950 --> 03:58:29.754
in education is absolutely crucial.

2997965311
03:58:29.755 --> 03:58:32.162
If we're going to equip
tomorrow's workers with

3510751787
03:58:32.163 --> 03:58:34.269
the skills they need to support industry.

463714022
03:58:34.270 --> 03:58:37.933
So there are many measures in this
bill that can make a real difference,

3553055186
03:58:37.934 --> 03:58:40.243
as well as the need to
go further and faster,

1565679998
03:58:40.244 --> 03:58:43.204
and I look forward to supporting
it again later this year.

1102871311
03:58:43.994 --> 03:58:44.947
>> Sir Roger Gale.

455486572
03:58:44.948 --> 03:58:48.446
>> Thank you, Madam Deputy Speaker.

1395312848
03:58:48.447 --> 03:58:52.749
If we are moving into
an era of electric cars,

2623199661
03:58:52.750 --> 03:58:56.353
thousands of them, and if we are
moving into mostly made in China,

2729897580
03:58:56.354 --> 03:58:59.852
of course, and if we are moving
into an era of artificial

2790481128
03:59:02.000 --> 03:59:04.255
intelligence developed
in the United States,

2873335168
03:59:04.256 --> 03:59:08.556
then we are going to need infinitely
more electric electricity

3478100919
03:59:09.000 --> 03:59:13.406
than the country is capable
of producing at present.

2596343621
03:59:13.407 --> 03:59:15.262
Madam Deputy Speaker, since the days

201994329
03:59:15.263 --> 03:59:17.118
of the great Walter Walter Marshall,

3550727186
03:59:17.119 --> 03:59:19.804
the head of British Nuclear
Fuels, at one time,

3339666897
03:59:19.805 --> 03:59:22.453
I have been a supporter of nuclear energy,

3575618444
03:59:22.454 --> 03:59:25.352
and I believe passionately
that we have to move much,

3153084771
03:59:25.353 --> 03:59:28.655
much faster towards small
nuclear reactors if we are

3869920356
03:59:28.656 --> 03:59:32.555
going to begin to meet
the needs of tomorrow,

58975584
03:59:32.556 --> 03:59:36.602
the needs of our children
and our grandchildren.

3269532369
03:59:36.603 --> 03:59:39.806
I hope very much that we can
unite behind that move.

46823119
03:59:39.807 --> 03:59:44.956
But in the meantime, we've
got to bridge the gap.

1613498977
03:59:44.957 --> 03:59:47.203
And I believe it is sheer folly for this

2211514403
03:59:47.204 --> 03:59:49.902
government not to take advantage of

3927738766
03:59:49.903 --> 03:59:53.907
the resource that we've got in
the North Sea to help to bridge that gap.

3028195267
03:59:53.908 --> 03:59:59.237
It is an fuel from
Norway absolute nonsense

792636265
03:59:59.239 --> 04:00:01.552
to buy in fuel from Norway or elsewhere,

473704102
04:00:01.553 --> 04:00:04.713
when we could be producing it
from the same sources ourselves,

51742465
04:00:04.714 --> 04:00:06.169
and we should be doing that.

2608628484
04:00:06.996 --> 04:00:09.004
Don't tell me it's a drop in the ocean.

1675862466
04:00:09.005 --> 04:00:12.308
It's an important contribution.

1545366621
04:00:12.308 --> 04:00:18.056
Potential contributor to bridging
the gap in our energy needs.

3217499840
04:00:18.057 --> 04:00:23.255
Madam Deputy Speaker,
the Secretary of State sadly

1603316526
04:00:23.255 --> 04:00:33.342
no Take no lessons from longer with us.

1765893388
04:00:33.343 --> 04:00:33.793
Derided.

3315138018
04:00:33.794 --> 04:00:37.005
Take no lessons from a former
failed Leader of the Opposition.

1658419826
04:00:37.005 --> 04:00:37.457
But the.

838990146
04:00:40.956 --> 04:00:46.451
But the Secretary of State, in
extremely derisory fashion,

484499082
04:00:46.451 --> 04:00:55.759
spoke of the minimal cost to
agricultural land of solar panels.

1455826868
04:00:55.760 --> 04:01:00.152
Those solar panels are
covering in East Kent,

2934167229
04:01:00.153 --> 04:01:04.906
agricultural land on which was
growing bread making wheat.

2431794516
04:01:04.907 --> 04:01:05.609
My right hon.

3929232859
04:01:06.999 --> 04:01:09.355
Friend referred to
the breadbasket of England.

2470904417
04:01:09.356 --> 04:01:11.665
We can't lose that land,
and we don't need to

663617310
04:01:13.961 --> 04:01:16.018
lose it when we've got acres of rooftops

3961368005
04:01:16.019 --> 04:01:20.010
in public ownership and acres of car parks

2763232984
04:01:20.011 --> 04:01:24.105
that could and should be used first.

2133426662
04:01:24.106 --> 04:01:24.706
Absolutely.

2300025437
04:01:24.707 --> 04:01:28.253
Now, the Secretary of State said,

1636212867
04:01:28.254 --> 04:01:32.505
we're going to have to produce
the network to get the future

1794231547
04:01:32.507 --> 04:01:35.856
power to the homes and
the businesses and the hospitals

1827583911
04:01:35.857 --> 04:01:40.504
and the schools that we have to feed.

3884618452
04:01:40.505 --> 04:01:46.104
He implied that that requires a network of

1366367004
04:01:46.105 --> 04:01:49.450
pylons right across the United Kingdom.

2052787206
04:01:49.451 --> 04:01:56.303
I am not prepared as a grandparent,
to see my grandchildren's

2065133541
04:01:56.304 --> 04:02:02.201
future environment sacrificed on the altar

2898767824
04:02:02.203 --> 04:02:05.203
of hideous pylons strung
up by National Grid simply

2771600302
04:02:05.204 --> 04:02:07.360
to meet the desires of their shareholders.

3515361315
04:02:07.361 --> 04:02:11.107
And we need to remember that
it is a private company.

3070199227
04:02:11.108 --> 04:02:11.860
>> For profit.

319967845
04:02:11.861 --> 04:02:15.661
>> We've got to learn.

829498951
04:02:15.662 --> 04:02:19.201
Madam Deputy Speaker, how
to underground our cables.

4240506348
04:02:19.201 --> 04:02:20.905
It's happening throughout Europe,

4036371217
04:02:20.906 --> 04:02:25.303
where they've already got overhead
cables and they're taking them down.

742720815
04:02:25.304 --> 04:02:27.650
But National Grid through, for example,

1245963430
04:02:27.651 --> 04:02:34.860
the Sea Link project is planning on
building in my corner of England,

1010874152
04:02:34.861 --> 04:02:38.755
a 90 foot high converter
station the size of

1247309223
04:02:38.755 --> 04:02:42.362
five football pitches built on marshland,

2209174646
04:02:42.362 --> 04:02:45.955
which they just discovered is wet,

433024977
04:02:45.956 --> 04:02:50.503
which means they're going to have
to import thousands of tonnes of

4183526522
04:02:50.504 --> 04:02:54.710
concrete and destroy the whole of
the local environment around it,

816909549
04:02:55.000 --> 04:02:56.805
which includes a nature reserve and

1431014732
04:02:56.806 --> 04:03:01.451
a site of special scientific interest.

3994003830
04:03:01.451 --> 04:03:02.555
That is not progress.

1970449752
04:03:02.556 --> 04:03:06.558
That is, selling the family silver.

510302485
04:03:06.558 --> 04:03:08.915
It's selling the environment
of our children's

2527393152
04:03:08.915 --> 04:03:12.612
future and we must not do that.

1965073480
04:03:12.612 --> 04:03:17.515
So I believe we have to strike a balance

1712977547
04:03:17.516 --> 04:03:19.219
between meeting our future needs,

88660764
04:03:19.221 --> 04:03:25.007
bridging the gap
and protecting our environment.

305317970
04:03:25.008 --> 04:03:29.609
And Madam Speaker, I've got 18 seconds
left, so I'm going to stop there.

3634163761
04:03:29.610 --> 04:03:30.663
Thank you very much.

1376064928
04:03:30.664 --> 04:03:32.851
>> Dame Anneliese Dodds.

3538968049
04:03:32.852 --> 04:03:34.505
Thank you, Madam Deputy Speaker.

1718604969
04:03:34.507 --> 04:03:39.855
I welcome the measures in
the King's speech on energy security.

2464066263
04:03:39.856 --> 04:03:41.962
As on many other issues, the opposition's

2104410813
04:03:41.963 --> 04:03:43.315
wrongheaded approach would

3667078374
04:03:43.316 --> 04:03:47.115
leave us tethered to global
markets that we cannot control.

1840766233
04:03:47.116 --> 04:03:51.415
They would lock our country
out of much needed jobs,

552448623
04:03:53.008 --> 04:03:55.014
and they condemn Brits to higher bills.

2782917172
04:03:55.015 --> 04:03:59.505
The energy independence and nuclear
regulation bills, in contrast,

2711010776
04:03:59.505 --> 04:04:04.253
are further leaps towards
the stronger energy security we need.

2726585641
04:04:04.254 --> 04:04:06.360
In my speech today, Madam Deputy Speaker,

3471893444
04:04:06.361 --> 04:04:09.704
I want to tackle an issue touched on by

2441143007
04:04:09.705 --> 04:04:11.559
the previous speaker in his remarks,

4128598574
04:04:11.561 --> 04:04:14.068
an issue which will
increasingly drive the amount

2808412459
04:04:14.069 --> 04:04:16.125
of energy our country needs to generate.

3771286065
04:04:16.126 --> 04:04:20.157
The development and deployment
of artificial intelligence.

912777086
04:04:20.158 --> 04:04:23.706
The government did not bring
forward, in this King's speech

583981993
04:04:23.707 --> 04:04:26.854
our manifesto commitment to
ensure the safe development

2751464932
04:04:26.855 --> 04:04:30.108
and use of AI models by
introducing binding regulation on

2140765350
04:04:30.109 --> 04:04:34.008
the handful of companies developing
the most powerful AI models.

228019774
04:04:34.009 --> 04:04:36.658
Indeed, AI was not
mentioned in the speech.

472567378
04:04:36.659 --> 04:04:40.206
The government has acted decisively on

1872068205
04:04:40.207 --> 04:04:42.713
one symptom of the lack of regulation.

3388183531
04:04:42.714 --> 04:04:46.954
The widespread production
of sexualised images.

1437161414
04:04:46.955 --> 04:04:50.456
This, however, followed 3 million
such images being generated.

1404821728
04:04:50.457 --> 04:04:53.057
Harm was already done,
and I underline here

3523226766
04:04:53.058 --> 04:04:56.555
recent comments made by my right hon.

2414868486
04:04:56.556 --> 04:04:58.109
Friend for Birmingham Yardley.

380473502
04:04:58.110 --> 04:05:01.009
Now, the government has
rightly, in my view,

1604874516
04:05:01.010 --> 04:05:03.665
launched its sovereign AI
fund supporting innovative

2133357241
04:05:03.666 --> 04:05:07.563
start ups to scale up
and generate value here in the UK,

1149535374
04:05:08.004 --> 04:05:09.457
including access to compute.

2650750550
04:05:09.458 --> 04:05:13.112
And I know many of the Ministers,

4064868894
04:05:13.114 --> 04:05:15.521
indeed from the Department
for energy have been

1525643272
04:05:15.522 --> 04:05:17.905
working hard to ensure
the capacity is there

2787231572
04:05:17.906 --> 04:05:19.710
to deliver that additional compute.

713569188
04:05:19.711 --> 04:05:23.273
However, when it comes to the design
and use of AI systems and models,

2132663960
04:05:23.275 --> 04:05:28.005
we have only the AI Security Institute,

3622296484
04:05:28.005 --> 04:05:31.466
a world first expert led organisation,
but one which lacks statutory

1637960940
04:05:31.467 --> 04:05:36.058
powers and which has to ask
companies politely to engage.

1289819432
04:05:36.059 --> 04:05:39.308
Even the Trump administration
now appears to recognise

2061402590
04:05:39.308 --> 04:05:44.808
the need for evaluation of
frontier AI models before release.

1920110591
04:05:44.809 --> 04:05:48.457
If we're genuinely serious about
our country's economic security,

1020919303
04:05:48.458 --> 04:05:51.056
we must devote as much attention to AI

265144121
04:05:51.057 --> 04:05:54.803
and its astonishingly transformative,

604306342
04:05:54.804 --> 04:05:58.151
productive and disruptive potential
as we're rightly devoting

1438348041
04:05:58.152 --> 04:06:01.761
to energy security and
the delivery of home grown renewables.

289611247
04:06:01.762 --> 04:06:06.603
That will require first working
with the EU on digital regulation,

3495254370
04:06:06.604 --> 04:06:08.662
and I will push for this to be reflected

2822110678
04:06:08.663 --> 04:06:11.658
in the welcome EU partnership Bill.

2370036391
04:06:11.659 --> 04:06:14.165
The government maintains
in the briefing pack for

3665288521
04:06:14.166 --> 04:06:17.214
the King's Speech that nearly
one third of UK AI start

1391999960
04:06:17.215 --> 04:06:21.409
up leaders are considering
relocating overseas due

3084441760
04:06:21.410 --> 04:06:24.360
to regulatory complexity
and capital constraints.

561269750
04:06:24.361 --> 04:06:26.607
Given that regulatory complexity will

242726496
04:06:26.608 --> 04:06:30.057
often relate to cross-border issues,

1487818283
04:06:30.058 --> 04:06:31.562
the prescription is not here.

3784770374
04:06:33.004 --> 04:06:35.157
Deregulation, but regulatory coordination.

890904403
04:06:35.158 --> 04:06:36.857
I want to keep to time.

1881655754
04:06:36.858 --> 04:06:37.409
Thank you.

1783044513
04:06:37.410 --> 04:06:42.607
Capital constraints and relatedly
constraints in compute are real here.

2424609135
04:06:42.608 --> 04:06:45.450
We must recognise that
while unilateral measures

3667534530
04:06:45.451 --> 04:06:47.406
to support sovereign AI are important,

1083405527
04:06:48.003 --> 04:06:49.807
their scope is necessarily limited.

668649646
04:06:49.808 --> 04:06:54.519
So we must again work with reliable
partners who share our values,

262732777
04:06:56.004 --> 04:06:57.258
not least within the EU.

3051093531
04:06:57.259 --> 04:07:00.218
And finally, Madam Deputy
Speaker, we must be brave enough

1835891774
04:07:00.219 --> 04:07:05.164
to open up discussion on
the fiscal framework for AI.

1347368753
04:07:05.165 --> 04:07:07.855
We currently tax the very thing labour.

411706133
04:07:07.856 --> 04:07:12.115
The AI will, in some sectors,
in specific ways, displace.

1404492508
04:07:12.116 --> 04:07:14.973
We must examine now how
we might be able to use

3207507937
04:07:14.974 --> 04:07:19.409
the public stake from our
sovereign AI investments,

1835626008
04:07:19.410 --> 04:07:23.314
or mechanisms like a token tax
or reform to capital gains.

155466431
04:07:23.315 --> 04:07:25.222
As the TUC has suggested, to build up

3380408493
04:07:25.223 --> 04:07:27.762
the resources that may well be needed,

2866785765
04:07:27.763 --> 04:07:31.012
there is potential for
significant disruption to

2878019926
04:07:31.013 --> 04:07:33.715
the labour market and we
must be more ready for it.

1164767589
04:07:33.716 --> 04:07:37.308
Research out today from King's College

1446051059
04:07:37.308 --> 04:07:40.961
London suggests 69% of workers and 64%

149502906
04:07:40.962 --> 04:07:44.654
of employers are worried
about the economic

2976702491
04:07:44.655 --> 04:07:46.309
impact of AI related job losses.

3990423648
04:07:46.311 --> 04:07:50.456
A majority of all groups
surveyed predict AI's benefits

3585425751
04:07:50.457 --> 04:07:53.558
will mainly go to wealthy
investors and companies,

2849533077
04:07:53.558 --> 04:07:57.358
not workers or society,
and a majority of all

196372188
04:07:57.359 --> 04:07:59.463
groups also back government intervention.

3355339090
04:08:01.004 --> 04:08:04.759
If we are to secure the government's
intention of the fastest

1113534051
04:08:04.760 --> 04:08:08.355
adoption of AI in the G7, we
must deal with these issues to.

3370336846
04:08:08.356 --> 04:08:11.759
Our young people in particular,
will not forgive us

1054831093
04:08:11.760 --> 04:08:14.518
if we fail to engage with
this generational challenge.

921991750
04:08:14.519 --> 04:08:15.254
>> Thank you.

2739912102
04:08:15.255 --> 04:08:16.208
>> Sir John Hayes.

1107378683
04:08:16.209 --> 04:08:18.804
>> Thank you, Madam Deputy Speaker.

2157727781
04:08:18.805 --> 04:08:22.408
Britain is becoming harder to govern.

2672982207
04:08:22.409 --> 04:08:24.664
That's not principally
because of disruptive

2730938633
04:08:25.004 --> 04:08:26.707
or destabilising societal change.

274383503
04:08:26.708 --> 04:08:29.967
And it's not even because of
the increasingly complicated world,

998055166
04:08:30.014 --> 04:08:35.654
which is creating more
uncertainty for all governments.

1800810702
04:08:35.655 --> 04:08:37.510
The problem is in governance itself.

29227856
04:08:37.511 --> 04:08:40.971
The Prime Minister complains that
he pulls levers in Downing Street,

1018814950
04:08:40.972 --> 04:08:44.168
but they have less effect
in practice than he hoped.

1674995112
04:08:44.169 --> 04:08:48.557
And Simon Case, when he left
office, put this very clearly,

731169623
04:08:48.558 --> 04:08:51.766
he said an increasing number of
English devolution settlements,

1272493358
04:08:53.010 --> 04:08:55.365
independent quangos, arm's
length body courts,

1256115178
04:08:56.008 --> 04:08:58.515
statutory consultees
and the like block the path.

3975358930
04:08:58.516 --> 04:09:00.521
What a winning political party promises

505270384
04:09:00.522 --> 04:09:03.714
an election and what it
can achieve in power.

3304552230
04:09:03.715 --> 04:09:07.811
Successive governments
have delegated power to

1648713135
04:09:07.812 --> 04:09:10.111
all kinds unelected, unaccountable bodies.

2208741084
04:09:10.112 --> 04:09:15.020
Everything from the Budget for
the office for Budget Responsibility

3263021029
04:09:15.021 --> 04:09:20.062
to Network Rail and
the Environment Agency,

1501978593
04:09:20.063 --> 04:09:26.655
to all kinds of other quangos, many
of whose names we barely know.

1776534520
04:09:26.656 --> 04:09:31.158
And neither do we know
how their membership is

498131044
04:09:31.159 --> 04:09:33.415
chosen or to whom they
are held accountable.

2954565629
04:09:34.008 --> 04:09:38.407
It's time for a more radical programme
than this Queen's Speech offers.

3664129872
04:09:38.408 --> 04:09:42.820
It's time for Parliament
and Government to be more

2583885315
04:09:42.821 --> 04:09:45.407
confident about
the difference it can make.

2900056982
04:09:45.408 --> 04:09:48.016
Now the Secretary of State,
in opening this debate,

621058267
04:09:48.017 --> 04:09:49.719
talked about economic resilience.

2844991940
04:09:49.721 --> 04:09:52.028
And he's right, by
the way, absolutely right.

3765351015
04:09:52.029 --> 04:09:55.459
In the age in which we
live, we need to build

3952656511
04:09:55.460 --> 04:09:57.213
more national economic resilience.

4113591148
04:09:57.214 --> 04:10:01.065
But that means facing
up to the fact that we

1583645416
04:10:02.004 --> 04:10:04.160
manufacture too little of what we consume.

1510141813
04:10:04.161 --> 04:10:08.612
We grow too little of the food
that we need to feed the nation,

4178362496
04:10:09.003 --> 04:10:13.463
and the sort of economic
resilience that he describes

1109187454
04:10:13.464 --> 04:10:18.508
requires us to look again
at the balance of payments.

1803141557
04:10:18.509 --> 04:10:22.265
Before the 1970 election, it was
said that that Harold Wilson,

3234879948
04:10:22.266 --> 04:10:24.507
the then Labour Prime Minister,

3524613401
04:10:24.508 --> 04:10:27.403
lost that election against
expectations because

773993753
04:10:27.404 --> 04:10:29.460
there were bad balance of trade figures.

1861812169
04:10:29.461 --> 04:10:34.011
No one now speaks of the balance of trade.

1523523261
04:10:34.012 --> 04:10:41.564
And yet the truth is that we
import far more than we did then.

2745181139
04:10:44.004 --> 04:10:50.862
In the mid 1980s, we grew about
75% of the food we consume.

3028640056
04:10:50.864 --> 04:10:52.068
That's now down to 40%.

2900974356
04:10:52.069 --> 04:10:58.353
It is preposterous that we've
lengthened supply lines that we've,

3265527746
04:10:58.354 --> 04:11:00.208
as a result, decreased traceability.

1981964059
04:11:00.209 --> 04:11:02.768
We don't really know where
much of what we consume

949363557
04:11:02.769 --> 04:11:05.179
is made or how it's made,
or by whom it's made.

488989128
04:11:05.180 --> 04:11:08.391
We know that in the Far East,
there's all kinds of unacceptable

1194246442
04:11:08.392 --> 04:11:11.362
conditions that wouldn't be
tolerated in this country,

3156317782
04:11:11.362 --> 04:11:16.276
and yet we still choose to import large
amounts of those kinds of goods.

502454334
04:11:16.277 --> 04:11:21.813
So let's have a fresh look at
the character, the shape of our economy.

1751352638
04:11:21.814 --> 04:11:24.923
If we really want to build more
national economic resilience.

2045670991
04:11:24.924 --> 04:11:28.763
To do that, we will also need
to look at productivity.

1558879503
04:11:28.764 --> 04:11:31.423
Because as the as the Father
of the House described,

4204775223
04:11:31.424 --> 04:11:33.513
it's not good enough for government to

1781951952
04:11:33.514 --> 04:11:36.461
spend endlessly with
looking without looking

1195038345
04:11:36.462 --> 04:11:38.669
at the value it gets
from that expenditure.

607141669
04:11:38.670 --> 04:11:41.664
And yet we know that both public
sector and private sector

1270275064
04:11:41.665 --> 04:11:44.620
productivity has stalled
for a considerable time.

2702105282
04:11:44.621 --> 04:11:47.454
Not unique to this country.

1945027360
04:11:47.455 --> 04:11:50.408
It's a problem for
the whole of Western Europe.

1154215291
04:11:50.409 --> 04:11:51.561
Most modern economies.

1659056226
04:11:51.562 --> 04:11:55.213
But nonetheless, we need new measures to

1738610722
04:11:55.214 --> 04:11:57.666
focus on productivity so that what we

3653622612
04:11:57.668 --> 04:11:59.725
get for what we spend becomes the issue,

1015034043
04:12:01.012 --> 04:12:02.719
not how much we spend as a whole.

3843441135
04:12:02.719 --> 04:12:03.522
I thank my hon.

3708694230
04:12:03.523 --> 04:12:06.311
Friend for giving me,
and he's giving quite

2940311544
04:12:06.312 --> 04:12:08.319
a good lecture on what needs to happen.

3365376517
04:12:08.320 --> 04:12:12.215
What incentives do we need to
provide farmers to grow more

2614568666
04:12:12.216 --> 04:12:15.516
and indeed use their land
as effectively as possible,

793445688
04:12:15.517 --> 04:12:19.410
and also employers to use their
time as effectively as possible,

102024254
04:12:19.411 --> 04:12:22.813
so that we can literally
operate on a 24 hour day,

2741933513
04:12:22.814 --> 04:12:25.260
three shift operation in production.

1908451404
04:12:25.261 --> 04:12:29.114
Yeah, let me just just before
I deal with that, excellent point.

857456603
04:12:29.115 --> 04:12:31.011
And I'm grateful to my hon.

1553631857
04:12:31.012 --> 04:12:32.115
Friend for making it.

2915300818
04:12:32.116 --> 04:12:39.458
I just remind the House the current
trade deficit is about 25 billion.

1914090092
04:12:39.459 --> 04:12:40.061
By the way.

375850141
04:12:40.062 --> 04:12:44.119
That would be unthinkable
a generation or two ago.

1662126978
