UK would now have 94 MPs
sitting on these benches.

2242914136
04:44:05.152 --> 04:44:08.552
The Green Party would have 42
MPs sitting on these benches.

1105220637
04:44:10.044 --> 04:44:12.001
Instead we have five and we have four.

3087801777
04:44:12.002 --> 04:44:14.859
Convinced the disparity
between votes cast and

3306814755
04:44:14.860 --> 04:44:19.500
the seats won adds significantly
to the disillusion,

166486006
04:44:19.501 --> 04:44:22.059
the disillusion that many
of us will have heard on

544752322
04:44:22.061 --> 04:44:24.722
the seat on the streets of
the UK when we were vote,

2486816879
04:44:24.723 --> 04:44:26.701
when we were out there campaigning in

657161270
04:44:26.703 --> 04:44:30.554
the local elections earlier this month,

3813112285
04:44:30.555 --> 04:44:31.659
I will on that point.

3135738752
04:44:32.043 --> 04:44:33.750
>> So I thank him for giving way.

957545077
04:44:33.751 --> 04:44:35.505
It's not the biggest problem with.

144843143
04:44:35.507 --> 04:44:36.711
>> First past the post.

2114033102
04:44:36.712 --> 04:44:40.945
>> That often you're voting against
someone rather than for someone,

221827253
04:44:40.946 --> 04:44:44.205
and that poisons our democracy
because everyone thinks

735188557
04:44:44.206 --> 04:44:48.147
they end up with someone
that they don't want.

1433145299
04:44:48.148 --> 04:44:48.751
>> The hon.

3663214229
04:44:48.752 --> 04:44:52.448
Member for Tunbridge Wells is spot on.

2820397326
04:44:52.449 --> 04:44:53.151
He's spot on.

3567199399
04:44:53.152 --> 04:44:57.293
Former Labour former Labour voters
I accept former Labour voters vote

1282216223
04:44:57.294 --> 04:45:02.449
for me to keep out the Tories
and reform former conservative voters.

1907227347
04:45:02.450 --> 04:45:05.059
Vote for me to keep out
Labour and the Green Party.

2151542170
04:45:05.061 --> 04:45:06.846
This is not a system we want.

2764148750
04:45:06.847 --> 04:45:10.698
We want a system where people can
vote positively for change with hope.

322503157
04:45:10.699 --> 04:45:13.657
Little wonder that the only
other European country besides

2483423893
04:45:13.658 --> 04:45:19.493
the UK that elects their
parliament this way is Belarus.

694773961
04:45:19.494 --> 04:45:22.997
If first past the post
continues, we could see just 30%

286223071
04:45:22.998 --> 04:45:27.155
of votes bringing in
a government with extremist ideas.

2949324941
04:45:27.156 --> 04:45:30.447
I want to see
a proportionate number of MPs

1113003874
04:45:30.448 --> 04:45:32.405
for reform UK and for the Green Party,

2473064655
04:45:32.406 --> 04:45:33.959
not a disproportionate number.

644408685
04:45:33.960 --> 04:45:37.203
I don't agree with them
on universal access,

2569179251
04:45:37.204 --> 04:45:42.053
on defence or on immigration,
on universal access.

1703559258
04:45:42.054 --> 04:45:44.261
It's the reform UK
that's talking about tax

801135972
04:45:44.262 --> 04:45:46.604
breaks for people who opt out of the NHS.

2893371832
04:45:46.605 --> 04:45:49.351
The Green Party is talking
about bringing in

1138291239
04:45:49.352 --> 04:45:52.550
a basic income for everybody
with no conditions.

3886511528
04:45:52.551 --> 04:45:54.959
One wants to strip us of
universal health care,

1340126538
04:45:54.960 --> 04:45:59.148
the other one wants to
have taxpayers paying

310050307
04:45:59.150 --> 04:46:01.493
for a universal income on defence.

3476500957
04:46:01.494 --> 04:46:03.550
Whether it is reform UK, apologising for

3987976152
04:46:03.551 --> 04:46:05.304
Putin's aggression against Ukraine

1192553929
04:46:05.305 --> 04:46:10.502
or the Green Party pledging to
dismantle the UK's nuclear weapons.

4072096883
04:46:10.503 --> 04:46:12.558
Whether it's lowering the Ukrainian flag

1561638813
04:46:12.558 --> 04:46:14.414
over town councils that it controls,

1133756686
04:46:14.415 --> 04:46:16.823
while the other would
hoist the white flag over

2874635480
04:46:16.824 --> 04:46:19.651
defence establishments in this country.

3677335851
04:46:19.652 --> 04:46:21.959
On immigration, whether
it is the Green Party

4229885725
04:46:21.960 --> 04:46:25.699
threaten to end proper controls or.

3389093464
04:46:25.700 --> 04:46:26.201
>> After.

2728454565
04:46:26.201 --> 04:46:27.607
>> Can I encourage the hon.

2766937791
04:46:27.608 --> 04:46:31.531
Gentleman to return to at
least some of the substance

4064815448
04:46:31.532 --> 04:46:33.286
of His Majesty's gracious address?

3274155926
04:46:33.287 --> 04:46:35.397
Richard Foord.

373823879
04:46:35.397 --> 04:46:38.194
>> Madam Deputy Speaker, these parties do

3364712509
04:46:38.195 --> 04:46:40.049
not represent the moderate majority,

1526214849
04:46:40.050 --> 04:46:44.548
but with as little as 30% of
the vote at the next general election,

1271452911
04:46:44.549 --> 04:46:49.397
they could control all
of the levers of power.

1353736475
04:46:49.398 --> 04:46:52.948
First past the post is
unfair, unrepresentative,

2047188373
04:46:52.949 --> 04:46:57.597
and it undermines
the legitimacy of our elections.

1753447945
04:46:57.598 --> 04:47:01.055
I urge the government not to
prolong the disenchantment,

3119788100
04:47:01.056 --> 04:47:03.564
the apathy and
the hopelessness people are fed up

2364154242
04:47:03.565 --> 04:47:06.700
with being told to vote
for the lesser evil.

2662686919
04:47:06.701 --> 04:47:09.558
The Representation of
the People Bill is the opportunity

3774437684
04:47:09.559 --> 04:47:13.397
this government has to get it right.

2419244948
04:47:13.398 --> 04:47:13.950
Thank you.

2662033029
04:47:13.951 --> 04:47:16.508
>> Nadia Whittome thank
you, Madam Deputy Speaker,

1875708757
04:47:16.509 --> 04:47:18.617
and I agree with every word that the hon.

2035333160
04:47:18.618 --> 04:47:21.828
Member has just said about first
past the post and proportional

4048401144
04:47:21.829 --> 04:47:25.100
representation is Labour Party policy.

2227261265
04:47:25.101 --> 04:47:27.811
It unites the left and
the right of the Labour Party.

3645111484
04:47:27.812 --> 04:47:30.723
I think it's probably one of
the few things that the hon.

3305897008
04:47:30.724 --> 04:47:35.556
Member for North Durham and
I work together on passionately.

2375842145
04:47:35.557 --> 04:47:37.565
And if if colleagues on on this side of

359098378
04:47:37.566 --> 04:47:39.623
the House think that first past the post

2942191079
04:47:39.624 --> 04:47:41.581
was great for us in the last election,

635259216
04:47:41.582 --> 04:47:43.757
then just wait till the next election.

151603690
04:47:43.758 --> 04:47:45.414
It's it's the right thing to do.

2520881361
04:47:45.415 --> 04:47:47.703
It's the most democratic thing to do.

1873377760
04:47:47.704 --> 04:47:52.407
And it's also the best thing to
do in our own self-interest.

4152361733
04:47:52.408 --> 04:47:55.065
Madam Deputy Speaker, our
party came into government

4199290442
04:47:55.066 --> 04:47:57.219
against a backdrop of deindustrialisation,

2911425220
04:47:58.047 --> 04:48:00.603
privatisation and austerity,
which over the course

1413924094
04:48:00.604 --> 04:48:02.802
of decades has bled this country dry.

3937511114
04:48:02.803 --> 04:48:05.160
It's left millions of
people in abject poverty

3087086367
04:48:05.161 --> 04:48:07.661
in the fifth richest country in the world,

3505675968
04:48:07.662 --> 04:48:11.110
and millions more struggling to get by.

1778851548
04:48:11.111 --> 04:48:16.503
Of course, people are enraged
by the state of our society,

2129570527
04:48:16.504 --> 04:48:21.252
but drifting far right politicians
declaring war on minority

195460476
04:48:21.253 --> 04:48:24.154
groups are exploiting this
rage to sow division.

3608117198
04:48:24.155 --> 04:48:26.263
They are funded by many of the people who

1686250039
04:48:26.264 --> 04:48:29.504
cause these problems in the first place,

695540843
04:48:29.505 --> 04:48:33.353
who want us to punch down
so we don't look up at them.

1616278119
04:48:33.354 --> 04:48:37.104
This threat is on our streets
and in our political system.

314149215
04:48:37.105 --> 04:48:40.300
From the Unite the Kingdom rally,

246589445
04:48:40.301 --> 04:48:43.559
mocking Muslim women
and calling for mass deportations,

444302199
04:48:43.561 --> 04:48:46.949
including of British citizens,

3381349899
04:48:46.950 --> 04:48:50.303
to the reform councillors celebrating
the rape of a sick woman

1105250710
04:48:50.304 --> 04:48:56.058
and saying that Nigerians should
be melted down to fill potholes.

1112183330
04:48:56.059 --> 04:49:02.056
Unless we want these people running
this country, we have to get our act

1304837052
04:49:02.057 --> 04:49:05.366
together because while we've done
some good things in government,

2073287423
04:49:05.367 --> 04:49:07.576
and I want to be clear
here that this isn't

2619850202
04:49:07.576 --> 04:49:09.533
a criticism of the Secretary of State,

3797297409
04:49:09.534 --> 04:49:13.401
who I think has done
an excellent job in his role,

867401736
04:49:13.402 --> 04:49:17.455
particularly against some of
the flat earthers opposite.

1469924276
04:49:17.456 --> 04:49:20.415
But while while we've done some
good things in government,

635135890
04:49:20.415 --> 04:49:23.306
like improving workers
rights and renters rights,

1337348486
04:49:23.307 --> 04:49:28.507
creating GB energy, increasing
funding to local councils,

233777869
04:49:29.049 --> 04:49:31.257
the fact is we have not
delivered change at

3372873469
04:49:31.258 --> 04:49:34.004
the pace and the scale that voters expect,

716739156
04:49:34.005 --> 04:49:38.402
and there is also far too much that
this government has got wrong,

302719961
04:49:38.403 --> 04:49:40.308
like attempting to limit jury trials,

1274845880
04:49:41.008 --> 04:49:43.163
like cutting benefits for disabled people.

1908204309
04:49:43.164 --> 04:49:47.857
It's failures over the genocide in Gaza.

3861005675
04:49:47.858 --> 04:49:50.858
These mistakes and
the refusal to learn from them,

226866983
04:49:50.859 --> 04:49:53.910
are fuelling the collapse
of the two party system

3015362899
04:49:53.911 --> 04:49:56.956
and the rise of a multi-party
political landscape.

3767022204
04:49:56.957 --> 04:50:01.903
But the leadership strategy to stop
reform has just reinforced their

1737332627
04:50:01.904 --> 04:50:05.955
narrative that immigration is
what's wrong with our society.

2444676491
04:50:05.956 --> 04:50:09.007
And not only is that completely
at odds with labour values,

2304358945
04:50:09.008 --> 04:50:12.563
but it's also been
a complete electoral disaster.

985313074
04:50:12.564 --> 04:50:15.556
We have smashed apart
our own voter coalition

1542115306
04:50:15.557 --> 04:50:18.102
and as we haemorrhage votes to the Greens,

2420628642
04:50:18.103 --> 04:50:21.602
we're also delivering seats to reform.

833676413
04:50:21.603 --> 04:50:24.312
Madam Deputy Speaker,
I refuse to put a positive spin

510558797
04:50:24.313 --> 04:50:28.155
on the last two years because
I want us to be better.

2537927563
04:50:28.156 --> 04:50:29.861
We have to face unpleasant facts.

3787839528
04:50:29.862 --> 04:50:30.915
I know it's painful.

2113273557
04:50:30.915 --> 04:50:33.708
It's painful for all of
us because we all believe

1374440757
04:50:33.709 --> 04:50:36.103
in the potential of a Labour government.

1844044700
04:50:36.104 --> 04:50:38.954
We all understand what is at stake here,

2085067194
04:50:38.955 --> 04:50:42.212
and I know that colleagues
who disagree with with this

2612171736
04:50:42.213 --> 04:50:46.806
analysis do also genuinely
want to improve people's

3781849053
04:50:46.807 --> 04:50:48.763
lives and stop a far right government.

3350474256
04:50:48.764 --> 04:50:52.025
But I'm afraid the argument that
we can achieve this by sticking

539549913
04:50:52.026 --> 04:50:56.305
to a failed political strategy
just does not hold water.

1328204049
04:50:56.306 --> 04:50:59.916
This Labour government needs a total
reset to show that it's listening,

4217527759
04:50:59.918 --> 04:51:02.402
that it understands what it got wrong,

4269801662
04:51:02.403 --> 04:51:04.411
and that it has a clear plan to change.

766711368
04:51:04.412 --> 04:51:06.768
But its response to
a catastrophic performance

2729433911
04:51:06.769 --> 04:51:09.056
in the local elections has

426555910
04:51:09.057 --> 04:51:12.719
been to double down on the same
incrementalism that we've seen thus far.

3666294573
04:51:12.719 --> 04:51:15.580
And this is what we've seen
again in this King's speech.

3377911338
04:51:15.581 --> 04:51:18.639
While there are positives like
the Hillsborough Law measures

4182953390
04:51:18.640 --> 04:51:21.246
for Ukraine commitment to
ban conversion practices,

2478373664
04:51:21.247 --> 04:51:23.807
it's clear to most of us
that they are not enough.

432578677
04:51:23.808 --> 04:51:26.266
There are much bolder
measures that we should be

3560835443
04:51:26.267 --> 04:51:28.474
taking to tackle
the cost of living crisis,

1743037598
04:51:28.475 --> 04:51:32.657
and to rebalance the economy so that
it works for working class people.

2014755818
04:51:32.658 --> 04:51:33.610
Just two examples.

1315795303
04:51:35.053 --> 04:51:35.804
Rent controls.

1394571826
04:51:35.805 --> 04:51:38.405
So housing costs are affordable and people

4179505843
04:51:38.406 --> 04:51:40.411
aren't priced out of their communities.

1698856134
04:51:41.013 --> 04:51:43.518
Nationalising utilities
to prioritise public need

1854562509
04:51:44.052 --> 04:51:46.158
over private profit and bring down bills.

1816113419
04:51:46.159 --> 04:51:50.854
And we need to do that at the same
time as unashamedly standing up for

3225307564
04:51:50.855 --> 04:51:54.265
the full diversity of the working
class, wherever people were born,

12510579
04:51:54.266 --> 04:51:56.823
whatever the colour of their
skin, their religion,

1780340034
04:51:56.824 --> 04:51:58.628
their sexuality or gender identity,

184911425
04:51:58.629 --> 04:52:03.055
whether they're disabled or not,
whether they're in work or not.

1050890160
04:52:03.056 --> 04:52:04.960
Madam Deputy Speaker Tinkering around

1673336109
04:52:04.961 --> 04:52:07.604
the edges was never going to cut it.

3674537586
04:52:07.605 --> 04:52:08.758
Chasing the far right.

2730803587
04:52:08.759 --> 04:52:09.009
Yes.

2291831185
04:52:09.010 --> 04:52:10.566
>> I thank her for giving way.

2101505765
04:52:10.567 --> 04:52:13.027
And I agree with so much
of what she's saying.

2790395172
04:52:13.028 --> 04:52:14.282
We need to be ambitious.

3524451887
04:52:14.283 --> 04:52:19.508
We need to be looking at the big
picture and fixing systems,

2573625958
04:52:19.509 --> 04:52:21.114
as well as situations like her.

2176665835
04:52:21.115 --> 04:52:23.509
I want to see us stepping out in a far

1570077959
04:52:23.510 --> 04:52:26.958
more ambitious way from here onward.

542181914
04:52:26.959 --> 04:52:29.511
And I see the headings of these bills in

979174546
04:52:29.512 --> 04:52:31.551
the King's Speech offer huge potential

4098482185
04:52:31.552 --> 04:52:34.913
for us to do things just a far more
transformative and meaningful,

3321838481
04:52:34.914 --> 04:52:38.476
and address the root causes of many
of the problems that we're facing.

3396174483
04:52:38.477 --> 04:52:40.937
So does she agree with me
that there is a chance

2132210538
04:52:40.938 --> 04:52:42.994
with the bills under this King's speech,

154543849
04:52:42.995 --> 04:52:46.813
but with a radical different
approach to working through to bring

3745540143
04:52:46.814 --> 04:52:51.654
the kind of change and delivery
that we've been hoping for.

2805515773
04:52:51.655 --> 04:52:52.609
>> I thank my hon.

2665552985
04:52:52.610 --> 04:52:55.753
Friend for his intervention.

3987206054
04:52:55.754 --> 04:52:58.362
I feel like to have a candid
discussion about this.

967134302
04:52:58.364 --> 04:53:02.707
It would probably be best not to
have it in the chamber, but yes,

2875958553
04:53:02.708 --> 04:53:06.461
I think I think that the King's
Speech provides headings,

922885549
04:53:06.462 --> 04:53:09.021
but I'm afraid I think
that's that's all they are.

681294835
04:53:10.056 --> 04:53:14.406
They're hints to what we need
and they're not the sum of it.

813414852
04:53:14.407 --> 04:53:15.460
And we haven't been.

2919275224
04:53:15.461 --> 04:53:19.210
It's not just that I don't believe
that the change is coming,

456518572
04:53:21.056 --> 04:53:22.259
but it's been promised.

2891255667
04:53:22.260 --> 04:53:23.513
It hasn't been promised.

2412464314
04:53:23.514 --> 04:53:28.357
We're doubling down on
the same mistakes that we made.

4148517771
04:53:28.358 --> 04:53:30.615
And what we've heard
from the Prime Minister

1005501712
04:53:30.616 --> 04:53:32.722
is we've done great things in government.

2894123639
04:53:32.723 --> 04:53:34.428
You just haven't realised it yet.

691735525
04:53:34.429 --> 04:53:35.732
So, Madam Deputy Speaker,

394472841
04:53:35.733 --> 04:53:38.455
tinkering around the edges
was not going to cut it.

1637583724
04:53:38.456 --> 04:53:41.566
Chasing the far right on immigration
was never going to work.

983150937
04:53:41.567 --> 04:53:45.571
And if we don't learn these lessons
now, then it will be too late.

1981935599
04:53:45.572 --> 04:53:49.711
We will be squandering
the generational opportunity of a Labour

2684083560
04:53:50.056 --> 04:53:52.713
government to transform this
country for the better,

4096299403
04:53:52.714 --> 04:53:55.022
and we will be allowing
the far right to win.

676196691
04:53:55.054 --> 04:53:57.764
And I refuse to sit here
quietly and let that happen.

1713110285
04:53:57.765 --> 04:53:58.216
>> Yeah.

3070290984
04:53:58.217 --> 04:53:58.768
>> Kruger.

1332382204
04:53:58.769 --> 04:54:00.703
>> Thank you very much indeed.

1180353765
04:54:00.704 --> 04:54:03.563
Madam Deputy Speaker, it's
a pleasure to follow the hon.

1537012133
04:54:03.564 --> 04:54:06.876
Lady, because I think she made
a very important point at the end.

3013707610
04:54:06.877 --> 04:54:07.579
There she is.

2970139902
04:54:07.580 --> 04:54:07.930
Right.

3787093084
04:54:07.931 --> 04:54:11.507
I'm afraid to say this is a very
underwhelming King's Speech.

454882413
04:54:11.508 --> 04:54:13.513
There are some welcome headlines there,

512619167
04:54:13.514 --> 04:54:15.972
but the fact is the ambition
is very diminished.

1836127751
04:54:15.973 --> 04:54:18.380
And the reason for that,
and she represents it,

3257658869
04:54:18.382 --> 04:54:21.107
is that the party opposite
is fundamentally split.

693308200
04:54:21.108 --> 04:54:25.463
They're unable to move forward boldly
in any direction that is needed.

3390128362
04:54:25.464 --> 04:54:28.713
And I don't don't make a personal
accusation against them.

3914242727
04:54:28.714 --> 04:54:29.868
I know what it's like.

3744236611
04:54:29.869 --> 04:54:33.433
I sat on I sat on those benches in
the last Parliament in a supporting

3956911635
04:54:33.433 --> 04:54:36.913
a government that was also fatally
split and unable to move forward.

3159335293
04:54:36.914 --> 04:54:39.673
This is the consequence of
the politics that we're in.

37789567
04:54:39.674 --> 04:54:43.236
And by the way, I welcome the very
eloquent and elegant repudiation of

2651775868
04:54:43.237 --> 04:54:46.748
her previous position by my friend
the the Shadow Secretary of State.

129582827
04:54:46.749 --> 04:54:49.107
I think she made
an excellent speech about the

776709601
04:54:49.108 --> 04:54:51.615
the difficulty of the of
the government's policy.

3280661603
04:54:51.616 --> 04:54:53.121
She's now in the right place.

2978735245
04:54:53.122 --> 04:54:56.783
But across the board, and particularly
on this topic of energy security,

2007887851
04:54:56.784 --> 04:54:58.990
Madam Deputy Speaker,
we see bold ambition,

2669952591
