3458618965
05:16:56.934 --> 05:16:59.794
And I recently helped organise
an event at the community

4047576638
05:16:59.795 --> 05:17:02.153
hub that was packed out
about new nuclear with

2470091370
05:17:02.154 --> 05:17:04.681
local residents who are
desperate for new nuclear

321039057
05:17:04.682 --> 05:17:07.038
power generation to return
to their community.

1843027761
05:17:07.039 --> 05:17:10.781
And so I commend the actions
of this government to

2215337578
05:17:10.782 --> 05:17:13.288
help speed up new nuclear
technology development.

1400087326
05:17:13.289 --> 05:17:17.034
And it was something that my
predecessor pushed the Tory government

4203916227
05:17:17.035 --> 05:17:20.383
for his own party for many, many
years to bring back Dungeness,

1134142939
05:17:21.080 --> 05:17:23.387
new nuclear to Dungeness,
but he got nowhere,

3499107585
05:17:23.388 --> 05:17:25.092
I'm afraid, Madam Deputy Speaker,

3410847202
05:17:25.093 --> 05:17:28.143
because his party were just not
interested in helping him.

789554336
05:17:28.144 --> 05:17:30.998
And so I do welcome
the nuclear regulation bill's

537339708
05:17:32.088 --> 05:17:34.343
intention to implement
the Fingleton review,

2336849176
05:17:34.344 --> 05:17:37.080
where it cuts unnecessary
delay and duplication.

663549234
05:17:37.081 --> 05:17:40.890
And this is not to say that we
undermine environmental protections.

3264139314
05:17:40.891 --> 05:17:42.044
Those must, of course,

354974744
05:17:42.045 --> 05:17:45.040
remain effective and credible
as well as evidence based.

4129473789
05:17:45.041 --> 05:17:48.035
And the argument is not
nature versus nuclear.

254734144
05:17:48.036 --> 05:17:52.530
Climate change is itself a major
threat to habitats and species.

2128117339
05:17:52.531 --> 05:17:54.687
So changes must focus on faster decisions.

3058318870
05:17:54.688 --> 05:17:57.839
But with real environmental integrity.

652762525
05:17:57.840 --> 05:18:00.586
If we are to achieve true energy security,

852796970
05:18:00.587 --> 05:18:03.096
then we need new nuclear
to play a critical role,

2901100602
05:18:03.097 --> 05:18:06.760
because the sun does not always shine
and the wind does not always blow.

2084285778
05:18:07.080 --> 05:18:10.430
We need warm, efficient
homes, fair energy bills,

528896398
05:18:10.431 --> 05:18:14.094
and a regulator with the teeth and
the remit to stand up for the public.

3144223109
05:18:14.096 --> 05:18:16.545
As the system changes,
new nuclear can generate

2987833282
05:18:16.546 --> 05:18:19.330
a significant number of
well-skilled, well-paid,

1932426303
05:18:19.331 --> 05:18:22.739
unionised jobs and help support
the reindustrialisation of Britain,

2371028713
05:18:22.740 --> 05:18:24.634
which we of course desperately need.

3692916266
05:18:24.635 --> 05:18:25.036
And so.

179997949
05:18:25.037 --> 05:18:29.141
So can the mass rollout of renewables,
grid upgrades and home retrofit.

1151961643
05:18:29.142 --> 05:18:32.733
So I welcome the Energy security Bill
and the Nuclear Regulation Bill,

2706331610
05:18:32.734 --> 05:18:35.333
especially the measures that help speed

32054431
05:18:35.334 --> 05:18:37.089
up the development of new nuclear.

1974310500
05:18:37.090 --> 05:18:40.250
This is about whether families
can afford to heat their homes,

426387867
05:18:40.251 --> 05:18:43.461
whether workers have good jobs
in the industries of the future,

1681627483
05:18:43.462 --> 05:18:47.094
and whether Britain can stand on its
own two feet in a dangerous world.

2524233268
05:18:47.094 --> 05:18:49.304
And I would say to
the champions of the oil

4229640035
05:18:49.305 --> 05:18:51.812
and gas industry sitting
on the benches opposite,

3405732084
05:18:51.813 --> 05:18:54.472
that they should do the right
thing for the country.

1443794854
05:18:54.473 --> 05:18:57.132
They should accept we can
never get bills down while

2043072338
05:18:57.133 --> 05:18:59.440
we rely on international
oil and gas markets,

2478170226
05:18:59.441 --> 05:19:02.853
and they should support the measures
in this bill to give us clean,

1470183835
05:19:02.854 --> 05:19:06.386
clean, cheap power and energy
independence for our great nation.

2564452990
05:19:06.387 --> 05:19:07.490
>> Anna Sabine Madam.

3119230338
05:19:07.491 --> 05:19:10.737
>> Deputy Speaker, one of
the many challenges facing rural

2970514278
05:19:10.739 --> 05:19:13.949
constituencies like mine is
the rising cost of fuel.

576337330
05:19:13.950 --> 05:19:15.907
When the war in Iran pushed up prices,

2298926664
05:19:15.908 --> 05:19:19.118
I had constituents telling me
they could no longer afford their

196451315
05:19:19.119 --> 05:19:21.828
planned orders of heating
oil and would try to manage

1849503018
05:19:21.829 --> 05:19:23.986
without heating for as long as they could.

4215755218
05:19:23.987 --> 05:19:26.144
And as you might expect, residents in fuel

377934693
05:19:26.145 --> 05:19:28.101
North Somerset rely heavily on car use

639078851
05:19:28.102 --> 05:19:30.208
and therefore fuel like diesel and petrol

1638033559
05:19:30.209 --> 05:19:32.014
in order to access health services.

419679994
05:19:32.015 --> 05:19:34.673
I'm very concerned about
the lack of community input

2041767217
05:19:34.674 --> 05:19:37.180
into decisions being made
around health services,

844179962
05:19:37.181 --> 05:19:40.790
which disproportionately affects
communities who have the drive to get,

3843090510
05:19:40.790 --> 05:19:44.353
drive or get the bus or run patient
transport services in rural areas.

3321751672
05:19:44.354 --> 05:19:47.513
The King's Speech brings forward
plans to abolish NHS England,

3862812850
05:19:47.514 --> 05:19:50.072
but in my constituency of
Frome and East Somerset,

675904367
05:19:50.073 --> 05:19:52.632
NHS Somerset has been running
what it calls a test

2537840326
05:19:52.633 --> 05:19:55.591
and learn exercise from community
hospital for six months.

1079573880
05:19:55.592 --> 05:19:58.502
The number of beds was temporarily
reduced from 24 to 16,

85574811
05:19:58.503 --> 05:20:00.963
and at the end of that
period the test and learn

3755773073
05:20:00.964 --> 05:20:03.170
was simply extended for
another six months,

2239359489
05:20:03.171 --> 05:20:04.676
meaning that for a full year,

2111798216
05:20:04.677 --> 05:20:07.234
capacity has been reduced
and no full consultation

3904051964
05:20:07.235 --> 05:20:10.041
with communities about these
changes has been required.

1532073994
05:20:10.043 --> 05:20:13.554
People are rightly concerned that
a reduction in a local service will

2003961070
05:20:13.555 --> 05:20:16.966
require them to travel further
afield, the cost of which is rising.

1565033707
05:20:16.967 --> 05:20:20.326
I have serious concerns about whether
the evidence provided so far

2990620552
05:20:20.328 --> 05:20:23.336
is strong enough to justify
making these changes permanent,

2069131471
05:20:23.337 --> 05:20:25.945
and I'm deeply troubled by
how little the community

1937548067
05:20:25.946 --> 05:20:27.951
has been involved in that conversation.

1587202221
05:20:27.951 --> 05:20:29.808
I decided to do my own consultation,

1069773365
05:20:29.808 --> 05:20:31.817
hosting a pop up in Frome two weeks ago

2923165343
05:20:31.818 --> 05:20:33.775
and asking local people to tell us why

4105541902
05:20:33.776 --> 05:20:35.581
the hospital was important to them.

1908578667
05:20:35.582 --> 05:20:38.490
One constituent wrote I feel
strongly that Frome Hospital

600981543
05:20:38.491 --> 05:20:40.697
provides so many services
for local people.

3328695069
05:20:40.698 --> 05:20:42.704
When I hear from elderly friends who've

384678737
05:20:42.705 --> 05:20:44.411
ended up with long stays in Bath,

3546040997
05:20:44.412 --> 05:20:46.518
I find it incomprehensible that once they

1199352504
05:20:46.519 --> 05:20:48.273
reach a certain stage of recovery,

998825135
05:20:48.275 --> 05:20:49.931
they can't be moved near a home.

3807851067
05:20:49.932 --> 05:20:52.190
Another said it's a shame
we must lose beds.

2165378442
05:20:52.191 --> 05:20:54.098
My friend was in Bath for five weeks,

804932286
05:20:54.099 --> 05:20:57.309
then had to go to Wincanton
Hospital for another seven weeks as

2686064321
05:20:57.311 --> 05:21:00.223
there were no beds and Frome
and this was so far for her,

4049607051
05:21:00.224 --> 05:21:02.331
hard for her family who lived miles away.

1272048657
05:21:02.332 --> 05:21:04.789
The people of Frome
and its surrounding villages

454957608
05:21:04.790 --> 05:21:06.494
rely on their community hospital,

2009481798
05:21:06.495 --> 05:21:09.356
and yet they woke up one morning
to find a decision had,

1677000958
05:21:09.357 --> 05:21:12.015
in effect, already been made
to reduce its capacity,

1736934765
05:21:12.016 --> 05:21:14.925
a decision that means some of
the most vulnerable members

3069225802
05:21:14.926 --> 05:21:17.336
of our community will not
have a bed in a local

1669759609
05:21:17.337 --> 05:21:20.043
hospital community setting
if they're discharged from

3613171232
05:21:20.044 --> 05:21:22.652
our general hospital in
Bath for an elderly person,

3704194758
05:21:22.653 --> 05:21:26.317
for a carer managing on their own,
or for those without access to a car.

3835431963
05:21:26.318 --> 05:21:29.277
The risk of being placed in
a community hospital somewhere

1551242731
05:21:29.278 --> 05:21:32.037
else in Somerset is a serious
barrier to suitable care

3012673473
05:21:32.038 --> 05:21:34.897
and a lack of public transport
and increasing fuel costs

3942993460
05:21:34.897 --> 05:21:37.706
places a huge additional
stress on families and carers.

1721137295
05:21:37.707 --> 05:21:41.070
Two weeks ago I was pleased to meet
with the Ministers for care to

1547445656
05:21:41.071 --> 05:21:44.278
discuss the government's plan for
neighbourhood health centres,

4243640308
05:21:44.279 --> 05:21:46.838
a policy I broadly welcome
and one which I believe

2287998591
05:21:46.839 --> 05:21:49.344
could genuinely benefit
parts of my constituency.

4260935870
05:21:49.346 --> 05:21:51.803
In this meeting,
the Ministers was explicit that

3160096302
05:21:51.804 --> 05:21:53.910
our Integrated Care Board was required to

4258140561
05:21:53.911 --> 05:21:56.117
consult local MPs
and other stakeholders on

2801211446
05:21:56.118 --> 05:21:58.224
their plans for these new health centres.

376156291
05:21:58.225 --> 05:22:00.433
Not only has really
been not been in touch,

2233474889
05:22:00.433 --> 05:22:02.691
but when we followed up
with them ourselves,

4115525701
05:22:02.692 --> 05:22:03.946
we were told two things.

2322784263
05:22:03.947 --> 05:22:06.104
First, they had no idea they were expected

472129139
05:22:06.105 --> 05:22:08.112
to engage with MPs on this, and second,

178080596
05:22:08.112 --> 05:22:10.319
they'd already decided
where the hubs would

2184558187
05:22:10.320 --> 05:22:12.074
go without consulting anyone else.

1739628896
05:22:12.075 --> 05:22:15.189
In both the cases I have set
out, there seems to be a lack of

1671666556
05:22:15.190 --> 05:22:18.148
mechanism to force ICBs
or trusts to consult local people,

221940374
05:22:18.150 --> 05:22:20.761
and a total lack of sanction
if they fail to do so.

3787730243
05:22:20.762 --> 05:22:23.469
People who live in Frome
and surrounding villages are

2548575541
05:22:23.471 --> 05:22:26.180
the experts in their own
lives and they have helpful,

2423938200
05:22:26.181 --> 05:22:29.038
constructive and innovative
ideas to input into decision

3741876324
05:22:29.039 --> 05:22:31.596
making around the future
of local health services.

1082932747
05:22:31.597 --> 05:22:34.655
The government is also overseeing
the removal of Healthwatch

3120749552
05:22:34.656 --> 05:22:36.962
and the Citizens Senate
to additional bodies,

108113857
05:22:36.963 --> 05:22:40.625
which sent a patient voice at the heart
of discussions about their care.

3689683531
05:22:40.626 --> 05:22:43.835
I'm worried that without these
bodies being replaced or without

3247800748
05:22:43.836 --> 05:22:46.291
mechanisms in place to
ensure good consultation,

1409032361
05:22:46.293 --> 05:22:49.551
communities risk being entirely
unheard in decisions which will,

1957963615
05:22:49.552 --> 05:22:51.307
for some affect their daily lives.

66786953
05:22:51.308 --> 05:22:53.615
I do hope that Ministers
will coordinate with

2381090609
05:22:53.616 --> 05:22:55.469
colleagues in departments of health,

2077160128
05:22:55.471 --> 05:22:57.777
transport and elsewhere
to ensure that people

1010578621
05:22:57.778 --> 05:22:59.534
in Frome and East Somerset can get

2370720474
05:22:59.535 --> 05:23:02.545
the health services they need
in the places they need them,

2624677239
05:23:02.546 --> 05:23:03.850
and in an affordable way.

3415141643
05:23:03.851 --> 05:23:06.308
>> Andrew Lewin thank you,
Madam Deputy Speaker,

1147712171
05:23:06.308 --> 05:23:09.372
can I say it's a real pleasure
to see you back in the chair.

3568309522
05:23:09.373 --> 05:23:11.228
The model of calmness and authority.

2954609072
05:23:11.229 --> 05:23:13.739
And I think after the week
that my party has had,

2564780750
05:23:13.740 --> 05:23:15.596
then there is a virtue in stability,

1758201628
05:23:15.597 --> 05:23:17.754
which I think you represent in that chair.

2025972595
05:23:17.755 --> 05:23:20.114
But I'm pleased to be
back in this chamber for

4061095338
05:23:20.115 --> 05:23:22.623
the first time in
the session of this Parliament,

1771423662
05:23:22.624 --> 05:23:25.684
to talk about policy and not
personality, to focus on one of

3612368478
05:23:25.686 --> 05:23:29.089
the biggest issues our country
faces, our energy security,

4144934093
05:23:29.090 --> 05:23:32.902
the decision by the United
States and Israel to strike Iran

383537997
05:23:33.084 --> 05:23:37.384
on the 27th of February has
seen thousands of lives lost,

498997412
05:23:37.385 --> 05:23:41.839
billions expended in weaponry,
a stalemate in the Strait of Hormuz,

4097547183
05:23:41.840 --> 05:23:43.244
and a global energy crisis.

770337068
05:23:43.245 --> 05:23:48.687
For many countries, the situation
has become very grave very quickly.

2375792581
05:23:48.688 --> 05:23:50.395
In the UK, the price at the pump.

3201098268
05:23:50.396 --> 05:23:53.842
On the day before
the strikes, petrol was £1,

1565869380
05:23:53.843 --> 05:23:55.448
35 per litre, diesel was £1.43.

1314545019
05:23:58.084 --> 05:24:01.143
Average price is now closer to
£1.58 and £1.86 respectively.

2957099137
05:24:01.144 --> 05:24:03.352
And while we are less
reliant on the Strait

3372475203
05:24:03.353 --> 05:24:04.907
of Hormuz than many countries,

3200509976
05:24:04.908 --> 05:24:07.666
our exposure to the fossil
fuel roller coaster that is

2477325576
05:24:07.668 --> 05:24:11.294
the global market means we
are being hit hard too.

1284264155
05:24:11.295 --> 05:24:14.857
The choice before us is simple get
off the fossil fuel roller coaster,

2545797705
05:24:14.858 --> 05:24:18.601
accelerate our transition
to green and clean

2519736513
05:24:18.602 --> 05:24:20.990
energy for people and planet or people.

3711475857
05:24:20.991 --> 05:24:22.797
And the planet will continue to pay

841705201
05:24:24.088 --> 05:24:26.246
the price for our reliance on gas and oil.

3462742632
05:24:26.247 --> 05:24:29.144
A word on climate change records on global

464130069
05:24:29.145 --> 05:24:32.040
temperatures date back to 1850.

4292864169
05:24:32.041 --> 05:24:37.043
And yet the past 11 years have been
the 11th warmest years on record.

351812518
05:24:37.044 --> 05:24:39.692
We must pursue the transition to clean,

1928552115
05:24:39.693 --> 05:24:45.394
to clean and green energy for our
political and economic security today,

2935915972
05:24:45.395 --> 05:24:49.340
but for the tomorrows of all of
the generations yet to come.

3032156788
05:24:49.341 --> 05:24:50.443
Madam Deputy Speaker.

4109672090
05:24:50.444 --> 05:24:52.700
When it comes to embracing
green technology,

3578106242
05:24:52.701 --> 05:24:54.908
the public is already
voting with its feet.

2616638069
05:24:54.909 --> 05:24:56.865
The CEO of Octopus Energy has reported

3497486382
05:24:56.866 --> 05:24:59.739
a 50% increase in demand for solar panels

368210521
05:24:59.740 --> 05:25:02.739
and a 30% uplift in demand
for heat pumps within

2957611163
05:25:02.740 --> 05:25:05.538
weeks of the conflict in Iran started.

1243572462
05:25:05.539 --> 05:25:08.441
This is welcome news,
but the transition to green,

2978282570
05:25:08.442 --> 05:25:12.548
clean and home grown
energy is not a challenge

1951690681
05:25:12.549 --> 05:25:14.104
that the market alone can fix.

1480060753
05:25:14.105 --> 05:25:16.742
I'm proud of the record
of our Labour government.

2387487809
05:25:16.743 --> 05:25:20.193
In the last two years, two
renewable energy auctions with

3837785680
05:25:20.194 --> 05:25:25.094
bids for enough power to
power 23 million homes,

3447090375
05:25:25.096 --> 05:25:29.342
ending the de facto ban on
onshore wind and scaling

859956316
05:25:29.343 --> 05:25:31.299
up the Social Housing Warm Homes Fund,

3063703364
05:25:31.300 --> 05:25:33.893
including more than £6
million for Welwyn Hatfield

4199045862
05:25:33.894 --> 05:25:35.698
Borough Council in my constituency,

3235480891
05:25:35.699 --> 05:25:40.443
which will see more than 600 council
homes retrofitted in my community.

1697589921
05:25:41.047 --> 05:25:45.089
But we have to go further and I,
and I hope the Energy Independence

537815220
05:25:45.090 --> 05:25:48.140
Bill can be a focal point
for this government.

1121408571
05:25:48.141 --> 05:25:50.735
Madam Deputy Speaker, we have to innovate.

3793864006
05:25:50.736 --> 05:25:53.997
I was with the Chief Secretary to
the Prime Minister in January,

2125324331
05:25:53.998 --> 05:25:56.290
when he made an excellent speech on how

1663926942
05:25:56.291 --> 05:25:58.098
to speed up the delivery of policy,

2949653978
05:25:58.099 --> 05:26:01.057
something that so many colleagues
have talked about today.

2497768493
05:26:01.058 --> 05:26:03.665
He talked about learning
the lessons of the vaccine

3613691988
05:26:03.666 --> 05:26:06.224
task force model and applying
it more universally.

939982005
05:26:06.225 --> 05:26:09.736
And I would encourage colleagues in
the Department for Energy and Net

3733041165
05:26:09.737 --> 05:26:13.249
Zero and the Cabinet Office to work
together with this model in mind,

4213370002
05:26:13.250 --> 05:26:16.689
particularly with a view to speeding up

814191936
05:26:16.690 --> 05:26:18.846
the all important connections to our grid.

549867467
05:26:18.847 --> 05:26:22.889
We have to work Madam Deputy
Speaker with the private sector.

1193087127
05:26:22.890 --> 05:26:26.350
I'm very proud that Ocado has its
national headquarters in Hatfield,

3504173658
05:26:26.351 --> 05:26:29.562
and they've been in touch with
me about their ambition to speed

1995018947
05:26:29.563 --> 05:26:31.819
up their grid connections
and the importance

2165746772
05:26:31.820 --> 05:26:33.474
of an EV charging infrastructure

3885866098
05:26:33.475 --> 05:26:36.132
that allows them to transition
to electric vehicles.

4051012172
05:26:36.133 --> 05:26:39.744
And I'm also very pleased that
Mitsubishi Europe, working in Hatfield,

197070778
05:26:39.745 --> 05:26:42.352
is training gas engineers
to transfer from boilers,

1603995611
05:26:42.353 --> 05:26:44.360
and so that their skills can be applied

3097508445
05:26:44.361 --> 05:26:46.950
to working on heat pumps in the future.

681389382
05:26:46.951 --> 05:26:49.761
But most importantly of all,
we have to make clear that

3661343882
05:26:49.762 --> 05:26:53.541
the green transition will work
for everyone in our society.

2919623239
05:26:53.543 --> 05:26:56.002
And the Social Housing
Warm Homes Fund is one of

3462811894
05:26:56.003 --> 05:26:58.309
the single most important
parts of this plan.

461215574
05:26:59.096 --> 05:27:01.553
Retrofitting the homes of
people on low incomes,

4094833816
05:27:01.554 --> 05:27:05.497
demonstrating beyond doubt that this
is not some kind of elite project.

3241915513
05:27:05.498 --> 05:27:08.660
As members on the other side of
this House want us to believe,

47464037
05:27:08.661 --> 05:27:10.666
it's a project that will ultimately get

449740207
05:27:10.668 --> 05:27:13.299
bills down for people who need it most.

2391994859
05:27:13.300 --> 05:27:16.208
Madam Deputy Speaker if
the Conservatives and Reform wish

774433562
05:27:16.209 --> 05:27:18.940
to cling to the fossil fuels
and the global markets,

3140047061
05:27:18.941 --> 05:27:22.249
it's their job to explain
the cost to their constituents.

2679001719
05:27:22.250 --> 05:27:25.350
But clean, green and cheap
energy is the future.

894109582
05:27:25.351 --> 05:27:27.707
And this, this Labour
government is absolutely

2792468242
05:27:27.708 --> 05:27:32.094
right to be striving for
energy independence.

2469220167
05:27:32.096 --> 05:27:34.290
>> From after the next speaker,

1263123915
05:27:34.291 --> 05:27:37.940
the time limit will be
reduced to four minutes.

1043912525
05:27:37.941 --> 05:27:41.746
>> Harriet Cross thank you very
much, Madam Deputy Speaker.

1674179070
05:27:41.747 --> 05:27:44.658
And too often we see when we
debate energy in this place,

2055923576
05:27:44.659 --> 05:27:46.545
it becomes tribal very quickly.

2808532432
05:27:46.546 --> 05:27:49.395
You're either oil and gas
or you're renewables.

3099893309
05:27:49.396 --> 05:27:50.800
There's no room for nuance.

2157170190
05:27:52.088 --> 05:27:53.090
We need renewables.

1273946371
05:27:53.091 --> 05:27:56.246
We need nuclear, but we
also need oil and gas.

2154884416
05:27:56.247 --> 05:27:59.496
And many members today have
spoken about the cost.

4187579266
05:27:59.497 --> 05:28:03.204
The cost is one element,
but supply is vital,

2412505080
05:28:03.205 --> 05:28:06.805
vitally important because
oil and gas makes up three

3224598578
05:28:06.806 --> 05:28:09.045
quarters of the energy we need every day.

1659394155
05:28:09.046 --> 05:28:13.056
The energy we need in the 24 million
homes who still rely on gas,

1716161332
05:28:13.057 --> 05:28:15.165
the energy we need in over half a million

1120021979
05:28:15.165 --> 05:28:16.871
businesses that need oil and gas,

3328032102
05:28:16.872 --> 05:28:18.929
the oil and gas that goes into different

3973041879
05:28:18.930 --> 05:28:20.733
industries such as pharmaceuticals,

1300404774
05:28:22.092 --> 05:28:24.449
petrochemicals, all of
these need oil and gas.

3074412536
05:28:24.450 --> 05:28:27.992
So this energy independence
bill assumes that

1178502083
05:28:27.993 --> 05:28:30.695
just by calling it energy independence,

257270588
05:28:30.696 --> 05:28:35.947
we suddenly do not become
dependent on oil and gas.

2711252360
05:28:35.948 --> 05:28:40.502
That is not true, and it will not
be true so far into the future,

464145593
05:28:40.503 --> 05:28:43.701
because we have not developed
the systems to move us away

2052847316
05:28:43.703 --> 05:28:46.844
from needing oil and gas
as quickly as we need to.

307766659
05:28:46.846 --> 05:28:51.194
So if we look at our nearest
neighbours in Norway.

1293751333
05:28:51.195 --> 05:28:55.044
Norway, who many people rightly think have

3615920844
05:28:55.045 --> 05:28:57.642
their energy system done correctly,

1248531563
05:28:57.643 --> 05:29:02.545
there are five flights a day from
Aberdeen to Norway, bringing workers,

50581836
05:29:02.546 --> 05:29:06.199
skilled workers from the oil and gas.

2156808400
05:29:06.200 --> 05:29:09.712
What was capital of Europe to Norway
to work in their industry there.

4253378515
05:29:09.713 --> 05:29:11.166
Norway, which has just said,

2495587463
05:29:11.168 --> 05:29:14.353
is going to open up three
more existing gas fields.

2137094883
05:29:14.354 --> 05:29:18.550
Norway, which has just announced
a licensing round for 17 new licences,

2628309033
05:29:21.048 --> 05:29:23.654
who incentivise drilling
because they recognise how

935042881
05:29:25.094 --> 05:29:27.652
important oil and gas is
to their energy security.

2430705865
05:29:27.653 --> 05:29:29.911
So if any member opposite
would like to tell

1079578669
05:29:29.912 --> 05:29:32.998
me that the Labour government in Norway,

3352867554
05:29:32.999 --> 05:29:36.646
by increasing their use of
oil and gas and exploiting

2509590089
05:29:36.647 --> 05:29:38.454
their oil and gas in the North Sea,

3949921808
05:29:38.455 --> 05:29:42.805
if that Norwegian Labour
government is making Norway

1385959685
05:29:42.806 --> 05:29:47.098
less energy independent by
using their oil and gas.

527867818
05:29:47.099 --> 05:29:49.094
No, of course they're not.

3088106074
05:29:49.096 --> 05:29:50.249
Of course they're not.

4274498801
05:29:50.250 --> 05:29:53.293
It's this Labour government,
the UK Labour government

1933223656
05:29:53.294 --> 05:29:55.596
who are making the UK more dependent,

2308073317
05:29:55.597 --> 05:29:58.097
more dependent on Norway for our gas.

1976457954
05:29:58.098 --> 05:30:00.493
Who'll be send £20 billion to pay for

479938505
05:30:00.494 --> 05:30:03.393
the privilege for the privilege of using

2078931723
05:30:03.394 --> 05:30:05.703
the same gas that is
from the same North Sea,

2607947734
05:30:08.092 --> 05:30:09.947
more dependent on Qatar, on America,

474379767
05:30:09.948 --> 05:30:12.406
on Mexico, where we will use our LNG,

2772975406
05:30:12.407 --> 05:30:15.989
which if we're taking
the climate argument,

2463144666
05:30:15.990 --> 05:30:19.594
we will liquefy transport
and regasified before using here.

4017996089
05:30:19.596 --> 05:30:23.140
So it is less good for the environment.

682598047
05:30:23.141 --> 05:30:24.597
And then we come on to jobs.

1392217766
05:30:24.598 --> 05:30:29.847
And I still can't understand,
and I will never understand why

3307422034
05:30:29.848 --> 05:30:33.843
anyone can sit on the Labour
benches and not understand

308651915
05:30:33.844 --> 05:30:37.699
the importance of protecting
jobs in the oil and gas sector,

3582784741
05:30:37.700 --> 05:30:39.755
and they mention new jobs in renewables.

1409851097
05:30:39.757 --> 05:30:42.315
And I understand there are
new jobs in renewables,

1216059812
05:30:42.316 --> 05:30:44.674
but they are not coming
on stream fast enough.

3163086150
05:30:44.675 --> 05:30:47.949
They are not comparable and they're
not for the same skill sets.

3512971804
05:30:47.950 --> 05:30:50.949
And yes, some are transferable,
but loads are not.

4137579547
05:30:50.950 --> 05:30:54.398
And the highly skilled people
who really have secured

3342567433
05:30:54.400 --> 05:30:57.199
our energy security for
the last few decades,

2479390009
05:30:57.200 --> 05:31:00.461
those are the ones who are really
going to struggle to transfer.

1215422655
05:31:00.462 --> 05:31:03.924
And if Labour want to say that they're
happy to sacrifice those jobs

2598316442
05:31:03.925 --> 05:31:07.285
and those livelihoods and
the communities that those jobs live in,

3477395512
05:31:07.286 --> 05:31:09.492
particularly in
the north east of Scotland,

2613200166
05:31:09.493 --> 05:31:12.503
they can do so because that is
the message they're sending.

1533776070
05:31:12.504 --> 05:31:14.710
And those skilled workers
are moving abroad

1991369753
05:31:14.711 --> 05:31:16.497
and taking with them the skills

3234828219
05:31:16.498 --> 05:31:22.791
that will help us with our energy
security and our energy independence.

3241490880
05:31:22.793 --> 05:31:24.248
They talk about price a lot,

3119403578
05:31:24.249 --> 05:31:28.083
and we understand that the price
of oil and gas goes up and down.

1784353577
05:31:28.084 --> 05:31:29.235
That's understandable.

3471682841
05:31:29.236 --> 05:31:33.501
R7 signed us up to higher
prices for 20 years.

4034566333
05:31:33.502 --> 05:31:37.051
For 20 years, we have committed
to paying those high prices,

398350869
05:31:37.052 --> 05:31:38.758
and they are higher than what oil

4200870344
05:31:38.759 --> 05:31:40.817
and gas has been for the last few years.

946533620
05:31:40.818 --> 05:31:43.126
I appreciate I don't
need I don't need Wales,

3620814886
05:31:43.127 --> 05:31:45.536
I appreciate oil and gas
is high at the moment,

937956289
05:31:45.537 --> 05:31:46.892
but it is not always high.

807713111
05:31:46.893 --> 05:31:47.746
It has been low.

1820612054
05:31:47.747 --> 05:31:47.947
It.

1537696369
05:31:47.948 --> 05:31:49.803
The Ministers says that's the issue.

1002816917
05:31:49.804 --> 05:31:50.794
It is the issue.

2966942098
05:31:50.795 --> 05:31:52.451
If you look at one part of time,

1181285525
05:31:53.097 --> 05:31:55.204
one time horizon over the last few years,

2697128602
05:31:55.205 --> 05:31:56.999
has oil and gas been low?

892190036
05:31:57.000 --> 05:32:00.300
The gas price has been low,
the oil price has been low,

3073633310
05:32:00.301 --> 05:32:01.556
and yet we still use it.

4256110037
05:32:01.557 --> 05:32:05.512
So we are sacrificing jobs in Aberdeen,
in the north east of Scotland.

3949564008
05:32:05.513 --> 05:32:08.646
We're sacrificing our energy
security just to deliver green

845251172
05:32:08.647 --> 05:32:11.755
energy because that's all this
government want to focus on.

4173282727
05:32:12.055 --> 05:32:15.214
This government should be looking
at our neighbours in Norway,

1904242122
05:32:15.215 --> 05:32:16.568
seeing what they're doing,

2010694680
05:32:16.569 --> 05:32:18.877
seeing how they are seen
as the true country,

3391359749
05:32:18.878 --> 05:32:21.097
which is energy independent,

4245320798
05:32:21.098 --> 05:32:24.350
and seeing that they are still
using their oil and gas,

1341714502
05:32:24.351 --> 05:32:27.301
still using it because
they know they need it,

1385805893
05:32:27.302 --> 05:32:32.704
because their energy systems, their
country is not set up not to use it.

4012283106
05:32:32.705 --> 05:32:33.608
UK is not either.

1048289517
05:32:33.609 --> 05:32:36.320
We need it, we must use it,
and we should be drilling

488657408
05:32:36.321 --> 05:32:39.098
all we can from the North
Sea starting today.

1849890506
05:32:39.099 --> 05:32:40.201
>> Alison Hume thank.

2894925666
05:32:40.203 --> 05:32:41.655
>> You, Madam.

3808177788
05:32:41.656 --> 05:32:42.457
Deputy Speaker.

1372233818
05:32:42.458 --> 05:32:45.601
I welcome the announcement
of a new energy.

533965867
05:32:45.602 --> 05:32:46.655
>> Security Bill in.

1534770593
05:32:47.093 --> 05:32:48.547
>> The King's Speech, which.

1134430361
05:32:48.548 --> 05:32:52.800
Will meet our manifesto
commitment not to issue

3176103122
05:32:52.801 --> 05:32:55.104
licences to explore new
oil and gas fields.

3172645072
05:32:55.105 --> 05:33:01.248
Crucially, it will also deliver on
our commitment to ban fracking,

848431984
05:33:01.249 --> 05:33:03.348
fracking, or hydraulic fracturing,

113662166
05:33:03.349 --> 05:33:08.099
involves injecting fluid
at high pressure to

935448748
05:33:08.100 --> 05:33:10.800
fracture rock and extract hydrocarbons.

1607441301
05:33:10.801 --> 05:33:12.707
And in 2019, a moratorium on fracking

1841618402
05:33:14.054 --> 05:33:15.907
was introduced following earthquakes

164146103
05:33:15.908 --> 05:33:20.753
linked to fracking activity at
Preston New Road in Lancashire.

2520657045
05:33:23.097 --> 05:33:27.548
Currently, UK legislation
defines fracking based on fluid

2725182207
05:33:27.549 --> 05:33:33.201
volume thresholds 1000m³ per
stage, or 10,000m³ in total.

3151204747
05:33:33.201 --> 05:33:36.094
Madam Deputy Speaker, this leaves a legal

1268758527
05:33:36.096 --> 05:33:39.747
loophole for oil and gas companies to

330691190
05:33:39.748 --> 05:33:42.862
exploit in beautiful
burnaston in my constituency

2334138105
05:33:42.864 --> 05:33:44.217
of Scarborough and Whitby,

4199707201
05:33:44.218 --> 05:33:48.659
Europa Oil and Gas has
proposed extracting gas

2573979265
05:33:48.660 --> 05:33:52.850
using a technique called prop and squeeze,

3961352378
05:33:52.851 --> 05:33:57.101
which is hydraulic fracturing
just at lower fluid volumes.

2260829430
05:33:57.102 --> 05:34:03.647
This means it exists outside
the fracking moratorium in Burnaston,

2669550427
05:34:03.647 --> 05:34:06.847
on the edge of the North
York Moors National Park,

4149354814
05:34:06.848 --> 05:34:08.854
villagers have been involved in a David

3052459345
05:34:11.055 --> 05:34:13.262
and Goliath battle with
Europa oil and gas.

3128692391
05:34:13.263 --> 05:34:16.020
I'm delighted to say that
North Yorkshire councillors,

724709781
05:34:16.055 --> 05:34:18.410
throughout the recommendations
of its officers

1655935831
05:34:20.105 --> 05:34:22.510
and formally rejected
the planning application,

289058845
05:34:24.098 --> 05:34:28.696
but to create indisputable clarity
over fracking legislation

1288067077
05:34:28.697 --> 05:34:30.703
in our country and close this loophole.

208618700
05:34:32.098 --> 05:34:34.656
Any future ban must include
all forms of fracking.

3831103928
05:34:36.097 --> 05:34:38.451
Currently, 66 existing
licences remain active.

998528377
05:34:39.102 --> 05:34:43.807
Planning applications can still
proceed under current rules.

1454520072
05:34:43.808 --> 05:34:46.797
If our definition of fracking
remains volume based,

3901538588
05:34:46.798 --> 05:34:52.008
then we risk companies continuing to
frack just under a different name.

2545275246
05:34:52.009 --> 05:34:56.854
Make no mistake, the frackers
haven't given up following North

831370598
05:34:57.100 --> 05:35:00.600
Yorkshire Council's rejection
of Europa's proposal,

3796420167
05:35:00.601 --> 05:35:02.606
Europa stated they felt confident about

3760953275
05:35:04.101 --> 05:35:06.106
winning an appeal against the decision.

58965367
05:35:06.107 --> 05:35:08.656
The evidence is there
for the government to

3132907835
05:35:08.657 --> 05:35:11.148
include small scale fracking in our ban.

1436798883
05:35:11.150 --> 05:35:13.456
A recent report published
from the University

3425793490
05:35:13.457 --> 05:35:16.209
of Edinburgh found that
earthquakes from high

1815357460
05:35:16.210 --> 05:35:18.751
volume fracking and low
volume fracking are

4043333992
05:35:18.752 --> 05:35:20.806
equally large and equally unpredictable.

1414282497
05:35:22.101 --> 05:35:26.101
This means that the risk of seismicity,
such as earthquakes induced

320206623
05:35:26.102 --> 05:35:31.010
or triggered from proppant squeezes,
cannot simply be ruled out.

1223370585
05:35:31.011 --> 05:35:33.768
This evidence echoes findings
commissioned by the then

3342344603
05:35:33.769 --> 05:35:37.253
Oil and Gas Authority in
two Preston New Road,

2453873110
05:35:37.254 --> 05:35:40.255
which also showed that
seismic impacts cannot be

3253868188
05:35:42.104 --> 05:35:44.558
accurately predicted
regardless of fluid volume.

3649093234
05:35:44.559 --> 05:35:46.851
I urge the government to use the upcoming

1890819596
05:35:46.852 --> 05:35:48.902
Energy Security Bill to replace

580959208
05:35:48.903 --> 05:35:53.751
the volume based definition with
one based on intent and process,

2172932054
05:35:53.752 --> 05:35:59.801
and introduce a blanket prohibition
on fracturing rock for hydrocarbons.

1731027480
05:35:59.802 --> 05:36:03.851
All forms of fracking
contribute to greenhouse gas

1027743905
05:36:03.852 --> 05:36:06.750
emissions and undermine
our net zero commitments,

711804394
05:36:06.751 --> 05:36:10.803
and therefore all forms of
fracking need to be banned.

2455606088
05:36:10.804 --> 05:36:12.658
Madam Deputy Speaker, last December,

1659753499
05:36:13.057 --> 05:36:15.465
I held a Westminster Hall
debate on this issue,

3673153082
05:36:16.102 --> 05:36:17.555
and the Ministers responded,

2694864187
05:36:17.556 --> 05:36:20.298
confirming that
the government remains open

239774694
05:36:20.299 --> 05:36:24.051
to evidence regarding a comprehensive ban.

2164143796
05:36:24.052 --> 05:36:25.708
To conclude, I would ask my hon.

149101371
05:36:27.100 --> 05:36:29.255
Friend to confirm what further evidence he

3761026935
05:36:30.106 --> 05:36:32.011
requires to ban small scale fracking,

3440370596
05:36:32.012 --> 05:36:37.754
unless, of course, it's
earthquakes in Scarborough.

536640600
05:36:37.755 --> 05:36:38.507
>> Ann Davies.

1631596231
05:36:41.055 --> 05:36:41.405
Madam.

807232418
05:36:41.406 --> 05:36:43.764
>> Energy has become one
of the most important

4165709551
05:36:43.765 --> 05:36:46.022
issues in Caerfyrddin
and the rest of Wales.

3397478006
05:36:47.100 --> 05:36:50.058
In recent years, global events
have exposed how vulnerable

1198048945
05:36:50.058 --> 05:36:54.102
our communities are to
energy shocks and Russia's

671432742
05:36:54.103 --> 05:37:00.556
invasion of Ukraine in 2022
cost the Welsh economy 6.5.6

313999001
05:37:00.557 --> 05:37:03.404
5 billion, averaging over
£2,000 per home in Wales.

634872655
05:37:03.405 --> 05:37:06.705
That's the impact of
the war in Iran intensifies.

623434890
05:37:06.706 --> 05:37:11.408
Welsh households are being hit
once again and rural households

3515370897
05:37:11.409 --> 05:37:15.450
are paying hundreds more in
fuel and heating oil costs,

930243812
05:37:15.451 --> 05:37:20.455
and the average on grid household
energy bill could rise by nearly £300.

2842483555
05:37:20.456 --> 05:37:24.104
When the energy cap is revised in July.

2472914188
05:37:24.105 --> 05:37:28.010
Off grid customers have seen
their oil and gas bills at least

610857255
05:37:28.011 --> 05:37:32.309
double over the past few months,
while the measures in the.

3061956437
05:37:32.311 --> 05:37:33.647
By all means.

239636372
05:37:33.647 --> 05:37:34.350
>> Thank you.

446093691
05:37:34.351 --> 05:37:35.204
I thank the hon.

1502689388
05:37:35.205 --> 05:37:37.906
Member for giving way.

1379031634
05:37:37.907 --> 05:37:40.869
I just wanted to point out to
her that it would be really,

2988243539
05:37:40.870 --> 05:37:44.508
really helpful if the new Welsh
Government could release the £3.8

1176754999
05:37:45.100 --> 05:37:49.103
million of funding that the UK
government has given to Welsh Government

3015383032
05:37:49.104 --> 05:37:51.912
to help people struggling
with their heating oil costs,

3055983789
05:37:51.913 --> 05:37:55.406
and I'm wondering when that's
actually going to be distributed.

2246616892
05:37:55.407 --> 05:37:56.905
>> I thank my hon.

3470036124
05:37:56.906 --> 05:37:58.159
Member for her question.

1546951254
05:37:58.160 --> 05:38:01.021
Can I assure her that I'm sure
that it will be released,

1737013955
05:38:01.022 --> 05:38:03.931
but shouldn't it have been
released by the previous Welsh

432175288
05:38:03.932 --> 05:38:07.696
Government when that money
was put in a few months ago?

564302940
05:38:07.697 --> 05:38:10.505
With all due respect, whilst
the measures in The King's

1904341924
05:38:10.507 --> 05:38:13.111
Speech sets out two steps
to reduce energy costs,

1490278663
05:38:13.112 --> 05:38:18.460
they do not get to grips with
the fundamental unfairness of our system.

2989394999
05:38:19.096 --> 05:38:23.057
People in Wales pay some of
the highest standing charges in the UK,

3403813823
05:38:23.058 --> 05:38:27.458
despite average salaries being
lower than the UK average.

2461542742
05:38:27.459 --> 05:38:31.409
This is unsustainable
and action needs to be taken.

3182748116
05:38:31.410 --> 05:38:34.103
Despite being an energy rich nation,

1531818973
05:38:34.104 --> 05:38:38.555
Wales is unable to make the most
of our abundant natural wealth.

1157106184
05:38:38.556 --> 05:38:41.802
This is simply due to
the lack of control over them.

3849606572
05:38:41.803 --> 05:38:46.411
Plight Chris Murray is clear
it is for the people of Wales

948907413
05:38:47.104 --> 05:38:49.661
to control and benefit from
our natural resources.

385402516
05:38:53.104 --> 05:38:55.159
This extractive economy model must cease

821736985
05:38:55.160 --> 05:38:56.865
and money generated from our wind

3909862410
05:38:56.866 --> 05:39:01.205
and sea power should be kept
and shared within local communities.

2079092007
05:39:01.206 --> 05:39:05.500
The Crown Estate must be devolved
to Wales as it is already

3284043634
05:39:05.501 --> 05:39:07.857
in Scotland and following
the Senedd election,

4088777696
05:39:09.100 --> 05:39:11.457
a majority of parties in
the Welsh Parliament,

3456137474
05:39:12.059 --> 05:39:14.515
including the plaid
Canterbury Welsh Government,

879041620
05:39:14.516 --> 05:39:16.307
are calling for devolution,

2408662851
05:39:16.308 --> 05:39:20.507
devolution of the Crown Estate,

3201957473
05:39:20.508 --> 05:39:25.605
as well as every single
local authority in Wales.

2679356434
05:39:25.606 --> 05:39:28.696
The case and democratic
mandate are inarguable.

504150917
05:39:28.697 --> 05:39:33.708
We have immense natural resources,
including wind and tidal power,

771991469
05:39:33.709 --> 05:39:35.604
which are not being fully utilised,

1308204309
05:39:35.605 --> 05:39:40.655
and electricity generation
in Wales has fallen

3153143845
05:39:40.656 --> 05:39:42.412
by almost 50% since its 2016 peak,

1604013181
05:39:42.413 --> 05:39:45.712
as growth in renewable capacity
has not kept pace with

3276405033
05:39:45.713 --> 05:39:49.210
the drop in generation
from coal and nuclear.

4041926022
05:39:49.211 --> 05:39:52.058
If we are to strengthen
our energy security,

61026794
05:39:52.059 --> 05:39:54.993
we need to see
the government and developers

3624469013
05:39:54.994 --> 05:39:57.566
working with the needs of communities

969594083
05:39:57.567 --> 05:40:00.851
to deliver investment in renewables.

421795762
05:40:00.852 --> 05:40:04.806
We need to see in
a sustainable and fair way,

1080978596
05:40:04.807 --> 05:40:07.604
with an emphasis on
offshore wind and community

791498311
05:40:07.605 --> 05:40:09.508
led onshore development developments.

1922230911
05:40:11.061 --> 05:40:13.518
And developers need to be
totally transparent in

409769809
05:40:15.100 --> 05:40:17.507
costs and how their
investment is being funded.

4159970453
05:40:17.508 --> 05:40:19.464
The King's Speech does include the new

3475619703
05:40:19.465 --> 05:40:22.754
coal licensing ban, which is welcome.

4144503040
05:40:22.755 --> 05:40:25.578
However, as I've raised
before in Parliament,

81630092
05:40:25.579 --> 05:40:27.755
the proposed ban in its current form

1774700587
05:40:27.755 --> 05:40:30.805
does not guarantee
the prevention of commercial

682808388
05:40:30.806 --> 05:40:32.561
extraction of coal from coal tips.

1937593950
05:40:32.562 --> 05:40:36.106
The government should bring measures
forward to close this loophole

609608760
05:40:36.107 --> 05:40:41.454
so that companies can never
profit from the over 2000,

2866770015
05:40:41.455 --> 05:40:42.860
2500 tips we have in Wales,

582214630
05:40:42.861 --> 05:40:46.802
which contain millions of
tonnes of coal between them.

3004054032
05:40:46.803 --> 05:40:49.354
In addition, Westminster must always must

2316788892
05:40:49.355 --> 05:40:51.160
also provide justice for our valley

926208032
05:40:51.161 --> 05:40:54.908
and coal mining communities
by fully funding

4015254713
05:40:54.909 --> 05:40:56.865
the remediation of coal tips in Wales,

3811249603
05:40:56.866 --> 05:41:01.906
which are the legacy of our
pre-revolution industrial past.

2468204792
05:41:01.907 --> 05:41:05.404
The price tag is estimated at 600 million.

732929445
05:41:05.405 --> 05:41:11.610
However, the UK government has
only committed around 143 million.

1187168781
05:41:11.611 --> 05:41:14.654
We needed a King's speech
that addressed the unfairness

3559956033
05:41:14.655 --> 05:41:16.611
at the heart of Wales's energy system.

3626245692
05:41:16.612 --> 05:41:20.261
For a country so rich in
energy and potential,

360329817
05:41:20.262 --> 05:41:22.106
we need to see so much more

1334785519
05:41:22.107 --> 05:41:25.467
ambition from the UK government for
Wales than what was announced,

1355669987
05:41:25.468 --> 05:41:28.125
and ambition that brings
communities on the journey.

578066994
05:41:28.126 --> 05:41:33.058
An ambition which listens to
the voice of Welsh constituents.

3522730599
05:41:33.105 --> 05:41:35.011
Plaid Cymru will continue to stand up

4135091057
05:41:35.012 --> 05:41:39.160
and demand the fairness
that Wales deserves.

2912184091
05:41:39.161 --> 05:41:40.414
>> John Jonathan Davies.

2676555695
05:41:40.415 --> 05:41:42.873
>> Thank you very much,
Madam >> Deputy Speaker,

1917518948
05:41:42.874 --> 05:41:44.230
and it is a pleasure to be

3373497575
05:41:44.231 --> 05:41:46.437
able to contribute to
this debate following

3571874519
05:41:46.438 --> 05:41:47.991
His Majesty's gracious speech,

2799441173
05:41:47.992 --> 05:41:50.500
because it is an opportunity
to reflect on things

2275057944
05:41:50.501 --> 05:41:53.311
the government has done
and also to look to the future.

2358754151
05:41:53.312 --> 05:41:56.875
And in so many areas, progress is
being made, whether it's in the NHS,

969512547
05:41:56.876 --> 05:42:00.504
and I was very pleased last
week to see the biggest

1181636931
05:42:00.505 --> 05:42:02.662
in month fall in waiting times since 2008,

2501101951
05:42:03.101 --> 05:42:05.308
and action on the cost
of living issues and

2127923213
05:42:05.309 --> 05:42:07.718
the economy and the cost
of living according to

3012113138
05:42:07.719 --> 05:42:10.309
the young people which
contributed to my survey

1898241443
05:42:10.311 --> 05:42:12.367
undertaken towards the end of last year,

548615447
05:42:12.368 --> 05:42:15.478
I identified the cost of living
as being a significant issue,

2261427047
05:42:15.479 --> 05:42:18.655
holding them back and with
measures like freezing rail fares

615044599
05:42:18.656 --> 05:42:23.655
and ensuring the economy can deliver
continued interest rates cuts,

324024476
05:42:23.656 --> 05:42:25.913
that is all extra money
in people's pockets.

1792468514
05:42:25.914 --> 05:42:29.058
But there is a huge amount more to do.

2309861048
05:42:29.059 --> 05:42:33.207
And looking ahead, I'm very
keen to see the government

1388454475
05:42:33.208 --> 05:42:35.966
recognise the value of our
Unesco World Heritage Sites

3490121972
05:42:35.967 --> 05:42:42.191
as the chair of the
an opportunity to offer in terms of

1283774340
05:42:42.192 --> 05:42:44.750
education and the all party
group for that sector,

3094014364
05:42:44.751 --> 05:42:46.957
opportunity to offer
in terms of education,

233641877
05:42:46.958 --> 05:42:50.611
and I'm very keen that the government
looks at VAT for hospitality.

944049363
05:42:51.110 --> 05:42:53.870
It's a sector which is is is
struggling at the moment,

2170150038
05:42:53.871 --> 05:42:55.928
and also we must progress and go further

3492499010
05:42:56.107 --> 05:42:58.263
and faster with our business rates reform.

2093718615
05:42:58.264 --> 05:43:02.765
Turning to energy, I was very
pleased with some of the steps

3617760029
05:43:02.766 --> 05:43:06.507
the government has taken in
the first session of this Parliament,

3572100321
05:43:06.508 --> 05:43:09.065
including to roll out
the community energy scheme.

2548713791
05:43:09.066 --> 05:43:12.525
That's going to make a massive
difference to community institutions,

1028371019
05:43:13.061 --> 05:43:14.263
sports clubs, churches,

794239326
05:43:14.264 --> 05:43:16.571
parish councils, as they
can generate more of

1293001540
05:43:16.572 --> 05:43:18.760
their energy and export that to the grid.

1132385901
05:43:18.761 --> 05:43:22.056
I was also very pleased
with the £600 million worth

3502981885
05:43:22.057 --> 05:43:24.213
of backing for the small modular reactors.

1131147444
05:43:24.214 --> 05:43:26.860
That's excellent news for
people in Derby who have

3286641655
05:43:26.861 --> 05:43:30.007
the skills to progress
that and bring it forward,

3958622937
05:43:30.008 --> 05:43:31.614
but there's so much more to do.

1794886601
05:43:32.110 --> 05:43:35.809
We do have many businesses
which are struggling in

657092326
05:43:35.811 --> 05:43:38.116
my constituency or nearby,
including Denbigh.

3439485311
05:43:38.117 --> 05:43:41.662
It lacks the grid connections
to export the renewables.

2185756156
05:43:41.663 --> 05:43:44.760
It's excess renewables that
it has at the weekend,

676452513
05:43:44.761 --> 05:43:47.305
back into the grid and also the cost for

3548104429
05:43:47.306 --> 05:43:49.262
ceramics of energy is a massive issue.

1590394730
05:43:50.109 --> 05:43:51.412
Holding the economy back.

1535802872
05:43:51.413 --> 05:43:54.610
>> On that point, and I'm grateful.

2321310068
05:43:54.611 --> 05:43:58.305
I'm grateful to my friend
for giving way and

1680051945
05:43:58.306 --> 05:44:00.814
and for for raising
the issue of Denbigh pottery,

2661207998
05:44:01.110 --> 05:44:06.558
which is, of course, in administration,
a business in my constituency.

3691628709
05:44:06.559 --> 05:44:09.461
Would he join me in urging
all of the members in this

2069847065
05:44:09.462 --> 05:44:12.770
House to sign the petition
to save Denbigh pottery?

3512442314
05:44:12.771 --> 05:44:17.019
And would he join me in encouraging
his constituents to do so as well?

46999045
05:44:17.020 --> 05:44:19.930
>> I absolutely would, it's
their jobs and they very much

237288478
05:44:19.931 --> 05:44:22.388
value the products that
are produced at Denbigh.

1031761803
05:44:22.389 --> 05:44:24.949
And I would just ask
the Ministers, if it can't be

1491796498
05:44:24.950 --> 05:44:27.859
the case that ceramics can go
to the supercharger scheme.

634389974
05:44:27.860 --> 05:44:30.969
We need a different package to
particularly help that sector.

2836460017
05:44:30.969 --> 05:44:34.130
It's the war in Iran that has
brought energy into sharp focus.

2293115943
05:44:34.132 --> 05:44:36.188
Again, we've seen shocks to the economy,

675047979
05:44:37.105 --> 05:44:40.504
the risks that people will
be paying much more people,

1077978859
05:44:40.505 --> 05:44:42.459
domestic customers and and businesses.

2506100039
05:44:42.460 --> 05:44:44.612
And that's why we must go further

1292218684
05:44:44.614 --> 05:44:47.213
and faster with our efforts to do more of

4121585076
05:44:47.214 --> 05:44:50.056
our home grown energy through renewables

1601774477
05:44:50.057 --> 05:44:51.761
and also through through nuclear.

1686796300
05:44:52.106 --> 05:44:57.357
But there is another side to this as
well, and that is the environment.

2379898580
05:44:57.358 --> 05:44:59.614
And I'm somewhat
disappointed that it hasn't

2433413565
05:44:59.615 --> 05:45:01.909
featured more prominently in this debate.

2959557509
05:45:01.910 --> 05:45:04.754
Ministers may be aware
of the the government's

867197139
05:45:04.755 --> 05:45:06.458
own National security assessment,

3128185851
05:45:06.459 --> 05:45:11.513
which linked the global ecosystem
degradation and and collapse

1827612642
05:45:11.514 --> 05:45:15.357
which threatens the UK's national
security and prosperity.

2180188188
05:45:15.358 --> 05:45:17.263
So dealing with our carbon emissions,

346796761
05:45:17.264 --> 05:45:19.069
with our impacts on the environment

3678228056
05:45:19.070 --> 05:45:21.981
is not just something that we
need to do for the economy.

2433503878
05:45:21.982 --> 05:45:24.540
It's something that we need
to do to prevent those

2036940881
05:45:24.541 --> 05:45:26.647
drivers of global conflict in the future,

1964286861
05:45:26.648 --> 05:45:29.106
because we know our access
to natural resources,

3024019838
05:45:29.107 --> 05:45:32.670
to water, to the way that we grow our
food, to extreme weather events,

1685097573
05:45:32.671 --> 05:45:34.609
is going to be a driver of conflict.

2902869857
05:45:34.610 --> 05:45:37.021
So yes, we do need to do
more on energy for our

3158749085
05:45:37.022 --> 05:45:39.405
economy and for domestic
customers at home.

1426294435
05:45:39.406 --> 05:45:41.715
But if we don't get
a grip of climate change,

1233595152
05:45:41.716 --> 05:45:43.673
of the threats that it poses to people

2715915365
05:45:43.674 --> 05:45:45.859
in this country and around the world,

174242647
05:45:45.860 --> 05:45:49.014
we will see more conflict
going forward in the future.

1427926410
05:45:49.015 --> 05:45:50.922
And I also believe that if this study

2066035595
05:45:50.923 --> 05:45:52.829
that has been published and it hasn't

4218682249
05:45:52.830 --> 05:45:56.140
had the attention which it has
needed, it's the government's own.

247079161
05:45:56.141 --> 05:45:57.795
It's the government's own study.

4075794045
05:45:57.796 --> 05:46:00.306
I believe it would have
had an impact on the SDR,

4235862792
05:46:00.307 --> 05:46:03.817
which does talk about climate change,
particularly in the high north.

3788720341
05:46:03.818 --> 05:46:07.281
But this is an issue that we're only
beginning to get to grips with.

2864321292
05:46:07.282 --> 05:46:09.339
So if the Ministers could take that away

754391490
05:46:09.340 --> 05:46:11.045
and raise it with his colleagues,

2612892432
05:46:11.046 --> 05:46:12.701
I would be most grateful indeed.

4042315797
05:46:12.701 --> 05:46:17.212
So as we look forward,
just some some reflections

2072400143
05:46:17.213 --> 05:46:19.018
of the first session of Parliament,

1447156318
05:46:19.213 --> 05:46:21.771
we have made significant
progress in this in terms

418879194
05:46:21.772 --> 05:46:24.028
of improving people's
lives in this country,

3799210581
05:46:24.104 --> 05:46:26.866
but it is clear that there
is a great deal more to do,

4282510132
05:46:26.867 --> 05:46:31.469
and people are not feeling the change
which we promised so profoundly.

1689476917
05:46:31.469 --> 05:46:34.711
But so often it would
seem to me that our frame

3071885954
05:46:34.712 --> 05:46:37.107
of reference for the challenges that

3863436273
05:46:37.108 --> 05:46:39.509
we face is the moment that we are in,

2016266711
05:46:39.510 --> 05:46:41.818
and not the long term
future of this country.

1142402929
05:46:41.819 --> 05:46:45.432
And that is why so many of the measures
that the government is bringing

4284056903
05:46:45.433 --> 05:46:48.340
forward through driving energy
security are so important.

827466757
05:46:48.341 --> 05:46:51.602
They will take time to deliver,
but they will make a difference.

4227624852
05:46:51.603 --> 05:46:53.759
Thank you very much, Madam Deputy Speaker.

2355324483
05:46:53.760 --> 05:46:54.960
>> Katie Lam thank.

134625824
05:46:54.961 --> 05:46:55.362
>> You.

2758532080
05:46:55.362 --> 05:46:58.925
>> Madam Deputy Speaker, time
and time again over the past few months,

1377972196
05:46:58.926 --> 05:47:00.330
and indeed, in this debate,

2097781987
05:47:00.331 --> 05:47:02.086
we have heard Ministers talk about

98273698
05:47:02.087 --> 05:47:04.040
the importance of energy independence,

1792273579
05:47:04.041 --> 05:47:05.498
and they are right to do so.

1622855360
05:47:05.499 --> 05:47:08.758
No country has ever succeeded
without cheap and abundant energy.

464168917
05:47:09.108 --> 05:47:12.967
For energy to be cheap and abundant,
its supply must be reliable.

3037373012
05:47:12.968 --> 05:47:16.260
If we are dependent on energy
imports from overseas,

1147584131
05:47:16.261 --> 05:47:19.463
the supply of energy will
necessarily be unreliable,

1452083011
05:47:19.464 --> 05:47:22.200
as the disruption caused
by recent events in

2261357721
05:47:22.201 --> 05:47:27.010
the Persian Gulf has
made abundantly clear.

3967770822
05:47:27.011 --> 05:47:30.120
But it is profoundly dishonest
to talk of energy independence

3218878707
05:47:30.121 --> 05:47:34.414
while making us more dependent
on energy imports from abroad.

2091954087
05:47:34.415 --> 05:47:37.267
And that's exactly what
the government's plans

4072965721
05:47:37.268 --> 05:47:40.915
to ban new North Sea oil and gas would do.

1920436254
05:47:40.916 --> 05:47:43.914
They should, at the very least,

542385138
05:47:43.915 --> 05:47:46.509
be brave enough to admit
that to the public.

253345558
05:47:46.510 --> 05:47:50.072
Ministers say there's no point in
using our vast oil and gas reserves.

3685760131
05:47:50.073 --> 05:47:52.330
They say that energy
prices are set entirely

520132489
05:47:52.331 --> 05:47:53.784
on the international market,

3338635809
05:47:53.785 --> 05:47:56.492
which means that increasing
our domestic supply would

3142876143
05:47:56.493 --> 05:48:00.509
have little to no impact
on the overall prices.

3133831638
05:48:00.510 --> 05:48:01.563
But this isn't true.

3304580046
05:48:01.564 --> 05:48:03.971
Gas, for example, is
a highly localised market,

1242532343
05:48:03.972 --> 05:48:06.665
specifically in the case
of liquefied natural gas.

694907648
05:48:06.666 --> 05:48:09.366
This is gas, which has
turned into a liquid

3406504935
05:48:09.367 --> 05:48:12.166
loaded onto ships
and transported globally.

3261337245
05:48:12.168 --> 05:48:14.174
The further those ships have to travel,

3160083634
05:48:14.175 --> 05:48:16.562
the more expensive it becomes to deliver.

3387953681
05:48:16.563 --> 05:48:19.425
So if we rely on gas imports
from the rest of the world,

2025290115
05:48:19.426 --> 05:48:22.487
we'll need to spend more money
to bring that gas to Britain.

1833302935
05:48:22.487 --> 05:48:27.170
The vast majority of homes in
the UK 87% use gas for heating.

133889259
05:48:27.171 --> 05:48:31.368
We currently import half
of the gas we consume.

2945603454
05:48:31.369 --> 05:48:34.831
If we produce more gas domestically,
it would be cheaper to buy gas,

172952258
05:48:34.832 --> 05:48:39.230
meaning heating bills would
in fact come down happily.

1379644918
05:48:39.231 --> 05:48:41.617
>> Polly Billington thank you very much,

285144825
05:48:41.618 --> 05:48:43.424
Madam Speaker, and I thank the hon.

2460773089
05:48:44.108 --> 05:48:45.161
Lady for giving way.

1551231894
05:48:45.162 --> 05:48:47.960
I know that the opposite
the member the party

412084452
05:48:47.961 --> 05:48:50.558
in opposition isn't very keen on experts,

3124101265
05:48:50.558 --> 05:48:53.068
but I would just simply
refer her to Fatih Birol,

3685182486
05:48:53.069 --> 05:48:55.508
the head of the International
Energy Agency,

1115884405
05:48:55.509 --> 05:48:58.418
who was pointed out that
expansion of production of North

80071261
05:48:58.419 --> 05:49:01.259
Sea oil and gas does not
significantly improve.

565572668
05:49:01.260 --> 05:49:04.872
UK's energy security, will not alter
the UK's status as a net importer,

2704264329
05:49:04.873 --> 05:49:07.683
and that it will take too
long to affect global prices.

2485562877
05:49:07.683 --> 05:49:09.813
Global demand for fossil fuels, he says,

2888237387
05:49:09.814 --> 05:49:12.368
has changed permanently and therefore

1628158019
05:49:12.369 --> 05:49:14.272
we should be prioritising renewables,

3016039691
05:49:14.273 --> 05:49:17.782
nuclear power and electrification
over further fossil fuel expansion.

1816357363
05:49:17.783 --> 05:49:21.466
>> Katie Lam thank you, Madam
Deputy Speaker and I thank the hon.

485950542
05:49:22.108 --> 05:49:23.461
Lady for her intervention.

1382175951
05:49:23.462 --> 05:49:26.512
As I just said, 80% of
houses use gas for heating.

1963973504
05:49:26.513 --> 05:49:33.711
We cannot simply substitute
that for renewables.

2216115938
05:49:33.712 --> 05:49:34.614
It is impossible.

2760729144
05:49:34.615 --> 05:49:38.027
And it >> Would also to return to
the issue of energy independence,

3047458197
05:49:38.028 --> 05:49:40.084
make us more resistant to global shocks.

3126103249
05:49:40.085 --> 05:49:42.342
If we were to produce
more gas domestically,

2528622382
05:49:42.343 --> 05:49:43.897
we would be far better served.

925496758
05:49:43.898 --> 05:49:46.406
If companies which provide
energy in Britain were

2143025888
05:49:46.407 --> 05:49:48.463
bidding on gas produced in this country,

4290042252
05:49:48.464 --> 05:49:51.021
rather than gas produced
halfway around the world,

353763773
05:49:51.022 --> 05:49:54.585
not only would bills come down,
but we would also mitigate the risk of

3425825071
05:49:54.586 --> 05:49:57.995
sudden cost increases as a result
of supply restrictions elsewhere.

2998132939
05:49:57.996 --> 05:50:00.353
Yet the government is
proposing a policy which

2383053966
05:50:00.354 --> 05:50:02.158
would achieve exactly the opposite.

2195976712
05:50:02.159 --> 05:50:04.066
The demand for gas is not going away,

772448883
05:50:04.067 --> 05:50:06.475
much as the government
might wish that it were.

124097754
05:50:06.476 --> 05:50:09.638
And even if British homes move
away from gas in the long term,

108536648
05:50:09.639 --> 05:50:11.847
it is absurd to impose
higher bills on them

3916530180
05:50:11.848 --> 05:50:14.056
in the short term, in
the name of ideology.

2198067334
05:50:14.057 --> 05:50:17.165
Those on the government benches
often talk of sustainability,

2096465551
05:50:17.165 --> 05:50:19.923
but there is nothing sustainable
about this situation.

1146271974
05:50:19.924 --> 05:50:21.879
Families across the country are facing

1625911036
05:50:21.880 --> 05:50:23.736
higher bills and extra taxes to fund

2732399498
05:50:23.737 --> 05:50:27.394
this government's ideological commitment
to intermittent energy sources.

3014651715
05:50:27.395 --> 05:50:29.753
Many will be forced to
do things like postpone

911355699
05:50:29.754 --> 05:50:31.459
holidays or delay moving house to

73163688
05:50:31.460 --> 05:50:33.415
be able to afford the increasing costs

1654028292
05:50:33.416 --> 05:50:35.322
imposed upon them by this government.

3872656673
05:50:35.323 --> 05:50:37.428
Meanwhile, businesses are being forced to

1965079918
05:50:37.429 --> 05:50:39.336
cut back on staff or shut their doors

761784053
05:50:39.337 --> 05:50:42.848
altogether because the cost of doing
business is now simply too high.

1090057250
05:50:42.849 --> 05:50:45.255
That's local pubs, family
farms, nursing homes,

1880982408
05:50:45.255 --> 05:50:46.661
all forced to shut up shop.

2896595035
05:50:46.662 --> 05:50:48.916
And for industrial
businesses in particular,

1279159890
05:50:49.108 --> 05:50:50.562
the situation is even worse.

3194861090
05:50:50.563 --> 05:50:52.619
These are the businesses in sectors like

3468460983
05:50:52.620 --> 05:50:54.374
AI and high skilled manufacturing,

2938063621
05:50:54.375 --> 05:50:57.536
which can provide some of
the best paid and most durable jobs,

1406556888
05:50:57.537 --> 05:51:00.114
revitalising whole communities
and enabling people

3004351578
05:51:00.115 --> 05:51:02.913
to build successful lives for themselves.

642937166
05:51:02.914 --> 05:51:05.321
Yet while China and India
fuel their industrial

218276218
05:51:05.322 --> 05:51:07.528
expansion with new coal
fired power plants,

3982108927
05:51:07.529 --> 05:51:09.684
British industry faces some of the highest

3234435576
05:51:09.686 --> 05:51:11.591
energy prices in the developed world,

1366578038
05:51:11.592 --> 05:51:15.129
the highest in Europe
and more than double the price

4156292314
05:51:15.130 --> 05:51:17.737
paid by industrial businesses
in the United States.

813051109
05:51:18.112 --> 05:51:20.369
We cannot hope to sustain
an industrial base

239728567
05:51:20.370 --> 05:51:22.176
in this country, let alone grow it.

2788680089
05:51:22.177 --> 05:51:25.237
While the price of energy is
so vulnerable to global shocks.

596351004
05:51:25.237 --> 05:51:28.117
Why would anybody start
a new industrial business

3399773276
05:51:28.118 --> 05:51:30.717
in Britain under these conditions?

111205954
05:51:30.718 --> 05:51:33.579
And if this is being done in
the name of climate change,

4197628068
05:51:33.580 --> 05:51:37.465
it is proving to be
a catastrophic failure.

1867689854
05:51:37.466 --> 05:51:41.028
In the eight years between 2013
and 2020, China pumped out more carbon

2349677410
05:51:41.029 --> 05:51:44.876
emissions than Britain has
produced over the past 250 years.

3700865912
05:51:44.877 --> 05:51:48.566
And that's not just because China
is a bigger country per person.

2357177654
05:51:48.567 --> 05:51:52.373
Emissions from China are more
than double those in Britain.

369162355
05:51:52.374 --> 05:51:55.468
We are sending our emissions
abroad to countries like

873996426
05:51:55.469 --> 05:51:57.926
China without making
a dent in addressing global

3742553249
05:51:57.927 --> 05:52:00.534
climate change and its
British families and British

2459638151
05:52:00.535 --> 05:52:02.793
businesses that are left
to pick up the tab.

2204271119
05:52:03.112 --> 05:52:05.118
Their plans on energy policy will leave

2364628460
05:52:05.119 --> 05:52:07.920
us more dependent on overseas imports,

2617493813
05:52:07.921 --> 05:52:11.130
and will leave the British people
worse off financially without

2010078219
05:52:11.130 --> 05:52:13.888
making any noticeable impact
on global climate change.

369813672
05:52:13.889 --> 05:52:17.397
If the government wants to genuinely
advance our energy independence,

562876322
05:52:17.398 --> 05:52:18.753
then we will welcome that.

2542088858
05:52:18.754 --> 05:52:21.463
But it will not do so by
wrecking domestic production

2076188283
05:52:21.464 --> 05:52:26.512
and leaving us reliant
on imports from abroad.

1969760140
05:52:26.513 --> 05:52:27.616
>> Jessica Toale, UK.

479350898
05:52:27.617 --> 05:52:30.868
>> Last November, the Children's Ministers

3956151124
05:52:30.869 --> 05:52:33.226
and I visited Saint
Joseph's Primary in Poole.

3066812904
05:52:33.227 --> 05:52:36.489
We were there because the school
was one of the first to benefit

4121386839
05:52:36.490 --> 05:52:38.998
from the rollout of solar
panels under GB energy,

192650871
05:52:38.999 --> 05:52:40.957
and we met members of the eco club who

781763493
05:52:40.958 --> 05:52:42.763
excitedly showed us how much energy

1764516227
05:52:42.764 --> 05:52:46.589
the panels were generating and how
much the school was consuming.

2821577736
05:52:46.590 --> 05:52:48.094
We joined a classroom lesson,

3432526278
05:52:48.094 --> 05:52:51.206
jogging on the spot with
the kids to generate CO2 and monitor

3055267328
05:52:51.207 --> 05:52:54.115
the levels so they could
practically learn about heating,

3071703336
05:52:54.116 --> 05:52:55.368
cooling and ventilation.

3118406520
05:52:55.369 --> 05:52:58.979
And we watched them design new energy
efficiency and greening measures,

2611857142
05:52:58.980 --> 05:53:01.088
and they told us with pride how the solar

212961315
05:53:01.089 --> 05:53:02.744
panels enabled them to give back

2586373044
05:53:02.745 --> 05:53:06.520
to their community by supplying power
to EV chargers in the car park.

3925966394
05:53:06.521 --> 05:53:09.629
Now, children care deeply about
preserving and protecting our

2526904806
05:53:09.630 --> 05:53:13.071
natural environment and preserving
it for future generations.

226037345
05:53:13.072 --> 05:53:15.581
They understand the need
for bold action to do so

1535819677
05:53:15.582 --> 05:53:18.315
better than some of
the adults in this chamber.

471739583
05:53:18.316 --> 05:53:22.013
But not only were
the solar panels a valuable

1476275061
05:53:22.014 --> 05:53:23.517
learning tool inspiring them,

259387444
05:53:24.111 --> 05:53:26.569
the school was saving money
about £8,500 a year,

1311989871
05:53:27.112 --> 05:53:30.621
enabling them to plough
resources back into teaching.

17044312
05:53:30.622 --> 05:53:32.427
And this speaks to something wider.

2780049176
05:53:32.428 --> 05:53:37.018
For many people, the promise that
hard work would deliver security,

2377258310
05:53:37.019 --> 05:53:38.975
home ownership and a decent quality of

1296069422
05:53:38.976 --> 05:53:40.880
life increasingly feels out of reach.

3065626257
05:53:40.882 --> 05:53:43.373
And that frustration is real.

2130934450
05:53:43.374 --> 05:53:46.934
And we see that acutely on energy,
with local residents in Bournemouth

2939738676
05:53:46.936 --> 05:53:50.246
West and businesses telling me
that their heating in their homes,

74048164
05:53:50.247 --> 05:53:53.306
fuelling their cars and sustaining
the energy costs of their

4029908231
05:53:53.307 --> 05:53:55.811
businesses is becoming
increasingly unaffordable.

3051096145
05:53:55.812 --> 05:54:00.374
Families are tired of living at
the mercy of global energy shocks.

1063396529
05:54:00.375 --> 05:54:04.816
They can't control where every
instance of international

3745853796
05:54:04.817 --> 05:54:06.572
instability is felt in food bills,

4247390175
05:54:06.573 --> 05:54:09.118
household bills and
the anxiety of sitting around

1459853380
05:54:09.119 --> 05:54:11.427
their kitchen tables at
the end of the month.

2632080439
05:54:11.428 --> 05:54:14.840
That's why I'm proud of the number
of measures we've taken as this,

4065680277
05:54:14.841 --> 05:54:19.422
as this government measures in
the Budget to bring down bills by £150.

480614102
05:54:19.423 --> 05:54:22.269
The energy price cap
action on heating oil,

1351775507
05:54:22.270 --> 05:54:24.717
a warm homes plan bringing the biggest

3888432982
05:54:24.718 --> 05:54:28.462
ever public investment to homes and record

384546508
05:54:28.463 --> 05:54:30.367
investment in clean home-grown power.

4163574312
05:54:30.368 --> 05:54:31.922
And now a cornerstone measure.

3939229382
05:54:31.923 --> 05:54:34.719
In this King's speech,
the Energy Independence Bill to

3647412615
05:54:34.721 --> 05:54:38.069
accelerate investment in
clean home grown energy,

2504487788
05:54:38.070 --> 05:54:41.730
strengthen consumer protections
and bring down bills over the long term.

3254963915
05:54:41.731 --> 05:54:44.591
And I want to make this point
clearly to the frontbench.

3584506256
05:54:44.592 --> 05:54:46.949
Towns like mine in
Bournemouth and Poole stand

3601923589
05:54:46.950 --> 05:54:48.905
ready to help deliver that transition.

2153427564
05:54:49.116 --> 05:54:53.619
It's an immense source of pride for
me to represent a constituency that

2859984301
05:54:53.620 --> 05:54:57.721
is full to the brim of extraordinary
talent, creativity and innovation.

3049816530
05:54:58.115 --> 05:55:01.967
We have outstanding colleges,
universities, skilled workers.

3472829989
05:55:01.968 --> 05:55:05.969
A great example of this is
Bournemouth and Poole Colleges Green

2692891253
05:55:05.971 --> 05:55:08.979
Energy Centre building
the skilled workforce of the future,

1541597086
05:55:08.980 --> 05:55:11.388
and we have the natural
assets on our coastline

3047062188
05:55:11.389 --> 05:55:13.777
and communities eager for investment,

309589125
05:55:13.778 --> 05:55:15.630
including huge opportunities through

1980483022
05:55:15.632 --> 05:55:17.536
the Dorset Clean Energy Supercluster.

2316057050
05:55:17.537 --> 05:55:18.390
In my right hon.

1758129561
05:55:18.391 --> 05:55:21.473
Friend the Member for South
Dorset Constituency.

1161655165
05:55:21.474 --> 05:55:24.269
Now, the transition to clean
energy must not simply

2342531508
05:55:24.270 --> 05:55:27.272
happen to places like
Bournemouth and Poole.

377478654
05:55:27.272 --> 05:55:30.420
It must include them because
creating a new generation

3811281802
05:55:30.421 --> 05:55:32.376
of skilled workers and the opportunity

151939445
05:55:32.377 --> 05:55:34.568
for well-paid jobs in areas that have too

733837367
05:55:34.569 --> 05:55:36.423
long been overlooked for investment,

3779150832
05:55:36.424 --> 05:55:39.724
is about making an economy
that works again for people

524126834
05:55:39.725 --> 05:55:42.083
who feel like it has
stopped working for them.

949387270
05:55:42.084 --> 05:55:43.188
>> Will she give way?

490747913
05:55:43.189 --> 05:55:44.143
>> I thank my hon.

466354106
05:55:44.144 --> 05:55:46.852
Friend for giving way
and making an excellent speech.

2554986045
05:55:47.116 --> 05:55:49.022
Does she share my view that actually,

3890013166
05:55:49.022 --> 05:55:51.229
what's really important
about the pieces of

565349442
05:55:51.230 --> 05:55:53.486
legislation put forward
in the King's Speech

2011069747
05:55:53.487 --> 05:55:55.293
is they will start to drive growth,

1490279590
05:55:55.294 --> 05:55:57.567
drive green job creation into parts of

1255779454
05:55:57.568 --> 05:55:59.575
the country that for too long have been

378080263
05:55:59.576 --> 05:56:04.369
left behind and have not felt
the benefits of growth and job creation.

2676439913
05:56:04.370 --> 05:56:05.324
>> I thank my hon.

1994376371
05:56:05.325 --> 05:56:05.725
Friend.

565347811
05:56:05.726 --> 05:56:07.180
And yes, I absolutely agree.

978936620
05:56:07.181 --> 05:56:09.992
And I think what he didn't
say to the Ministers is that

4253121611
05:56:09.993 --> 05:56:13.030
we would very much welcome
a visit in Dorset to

3100170028
05:56:13.031 --> 05:56:17.716
support the the Dorset Clean Energy
Supercluster and ultimately,

1694167113
05:56:17.717 --> 05:56:19.420
ultimately, Madam Deputy Speaker.

430740307
05:56:19.421 --> 05:56:21.775
This is why I support the King's Speech.

3156814841
05:56:21.776 --> 05:56:24.282
While others offer anger,
division, easy answers,

1113827861
05:56:24.283 --> 05:56:28.275
or simply change their minds
about important issues.

1107543388
05:56:28.276 --> 05:56:32.442
This government is choosing a path
that will deliver long term reform,

4142131370
05:56:32.443 --> 05:56:34.566
economic resilience and national renewal.

3397823479
05:56:34.567 --> 05:56:36.875
That work will take time,
but we can rebuild.

3443530861
05:56:38.116 --> 05:56:40.472
We cannot rebuild prosperity
on short termism.

1349368449
05:56:40.473 --> 05:56:45.277
This king's speech is an important
step towards building a more secure,

2937895748
05:56:45.278 --> 05:56:48.537
more resilient and more hopeful
future for communities like mine

4035531414
05:56:48.538 --> 05:56:53.372
in Bournemouth West and across
the country, Carla Lockhart.

1687230317
05:56:53.373 --> 05:56:55.424
And to get everybody else in.

3714089762
05:56:55.425 --> 05:56:56.076
The speaker.

1267222524
05:56:56.076 --> 05:56:59.874
>> Limit will be dropped to three
minutes after Carla Lockhart.

2903680351
05:57:00.117 --> 05:57:04.670
>> Madam Deputy Speaker, having
listened intently to the King's Speech,

2379861724
05:57:04.671 --> 05:57:08.773
I was left with one conclusion that
this government just doesn't get it.

3022918792
05:57:11.076 --> 05:57:14.586
A government completely out of touch
after recent election results in

3460649613
05:57:14.587 --> 05:57:18.324
the surge in support for parties
campaigning on illegal immigration,

3496991894
05:57:18.325 --> 05:57:21.784
sovereignty and cost of living
pressures, you would think government

2551062661
05:57:21.785 --> 05:57:24.290
might finally have recognised
public frustration.

1410381115
05:57:24.290 --> 05:57:27.147
Instead, they appear to have
learned absolutely nothing.

3460824867
05:57:27.148 --> 05:57:28.051
People are angry.

1657419447
05:57:28.052 --> 05:57:29.705
Angry about illegal immigration,

1476155354
05:57:29.706 --> 05:57:31.913
angry about the cost
of living and pressure

3214474565
05:57:31.914 --> 05:57:34.975
they feel every time they fill
their car or heat their home,

3998331277
05:57:34.976 --> 05:57:37.080
angry about overstretched public services

1903527537
05:57:37.081 --> 05:57:38.934
and increasingly angry that ordinary

2507973634
05:57:38.936 --> 05:57:40.992
people feel they are losing control over

925151490
05:57:40.993 --> 05:57:42.646
decisions affecting their lives.

272059921
05:57:42.647 --> 05:57:45.356
Today's debate is about
energy, and there is no doubt

996995136
05:57:45.357 --> 05:57:48.377
that is the the topic
around every kitchen table.

2454542976
05:57:48.378 --> 05:57:52.779
Yes, the King's Speech had
very little to say to families

3011380732
05:57:52.780 --> 05:57:54.934
facing those pressures on energy security.

4026578816
05:57:55.116 --> 05:57:57.422
Nowhere is the gap between
Westminster policy

2765770664
05:57:57.423 --> 05:57:59.729
and reality clearer than
in Northern Ireland.

3273101880
05:57:59.730 --> 05:58:03.290
Around 60% of households in Northern
Ireland rely on home heating oil.

1516521706
05:58:03.291 --> 05:58:07.273
Many live in rural communities
where a car is not optional.

1968205841
05:58:07.275 --> 05:58:09.682
It is absolutely essential
to get away quickly.

2528083163
05:58:09.683 --> 05:58:10.686
>> Very quickly on.

3865474490
05:58:10.687 --> 05:58:11.138
>> That.

1566262781
05:58:11.139 --> 05:58:14.652
>> Point, one of the reasons why
the heat is so expensive in Northern

1403832146
05:58:14.653 --> 05:58:17.463
Ireland because of the travel
and to get it over there.

4139540023
05:58:17.464 --> 05:58:20.322
But the Conservative Party
have put forward an amendment

2507790198
05:58:20.323 --> 05:58:22.783
to that to open the oil
fields in the North Sea.

1831207290
05:58:22.784 --> 05:58:24.691
Does she feel, if that was to happen,

3964660551
05:58:24.692 --> 05:58:28.153
that would reduce the oil price
and heating oil in Northern Ireland?

3669914650
05:58:28.154 --> 05:58:29.156
>> Yes, absolutely.

85314740
05:58:29.157 --> 05:58:29.859
Come to that.

4126913327
05:58:29.860 --> 05:58:32.569
So when fuel prices, when
oil prices increase or when

377407124
05:58:32.570 --> 05:58:35.225
instability sends shockwaves
through energy markets,

2921619240
05:58:35.226 --> 05:58:37.682
families in my constituency
feel it immediately.

3581784892
05:58:37.683 --> 05:58:40.891
Hauliers, farmers and many
businesses are feeling the pressure.

803987324
05:58:40.892 --> 05:58:43.450
Also in Northern Ireland,
there is no easy switch,

1380693032
05:58:43.451 --> 05:58:46.559
no ready made alternative
and certainly no escaping the cost.

1706688747
05:58:46.561 --> 05:58:50.171
I've repeatedly raised concerns in
this House around heating oil costs,

256365841
05:58:50.172 --> 05:58:53.670
fuel affordability
and support for households

257455450
05:58:53.671 --> 05:58:55.525
uniquely exposed to these pressures.

1323041851
05:58:55.526 --> 05:58:58.433
I've repeatedly pressed for
practical measures that would

4204363246
05:58:58.433 --> 05:59:00.840
make an immediate difference
cutting fuel duty,

3436293419
05:59:01.122 --> 05:59:03.678
reducing that burden on
hard pressed householders,

4055641073
05:59:03.679 --> 05:59:06.537
greater support for those
dependent on home heating oil,

2599792749
05:59:06.538 --> 05:59:08.893
and stronger protections
for consumers exposed

141448916
05:59:08.894 --> 05:59:10.749
to volatility in heating oil market.

3212890834
05:59:10.750 --> 05:59:12.204
These are not radical ideas.

2343812124
05:59:12.205 --> 05:59:13.358
They're not long term.

3408023797
05:59:13.359 --> 05:59:15.514
They're a practical intervention that show

459757369
05:59:15.515 --> 05:59:20.326
a government that is in
touch with the needs.

2262827198
05:59:20.328 --> 05:59:21.231
>> Thank the hon.

2861925754
05:59:21.232 --> 05:59:22.385
Member for giving way.

3421100998
05:59:22.386 --> 05:59:25.045
Would you agree with me when
she mentions fuel duty,

924588245
05:59:25.046 --> 05:59:27.553
that a contribution, even
though a temporary one,

1199914858
05:59:27.554 --> 05:59:30.063
would be if the government
were to announce a cut

204701746
05:59:30.064 --> 05:59:32.221
in fuel duty rather than just freezing it.

3922383976
05:59:32.222 --> 05:59:34.128
And that would be a significant step,

4184173580
05:59:34.129 --> 05:59:36.486
particularly as we come
into the summer months

3052856693
05:59:36.487 --> 05:59:38.241
and then subsequently into winter.

2513126714
05:59:38.242 --> 05:59:41.451
>> Absolutely practical step that
would make a real difference.

3188929427
05:59:41.451 --> 05:59:44.460
Families are entitled to ask
what possible justification is

2183578140
05:59:44.461 --> 05:59:47.418
there for support sitting
untouched while people struggle?

1959911811
05:59:47.419 --> 05:59:50.731
When we look at the 81 million
that has been given by Westminster

1240223266
05:59:50.732 --> 05:59:53.691
to Stormont and sitting in
a Sinn Féin control department,

4276265338
05:59:53.692 --> 05:59:56.549
rather than reaching households
who desperately need it,

2431037619
05:59:56.550 --> 05:59:59.744
and I would ask for
the Ministers to intervene on that.

1601432305
05:59:59.745 --> 06:00:03.253
Energy security means affordability
and policies grounded in reality.

3336976504
06:00:03.254 --> 06:00:08.178
People support protecting the environment,
but they also expect realism.

4108461132
06:00:08.179 --> 06:00:12.483
And realism means
recognising a simple truth.

2175540547
06:00:12.484 --> 06:00:16.125
Energy security begins with producing
the energy we need ourselves.

3480037924
06:00:16.126 --> 06:00:20.483
The North Sea has the ability
to help power our economy,

992182793
06:00:21.120 --> 06:00:26.772
support jobs and strengthen our
energy resilience for decades.

2217165119
06:00:26.772 --> 06:00:29.330
Yet instead of backing
a strategic national asset.

672066231
06:00:29.331 --> 06:00:32.878
Too often, government appears
determined to turn its back on it.

771878597
06:00:32.879 --> 06:00:35.973
As Secretary of State, who is so wedded

297536610
06:00:35.974 --> 06:00:37.780
to a failing crazy net zero agenda,

867324922
06:00:37.781 --> 06:00:42.734
rather than helping those most in
need at a time of global instability,

1206500954
06:00:42.735 --> 06:00:46.526
increasing dependence on imported
energy while restricting

660211874
06:00:47.122 --> 06:00:49.426
domestic production
raises serious questions.

326368902
06:00:49.427 --> 06:00:52.172
That is not energy security.

3166116909
06:00:52.173 --> 06:00:54.378
It is exporting jobs,
exporting investment,

276791293
06:00:54.379 --> 06:00:56.520
and increasing dependence on others.

2130787735
06:00:56.521 --> 06:00:58.776
We should be supporting
domestic production,

3457253937
06:00:59.121 --> 06:01:01.576
backing strategic industries
and ensuring we are

2155413610
06:01:02.120 --> 06:01:04.275
using our own resources wherever possible,

4281897295
06:01:04.276 --> 06:01:08.771
and we should stop loading further
costs onto households and industry

3833496651
06:01:08.772 --> 06:01:12.433
through increasingly unrealistic
and punitive carbon taxes,

2961143066
06:01:12.433 --> 06:01:15.130
which ultimately make life more expensive

2062085241
06:01:15.130 --> 06:01:16.885
for working people and businesses.

1379454631
06:01:19.125 --> 06:01:26.326
The cost associated with net zero
from 2025 to 2050 is 116 to 135

4032430095
06:01:26.328 --> 06:01:27.230
billion per year.

3268642679
06:01:27.231 --> 06:01:32.223
Those are eye watering sums and it's
the taxpayer that's paying for it.

4094898486
06:01:32.224 --> 06:01:34.730
Madam Deputy Speaker,
the election results should

351910767
06:01:34.731 --> 06:01:37.237
have been a political
earthquake, a warning shot.

1734022023
06:01:37.239 --> 06:01:38.893
Yet government has not listened.

1550221138
06:01:38.894 --> 06:01:41.651
Instead, it remains trapped
in the Westminster bubble,

687738095
06:01:41.652 --> 06:01:46.082
a lack of understanding of
what life actually looks like

14164301
06:01:46.083 --> 06:01:48.941
outside SW1 because lets us
look at illegal immigration.

1208274078
06:01:48.942 --> 06:01:51.097
The public were promised stronger borders,

3323591074
06:01:51.098 --> 06:01:54.025
promised tougher action, promised control.

1212118224
06:01:54.026 --> 06:01:58.230
Instead, what we're seeing is expensive
failure dressed up as progress.

320017734
06:01:58.231 --> 06:02:02.775
More than 200 000 people have now
crossed the channel in small boats.

2596976868
06:02:02.776 --> 06:02:06.741
Since records began in 2025
alone, more than 41,000

3986232511
06:02:06.742 --> 06:02:09.933
cross, making it the second
highest year on record.

522209255
06:02:09.934 --> 06:02:14.486
I have repeatedly raised concerns
around the asylum accommodation costs,

700455504
06:02:18.126 --> 06:02:23.130
rehousing in the next decade is set
to total £15 billion £15 billion

2268179789
06:02:23.130 --> 06:02:26.527
of taxpayers money to rehouse
asylum in Northern Ireland.

3446370736
06:02:26.528 --> 06:02:28.801
It's set to rise to 400 million.

2337668420
06:02:28.802 --> 06:02:33.779
I know that money would be better
spent on our own citizens first.

4119783678
06:02:33.780 --> 06:02:35.585
At a time when pensioners struggle,

1908923416
06:02:35.586 --> 06:02:38.527
businesses face pressure
and families watch every penny,

1920161943
06:02:38.528 --> 06:02:41.326
the government are more
concerned about forcing

3644539945
06:02:41.326 --> 06:02:45.188
unwanted and not needed
agendas and ideology.

3010996950
06:02:45.189 --> 06:02:46.291
Digital IDs net zero.

3108482428
06:02:46.293 --> 06:02:48.379
What would that money not be?

3770695837
06:02:48.380 --> 06:02:51.780
That money would be better
spent on our WASPI women,

302268963
06:02:51.781 --> 06:02:54.728
our pensioners, pensioners.

1580341189
06:02:54.729 --> 06:02:56.130
Meaningful welfare reforms.

1594579039
06:02:56.132 --> 06:02:58.879
Where was the support for
businesses and farmers

4117634851
06:02:58.880 --> 06:03:01.286
sustaining our rural
economy and food security?

4225598047
06:03:01.287 --> 06:03:03.025
And where was Northern Ireland?

3989566538
06:03:03.026 --> 06:03:06.276
There was no meaningful recognition
of continuing barriers

3717761373
06:03:06.277 --> 06:03:10.376
within our own United
Kingdom internal market.

515054204
06:03:10.377 --> 06:03:13.237
Madam Deputy Speaker, what
frustrates people most

261860175
06:03:13.237 --> 06:03:17.235
is what was simply not
in the King's Speech.

1125708948
06:03:17.236 --> 06:03:21.781
When we look at the antisemitism
Islamist extremism.

2162193640
06:03:21.782 --> 06:03:23.675
Our veterans weren't mentioned.

3669455017
06:03:23.676 --> 06:03:25.432
And then you have the EU rhetoric.

1522619766
06:03:25.433 --> 06:03:27.691
The public sent a message
at the ballot box.

1254855183
06:03:27.692 --> 06:03:30.936
It's time for the government to
wake up and start listening.

1202218544
06:03:30.937 --> 06:03:34.487
>> >> Making or taking interventions will

1805380551
06:03:34.487 --> 06:03:36.594
deny another member from making a speech.

1152247105
06:03:37.084 --> 06:03:40.093
>> Julia Buckley thank you very
much, Madam Deputy Speaker.

3441288934
06:03:40.094 --> 06:03:43.590
I am grateful to contribute to
this debate on the new legislative

2018776781
06:03:43.591 --> 06:03:46.632
programme included in this
year's King's Speech.

2142380355
06:03:46.633 --> 06:03:50.735
At a time when all eyes are on our
government to demonstrate delivery,

1960756622
06:03:50.736 --> 06:03:53.380
we should not underestimate
the impact we can have

2105256461
06:03:53.380 --> 06:03:55.537
on daily lives by improving the invisible,

1527547972
06:03:55.538 --> 06:03:59.624
yet critical infrastructure that
holds our country together.

1658706894
06:03:59.625 --> 06:04:01.330
As a matter of national security,

2277326641
06:04:01.331 --> 06:04:04.029
with impact for growth across all regions,

463885703
06:04:04.030 --> 06:04:07.057
it's imperative we unlock better planning,

2606488929
06:04:07.058 --> 06:04:09.362
coordination and investment
in core services,

3009619653
06:04:09.364 --> 06:04:12.591
the lack of which has been
holding back our growth.

1996022151
06:04:12.592 --> 06:04:15.790
Now, with strategic plans
to grow capacity in power,

3460520283
06:04:15.790 --> 06:04:19.087
energy, connectivity
and water infrastructure,

3094824121
06:04:19.088 --> 06:04:22.135
we can set this country on
the path to sustainable

2163820918
06:04:22.136 --> 06:04:25.080
growth because in
the face of climate change,

1996062021
06:04:25.081 --> 06:04:27.478
we must adapt and improve our readiness.

3108276333
06:04:27.479 --> 06:04:29.836
This is vital in
the Energy Independence Bill,

2537651990
06:04:29.837 --> 06:04:32.030
as we have heard from colleagues today.

800643363
06:04:32.031 --> 06:04:35.783
But nowhere is this more needed
than in the water sector,

2390294581
06:04:35.784 --> 06:04:38.586
where we have witnessed the abject failure

1001687402
06:04:38.587 --> 06:04:41.586
of privatisation in the industry,

2332131683
06:04:41.587 --> 06:04:43.791
leaving us with dangerously
polluted water,

121284064
06:04:43.793 --> 06:04:47.280
inadequate sewage management
and increasingly expensive water bills.

176910499
06:04:47.281 --> 06:04:51.233
Add to this the effect of climate
change, and we are simultaneously

1246395860
06:04:51.234 --> 06:04:53.985
seeing an increase in
flooding and drought,

3870981615
06:04:53.986 --> 06:04:58.236
which sounds like an oxymoron,
but it's just a symptom

596524392
06:04:58.237 --> 06:05:01.434
of the mismanagement of our
precious water resource.

3680465178
06:05:01.436 --> 06:05:04.282
With the inadequate
infrastructure, the public,

2297675650
06:05:04.283 --> 06:05:06.683
as we know, are quite rightly angry.

985615037
06:05:06.683 --> 06:05:09.337
Angry that the asset stripping of water

1576330764
06:05:09.338 --> 06:05:11.294
companies and failure to invest in our

463317532
06:05:11.295 --> 06:05:13.249
drainage and sewage infrastructure has

3822425191
06:05:14.087 --> 06:05:15.992
allowed this to continue for decades.

2357276952
06:05:15.993 --> 06:05:18.530
In my constituency of Shrewsbury,

1942870539
06:05:18.531 --> 06:05:21.642
a beautiful town is enclosed by
the loop of the River Severn.

4044966272
06:05:21.643 --> 06:05:25.082
It's a beautiful, historic
natural asset that

709705615
06:05:25.083 --> 06:05:27.838
has also been allowed to fill with sewage,

1966325543
06:05:27.839 --> 06:05:32.941
breach its banks and pollute our
homes, businesses and play areas.

3709549837
06:05:33.133 --> 06:05:36.793
Bill payers are ready for change
and from an infrastructure perspective,

512707097
06:05:36.794 --> 06:05:40.235
we also need assurances
that our water assets

2356081757
06:05:40.236 --> 06:05:42.788
are being considered holistically.

2133075250
06:05:42.789 --> 06:05:46.234
From rainwater reuse to
infrastructure upgrades and stronger

33265133
06:05:46.235 --> 06:05:50.531
oversight of what has become
a very fragmented industry.

399412503
06:05:50.532 --> 06:05:52.839
So, Madam Deputy Speaker,
I welcome the Clean

2606094314
06:05:52.840 --> 06:05:56.334
Water Bill introduced
this session, a sequel,

2339164229
06:05:56.335 --> 06:05:58.778
you could say to our first blockbuster,

524802239
06:05:58.779 --> 06:06:01.136
the Water Special Measures
Act from last year,

1019781387
06:06:01.137 --> 06:06:04.795
which introduced criminal liabilities
for polluters and banned executive

2708957536
06:06:04.796 --> 06:06:09.088
bonuses for water bosses guilty
of environmental damage.

231677943
06:06:09.089 --> 06:06:11.195
The Clean Water Bill is much anticipated.

3857595191
06:06:11.196 --> 06:06:14.596
Follow on is needed to overhaul
the current regulatory system.

455721606
06:06:14.597 --> 06:06:17.878
It's an ambitious programme
of high level restructuring,

576112669
06:06:17.879 --> 06:06:20.638
and I look forward to this
vital piece of legislation.

1890848059
06:06:20.639 --> 06:06:23.199
It's long overdue and it's
high time we got a grip

2150801389
06:06:23.200 --> 06:06:25.306
of the problem of our polluted waterways.

1941509620
06:06:25.307 --> 06:06:28.165
I've always described the Water
Special Measures Bill as

2157571924
06:06:28.165 --> 06:06:31.276
the last chance saloon for water
companies to get this right,

1618496267
06:06:31.277 --> 06:06:34.639
whereas the clean water bill is
surely our last throw of the dice.

4208298189
06:06:34.640 --> 06:06:38.288
Before we move to nationalising
the water sector.

2883143574
06:06:38.289 --> 06:06:41.778
>> Lincoln thank you very
much, Madam Deputy Speaker.

4230460362
06:06:41.779 --> 06:06:45.834
In East Thanet, almost 15% of
people are in fuel poverty,

1124414864
06:06:45.835 --> 06:06:48.391
significantly above
the national average of 11.4%.

4114746205
06:06:48.392 --> 06:06:50.748
That's thousands of my
constituents who cannot

206570785
06:06:50.749 --> 06:06:52.755
afford for their energy bills to go up.

3085145372
06:06:52.757 --> 06:06:54.611
But because of international events,

2748769059
06:06:54.612 --> 06:06:57.721
completely out of their control,
are now facing exactly that.

796766387
06:06:57.722 --> 06:07:00.932
Working people should not like
this, should not bear the burden

4027168661
06:07:00.933 --> 06:07:05.084
of decisions made by Donald
Trump or Vladimir Putin.

2299603021
06:07:05.085 --> 06:07:08.197
That is why I am glad to see
the government's focus on energy

1360902387
06:07:08.198 --> 06:07:11.687
and energy independence in this
upcoming legislative session.

2435761557
06:07:11.688 --> 06:07:14.299
There is no one silver
bullet for achieving this.

3498972879
06:07:14.300 --> 06:07:16.456
It requires action to reduce energy usage,

3189159849
06:07:16.457 --> 06:07:19.391
which is why the Warm Homes
Agency is so important

418586806
06:07:19.392 --> 06:07:21.598
for giving people trusted
advice and access

3942318224
06:07:21.599 --> 06:07:23.335
to grants and low interest loans.

2306307848
06:07:23.336 --> 06:07:26.586
It requires more generation
of energy at home

1106084761
06:07:26.587 --> 06:07:29.237
because the more we produce domestically,

3192494651
06:07:29.239 --> 06:07:32.635
the less exposed we are to
volatile fossil fuel markets.

3876570862
06:07:32.636 --> 06:07:36.540
It requires reform of the market
and it requires diversity of supply.

2561233086
06:07:37.128 --> 06:07:39.585
But, Madam Deputy Speaker,
this is in particular

1770261216
06:07:39.586 --> 06:07:41.582
a new international situation,

228085287
06:07:41.583 --> 06:07:44.643
which is different from
the kind of circumstances

2236373720
06:07:44.644 --> 06:07:47.433
we were previously
considering when tackling

2037888341
06:07:47.434 --> 06:07:50.237
the science of climate
change and the failed

4016645215
06:07:50.239 --> 06:07:51.944
market of energy in this country.

3048149056
06:07:51.945 --> 06:07:54.705
We now live in a situation
where the global context is

4145057375
06:07:54.706 --> 06:07:57.884
more volatile and more
unstable than has ever been.

1845437308
06:07:57.885 --> 06:08:00.790
Therefore, this legislative
programme that the government

4224118243
06:08:00.791 --> 06:08:03.233
has announced is absolutely necessary,

962919963
06:08:03.234 --> 06:08:06.038
but it may not be sufficient
on its own to secure

2459630347
06:08:06.039 --> 06:08:08.594
the energy independence
and resilience we require.

1772798305
06:08:08.596 --> 06:08:11.836
The government needs to consider
its role in establishing

1164218629
06:08:11.837 --> 06:08:14.694
greater international agreements on how

1521077957
06:08:14.695 --> 06:08:17.152
we increase the resilience
of our global economy

2007863955
06:08:17.153 --> 06:08:19.409
against our exposure to
fossil fuel markets.

3821624846
06:08:19.410 --> 06:08:21.683
I have called on the government to convene

325021743
06:08:21.683 --> 06:08:23.237
an international energy summit

3008450637
06:08:23.237 --> 06:08:26.040
with the same boldness and scope of Gordon

1530604218
06:08:26.041 --> 06:08:29.287
Brown's crisis Summit in 2009,

2715280170
06:08:29.288 --> 06:08:32.482
following the great financial crash,

1977471174
06:08:32.483 --> 06:08:34.790
I saw firsthand the role
of Britain using its

3081672977
06:08:34.791 --> 06:08:36.947
convening power to bring nations together,

193437482
06:08:36.948 --> 06:08:38.705
and we should look to do so again.

1036227275
06:08:38.706 --> 06:08:40.763
I'm delighted to hear in the speech that

1626812302
06:08:40.764 --> 06:08:42.671
we will be hosting the G20 next year,

1870200188
06:08:42.672 --> 06:08:46.083
and I hope the government
will make energy cooperation

1073365887
06:08:46.084 --> 06:08:47.840
right at the heart of that summit.

529857143
06:08:48.132 --> 06:08:50.540
This is crucial because
20% of the world's oil.

1994305366
06:08:53.549 --> 06:08:56.912
and one third of 20% of global
liquid natural gas and one third of

808971245
06:08:56.913 --> 06:09:00.222
seaborne fertiliser pass through
the Straits of Hormuz every day.

941315783
06:09:00.223 --> 06:09:02.939
The economic pain of
this has not yet hit us.

3101436303
06:09:02.940 --> 06:09:06.049
People are already talking about
the risk of family holidays,

1318607979
06:09:06.050 --> 06:09:08.759
but there is a risk of food
shortages and starvation,

1920067009
06:09:08.760 --> 06:09:12.492
a risk of blackouts in countries
that are vital to our supply chains.

1136862446
06:09:12.493 --> 06:09:15.053
So that is why this is
serious, that we are facing

1649513692
06:09:15.054 --> 06:09:17.058
and requires an international solution.

2851275623
06:09:17.058 --> 06:09:19.317
I'm delighted that we
have a deep and broad,

2292516772
06:09:19.318 --> 06:09:22.376
integrated approach to tackling
some of the most challenging

2262630281
06:09:22.377 --> 06:09:24.882
elements of creating
increased energy resilience,

841276284
06:09:24.883 --> 06:09:27.140
as outlined in the in
the legislative plans,

2492342306
06:09:27.141 --> 06:09:28.949
but it does need to be seen in that

1007457342
06:09:28.950 --> 06:09:30.955
wider global context and demands global

2173831903
06:09:30.956 --> 06:09:32.960
leadership from the British government.

3020622067
