06:11:07.836 --> 06:11:12.144
Last Christmas my Labour
government did step in and save

132811922
06:11:12.145 --> 06:11:17.840
the UK chemicals industry at
Grangemouth, 500 jobs secured,

2415983978
06:11:17.841 --> 06:11:21.089
a profit sharing agreement,
reached positive government

531018980
06:11:21.090 --> 06:11:24.192
action for Grangemouth
and for all of Scotland.

496257878
06:11:24.193 --> 06:11:27.290
That was the right thing to do.

3375011900
06:11:27.290 --> 06:11:29.338
That was the Labour thing to do.

3053306156
06:11:29.339 --> 06:11:34.883
And the same goes for
nationalising British Steel.

397240572
06:11:34.884 --> 06:11:37.441
15 months ago at Scottish
Labour Party conference,

3471110978
06:11:37.442 --> 06:11:41.890
the Prime Minister announced project
will £200 million for Grangemouth.

4044219254
06:11:41.891 --> 06:11:47.046
Bold industrial future.

1867929451
06:11:47.047 --> 06:11:52.198
Let us get those new green, clean
future industries into Grangemouth,

4035153841
06:11:52.199 --> 06:11:55.582
but do it quicker.

299645301
06:11:55.583 --> 06:12:00.092
It has taken far too long
because workers need jobs.

3904000010
06:12:00.093 --> 06:12:02.683
The local community
must see the benefit of

1979676211
06:12:02.684 --> 06:12:04.689
those industries coming to Grangemouth.

2420156823
06:12:07.137 --> 06:12:08.741
Scandalously, for far too long,

944000291
06:12:08.742 --> 06:12:11.434
private capital has
exploited the local area,

3065578595
06:12:11.436 --> 06:12:15.448
extracted profits and not
put anything back into

2626175429
06:12:15.449 --> 06:12:18.985
the town that has given them oh so much.

1430520032
06:12:18.986 --> 06:12:23.389
Let us take public ownership
of these new industries,

4136215137
06:12:23.390 --> 06:12:26.841
reinvest in Grangemouth, reinvest
in the town, the people.

1717337467
06:12:26.842 --> 06:12:30.039
It is about high time that
we, the working class,

2107670588
06:12:30.040 --> 06:12:33.536
started to reap
the benefits of our labour.

2339848778
06:12:33.537 --> 06:12:33.837
Well.

2684565092
06:12:33.838 --> 06:12:36.237
>> Thank you, Madam Deputy Speaker.

2457632170
06:12:36.239 --> 06:12:39.651
>> I would like to welcome last
week's King's Speech and the bills,

1895924865
06:12:39.652 --> 06:12:42.915
with him aiming to put the UK on
a stronger path for the future.

1379548312
06:12:42.915 --> 06:12:46.075
My constituents in Heywood
and Middleton North have been clear

934434792
06:12:46.076 --> 06:12:48.687
with me if we are to build
a future that is fairer,

3486184118
06:12:48.688 --> 06:12:51.642
where they are not just
getting by but thriving,

2047161974
06:12:51.643 --> 06:12:53.448
we need to do politics differently.

567815250
06:12:53.449 --> 06:12:56.961
It is not good enough to suggest
that someday, in the distant future,

4267231020
06:12:56.962 --> 06:12:59.395
things might get a little bit better.

4204432402
06:12:59.396 --> 06:13:01.737
That's not going to cut it anymore.

354629391
06:13:01.739 --> 06:13:03.745
Today, our focus is on energy security,

4205585724
06:13:03.746 --> 06:13:06.633
an issue which underscores
perhaps more than any other

2531232793
06:13:06.634 --> 06:13:09.486
that we cannot carry on
with business as usual.

2968277293
06:13:09.487 --> 06:13:11.342
Looking across the north of England,

3490106393
06:13:11.343 --> 06:13:14.349
we can see the consequences
of deindustrialisation,

655545045
06:13:14.350 --> 06:13:18.237
the hollowing out of local economies
and the impacts of austerity.

2564574257
06:13:18.239 --> 06:13:21.642
And it's abundantly clear that
we need to view achieving energy

373931169
06:13:21.643 --> 06:13:25.344
security as an opportunity to
right these historic wrongs.

3056919637
06:13:25.346 --> 06:13:28.405
The inequalities brought about
by this have been eating away

968215204
06:13:28.406 --> 06:13:31.265
at communities and the values
that once made them whole,

3945632197
06:13:31.266 --> 06:13:34.743
and reframing energy security as
a positive opportunity to reverse

332204663
06:13:34.744 --> 06:13:38.047
the fortunes of towns like mine
is the only way to proceed.

2817068178
06:13:38.048 --> 06:13:41.497
The poverty experienced by
far too many in Heywood

1793565741
06:13:41.498 --> 06:13:44.106
and Middleton and the other
towns that I represent,

3761409655
06:13:44.107 --> 06:13:47.668
will not be addressed unless we accept
that we need to reindustrialise

3296372800
06:13:47.669 --> 06:13:50.479
and do so in a way that
safeguards our energy security.

156964549
06:13:50.480 --> 06:13:53.941
I would therefore like to express
my full support for the provisions

940401310
06:13:53.942 --> 06:13:56.498
made in the government's
Energy Independence Bill.

2328808630
06:13:56.499 --> 06:13:59.540
The next step in tackling
the fact that builds a totally

702339041
06:13:59.540 --> 06:14:01.695
unmanageable for consumers and businesses,

3619195389
06:14:02.144 --> 06:14:04.851
and ending our overreliance
on global energy markets.

2608692702
06:14:05.136 --> 06:14:08.938
But challenges with the cost of
energy are not only a consideration

1093752084
06:14:08.939 --> 06:14:12.548
when it comes to how we heat
the homes or power industry.

1381510937
06:14:12.549 --> 06:14:15.658
As the sole Greater Manchester
MP on the Transport Committee.

2189256642
06:14:15.659 --> 06:14:17.666
I also want to consider how the cost of

3914170337
06:14:17.668 --> 06:14:19.990
energy affects how we get from A to B,

2679558199
06:14:19.991 --> 06:14:23.200
giving local people the ability
to reach employment and leisure

1825238003
06:14:23.201 --> 06:14:26.298
opportunities both affordably
and in a joined up manner,

2212907025
06:14:26.299 --> 06:14:29.692
is something we have pioneered
in Greater Manchester.

1104665619
06:14:29.693 --> 06:14:33.104
We have made these arguments, taken
our detractors head on and won,

3648769278
06:14:33.105 --> 06:14:36.143
and we have done so through
a vision led approach

2316930367
06:14:36.144 --> 06:14:37.848
and through place based delivery.

303908357
06:14:38.141 --> 06:14:40.498
The delivery of the largest
light rail network

1571080571
06:14:41.097 --> 06:14:43.201
in the country has completely transformed

3158568976
06:14:43.203 --> 06:14:47.349
the prospects of tens of thousands
of people in Greater Manchester.

4276889073
06:14:47.350 --> 06:14:49.790
And with the tram arriving
in my constituency

2241415525
06:14:49.790 --> 06:14:51.547
with spades in the ground by 2028,

925127204
06:14:51.548 --> 06:14:53.844
we are closing gaps in provision so that

3643349825
06:14:53.844 --> 06:14:56.748
the whole of Greater
Manchester can benefit,

1724131546
06:14:56.749 --> 06:15:00.207
including Heywood and Middleton North
delivery through a responsive,

1977415042
06:15:00.208 --> 06:15:02.362
integrated and affordable bus service that

1325528621
06:15:02.364 --> 06:15:04.370
reaches all corners of the city region.

1015991385
06:15:04.371 --> 06:15:06.929
Taken back into public
ownership in terms of rail,

4200850095
06:15:06.930 --> 06:15:10.545
I also welcome the government's
Northern Powerhouse Rail Bill,

1316890080
06:15:10.546 --> 06:15:13.896
a clear reflection of our region's
ambition and a firm commitment

1130891505
06:15:13.897 --> 06:15:17.691
from government to decarbonisation
and delivery across the north.

1704981546
06:15:17.692 --> 06:15:21.386
In closing, Madam Deputy Speaker,
I welcome the King's Speech and what

2125652116
06:15:21.387 --> 06:15:24.697
it could mean for my constituents
in Heywood and Middleton North.

1910779169
06:15:24.698 --> 06:15:28.311
And with that being said, I want to
be completely clear the window that

3005278200
06:15:28.312 --> 06:15:31.772
we have to demonstrate that there
is another way is rapidly closing.

2568242162
06:15:31.773 --> 06:15:34.683
The security my constituents
deserve is not a pipe dream.

74032027
06:15:34.683 --> 06:15:36.841
It is entirely deliverable and in my view.

3595848322
06:15:36.842 --> 06:15:37.944
Madam Deputy Speaker.

4014743213
06:15:37.945 --> 06:15:39.298
>> Torcuil Crichton thank.

3151727088
06:15:39.299 --> 06:15:40.803
>> You, Madam Deputy Speaker.

3909721214
06:15:40.804 --> 06:15:42.811
Much of the debate we have heard today,

1934648535
06:15:42.812 --> 06:15:45.674
I heard in the village of yawp
on the Isle of Lewis last

1757809395
06:15:45.675 --> 06:15:50.692
Saturday morning when I visited
there with Donald MacKinnon,

968841220
06:15:50.693 --> 06:15:52.299
our new Labour MSP, for a year.

3772104325
06:15:52.300 --> 06:15:54.154
Donald fought a tremendous campaign.

1240111895
06:15:54.155 --> 06:15:57.818
He'd be a brilliant MSP who raced
against the tide for the Western Isles

2865621856
06:15:58.146 --> 06:16:00.152
and kept the Atlantic beacon alight for

1313424856
06:16:00.153 --> 06:16:02.493
Labour during our summer squalls.

1138004166
06:16:02.494 --> 06:16:05.695
And I must pay tribute to
Doctor Arthur Allen for his

674683428
06:16:05.696 --> 06:16:08.946
public service to the Islands
MSP over many years.

1089770274
06:16:08.947 --> 06:16:11.155
And just as the islands
were at a political

3848875668
06:16:11.156 --> 06:16:12.700
tipping point the other week,

1050123069
06:16:12.701 --> 06:16:16.848
so too are they at the fulcrum of
this debate over energy security.

1402983497
06:16:16.849 --> 06:16:19.709
To the east, the District of
Ness looks to the mainland,

1138926972
06:16:19.710 --> 06:16:22.771
over the horizon, to the North
Sea, with much of its wealth,

3838706958
06:16:22.772 --> 06:16:26.436
has come from over the past decade out
to the west as the wild Atlantic,

3009617510
06:16:26.437 --> 06:16:29.096
from where the wealth of
wind will provide and power

4042480515
06:16:29.097 --> 06:16:31.503
the transition away from
carbon and renewables.

1906308203
06:16:31.504 --> 06:16:32.992
And at this football ground,

3476471266
06:16:32.993 --> 06:16:35.500
where the under eight were
in fierce competition,

1383217657
06:16:35.501 --> 06:16:37.644
one parent gave me his simple political

3085765250
06:16:37.645 --> 06:16:39.501
priority to keep the North Sea open.

3953008801
06:16:39.502 --> 06:16:42.564
It has provided him and his
family with the means to stay on

1053419174
06:16:42.565 --> 06:16:45.724
the island and many other families
around that football pitch,

1866259368
06:16:45.725 --> 06:16:48.783
although that means that many
mothers are effectively single

313715612
06:16:48.784 --> 06:16:51.190
parent families with half
the children's lives.

1756379062
06:16:51.191 --> 06:16:54.150
And just further up the road,
walking our neighbour's dog.

428109461
06:16:54.151 --> 06:16:56.156
Another constituent stopped us to state

1354320645
06:16:56.157 --> 06:16:58.173
our concerns and objections about

3528803209
06:16:58.174 --> 06:17:01.583
plans for a multinational 900
megawatt offshore wind turbine array,

3480949370
06:17:01.584 --> 06:17:03.590
which, being less than four miles away,

3625357171
06:17:03.591 --> 06:17:06.245
is actually really near
shore rather than offshore.

94677248
06:17:06.246 --> 06:17:09.594
And both these conversations
reflect the concerns of many

1043494781
06:17:09.596 --> 06:17:12.203
who find the scale of this
transition overwhelming,

3913007192
06:17:12.204 --> 06:17:14.311
who feel they are not being carried along

2493521727
06:17:14.312 --> 06:17:16.117
in the journey to renewable energy,

1261930129
06:17:16.118 --> 06:17:18.625
and that workers
and communities affected by this

3802215719
06:17:18.626 --> 06:17:20.983
revolution are in danger
of being left behind.

2618958715
06:17:22.144 --> 06:17:25.644
Now, previous governments
have not backed community

4209011705
06:17:25.645 --> 06:17:27.852
energy on a scale that
they previously did,

1789406569
06:17:28.336 --> 06:17:33.146
and I look forward to GB energy
and the new energy Bill energy,

3630063907
06:17:33.147 --> 06:17:35.604
enabling a big leap forward
in community energy.

638276156
06:17:35.605 --> 06:17:39.117
And when it comes to the North Sea,
these guys are skilled engineers,

4121184624
06:17:39.118 --> 06:17:40.822
mariners, experts in their field.

2059701950
06:17:40.823 --> 06:17:43.130
They know the North Sea
is a declining field,

3590188892
06:17:43.132 --> 06:17:45.940
but they also know that
the technicalities of tiebacks,

2947263676
06:17:45.941 --> 06:17:48.197
which this government
hasn't made enough of,

954135450
06:17:48.198 --> 06:17:51.058
are the quickest way to bring
onstream more oil and gas.

3005574365
06:17:51.058 --> 06:17:53.566
Some 2.5 million barrels
could be developed using

3868247718
06:17:53.567 --> 06:17:55.999
subsidy tiebacks
and these guys in the North

1639260881
06:17:56.000 --> 06:17:59.451
Sea want what that guy
at the football pitch

4037244768
06:17:59.453 --> 06:18:02.145
wanted certainty
and an orderly transition,

3208454581
06:18:02.146 --> 06:18:05.493
but that puts their jobs at
the centre of this transition.

1937412286
06:18:05.494 --> 06:18:08.001
And the Ministers knows
from visiting the islands

3838271806
06:18:08.002 --> 06:18:10.157
and talking to community energy companies,

1016931374
06:18:10.158 --> 06:18:13.859
that we are at the centre of
transition and produce more energy

1824322092
06:18:13.860 --> 06:18:17.453
than any other than any other
place in the in the in the UK.

593968779
06:18:17.454 --> 06:18:20.748
The problem is that there is no
space to get that energy out,

2991923327
06:18:20.749 --> 06:18:24.997
that commercial companies are
dominating the 1.8GW interconnector.

3116115757
06:18:24.998 --> 06:18:28.104
And I urge the Ministers,
as I have urged him before,

2685988886
06:18:28.105 --> 06:18:29.497
not to talk to Nyiso,

3191916315
06:18:29.498 --> 06:18:32.696
but to sit on Neso Ofgem
on the grid operators,

2813817772
06:18:32.697 --> 06:18:35.640
to find a route through
and to expand community

858424904
06:18:35.641 --> 06:18:37.796
owned energy islands and indeed elsewhere.

2439566672
06:18:37.797 --> 06:18:39.151
>> Jen Craft Madam Deputy.

98439091
06:18:39.152 --> 06:18:39.753
>> Speaker.

939631991
06:18:39.754 --> 06:18:42.413
>> Earlier this year I had
the pleasure of welcoming

4280698278
06:18:42.414 --> 06:18:45.071
the Energy Ministers to my
constituency in Thurrock,

599046578
06:18:45.144 --> 06:18:47.051
where we took part in the blessing of

3252295627
06:18:47.052 --> 06:18:49.698
a tunnel underneath the Thames and that

444870927
06:18:49.699 --> 06:18:51.706
formed the final part of the Tilbury to

3500751905
06:18:51.707 --> 06:18:53.512
Grane upgrade of the National Grid.

1211191861
06:18:53.513 --> 06:18:55.722
And I reflected at
the time it put us right

3026649805
06:18:56.144 --> 06:18:57.900
at the forefront of seeing a green

264306344
06:18:57.901 --> 06:19:02.895
energy revolution in my constituency
of Thurrock and once again Tilbury.

3145562359
06:19:02.896 --> 06:19:04.953
This place on the estuary of the Thames,

910342541
06:19:04.954 --> 06:19:08.364
is playing its part in delivering
and securing our nation's future.

1385130847
06:19:08.365 --> 06:19:11.928
And I think it's very pertinent to
the debate today as we hear whether

3247923346
06:19:11.929 --> 06:19:15.996
or not we need to continue with our
slavish devotion to fossil fuels,

1111835938
06:19:15.997 --> 06:19:19.201
or whether we actually look
to switch to a greener,

2968412022
06:19:19.201 --> 06:19:22.747
better future for our children
and our grandchildren.

157046608
06:19:22.748 --> 06:19:25.357
This makes sense for
the planet and for the pocket.

2324191487
06:19:25.358 --> 06:19:28.369
We know that the cost of
transition to clean energy is less

4186350665
06:19:28.370 --> 06:19:31.502
than the cost incurred by one
fossil fuel crisis alone.

3769013963
06:19:31.503 --> 06:19:34.162
And with the recent action
that has happened in Iran

102216286
06:19:34.163 --> 06:19:36.922
and the impact that that has
on people's energy bills,

1060999462
06:19:36.923 --> 06:19:40.949
we can really see
the crucial and pressing nature

2992340812
06:19:40.950 --> 06:19:43.257
of affecting this switch
as soon as possible.

2485958957
06:19:43.258 --> 06:19:43.659
And in.

2666202822
06:19:43.660 --> 06:19:44.614
>> I thank my hon.

1142778157
06:19:44.615 --> 06:19:45.996
Friend for giving away.

2416079583
06:19:45.997 --> 06:19:48.052
She mentioned investment in green energy

648564602
06:19:48.053 --> 06:19:49.857
Beckenham and Penge my constituency

127256016
06:19:49.858 --> 06:19:53.597
has had significant investment
from GB energy over £700,000

1968362980
06:19:53.598 --> 06:19:56.808
for rooftop solar panels at
the NHS Bethlehem Hospital and also

2582690332
06:19:56.808 --> 06:19:59.665
on local primary schools like
Harris Primary Shortlands.

4187725735
06:19:59.666 --> 06:20:00.871
Does she agree with me?

3059281732
06:20:00.872 --> 06:20:03.630
It's a win win for everyone,
good for the environment,

753120981
06:20:03.632 --> 06:20:06.742
good for bills and more money
spent on patients and students.

2925049194
06:20:06.743 --> 06:20:07.697
>> I thank my hon.

600493709
06:20:07.698 --> 06:20:10.859
Friend for his intervention
and I very much do agree with him.

4276668915
06:20:10.860 --> 06:20:13.568
And indeed, a secondary
school in my constituency has

2364046512
06:20:13.569 --> 06:20:16.025
benefited from
the installation of solar panels,

4021197711
06:20:16.026 --> 06:20:19.336
and I expect to see their energy
bill reduce quite significantly,

517597780
06:20:19.337 --> 06:20:22.499
which will make a huge impact on
what they are able to deliver

2268888183
06:20:22.500 --> 06:20:25.459
for their students in their
school and in my constituency.

3669771715
06:20:25.460 --> 06:20:28.844
We are already seeing benefits
from the switch to green energy.

1550505006
06:20:28.846 --> 06:20:31.003
I recently helped to open the Green Energy

3531279919
06:20:31.004 --> 06:20:32.558
Centre at South Essex College,

3048073357
06:20:32.558 --> 06:20:37.499
which is helping people train
and retrain in retrofitting homes,

2101408041
06:20:37.500 --> 06:20:41.062
existing homes to become bill free
and to really reduce the price that

3688139759
06:20:41.063 --> 06:20:44.325
people have to pay to heat their
homes and get energy into them.

4288555937
06:20:44.326 --> 06:20:46.046
And the Thames Free port.

1935905728
06:20:46.047 --> 06:20:49.146
A large proportion of which
is in my constituency,

3039327590
06:20:49.147 --> 06:20:53.447
is a real focus on
renewable energy and will

2876940804
06:20:53.448 --> 06:20:55.755
bring career lifelong
jobs for people who can

2426333934
06:20:55.755 --> 06:20:57.862
really look to stay local and work local,

3723053367
06:20:57.864 --> 06:20:59.719
and will have a huge transformation,

3216839590
06:21:00.148 --> 06:21:02.504
could potentially have
a huge transformational

1928273053
06:21:02.505 --> 06:21:05.407
change to the lives of
people who live in Thurrock.

1041507022
06:21:05.408 --> 06:21:07.565
I firmly hope that the new Reform Council,

886299768
06:21:07.566 --> 06:21:09.900
and I see that there are
no members on their

2903955048
06:21:09.901 --> 06:21:13.356
bench here to represent that party,

1455970521
06:21:13.357 --> 06:21:16.898
will continue on this approach
and will engage in seeing

150384745
06:21:16.900 --> 06:21:19.407
the economic success that
places like the Thames,

739901920
06:21:19.408 --> 06:21:22.351
Freeport and their focus
on renewables can bring,

3689192890
06:21:22.352 --> 06:21:26.110
and that they are not
blinded by sheer political

608950159
06:21:26.111 --> 06:21:28.752
ideology to really
hamper the progress that

3822592080
06:21:28.753 --> 06:21:31.302
people in my part of the world can make.

3297322383
06:21:31.303 --> 06:21:34.803
However, given that their first
act in office was removing

1384293881
06:21:34.804 --> 06:21:37.861
the Ukrainian flag flying outside
Thurrock counsel's office,

305962939
06:21:38.147 --> 06:21:40.705
which had previously been
there to show solidarity

3840937669
06:21:41.106 --> 06:21:43.110
and resistance to Russian expansionism.

2238075196
06:21:43.111 --> 06:21:45.017
One of the greatest threats, I think,

215312716
06:21:45.018 --> 06:21:48.005
facing Europe at this time,
I wouldn't hold out much hope.

3823601381
06:21:48.005 --> 06:21:50.451
Indeed, it seems that Vladimir Putin

993457996
06:21:50.451 --> 06:21:53.898
is indeed getting his money's worth.

2604708542
06:21:53.900 --> 06:21:57.551
And talking of malign foreign
influence in our democracy.

1095967246
06:21:57.552 --> 06:22:02.454
I very strongly welcome measures
outlined in the King's Speech around

3997713512
06:22:02.455 --> 06:22:05.966
the Representation of the People
Bill in order to tackle this threat,

3300418235
06:22:05.967 --> 06:22:07.969
tightening foreign political donations,

1835891731
06:22:07.971 --> 06:22:10.027
strengthening the role and the powers of

2877031884
06:22:10.028 --> 06:22:11.933
the Electoral Commission will go far.

1739501514
06:22:11.933 --> 06:22:16.064
However, I fear we are at
a precipice and find in

3431778176
06:22:16.065 --> 06:22:20.002
finding an existential
threat to our democracy.

677292257
06:22:20.003 --> 06:22:25.647
Social media algorithms have
a parasitic relationship with populism,

2629584303
06:22:25.648 --> 06:22:27.705
both driven by outrage, anger, fear and.

3834205637
06:22:28.161 --> 06:22:31.498
They poison our social discourse
and our public space.

3938782671
06:22:31.499 --> 06:22:33.605
We know that 18 million Facebook accounts

2029521943
06:22:35.147 --> 06:22:37.103
were harvested and mine to gather data

1706556546
06:22:37.104 --> 06:22:39.259
on how to psychologically manipulate users

582406073
06:22:39.260 --> 06:22:40.967
in the run up to the Brexit vote,

1982121024
06:22:40.968 --> 06:22:43.978
and in the run up to the first
Trump presidential campaign.

3084401854
06:22:43.979 --> 06:22:46.802
Again, Vladimir Putin
getting his money's worth.

2275365107
06:22:46.803 --> 06:22:49.201
The government must take action to stand

995240338
06:22:49.203 --> 06:22:51.260
up to Big Tech and urgently address this

76740122
06:22:51.261 --> 06:22:55.903
threat before the damage
done to our democratic

3086766668
06:22:55.904 --> 06:22:57.356
institutions is irreparable.

2846691230
06:22:57.357 --> 06:22:58.058
>> Thank you.

3915740535
06:22:58.059 --> 06:23:01.949
>> Madam Deputy Speaker,
and as today's remarks

1319075260
06:23:01.950 --> 06:23:03.854
focus on key national infrastructure,

2964965325
06:23:03.855 --> 06:23:07.749
I thought I would speak briefly
on the Clean Water Bill,

3390488605
06:23:07.750 --> 06:23:11.501
which was outlined in the King's
Speech, which is another essential

776293049
06:23:11.502 --> 06:23:16.512
piece of national infrastructure
that is long overdue for reform.

3440792076
06:23:16.513 --> 06:23:20.126
Like many in this House, I welcome
the clean water bill with open arms.

1297092205
06:23:20.127 --> 06:23:23.200
And as I see it, the bill
is our best opportunity

3817455557
06:23:23.201 --> 06:23:27.050
to create a water sector
which puts bill payers,

306588917
06:23:27.051 --> 06:23:30.099
water users and the environment first.

690495563
06:23:30.100 --> 06:23:32.357
For too long, it has
felt like shareholders,

3029551599
06:23:32.358 --> 06:23:34.563
overseas investment
banks or indeed private

3044550928
06:23:34.564 --> 06:23:36.570
equity firms have been at the forefront

3286124267
06:23:36.571 --> 06:23:39.752
of the priority of the water industry.

2229667777
06:23:39.753 --> 06:23:41.760
That I hope will change with this bill,

688980031
06:23:41.761 --> 06:23:43.467
and I am pleased that this builds

645648467
06:23:43.468 --> 06:23:47.346
upon the early action already
taken by this Labour government.

1040816984
06:23:47.347 --> 06:23:50.909
For me, I think what's most important
is that my constituents in South

3394082834
06:23:50.910 --> 06:23:55.598
Dorset know that getting the clean
water bill right really matters.

257734298
06:23:55.599 --> 06:23:57.254
We're so proud of our coastline.

2454873531
06:23:57.255 --> 06:24:00.699
It is perhaps the most impressive,
certainly in the southwest,

3320324883
06:24:00.700 --> 06:24:02.155
if not in the whole country.

3539435651
06:24:02.156 --> 06:24:06.501
So protecting that coastline from
unwanted and unwanted sewage

1223087963
06:24:06.502 --> 06:24:09.058
spills and failing water
companies really matters.

597359683
06:24:09.058 --> 06:24:11.165
And that's why this bill matters as well.

4227344354
06:24:11.166 --> 06:24:12.020
>> Well, my hon.

454519249
06:24:12.021 --> 06:24:13.324
Friend, give way happily.

6852013
06:24:13.325 --> 06:24:15.231
I'm actually quite jealous of my hon.

499026275
06:24:15.232 --> 06:24:17.890
Friend because his beaches
were listed at about four

501474547
06:24:17.891 --> 06:24:20.299
of them in the top beaches
in timeout recently.

2273883811
06:24:20.300 --> 06:24:23.112
But I did visit Durdle door
with him to call for a year

491513248
06:24:23.112 --> 06:24:25.521
round water testing
and to clean up our waters.

435935230
06:24:25.522 --> 06:24:28.031
So does he agree that this
bill will take further

3845639028
06:24:28.032 --> 06:24:29.938
the action to clean up sewage spills?

274679261
06:24:29.939 --> 06:24:31.593
That we've taken action already.

3473548343
06:24:31.594 --> 06:24:33.350
>> I completely agree with my hon.

2476298445
06:24:33.351 --> 06:24:33.751
Friend.

2809984485
06:24:33.752 --> 06:24:36.058
This certainly builds
upon the early progress

3565064752
06:24:36.058 --> 06:24:38.116
that has been made to be most effective.

2232296036
06:24:38.117 --> 06:24:41.587
I think the Clean Water
Bill does need to include

378054671
06:24:41.588 --> 06:24:43.593
a clear understanding that there should

317886203
06:24:43.594 --> 06:24:46.111
be a meaningful duty for
all water companies

2925614210
06:24:46.112 --> 06:24:47.817
to operate in the public benefit.

3305837119
06:24:47.818 --> 06:24:52.208
We all know that the current
model for ownership in the water

3413507994
06:24:52.209 --> 06:24:55.168
sector is failing both public
and the environment as well.

1685489774
06:24:56.152 --> 06:24:58.557
And instead of fixing
crumbling infrastructure,

1597057312
06:24:58.558 --> 06:25:01.115
water companies have been
lining their own pockets

3315616590
06:25:01.148 --> 06:25:03.155
and accumulating debt for far too long.

789512519
06:25:03.156 --> 06:25:07.652
Until we have that clear obligation
for the big water companies

1810310648
06:25:07.653 --> 06:25:10.602
to deliver both public
and environmental benefit.

1626480873
06:25:10.603 --> 06:25:12.809
I fear they will continue
to make decisions

1523581056
06:25:13.152 --> 06:25:14.906
that increase their profit shares,

638190495
06:25:14.907 --> 06:25:18.450
but also vandalise our coastlines.

3842924347
06:25:18.451 --> 06:25:21.713
This is why a duty to operate in
the public benefit is critical.

2506043577
06:25:21.714 --> 06:25:26.652
It will help to overhaul the day to
day operations of water companies

3823183368
06:25:26.653 --> 06:25:30.065
and change the corporate culture
at the top of many of these firms.

4041951652
06:25:30.066 --> 06:25:33.377
If we look elsewhere to similar
sectors where you have this duty,

1861655553
06:25:33.378 --> 06:25:35.606
it does begin to change the culture,

439643436
06:25:35.607 --> 06:25:39.408
such as, for example, in public
transport and buses in particular.

107360500
06:25:40.152 --> 06:25:41.708
I think what for me is really,

807341560
06:25:41.709 --> 06:25:44.813
really important is that
within the clean water bill,

2376701642
06:25:44.814 --> 06:25:48.265
the government can and should
use this as an opportunity

1005013772
06:25:48.266 --> 06:25:51.409
to move towards a different
way of the water sector,

3780318595
06:25:53.153 --> 06:25:55.509
operating with a different
model of ownership.

1841530243
06:25:55.510 --> 06:25:58.561
I think that can only be
achieved if we start to compel

3033550009
06:25:58.562 --> 06:26:00.719
water companies to act in a different way,

987689647
06:26:02.147 --> 06:26:04.856
and that requires a mechanism
such as public benefit.

582473076
06:26:05.155 --> 06:26:10.005
I think what I would just say
is that this bill is a golden

1235346456
06:26:10.007 --> 06:26:13.304
opportunity to put the public
and the environment first,

3138984906
06:26:13.305 --> 06:26:18.558
and is our chance to fundamentally
reform the water sector for good.

2512417371
06:26:18.559 --> 06:26:21.166
>> Connor Naismith thank
you, Madam Deputy Speaker.

777484384
06:26:21.168 --> 06:26:24.127
Please to speak for my constituents
in Crewe and Nantwich.

1597754108
06:26:24.128 --> 06:26:24.680
>> On the.

2043799901
06:26:24.681 --> 06:26:27.661
>> Legislative agenda set
out in The King's Speech,

3151309109
06:26:27.662 --> 06:26:33.010
a programme designed
over the basics in life.

1152047329
06:26:33.011 --> 06:26:34.465
And for to restore security,

1991167594
06:26:34.466 --> 06:26:36.823
stability and control
over the basics in life.

3766031449
06:26:36.824 --> 06:26:40.505
And for too long, our people
have felt the consequences

649993308
06:26:40.505 --> 06:26:43.766
of economic shocks over
which they have no control,

3075683233
06:26:43.767 --> 06:26:48.903
and an economic model which
doesn't work for them.

1121274844
06:26:48.904 --> 06:26:52.258
Now is the time to break that
model and build something new,

3547804062
06:26:52.259 --> 06:26:55.608
which serves every community
across our great country.

1698648198
06:26:57.155 --> 06:26:59.261
You can't improve what you don't control.

2406490142
06:26:59.262 --> 06:27:02.597
And the legacy of the last
40 years is that the British

2976847157
06:27:03.110 --> 06:27:05.366
state has relinquished
too much control over

3816850220
06:27:07.151 --> 06:27:09.759
those things which impact
the pounds in the pockets

2457985608
06:27:09.760 --> 06:27:13.118
and the life chances
of the British people.

2668746861
06:27:14.154 --> 06:27:18.502
Control over the basics means
securing our everyday lives,

3338384667
06:27:18.503 --> 06:27:20.158
and that starts with the energy,

868370007
06:27:20.159 --> 06:27:22.806
heating our homes
and powering our industry.

3310960877
06:27:22.807 --> 06:27:29.063
The Energy Independence Bill and
the Electricity Generator Levy Bill

3668419027
06:27:29.064 --> 06:27:32.402
represent a structural shift in
how this country powers itself.

765134351
06:27:32.403 --> 06:27:34.753
Crucially, by breaking the broken link

2964864543
06:27:34.754 --> 06:27:36.657
between electricity and skyrocketing,

1684408679
06:27:38.153 --> 06:27:40.558
skyrocketing gas prices
and investing in clean,

3916931854
06:27:40.559 --> 06:27:47.257
home grown energy of the future,
thereby permanently shielding

1671833809
06:27:47.258 --> 06:27:49.612
working families from
volatile global markets.

1637005727
06:27:49.614 --> 06:27:53.854
However, I must challenge
the government to go further

3855546343
06:27:53.855 --> 06:27:56.601
by restoring control over another utility,

1325300059
06:27:56.602 --> 06:28:01.356
that being the water
that flows through our

2508838454
06:28:01.357 --> 06:28:03.263
taps and into our rivers and streams,

215077334
06:28:03.264 --> 06:28:08.749
and the private water monopolies
strip out private equity from

3578724852
06:28:08.750 --> 06:28:12.117
this basic necessity and ensure
that every pound spent in this

3332241447
06:28:12.118 --> 06:28:15.759
system goes towards investing
in the infrastructure

2335797902
06:28:15.760 --> 06:28:16.912
and controlling bills,

384296760
06:28:19.156 --> 06:28:21.511
not towards shareholder
dividends and profits.

286026566
06:28:23.156 --> 06:28:23.607
I won't.

3730730354
06:28:23.608 --> 06:28:27.951
It's time to bring water
back under public control,

2490415714
06:28:27.953 --> 06:28:31.108
ensuring that this life
essential utility is managed

3151779994
06:28:31.109 --> 06:28:34.208
as a secure public good,
not a private commodity.

812490096
06:28:34.209 --> 06:28:37.805
And in the time I have
remaining, Madam Deputy Speaker,

2624046646
06:28:37.806 --> 06:28:39.562
I wish to talk about high streets.

1340245310
06:28:39.563 --> 06:28:42.221
High streets are the visible
heartbeat of our towns,

3862481416
06:28:42.222 --> 06:28:44.229
and I warmly welcome the steps taken by

3976386865
06:28:44.230 --> 06:28:47.802
this government to date to
support local authorities,

148408123
06:28:47.803 --> 06:28:49.558
to intervene, to fill empty shops.

644881271
06:28:49.558 --> 06:28:52.061
But intervention is only half the battle.

3837011773
06:28:52.062 --> 06:28:54.268
We must also cultivate
an environment where

4059690287
06:28:54.269 --> 06:28:58.858
small businesses can genuinely succeed.

3330054842
06:28:58.859 --> 06:29:01.465
Hospitality businesses are
vital to that endeavour,

2749152866
06:29:01.466 --> 06:29:03.858
and I call on the government to

3506468087
06:29:03.859 --> 06:29:06.314
support hospitality together
and and hospitality

1228122239
06:29:06.315 --> 06:29:07.868
businesses in my constituency.

1102885770
06:29:07.869 --> 06:29:11.912
In calling for a sector specific
VAT cut for hospitality.

2397986217
06:29:12.156 --> 06:29:15.505
While there is room to go
further, this King's Speech

4077558244
06:29:15.507 --> 06:29:17.912
delivers a comprehensive
framework of security.

2126331621
06:29:17.913 --> 06:29:20.020
It tells the people of Crewe and Nantwich

2751650653
06:29:20.021 --> 06:29:22.028
that the state is back in their corner.

1999398196
06:29:22.029 --> 06:29:23.432
>> Secure Catherine Fookes.

1798214106
06:29:23.433 --> 06:29:26.241
>> Madam Deputy Speaker, I'm
delighted that measures in

3121122574
06:29:26.242 --> 06:29:29.099
the King's Speech will strengthen
our economic security,

4207142667
06:29:29.100 --> 06:29:31.757
our national security
and what we're debating today,

1046822973
06:29:31.758 --> 06:29:32.809
our energy security.

3913842587
06:29:33.157 --> 06:29:36.553
And while the Tories
and Reform want to ditch our net

105191704
06:29:36.554 --> 06:29:39.509
zero policies and our clean
power targets is a huge

1642270128
06:29:39.510 --> 06:29:42.460
relief to people in
Monmouthshire and across

2438369857
06:29:42.461 --> 06:29:45.119
the UK that Labour is taking
clean energy seriously.

2731311583
06:29:45.120 --> 06:29:49.207
And anyone hearing the debate
from those opposite today would

3432818993
06:29:49.208 --> 06:29:52.459
think they wanted to take us
back to oil lamps and candles,

2744927
06:29:52.460 --> 06:29:57.264
such as their disdain for
clean energy and modern ways.

1725095544
06:29:57.265 --> 06:30:01.753
I'd also like to flag today my strong
support for the clean water Bill.

916389374
06:30:01.754 --> 06:30:05.809
Rivers such as the Wye and ask in
my constituency of Monmouthshire

793561102
06:30:05.811 --> 06:30:07.916
are incredibly important to the people of

3939070437
06:30:07.918 --> 06:30:10.676
Monmouthshire and they are
polluted and we must tackle

730625100
06:30:10.677 --> 06:30:13.235
this and I'm really pleased
that we're doing that.

70140385
06:30:13.236 --> 06:30:18.862
With stronger regulation promised
by the Clean Water Bill.

1385932458
06:30:18.864 --> 06:30:22.272
People in Monmouthshire are facing
the realities of our dependence,

1322847063
06:30:22.273 --> 06:30:24.605
though, on global oil and gas markets,

4175895180
06:30:24.606 --> 06:30:28.112
and many of us in the countryside
rely on heating oil or LPG

1985454379
06:30:28.114 --> 06:30:31.125
and have little choice but to
pay up when the prices spike.

3202735779
06:30:31.126 --> 06:30:35.869
And earlier this year, a woman in her
70s wrote to me and told me her,

1336150337
06:30:38.155 --> 06:30:43.016
quote, for 500l of oil had risen
by £250 in less than a week,

1939577341
06:30:43.017 --> 06:30:45.574
and others are hamstrung
as their electricity bill

1373291390
06:30:45.575 --> 06:30:48.605
goes up or as their commute
gets more expensive.

223497072
06:30:48.606 --> 06:30:51.008
And all this is triggered by international

3272705061
06:30:51.009 --> 06:30:53.757
conflict that is out of the UK's hands.

1519916762
06:30:53.758 --> 06:30:55.614
And that is why Labour has delivered

993830518
06:30:55.615 --> 06:30:57.719
the biggest ever investment in Home-grown

3025554146
06:30:57.721 --> 06:31:01.762
clean power in British history,
including Wylfa in North Wales,

1598924056
06:31:01.763 --> 06:31:05.610
as part of the biggest nuclear
building programme in half a century,

3463510666
06:31:05.611 --> 06:31:09.365
and serious investment also in tidal
power off the coast of Wales.

4005776940
06:31:09.366 --> 06:31:11.811
And I must point out to the frontbench

822458728
06:31:11.812 --> 06:31:14.204
that there is a really big potential

3519267316
06:31:14.205 --> 06:31:17.413
in the River Severn that borders
my Monmouthshire constituency,

3471560893
06:31:17.414 --> 06:31:21.610
and it would be an amazing
spot for new tidal projects.

4102499327
06:31:21.611 --> 06:31:26.717
So I do hope the Ministers
can respond to that later.

3421961289
06:31:27.152 --> 06:31:29.558
The Climate Change Act,
the Climate Change Act,

2086337262
06:31:30.158 --> 06:31:32.666
has been emulated all over
the world as a leading

3745626129
06:31:33.158 --> 06:31:35.364
framework to Budget
and plan our emissions,

994748786
06:31:35.365 --> 06:31:38.309
and hold governments
accountable for polluting

1798531060
06:31:38.311 --> 06:31:40.660
the Tories who did support it years ago,

3391208119
06:31:40.661 --> 06:31:44.871
now want to scrap it,
reform back fracking and

601875196
06:31:44.872 --> 06:31:49.757
the deputy leader actually
calls net zero a cult.

167669350
06:31:49.758 --> 06:31:52.314
The Energy Independence
Bill and other legislation

2497025606
06:31:52.315 --> 06:31:54.171
set out in The King's Speech affirms

1681771216
06:31:54.172 --> 06:31:56.126
this Labour government's commitment to

624565653
06:31:56.127 --> 06:31:57.930
harnessing clean, home-grown power.

2263226924
06:31:57.931 --> 06:32:02.456
And I'm proud to back
the government that takes

1069240064
06:32:02.457 --> 06:32:04.562
decisions that protect our natural world,

173651732
06:32:04.563 --> 06:32:09.415
our natural world, our
security and our wallets.

367492126
06:32:09.416 --> 06:32:12.512
These decisions will not
only benefit my generation,

2012574527
06:32:12.513 --> 06:32:14.458
but also generations to come.

1052527328
06:32:14.459 --> 06:32:17.909
>> Sureena Brackenridge
Madam Deputy Speaker.

2514334156
06:32:17.910 --> 06:32:18.211
>> I.

1799112272
06:32:18.212 --> 06:32:23.657
>> Welcome His Majesty's gracious
speech as it puts energy security,

812016152
06:32:23.658 --> 06:32:27.407
economic security
and industrial renewal back

3794449897
06:32:27.408 --> 06:32:29.515
on track for the people that I represent.

3019179411
06:32:30.153 --> 06:32:33.660
Wolverhampton and Willenhall has
a proud history of industry,

1519991555
06:32:33.661 --> 06:32:34.964
innovation and hard work.

788995077
06:32:34.965 --> 06:32:38.311
From our foundries
and factories to our engineering

4241819283
06:32:38.312 --> 06:32:41.413
and manufacturing expertise,

1893695268
06:32:41.414 --> 06:32:44.616
our communities help power Britain's

3496523897
06:32:44.617 --> 06:32:46.572
and the global growth for generations.

3722216817
06:32:46.573 --> 06:32:52.510
Yet the policies of the past
are taking their toll today.

3646670853
06:32:52.511 --> 06:32:56.016
Policies of turning the UK
away from manufacturing,

2469181571
06:32:56.017 --> 06:32:57.370
away from council housing,

3554750221
06:32:57.371 --> 06:33:02.975
away from public ownership all being
felt today by my communities.

3336890506
06:33:02.976 --> 06:33:06.505
One of the most pressing issues facing

547483583
06:33:06.507 --> 06:33:08.412
our country today is energy security.

818798131
06:33:08.413 --> 06:33:13.556
Recent energy crises exposed how
vulnerable Britain has become.

3078878602
06:33:13.557 --> 06:33:17.962
In fact, half of the UK's
recessions since the 1970s

4041471082
06:33:17.963 --> 06:33:21.857
have been caused by
exposure to fossil fuels.

2129789111
06:33:21.858 --> 06:33:25.964
The only way to have true
sovereignty for our country

2332240202
06:33:25.965 --> 06:33:29.564
is to be in control of our own energy.

3541545847
06:33:29.565 --> 06:33:32.811
That is why I strongly
welcome the government's

458786944
06:33:32.812 --> 06:33:34.114
Energy Independence Bill,

2148492922
06:33:34.115 --> 06:33:36.465
which recognises that Britain must get off

3083582372
06:33:36.466 --> 06:33:40.162
the fossil fuel roller coaster with clean,

1694696063
06:33:40.163 --> 06:33:46.068
home-grown power, that
we control ourselves.

2735847009
06:33:46.069 --> 06:33:47.022
The I won't sorry.

2478321353
06:33:47.022 --> 06:33:50.282
The bill takes important steps to
tackle rising household bills,

2288797919
06:33:50.283 --> 06:33:52.737
strengthen protections for
vulnerable households

787985393
06:33:54.156 --> 06:33:56.264
and pave the way for the Warm Homes plan.

974381682
06:33:56.265 --> 06:34:00.216
It also rightly accelerates
Britain's drive

571935672
06:34:00.217 --> 06:34:02.367
for energy security by speeding up

3408694424
06:34:02.368 --> 06:34:07.157
investment in clean power
grid infrastructure

2240159929
06:34:07.158 --> 06:34:08.561
and modern energy networks.

2736742996
06:34:08.562 --> 06:34:10.766
Wolverhampton is already
positioning itself

2819880522
06:34:10.767 --> 06:34:12.672
at the forefront of green innovation,

1463458168
06:34:12.673 --> 06:34:15.511
with investment in advanced manufacturing,

2334531266
06:34:15.512 --> 06:34:18.212
clean technologies and green innovation

2728238761
06:34:18.213 --> 06:34:21.706
corridor by linking the University

2409745558
06:34:21.707 --> 06:34:26.765
of Wolverhampton with the Science
Park and the I 54 manufacturing hub,

2910361110
06:34:26.766 --> 06:34:31.165
the corridor brings together
research, industry and skills.

3449340792
06:34:31.165 --> 06:34:34.512
Wentzville Tata Steel Park is home to

1099697815
06:34:34.513 --> 06:34:37.361
the UK's largest steel processing plant,

4219300343
06:34:37.362 --> 06:34:40.362
and generations of local
families have dedicated

2533259657
06:34:40.364 --> 06:34:43.368
their working lives to
steel and manufacturing.

3339653551
06:34:43.369 --> 06:34:45.862
So I'm calling for British made steel to

3682444521
06:34:45.862 --> 06:34:49.557
build the infrastructure of the future,

3472599019
06:34:49.558 --> 06:34:52.657
where the wind turbines,
railways and energy networks.

2740090830
06:34:52.658 --> 06:34:55.005
Backing steel means
creating apprenticeships,

1888478374
06:34:55.007 --> 06:34:57.456
expanding technical
education and giving young

3562805707
06:34:57.457 --> 06:35:02.760
people in Wolverhampton
North East the opportunity

1058966223
06:35:02.761 --> 06:35:04.566
to build rewarding careers at home.

1229210819
06:35:04.567 --> 06:35:06.014
>> And Jim Dickson.

981129958
06:35:06.015 --> 06:35:07.068
>> Thank you, Madam.

302693876
06:35:07.069 --> 06:35:08.021
>> Deputy Speaker.

3449790431
06:35:08.022 --> 06:35:09.877
>> I'm grateful for the opportunity.

2619549360
06:35:09.878 --> 06:35:12.318
>> To speak today, because
it's vital that we

1917932504
06:35:13.157 --> 06:35:15.214
transition to a new era of clean energy,

473393363
06:35:15.215 --> 06:35:17.520
driving our nation's
energy security forward,

975160770
06:35:17.521 --> 06:35:22.456
whilst rebuilding our public services
and backing businesses to grow.

3914218998
06:35:22.457 --> 06:35:25.556
And one of the most telling
themes that emerges

4198901254
06:35:25.557 --> 06:35:27.562
from what businesses in my constituency

1174269698
06:35:27.563 --> 06:35:31.209
of Dartford tell me at one of our
regular roundtable meetings,

3212801391
06:35:31.210 --> 06:35:36.059
is the slowness of our country to
create the infrastructure our economy

730772487
06:35:36.061 --> 06:35:41.868
needs to succeed and underpin
this transition to clean energy.

1444740439
06:35:41.869 --> 06:35:45.901
Of the 35 bills in the speech,
there are many which help build,

1544571595
06:35:45.902 --> 06:35:49.724
build and boost economic growth
and strengthen our energy security,

390848149
06:35:49.725 --> 06:35:54.165
including the Energy
Independence Bill and the Energy

4100444008
06:35:54.166 --> 06:35:56.575
Generator Levy Bill that
seek to break the link

2441375414
06:35:56.576 --> 06:35:59.312
between electricity and gas
prices by moving older

1305440814
06:35:59.313 --> 06:36:02.761
generators onto new fixed price contracts.

1320089239
06:36:02.762 --> 06:36:08.367
One of the bills is particularly
welcome to my constituents,

3713357484
06:36:08.368 --> 06:36:09.859
is to my constituents,

999619033
06:36:09.860 --> 06:36:12.467
and my constituency is
the highways financing bill.

3123905829
06:36:12.468 --> 06:36:15.612
This sets out, for the first time how

1087509942
06:36:15.612 --> 06:36:17.518
the government can use the regulated,

1002179714
06:36:17.519 --> 06:36:23.209
asset based funding model used in
energies in sectors like energy,

215061811
06:36:23.210 --> 06:36:26.308
to build new large scale
road schemes and crucially,

2852676611
06:36:26.308 --> 06:36:30.264
for me and for the people of Dartford,
it will be the new Lower Thames

2744634683
06:36:30.265 --> 06:36:34.765
Crossing that is the first project
to be built on this model,

986725468
06:36:34.766 --> 06:36:37.864
using private capital to get
this crucial scheme built.

3170917571
06:36:37.865 --> 06:36:39.922
We already have spades in the ground for

1707924766
06:36:39.923 --> 06:36:41.828
the preparatory work on the crossing,

540200248
06:36:41.829 --> 06:36:44.771
and this new bill should see this project

1623569684
06:36:44.772 --> 06:36:48.112
long promised finally delivered.

2769563133
06:36:48.112 --> 06:36:50.567
Dartford regularly experiences
traffic gridlock,

3489849133
06:36:50.568 --> 06:36:52.574
where there are delays at the crossing,

179769597
06:36:52.575 --> 06:36:54.882
with children unable to
get home from school,

2055500277
06:36:54.883 --> 06:36:58.061
missed appointments and a stifling
effect on local businesses.

3796015977
06:36:58.062 --> 06:37:01.812
And this is without
mentioning the terrible

99087817
06:37:01.813 --> 06:37:04.611
air quality impact of 5000 vehicles

2324304278
06:37:04.612 --> 06:37:09.413
a day using the crossing that it was
originally designed to accommodate.

2460651837
06:37:09.414 --> 06:37:11.620
The Lower Thames Crossing
is the government

1382712907
06:37:11.621 --> 06:37:14.615
backing those businesses to succeed,

3119527297
06:37:14.616 --> 06:37:16.773
the ones that are taking part in the Lower

3026614805
06:37:16.775 --> 06:37:18.830
Thames Crossing consortium that I chair,

939258860
06:37:18.831 --> 06:37:22.668
and improving vital links
with our ports and creating

2262208518
06:37:22.669 --> 06:37:24.725
the conditions for growth in the future.

471796829
06:37:24.726 --> 06:37:26.783
And while I'm on the topic of transport,

2826299313
06:37:26.784 --> 06:37:29.215
it would be remiss of me not to mention

312605002
06:37:29.216 --> 06:37:31.860
Gally Hill Road in my constituency,

2597265719
06:37:31.861 --> 06:37:34.825
the crucial route between
Dartford and Gravesend,

238308813
06:37:34.826 --> 06:37:39.674
which has been collapsed and out of
use for more than three years now.

2517508226
06:37:39.675 --> 06:37:42.974
I hope this session will see
Kent County Council bid for

2674532676
06:37:42.975 --> 06:37:46.868
and secure funding from
the excellent New Structures Fund

1948380860
06:37:47.160 --> 06:37:52.011
to get the road repaired and back
open so that local businesses

4111577787
06:37:52.012 --> 06:37:55.866
like MPC Despatch Racing can thrive again,

232665490
06:37:55.867 --> 06:37:58.023
and Swanscombe can see an end to oversized

4270700296
06:37:58.025 --> 06:37:59.779
lorries blocking its narrow roads.

1822376089
06:37:59.780 --> 06:38:03.620
I welcome this King's speech
and the bills that are in it.

3454591457
06:38:04.160 --> 06:38:05.965
>> Thank you, Madam Deputy Speaker.

1675991193
06:38:05.966 --> 06:38:11.368
We've been trapped inside a vicious
economic circle for decades now,

2494559615
06:38:11.369 --> 06:38:14.764
and that vicious economic
circle is underpinned

1631592457
06:38:14.765 --> 06:38:16.520
by our dependence on fossil fuels,

2317619762
06:38:16.521 --> 06:38:18.426
fossil fuels which bear lower growth,

207280180
06:38:18.427 --> 06:38:21.969
which mean higher inflation
and a higher debt burden.

1571128969
06:38:21.971 --> 06:38:25.865
And more than that, lower
growth, lower income.

2217330093
06:38:25.866 --> 06:38:28.915
What that means for our
constituents is more fear,

898737257
06:38:28.915 --> 06:38:31.214
more fury, more far right agitation.

2746633809
06:38:31.215 --> 06:38:33.673
What we see on our screens
and more increasingly

1006085788
06:38:33.674 --> 06:38:37.016
and worryingly on our streets as well.

2334318957
06:38:37.017 --> 06:38:39.223
And that's why today,
Madam Deputy Speaker,

1386211745
06:38:39.224 --> 06:38:41.130
we are setting out how we're breaking

3218398111
06:38:41.130 --> 06:38:43.188
out of that trap and building a virtuous

1383500785
06:38:43.189 --> 06:38:45.416
economic circle of higher growth,

1387473497
06:38:45.418 --> 06:38:50.319
of lower inflation
and a lower debt burden to

128666083
06:38:50.320 --> 06:38:52.916
set out how and why we are in this place.

2773200567
06:38:52.918 --> 06:38:54.222
It is really very simple.

451099490
06:38:56.164 --> 06:39:00.861
Fossil fuels are more expensive than
wind, than solar, than nuclear.

3019394570
06:39:00.862 --> 06:39:04.162
There's 50% more before
the Iran crisis struck.

618420922
06:39:04.163 --> 06:39:06.171
And what does that mean for us at home?

3424248502
06:39:06.172 --> 06:39:07.375
It means less spending.

4230838648
06:39:07.376 --> 06:39:09.119
Less spending means less growth.

2700931081
06:39:09.120 --> 06:39:12.022
It meant higher prices
and higher inflation.

1897664695
06:39:12.022 --> 06:39:17.565
And both of those things also
meant a higher debt burden.

1632342067
06:39:17.566 --> 06:39:21.267
And because, Madam Deputy Speaker,
our debt is linked to inflation,

3288495957
06:39:21.268 --> 06:39:24.317
that also means high
interest payments as well.

368024671
06:39:24.318 --> 06:39:27.075
There is a fundamental,
perverse economic link between

2682501557
06:39:29.172 --> 06:39:31.578
fossil fuel prices
and our economic prosperity.

2685848167
06:39:31.579 --> 06:39:34.966
And that is what we are breaking today.

130169539
06:39:34.967 --> 06:39:37.877
Today, we are breaking out of
that trap by ensuring we're

2250492923
06:39:39.160 --> 06:39:41.718
getting lower energy prices
now and in the future.

4029424508
06:39:41.719 --> 06:39:44.480
In the first instance,
immediate relief on bills,

3921092415
06:39:45.164 --> 06:39:47.268
lowering affordability or rather lowering

1009460744
06:39:47.269 --> 06:39:49.963
energy prices with affordability payments,

1949553464
06:39:49.964 --> 06:39:51.568
funding that by windfall taxes.

1302344747
06:39:51.569 --> 06:39:53.916
And not only does that mean more spending,

1175634428
06:39:53.918 --> 06:39:55.673
but it also means lower inflation.

1390663416
06:39:55.674 --> 06:39:59.862
And lower inflation means
the bank has more space to cut rates.

470630177
06:39:59.862 --> 06:40:02.561
Because at this time, when the bank is

1178231172
06:40:02.562 --> 06:40:04.366
worried about second order effects,

3775722481
06:40:04.367 --> 06:40:07.629
it is not right to borrow money
to ensure those bills come down.

1540144485
06:40:07.630 --> 06:40:11.368
It is right to ensure we raise
the money from tax to lower

3131980632
06:40:11.369 --> 06:40:15.715
bills and lower interest
rates, and in the longer term,

1850235199
06:40:15.716 --> 06:40:18.765
Madam Deputy Speaker, when
we invest in clean energy,

2407805194
06:40:18.766 --> 06:40:23.559
we know that means lower energy bills
and higher growth in the future.

3017605046
06:40:23.561 --> 06:40:26.559
And we know this works
because there are natural

1816522190
06:40:26.561 --> 06:40:28.971
gas used to set our price
over 90% of the time.

3486249702
06:40:30.160 --> 06:40:32.369
It now sets our price
only 60% of the time.

2763163741
06:40:32.370 --> 06:40:37.969
We know that we can break out of
this trap because we already are.

1248118805
06:40:37.971 --> 06:40:43.273
And finally, Madam Deputy
Speaker, I want to close on this.

21867840
06:40:43.275 --> 06:40:46.666
This is more than just about
affordability or bills.

4047053738
06:40:46.668 --> 06:40:50.969
It's about the way we cohere
and we live together as one.

1944539392
06:40:50.971 --> 06:40:53.421
We cannot expect people
in this country to have

632384697
06:40:53.422 --> 06:40:56.073
a stake in it if we do not
have a stake in them.

4178303804
06:40:56.074 --> 06:40:59.572
If we do not show, we can make
life affordable for them.

2558900741
06:41:00.164 --> 06:41:01.971
Only then can we build a country by

2657427194
06:41:01.972 --> 06:41:04.416
the strength of our common endeavour,

3506190434
06:41:04.418 --> 06:41:06.514
we achieve more than we do alone.

1044192219
06:41:06.515 --> 06:41:07.066
Thank you.

1912515643
06:41:07.067 --> 06:41:08.469
>> Linsey Farnsworth thank.

3836984703
06:41:08.471 --> 06:41:09.769
>> You, Madam.

2437070064
06:41:09.770 --> 06:41:10.722
>> Deputy Speaker.

1680847385
06:41:10.723 --> 06:41:13.730
I welcome the package
of bills in this King's

1378130033
06:41:13.731 --> 06:41:16.566
speech by accelerating the transition

2066288551
06:41:16.567 --> 06:41:20.373
to renewables and by producing
energy here in the UK for the UK.

388613577
06:41:20.374 --> 06:41:24.922
We will strengthen our energy
resilience and make bills lower.

1351488465
06:41:24.923 --> 06:41:26.177
But for this to succeed,

4227934271
06:41:26.178 --> 06:41:28.936
another barrier must be
addressed time and time again.

361533703
06:41:28.937 --> 06:41:32.471
Manufacturers in my constituency
tell me they're being held

2288120394
06:41:32.472 --> 06:41:36.530
back by the constraints on
our grid infrastructure.

3005372354
06:41:38.169 --> 06:41:40.224
It's stifling expansion and the creation

3061240502
06:41:40.225 --> 06:41:42.559
of new jobs for people in Amber Valley.

1996395447
06:41:42.561 --> 06:41:45.580
This combined double burden of high energy

3822143130
06:41:45.581 --> 06:41:49.066
prices and insufficient grid capacity has

4141662610
06:41:49.067 --> 06:41:50.822
been keenly felt by Denby Pottery,

1947637259
06:41:50.823 --> 06:41:53.964
which has now sadly gone
into administration.

2434514955
06:41:53.965 --> 06:41:56.272
I was shocked to learn
that for years they've

2851644303
06:41:56.273 --> 06:41:57.879
been forced to switch off their

3457783400
06:41:57.880 --> 06:42:03.464
solar panels at weekends rather than
sell excess power back to the grid.

4152726874
06:42:03.465 --> 06:42:05.420
A cruel irony given the circumstances,

94667963
06:42:05.421 --> 06:42:08.464
the Ministry Ministers for
industry will be acutely aware

2551434026
06:42:08.465 --> 06:42:10.672
from our many meetings
on this subject that

202227903
06:42:10.673 --> 06:42:13.331
I will not stop pushing
for support for that,

1537307445
06:42:13.332 --> 06:42:16.176
for the energy intensive
ceramics industry,

2728386353
06:42:16.177 --> 06:42:19.120
and I will not stop fighting
to save Denby unless

2988205825
06:42:19.121 --> 06:42:24.171
and until the doors close
for the very last time.

3547551702
06:42:24.172 --> 06:42:27.572
National grid's plans to upgrade
the network are central

511796457
06:42:27.573 --> 06:42:29.778
to increasing capacity
across Amber Valley,

3706235723
06:42:29.779 --> 06:42:32.927
which in turn will support
local businesses.

698439728
06:42:32.928 --> 06:42:35.467
However, I know many residents are deeply

3371584956
06:42:35.468 --> 06:42:37.573
concerned about the proposed pylon route,

585964472
06:42:37.574 --> 06:42:40.219
which is set to run through
my constituency from

471914177
06:42:40.221 --> 06:42:42.876
top to bottom and working
hard to ensure that

3654234583
06:42:42.877 --> 06:42:46.617
the final route minimises impact
and intrusion for residents,

3813839590
06:42:46.618 --> 06:42:47.820
schools and businesses.

314052718
06:42:49.164 --> 06:42:51.971
Now, in Amber Valley, our
communities have consistently

1857654994
06:42:51.972 --> 06:42:54.964
stepped up to support our
nation's infrastructure,

2697446838
06:42:54.965 --> 06:42:56.920
from opencast mining to our ironworks,

3267230789
06:42:58.500 --> 06:43:00.605
and that contribution must be recognised.

3686846433
06:43:00.606 --> 06:43:03.730
The Community Benefit Fund
can be used to support local

1222791109
06:43:03.731 --> 06:43:06.287
priorities like health care,
education and skills.

3306598370
06:43:06.288 --> 06:43:09.599
While I know no level of funding
can fully offset the disruption,

2339861310
06:43:09.600 --> 06:43:13.275
it's nonetheless essential
that those communities most

935545219
06:43:13.276 --> 06:43:15.582
affected see a fair
and proportionate return.

1039220822
06:43:15.583 --> 06:43:19.173
Now, I've raised this directly
with the Ministers for energy,

1580024042
06:43:19.174 --> 06:43:21.369
who knows that I will always fight for

124883480
06:43:21.370 --> 06:43:23.125
what is right for my constituents,

3921039808
06:43:23.126 --> 06:43:27.067
and that is why I want to
take the opportunity today

1986617923
06:43:27.068 --> 06:43:29.225
to to reiterate that given Amber Valley is

472758804
06:43:29.226 --> 06:43:31.669
once again being asked
to contribute more than

3548490529
06:43:31.670 --> 06:43:34.619
others to this nationally
significant project,

1128657490
06:43:34.620 --> 06:43:36.876
it's only right that my
constituents receive

4187788764
06:43:37.164 --> 06:43:38.818
a ring fenced and proportionate,

291812975
06:43:38.819 --> 06:43:41.619
proportionate share of the community fund.

2986019950
06:43:41.620 --> 06:43:45.482
Madam Deputy Speaker, some in
this place seek to use energy

1864549159
06:43:46.165 --> 06:43:48.522
policy as an opportunity
to play culture wars,

2349489775
06:43:48.522 --> 06:43:53.574
but my constituents know more than
most that this is not a game.

2377638218
06:43:53.575 --> 06:43:57.530
The measures in the King's Speech
will make our energy resilient,

2700150657
06:43:57.531 --> 06:44:01.091
stronger, our energy supply fairer,

1911882904
06:44:01.092 --> 06:44:04.678
and whilst preserving and creating
jobs and making bills cheaper.

2085393751
06:44:04.679 --> 06:44:08.379
And for my constituents, this
cannot come soon enough.

1894871078
06:44:08.380 --> 06:44:08.831
>> Here.

1022952922
06:44:09.176 --> 06:44:10.479
Thank you, Madam Speaker.

209906247
06:44:10.480 --> 06:44:11.380
The government's.

3019356302
06:44:11.382 --> 06:44:13.539
>> Commitment set out in the King's Speech

1845570721
06:44:13.540 --> 06:44:15.245
to drive innovation in the energy

1126537341
06:44:15.246 --> 06:44:17.971
sector and deliver cleaner and more secure

1607612377
06:44:17.972 --> 06:44:19.525
energy for future generations.

1168315439
06:44:19.526 --> 06:44:23.718
Now, Gravesham is stepping
forward to meet this challenge.

431961098
06:44:23.719 --> 06:44:26.226
The >> Northfleet Green
Hydrogen Project was one.

723010548
06:44:26.227 --> 06:44:26.578
>> Of.

3954967041
06:44:26.579 --> 06:44:29.438
>> 11 successful projects as
part of the UK government's

2140882571
06:44:29.439 --> 06:44:31.092
first hydrogen allocation round,

1731207856
06:44:31.093 --> 06:44:33.299
designed for its ambition
of supporting ten

2463083345
06:44:33.300 --> 06:44:35.579
gigawatts of green
and blue energy by 2030.

1017241031
06:44:35.580 --> 06:44:40.174
Now for Gravesham, this means
they will decarbonise a paper

1465894201
06:44:40.175 --> 06:44:43.281
making process for a much
beloved household like Andrex.

181610725
06:44:43.282 --> 06:44:46.322
At Kimberly-Clark, which
has been part of Gravesham

4255581412
06:44:46.323 --> 06:44:49.622
businesses for over 70 years
now, the science part.

1828053534
06:44:49.623 --> 06:44:52.973
Having taught this in
the classroom in Norfolk schools

178278567
06:44:52.974 --> 06:44:56.175
now we'll be able to see it
in action in Northfleet,

3975600737
06:44:56.176 --> 06:44:58.932
where hydrogen will be generated
through electrolysis.

3931078140
06:44:58.933 --> 06:45:03.418
Don't worry, I'm not going to go
through electrolysis with you,

3963119570
06:45:03.419 --> 06:45:05.727
but it will generate
steam to really work out

1169615368
06:45:05.728 --> 06:45:08.618
and work through the paper
manufacturing process.

1589613740
06:45:08.619 --> 06:45:10.627
Now this will be a hybrid process so it

1096899577
06:45:13.127 --> 06:45:14.933
can run on hydrogen or natural gas,

3665630616
06:45:14.933 --> 06:45:18.625
which is absolutely going to
enhance our energy security,

1985037594
06:45:19.168 --> 06:45:24.270
reduce our reliance on fossil fuels,
but also provide clean energy.

4211668389
06:45:24.271 --> 06:45:26.679
But not only that, it's
about good quality jobs

3925151260
06:45:26.680 --> 06:45:28.977
for Northfleet and
the wider Gravesham area.

130852058
06:45:28.978 --> 06:45:30.932
Now, however, this particular project,

1947505437
06:45:31.168 --> 06:45:34.768
which has had 90 million
capital investment nationally,

2074429113
06:45:34.769 --> 06:45:37.023
has unlocked 400 million
private investment.

3129816826
06:45:37.172 --> 06:45:38.927
There is a critical risk, however,

2439000135
06:45:38.928 --> 06:45:42.123
and that is about connection
to the national grid.

1511755138
06:45:42.124 --> 06:45:45.885
So I'll be asking the Ministers
if he can intervene and meet with

3908656581
06:45:45.886 --> 06:45:50.969
me about how we can make sure
this project stays on track.

893136952
06:45:50.971 --> 06:45:53.820
Looking less than a mile down the river of

4130513404
06:45:53.821 --> 06:45:55.877
the Thames to the Lower Thames Crossing,

89932258
06:45:56.168 --> 06:45:57.622
which is in my constituency.

2993961059
06:45:57.623 --> 06:46:00.880
Gravesham also faced congestion
linked to the Dartford Crossing,

1311090066
06:46:02.172 --> 06:46:03.575
affecting their daily life.

829643042
06:46:03.576 --> 06:46:08.373
Air quality indeed, parts of Gravesham
have air quality management areas

4126058321
06:46:08.374 --> 06:46:13.182
with increased amounts of nitrogen
dioxide levels linked to transport.

392193038
06:46:13.183 --> 06:46:15.339
Now, the theory is that increased capacity

1151382101
06:46:15.340 --> 06:46:16.894
with the Lower Thames Crossing

2727678678
06:46:16.895 --> 06:46:21.083
will lead to increased congestion
within and around Gravesham,

3518791569
06:46:21.084 --> 06:46:24.676
and therefore it is essential that
this delivery is linked to forward

2921809202
06:46:24.677 --> 06:46:28.777
looking transport solutions that
genuinely benefit local communities.

2152942630
06:46:28.778 --> 06:46:30.826
Now, this has yet to be truly felt by

507894227
06:46:30.826 --> 06:46:32.925
my constituents and local businesses,

1544510706
06:46:32.926 --> 06:46:35.186
so there is a lot more
work to be done here.

1372564681
06:46:35.187 --> 06:46:40.471
In particular, the use of
the Thames Estuary itself

3863069767
06:46:40.472 --> 06:46:43.380
to be a vehicle to
transport people around,

672351617
06:46:43.380 --> 06:46:45.788
such as the Gravesend
Tilbury Ferry and beyond.

4242288998
06:46:45.789 --> 06:46:48.270
And I would encourage
the government to explore

470789379
06:46:48.271 --> 06:46:50.023
these sustainable transport modes.

4260626669
06:46:51.172 --> 06:46:53.377
Hydrogen or electric
powered ferries across

3105778285
06:46:53.378 --> 06:46:56.374
the Thames and removing
the congestion on roads

763164903
06:46:58.170 --> 06:47:00.478
for continuing to rely
solely on roads is not

2894328723
06:47:00.479 --> 06:47:02.536
going to be a viable long term solution,

2968592583
06:47:02.537 --> 06:47:05.126
and more balanced, community
focussed transport

2699398972
06:47:05.127 --> 06:47:07.320
is essential to getting people around.

1772068423
06:47:07.321 --> 06:47:08.073
We have three.

4073659722
06:47:08.074 --> 06:47:10.170
>> Speakers remaining.

1321795797
06:47:10.171 --> 06:47:11.575
We've gained a few minutes.

2118774342
06:47:11.576 --> 06:47:14.236
The last three speakers
can have five minutes

1503476116
06:47:14.237 --> 06:47:16.931
each if they do not take interventions.

949812568
06:47:16.932 --> 06:47:19.869
Elaine Stewart five minutes.

3949584830
06:47:19.870 --> 06:47:20.321
>> Yeah.

3846819918
06:47:20.322 --> 06:47:21.375
>> Thank you, Madam.

3326545321
06:47:21.376 --> 06:47:24.973
>> Deputy Speaker.

1689533349
06:47:24.974 --> 06:47:28.728
>> I've cut it down that much
I don't know whether I can do.

3406268892
06:47:28.729 --> 06:47:31.573
In the King's Speech.

3363679419
06:47:31.574 --> 06:47:34.032
His Majesty set out a clear
and sober assessment

3446509229
06:47:34.033 --> 06:47:35.938
of the challenges facing our country.

193975775
06:47:35.939 --> 06:47:38.172
He reminded us of the energy independence

1910828266
06:47:38.173 --> 06:47:40.230
is now a matter of national security,

3819462894
06:47:40.231 --> 06:47:42.633
not just environmental ambition.

3099589895
06:47:42.634 --> 06:47:44.790
He warned that recent events in the Middle

3316446379
06:47:45.169 --> 06:47:47.075
East have shown once again how global

4197991476
06:47:47.076 --> 06:47:49.379
instability can reach directly into

3378506574
06:47:49.380 --> 06:47:53.174
the homes of families across the country.

1028919459
06:47:53.175 --> 06:47:55.382
That is why the government
has committed to

488286855
06:47:55.383 --> 06:47:58.624
an energy independence
bill designed to scale

2733060068
06:47:58.625 --> 06:48:00.781
up home grown renewable energy and protect

2469501372
06:48:02.177 --> 06:48:03.982
living standards for the long term.

1353275037
06:48:03.983 --> 06:48:08.628
There are significant commitments
to deliver them to build

2104675317
06:48:08.629 --> 06:48:11.729
an energy system that is
secure, clean and resilient.

2139645785
06:48:12.128 --> 06:48:14.034
Then we must learn from the evidence.

94399569
06:48:14.035 --> 06:48:17.681
The reality is we will not
win the argument for clean

3741212292
06:48:19.172 --> 06:48:21.528
climate action unless
people feel the benefit.

2466808062
06:48:21.529 --> 06:48:24.987
Energy independence cannot be something
that happens to communities.

1436828796
06:48:24.987 --> 06:48:30.126
It must be something
that happens with them.

1030697266
06:48:30.127 --> 06:48:34.080
The transition of clean energy is
already shaping our energy landscape.

326947766
06:48:34.081 --> 06:48:36.927
Renewables are reducing
the numbers of hours.

1263363853
06:48:36.928 --> 06:48:39.526
When gas sets the price for electricity.

791845108
06:48:39.527 --> 06:48:43.384
New technologies are
emerging as the backbone

403601097
06:48:43.385 --> 06:48:45.874
of modern energy system, and the grid,

311152794
06:48:45.875 --> 06:48:49.572
long overdue for investment, is finally

1089723230
06:48:49.573 --> 06:48:51.528
being reimagined for the 21st century.

4293927192
06:48:53.285 --> 06:48:55.439
Faced with decades of deindustrialisation,

1403331736
06:48:55.440 --> 06:48:57.094
communities like my own and Ayr,

1508484061
06:48:57.096 --> 06:49:01.588
Carrick and Cumnock need to see
and feel real benefits like lower bills,

3065111905
06:49:04.172 --> 06:49:06.227
good jobs, investment in local services.

374131127
06:49:07.173 --> 06:49:09.679
Otherwise, support for
the transition will erode.

2618772232
06:49:09.680 --> 06:49:12.088
And if support erodes,
we risk losing the wider

4057102627
06:49:14.134 --> 06:49:16.439
public argument on climate
change altogether.

4268204762
06:49:16.440 --> 06:49:18.645
In Scotland, delivering
those real benefits

3410196609
06:49:18.646 --> 06:49:20.674
means governments working together.

1613075181
06:49:20.675 --> 06:49:24.128
The Clean Power Mission
is a shared objective

1725976908
06:49:24.129 --> 06:49:26.822
by both UK and Scottish governments,

1020832911
06:49:26.823 --> 06:49:30.428
and it is important to acknowledge
constructive cooperation

1483660665
06:49:30.429 --> 06:49:34.232
and encourage more of this where possible.

3502742028
06:49:34.233 --> 06:49:38.379
Madam Deputy Speaker, as
we debate energy security,

1747449894
06:49:38.380 --> 06:49:42.329
we must also place community benefit
at the very heart of our approach,

3868555416
06:49:42.330 --> 06:49:46.141
not a voluntary gesture,
not a token payment,

712602209
06:49:46.142 --> 06:49:51.576
but a core principle of how we build
the energy system of the future.

2462735811
06:49:51.576 --> 06:49:53.835
In my own area and Ayr,
Carrick and Cumnock,

2662039405
06:49:53.836 --> 06:49:56.040
the nine community
council group administer

728019069
06:49:56.172 --> 06:49:58.026
large amounts of community benefits,

3767362377
06:49:58.027 --> 06:50:00.478
of which over 60 young apprenticeships,

171468517
06:50:00.479 --> 06:50:03.625
alongside other fantastic
community support,

3308663967
06:50:03.626 --> 06:50:06.973
creates ongoing legacy to my communities.

3110237675
06:50:06.974 --> 06:50:11.978
I invite the Ministers to attend
and have a meeting with that group,

3357121519
06:50:11.979 --> 06:50:13.982
but we also must go further.

1880929557
06:50:13.983 --> 06:50:16.826
Community ownership, giving local people

2441591727
06:50:16.828 --> 06:50:18.483
a real stake in energy producing

959633247
06:50:18.484 --> 06:50:22.629
their doorstep should be
a core feature of transition.

2022641197
06:50:23.172 --> 06:50:27.630
When communities share in
profits, they share in purpose.

1116417574
06:50:27.630 --> 06:50:32.475
When they have a voice, they feel
much better to support change,

1778291666
06:50:32.476 --> 06:50:34.772
both locally and nationally.

3467043871
06:50:34.772 --> 06:50:37.922
It is not just about fairness,
it's about effectiveness.

799661592
06:50:37.923 --> 06:50:40.480
Because the fastest way
to lose public trust

3513611854
06:50:40.481 --> 06:50:42.687
is to impose changes
without their consent.

1487590974
06:50:44.134 --> 06:50:46.593
The fastest way to build
trust is to ensure that

3186422929
06:50:48.176 --> 06:50:50.431
communities are partners
and not bystanders.

1915140674
06:50:50.432 --> 06:50:53.680
Finally, I will touch on
the Scottish Government's continued

1738460504
06:50:53.681 --> 06:50:56.679
opposition to the new nuclear
development in Scotland.

3505535206
06:50:56.680 --> 06:50:59.839
The stance was clearly shaped in
a different political moment,

3958504934
06:50:59.840 --> 06:51:04.734
but today it means Scotland risks
standing apart from what the King's

2437627491
06:51:04.735 --> 06:51:08.572
Speech rightly called a new era
of British nuclear energy.

3605074170
06:51:08.573 --> 06:51:10.528
By ruling out nuclear energy entirely,

3554512824
06:51:12.183 --> 06:51:14.842
Scotland risks losing out
in long term skilled jobs,

2885893045
06:51:15.133 --> 06:51:16.536
major investment and words.

2378611899
06:51:16.537 --> 06:51:18.728
At a time when UK is moving to expand,

3185424290
06:51:18.729 --> 06:51:21.580
nuclear Scotland risks being left behind,

3299011290
06:51:21.581 --> 06:51:24.780
missing opportunities that
could support communities

1150765172
06:51:24.781 --> 06:51:26.285
and contribute to the secure,

496271508
06:51:26.286 --> 06:51:31.436
clean energy mix that we
need for decades to come.

3011318002
06:51:31.437 --> 06:51:32.927
Thank you Sean Woodcock.

2253931789
06:51:32.928 --> 06:51:34.733
>> Very much, Madam Deputy Speaker.

3881088148
06:51:34.734 --> 06:51:36.641
I want to start by addressing some of

3538594925
06:51:36.642 --> 06:51:40.235
the comments made from
the benches opposite,

2390633050
06:51:40.236 --> 06:51:42.288
in particular by the hon.

3639419468
06:51:42.289 --> 06:51:46.179
Member for Upper Bann
and Isle of Wight East,

2532606634
06:51:46.180 --> 06:51:49.328
who decried government policy
on energy as ideological.

2300864111
06:51:49.329 --> 06:51:54.086
Now I want to hold my hands up
and say, for me it is ideological,

2150193556
06:51:54.087 --> 06:51:58.186
making the UK more secure
and having people better

3185386192
06:51:58.187 --> 06:52:02.983
off is at the very core of my ideology.

3523500960
06:52:02.984 --> 06:52:06.245
So I class that as ideological
because events in the Middle East

1582185342
06:52:06.246 --> 06:52:09.536
have made it Madam Deputy
Speaker have been very clear,

3637842787
06:52:09.537 --> 06:52:11.692
although I do appreciate his contribution.

2077866885
06:52:11.693 --> 06:52:13.047
Normally I vote this time.

892367799
06:52:13.048 --> 06:52:13.599
Thank you.

26518715
06:52:13.600 --> 06:52:18.477
Events in the Middle East have given
us a very clear reminder that.

2589643212
06:52:18.478 --> 06:52:19.482
I will end on that.

455886936
06:52:19.483 --> 06:52:21.580
I did ask, though nicely.

4049683384
06:52:21.581 --> 06:52:22.535
I will let him to.

1963820120
06:52:22.536 --> 06:52:23.237
>> Gentleman.

3488898472
06:52:23.237 --> 06:52:23.890
>> He talks.

1552768029
06:52:23.891 --> 06:52:26.326
>> He prioritises energy security and of

3352943003
06:52:26.326 --> 06:52:28.181
course transition to cleaner energy.

1037383514
06:52:29.296 --> 06:52:31.754
Affordable energy is what
we would all wish for.

3914678893
06:52:31.755 --> 06:52:35.928
But this country is going to burn
through billions of barrels of oil

366242368
06:52:35.929 --> 06:52:40.535
and gas between now and 2050, even
if we meet net zero and 2050.

2560245083
06:52:40.536 --> 06:52:42.743
So on what basis does
he support government

3270172923
06:52:42.744 --> 06:52:44.677
proposals to stop us producing

3856117948
06:52:44.678 --> 06:52:47.787
that oil and gas to the highest
environmental standards here,

3429118066
06:52:47.788 --> 06:52:50.534
and instead importing it from abroad

2857649786
06:52:50.535 --> 06:52:52.389
with much higher emissions attached?

1455736197
06:52:52.390 --> 06:52:57.236
>> I think he misrepresents the in
intent missing intentionally in Mr.

4039692267
06:52:57.237 --> 06:53:00.547
presents the government policy as
my understanding is that we are

361475377
06:53:00.548 --> 06:53:03.558
going to continue to use oil
and gas going into the future,

951083045
06:53:03.559 --> 06:53:06.790
and it's going to play a key
part of of the just transition,

46370005
06:53:06.790 --> 06:53:10.437
because events in the Middle East
have made it very clear and reminding

1382896921
06:53:10.438 --> 06:53:14.049
us that national security and energy
security actually go hand in hand,

3807322687
06:53:14.176 --> 06:53:18.589
because when global events
destabilise supply is families

1105926815
06:53:18.590 --> 06:53:22.183
here at home who feel
the impact in their energy bills.

3054430457
06:53:22.183 --> 06:53:25.227
That means we must prioritise
energy independence.

3641277902
06:53:25.228 --> 06:53:27.987
And that is why I welcome
the ambition that we've seen

653920589
06:53:27.989 --> 06:53:30.734
set out in the King's Speech,
which do exactly that.

612020127
06:53:30.735 --> 06:53:34.386
Because this isn't just some
abstract idea in my constituency,

2552338210
06:53:35.180 --> 06:53:38.089
we're already seeing what this
can look like in practice.

2178073436
06:53:39.176 --> 06:53:43.087
I would refer to Salford solar
Farm in the town of Charlbury.

2227404839
06:53:43.088 --> 06:53:44.693
Now, this is not a corporation.

3617173739
06:53:44.694 --> 06:53:48.391
It is a cooperative set
up by local volunteers

585019128
06:53:48.392 --> 06:53:50.634
who wanted to make a difference.

1614579259
06:53:50.635 --> 06:53:53.333
Since 2016, they've been generating enough

3890860352
06:53:53.334 --> 06:53:56.132
clean energy to power around 1500 homes.

816839924
06:53:56.133 --> 06:53:57.987
Then there's Hook Norton Low Carbon,

2148338177
06:53:58.182 --> 06:54:00.589
which is doing brilliant
work to keep household

878075833
06:54:01.180 --> 06:54:03.136
energy bills down below the price cap.

3567629528
06:54:03.137 --> 06:54:06.089
They've done that by teaming
up with another local

3204477525
06:54:06.090 --> 06:54:10.089
solar farm and
an anaerobic digester plant.

1048574289
06:54:10.090 --> 06:54:13.842
Again, a practical, community led solution

333812918
06:54:13.843 --> 06:54:16.431
to a national and international challenge.

3069867109
06:54:16.432 --> 06:54:19.507
What these projects show
is Britain at its best.

1714306118
06:54:19.508 --> 06:54:23.943
If people stepping up when
they are given the opportunity

924992673
06:54:23.944 --> 06:54:26.653
to do so because they don't
just want greener energy,

1796104395
06:54:26.654 --> 06:54:28.688
they want control, they want stability,

818753439
06:54:28.689 --> 06:54:31.338
and they want a sense that they are no

3753153850
06:54:31.339 --> 06:54:34.981
longer at the mercy of global markets.

2142088238
06:54:34.982 --> 06:54:38.044
But if we want to see more of
this right across the country,

2330959524
06:54:38.045 --> 06:54:41.355
we've got to address the barriers
that are holding progress back.

1614031276
06:54:41.356 --> 06:54:45.198
Too many brilliant community energy
projects are stuck in limbo,

2798602024
06:54:45.199 --> 06:54:47.355
not because they lack ambition or funding,

960293431
06:54:48.181 --> 06:54:51.836
but because they simply cannot
get connected to the grid.

10421989
06:54:51.837 --> 06:54:55.337
In some cases, they are waiting
years just for a connection.

3850057793
06:54:55.338 --> 06:54:58.737
That's not only frustrating,
it's holding back

1210260698
06:54:58.737 --> 06:55:00.981
our entire transition to cleaner energy.

1275916066
06:55:00.982 --> 06:55:03.930
We need to modernise our
grid infrastructure

3384675304
06:55:03.931 --> 06:55:05.735
and streamline the planning system.

3122280803
06:55:05.736 --> 06:55:07.795
If we do that, we can unlock a huge wave

2987148978
06:55:07.796 --> 06:55:10.537
of locally generated renewable power.

4022792382
06:55:10.538 --> 06:55:14.194
But these are only part of the picture.

4052596040
06:55:14.195 --> 06:55:16.931
If we want a truly secure energy system,

777034679
06:55:16.932 --> 06:55:20.530
we also need reliable, consistent power.

2434469896
06:55:20.531 --> 06:55:25.136
So I welcome the nuclear regulation
bill by making the process

150603033
06:55:25.137 --> 06:55:28.632
the process more efficient
without compromising safety,

1527715831
06:55:28.633 --> 06:55:31.941
we can finally start moving
at a pace we need and usher

2417809517
06:55:31.942 --> 06:55:35.587
in a new chapter for
British nuclear energy.

1540014796
06:55:35.588 --> 06:55:38.848
But energy security isn't just
about how much power we generate.

673616668
06:55:38.849 --> 06:55:41.458
It has to have a positive
impact on people's lives.

3084143615
06:55:43.140 --> 06:55:45.346
That's why the Energy
Independence Bill and

3297062642
06:55:45.347 --> 06:55:47.755
the 15 billion warm home
plan are so important.

2182842157
06:55:47.755 --> 06:55:50.692
Helping people to insulate
their homes properly is one of

3635824335
06:55:51.183 --> 06:55:54.530
the most effective ways that
we can cut people's bills.

4153494586
06:55:54.531 --> 06:55:56.737
Because when families
save money on energy,

1131773993
06:55:56.737 --> 06:55:58.241
that money doesn't disappear.

1289201775
06:55:58.242 --> 06:56:01.186
It gets spent in local shops, cafes,

2427906674
06:56:01.187 --> 06:56:04.293
businesses supporting jobs
and strengthening local economies.

1366721528
06:56:04.294 --> 06:56:06.987
That's why it's not just
good environmental policy.

1536673144
06:56:06.987 --> 06:56:09.043
It's actually also good economic policy.

1389556625
06:56:09.044 --> 06:56:11.939
That's how we build
a system that's more secure,

876381016
06:56:11.940 --> 06:56:15.198
more resilient and fairer for
the people that we represent.

3903005916
06:56:15.199 --> 06:56:17.357
And which is why I'm so pleased to support

3616973515
06:56:17.358 --> 06:56:20.236
the King's Speech Josh Newbury.

372571929
06:56:20.237 --> 06:56:22.634
>> Thank you, Madam Deputy Speaker.

3376793072
06:56:22.635 --> 06:56:24.390
And after an increased time limit,

1596616373
06:56:24.391 --> 06:56:27.894
I think I'm going to go out
and buy a lottery ticket tonight.

4007655836
06:56:27.895 --> 06:56:30.505
Having worked in energy,
I am all too aware that it

3999080884
06:56:30.505 --> 06:56:33.114
hasn't always been high up
on the political agenda.

1444474336
06:56:33.115 --> 06:56:34.870
But since the invasion of Ukraine,

2820242426
06:56:34.871 --> 06:56:36.990
it has of course seized the headlines.

1427629254
06:56:36.991 --> 06:56:39.200
And it is in the news
once again because of

2926387851
06:56:39.201 --> 06:56:41.406
President Trump's
distraction plan in Iran.

2219386378
06:56:41.407 --> 06:56:44.096
I welcome the government's
focus on energy security,

807660185
06:56:44.097 --> 06:56:46.589
but I hope that we will
not narrow our view of

3746826209
06:56:46.590 --> 06:56:50.389
what energy security
and clean energy means.

216911391
06:56:50.390 --> 06:56:53.350
Reliance on fossil fuels is
a growing drag on our economy,

4001501187
06:56:53.351 --> 06:56:57.291
so the government is right to push
for electrification where viable,

3425478323
06:56:57.293 --> 06:57:02.588
alongside home grown renewable energy
to get us off that roller coaster.

294161261
06:57:02.589 --> 06:57:06.194
But zero carbon renewable gas
should also be a critical

1397704372
06:57:06.195 --> 06:57:09.687
part of our plan for energy independence.

15042209
06:57:09.688 --> 06:57:13.143
Many aspects of the Energy
Independence Bill are fantastic,

3746420652
06:57:13.144 --> 06:57:16.403
like new obligations on landlords
to invest in renewable energy,

1595869722
06:57:16.404 --> 06:57:19.112
and beefing up Ofgem with
new powers that will enable

2179544831
06:57:19.114 --> 06:57:21.823
them to step in where consumers
have been ripped off.

4120306223
06:57:21.824 --> 06:57:24.584
When it comes to the Warm Homes Agency.

977125058
06:57:24.585 --> 06:57:28.336
I welcome the huge investment that
will be going into insulation,

2254828089
06:57:28.337 --> 06:57:30.894
but remain concerned about
the direction of travel

496143275
06:57:30.895 --> 06:57:33.082
of electrification for almost all homes.

540434497
06:57:33.083 --> 06:57:37.839
Since I first entered the energy
industry just over a decade ago,

3518941780
06:57:37.840 --> 06:57:40.338
the Zealousness in the London based civil

771068532
06:57:40.339 --> 06:57:43.195
service around heat pumps has not waned,

2193142834
06:57:43.196 --> 06:57:46.993
despite years of evidence that
the rollout and cost cost reduction

3201466464
06:57:46.994 --> 06:57:50.088
of heat pumps has not matched
optimistic estimates.

1618699899
06:57:50.089 --> 06:57:53.191
I say this as somebody who
got a heat pump last year.

4056045589
06:57:53.192 --> 06:57:58.591
The total cost of my
installation was over £14,000.

984500290
06:58:00.184 --> 06:58:02.641
Beyond the £7,500 Boiler
Upgrade Scheme payment.

2483441349
06:58:02.642 --> 06:58:04.297
Now I'm in a fortunate position,

3150792251
06:58:04.298 --> 06:58:08.994
but I can't say to my
constituents that they should

2152686456
06:58:08.995 --> 06:58:11.151
spend their savings or get themselves into

1975592296
06:58:11.152 --> 06:58:12.859
heaps of debt to get a heat pump.

627958046
06:58:12.860 --> 06:58:14.365
The way things are right now,

2754096796
06:58:14.366 --> 06:58:17.576
the vast majority of people in
Cannock Chase cannot afford one,

2247486359
06:58:17.576 --> 06:58:20.386
and I haven't seen anything
about the Warm Homes Agency

39765568
06:58:20.387 --> 06:58:22.642
that will fundamentally
change that reality.

2990964924
06:58:22.643 --> 06:58:25.349
If we're serious about helping
struggling households,

2489749909
06:58:25.350 --> 06:58:28.135
we have to make sure
that agencies immediate

2410097008
06:58:28.136 --> 06:58:29.741
mission is to bring bills down.

3149865857
06:58:29.742 --> 06:58:34.338
And let's make sure the Energy
Independence Bill really lives up to its

3621853461
06:58:34.339 --> 06:58:38.192
name by also kickstarting a revolution
in renewable gas production.

2607186524
06:58:38.193 --> 06:58:41.495
A boost to biomethane production
could support farmers to handle

637485576
06:58:41.496 --> 06:58:44.934
organic wastes better and secure
a reliable income stream.

3123016121
06:58:44.936 --> 06:58:48.496
It would bring down emissions in
sectors that cannot easily electrify,

1744094423
06:58:48.497 --> 06:58:51.346
including with the potential
for carbon negative gas

3597287108
06:58:51.347 --> 06:58:53.804
through the usage of carbon
capture and storage,

249641463
06:58:53.805 --> 06:58:55.944
and it would ensure we are masters of our

3731794240
06:58:55.945 --> 06:58:57.951
own destiny when it comes to a critical

3937670975
06:58:57.953 --> 06:59:02.396
fuel that will remain part of our
energy mix for decades to come.

4182810692
06:59:02.397 --> 06:59:04.939
The extension of the Green Gas Support

2285488148
06:59:04.940 --> 06:59:07.037
Scheme out to 2030 is very welcome,

2240508861
06:59:07.038 --> 06:59:10.286
but like all energy investment pipelines,

2707950894
06:59:10.287 --> 06:59:12.342
producers and investors need longer term

316355332
06:59:12.343 --> 06:59:14.347
certainty on the government's position.

4255640363
06:59:14.348 --> 06:59:17.155
I've heard similar concerns
from the hydrogen industry.

4084933603
06:59:17.156 --> 06:59:20.514
Whilst there is widespread support
for the government's investment

605667863
06:59:20.515 --> 06:59:23.073
in CCS and the first round
of hydrogen investment,

4023068929
06:59:23.074 --> 06:59:25.230
we still don't have the hydrogen strategy.

2144746213
06:59:25.231 --> 06:59:27.689
All of these strands need
to be knitted together

3327507474
06:59:27.690 --> 06:59:29.847
as part of a balanced approach on reaching

2441600422
06:59:29.848 --> 06:59:31.903
net zero and supporting our constituents

2291306279
06:59:32.188 --> 06:59:34.094
and businesses with us along the way.

3582324505
06:59:34.094 --> 06:59:37.607
In the government's focus on clean
energy and the jobs of the future,

2732314229
06:59:37.608 --> 06:59:40.768
let's not lose sight of the promise
of biomethane and hydrogen

1068375984
06:59:40.769 --> 06:59:43.394
as other examples of
home-grown clean energy.

1763646003
06:59:43.395 --> 06:59:46.789
And above all, let's always be
on the side of our constituents

1159910511
06:59:46.790 --> 06:59:49.850
who want to do the right thing
in decarbonising their homes,

3628038196
06:59:50.189 --> 06:59:52.799
but worry how on earth they
are going to afford it.

2917564359
06:59:54.188 --> 06:59:55.040
Thank you chair.

1159439749
06:59:55.040 --> 06:59:56.646
>> I call the shadow Ministers.

362049886
06:59:57.188 --> 06:59:58.743
>> Andrew Bowie you very much.

3226340403
06:59:58.744 --> 07:00:01.944
>> Madam Deputy Speaker,
and I'd like to thank all

724891733
07:00:01.945 --> 07:00:05.293
the speakers and contributions
to this afternoon's debate,

1159681430
07:00:06.188 --> 07:00:08.043
especially like to thank and welcome

1507671647
07:00:08.044 --> 07:00:10.196
the contributions from the right hon.

1754671351
07:00:10.197 --> 07:00:11.049
Members and hon.

148457957
07:00:11.050 --> 07:00:13.505
Members for Gainsborough
Herne Bay and Sandwich,

3164853009
07:00:13.507 --> 07:00:15.763
South Holland and
The Deepings, Harrow East,

1008588118
07:00:15.764 --> 07:00:17.719
Isle of Wight, East, Gordon and Buchan

3414946900
07:00:17.721 --> 07:00:19.978
and the Weald of Kent,
Folkestone and Hythe.

3546224371
07:00:19.979 --> 07:00:22.438
He's not in his place just
yet, but he mentioned

179081432
07:00:22.439 --> 07:00:25.248
the Dungeness nuclear power
plant and I agree with him.

1703117696
07:00:25.249 --> 07:00:28.108
There's potential at that plant
is huge for new nuclear,

3827868340
07:00:28.109 --> 07:00:30.092
especially small modular reactors,

4006245580
07:00:30.093 --> 07:00:33.707
and I can very much recommend
the fish and chips or fish and chips that

2085535299
07:00:33.708 --> 07:00:38.798
they sell at the pilot pub just outside
the gates of that power plant.

1185416907
07:00:38.799 --> 07:00:41.860
If anybody is looking to visit,
I'd also like to pay tribute

568292296
07:00:41.861 --> 07:00:45.254
and welcome the comments from
the Member for Honiton and Sidmouth,

874179885
07:00:45.255 --> 07:00:47.865
who seem to suggest that
we are all here because of

3497699977
07:00:47.866 --> 07:00:50.525
a lack of positive votes for
any of us individually.

392970123
07:00:50.526 --> 07:00:53.187
I'm not quite sure how that
will go down at the next

655461828
07:00:53.188 --> 07:00:55.492
Parliamentary Liberal
Democrat Party meeting,

368283523
07:00:55.493 --> 07:00:58.101
given that that's what he
thinks of his colleagues,

2070591880
07:00:58.102 --> 07:01:00.808
but it was a very enjoyable
contribution nonetheless.

276854680
07:01:00.809 --> 07:01:02.815
Madam Deputy Speaker, across this House

2918887372
07:01:02.816 --> 07:01:04.671
we all recognise the turbulent world

2718438114
07:01:04.672 --> 07:01:08.487
we live in and that our energy security
is being tested at every turn.

2016360349
07:01:08.489 --> 07:01:11.997
Russia seeks to exploit vulnerabilities
in our subsea infrastructure.

2629605514
07:01:11.998 --> 07:01:15.708
Iran is weaponizing the supply of oil
and gas from the Gulf and China,

2705692783
07:01:16.188 --> 07:01:18.994
seeking to access our critical
national infrastructure.

591849368
07:01:18.995 --> 07:01:21.052
So it was incredibly welcome to see that

1465223952
07:01:21.053 --> 07:01:23.058
a bill will be introduced to strengthen

1224736648
07:01:23.059 --> 07:01:28.139
the United Kingdom's Energy Security
and Energy Independence Bill.

3510767566
07:01:28.140 --> 07:01:29.795
Finally, we thought they get it.

129243656
07:01:29.796 --> 07:01:32.904
Finally, they've listened to
the academics, the trade unions,

3579717552
07:01:32.905 --> 07:01:35.210
renewable Scotland, Tony
Blair, Jurgen Meyer.

3234519009
07:01:35.211 --> 07:01:37.618
Finally, we're going to
see the government take

2547596580
07:01:37.619 --> 07:01:40.126
the action necessary to
secure our energy future,

347023072
07:01:40.127 --> 07:01:44.902
secure jobs and deliver much needed
revenue to His Majesty's Treasury.

2513886901
07:01:44.903 --> 07:01:49.894
Or so we thought, because sadly
and predictably, they haven't listened.

1828894735
07:01:50.190 --> 07:01:51.192
They haven't acted.

1024206598
07:01:51.193 --> 07:01:53.951
In fact, Madam Deputy Speaker,
they are doubling down,

374196526
07:01:53.951 --> 07:01:56.208
doubling down on making
this country poorer,

358642255
07:01:56.209 --> 07:02:00.246
doubling down on making this
country weaker and doubling,

4023611766
07:02:00.247 --> 07:02:04.588
doubling down on callously
abandoning the high skilled workers

441815871
07:02:04.589 --> 07:02:07.839
and people of Aberdeen
and the north east of Scotland.

775826393
07:02:07.840 --> 07:02:09.546
I would be delighted to give way.

189275253
07:02:10.188 --> 07:02:11.090
>> Very grateful.

842077371
07:02:11.091 --> 07:02:13.447
I would never accuse my
constituency neighbour

1137686171
07:02:13.448 --> 07:02:15.303
of being a rank, rotten revisionist,

2263737751
07:02:15.304 --> 07:02:19.795
Madam Deputy Speaker, but
the problem is, the problem is,

506121760
07:02:19.796 --> 07:02:23.646
when he was in government for
the last ten years of his government,

2322297010
07:02:23.647 --> 07:02:29.650
oil and gas jobs in the north east
of Scotland went down by 100,000.

1364867612
07:02:29.651 --> 07:02:32.737
And in just in the two years
that he was a Ministers,

1976015423
07:02:32.739 --> 07:02:35.346
including a Ministers in
the Department for energy,

3971464398
07:02:35.347 --> 07:02:36.852
they went down a further 10%.

2052771427
07:02:36.853 --> 07:02:38.961
Why is he now manifesting as some sort of

2122413618
07:02:38.962 --> 07:02:41.447
caped crusader for oil and gas workers?

2850407896
07:02:41.448 --> 07:02:44.052
Because it's difficult for many of us in

3483363727
07:02:44.053 --> 07:02:47.642
the north east of Scotland to believe.

3011449942
07:02:47.643 --> 07:02:50.442
>> Representing a party that for the best

3271264474
07:02:50.443 --> 07:02:52.249
part of ten years had a presumption

1737266043
07:02:52.250 --> 07:02:55.763
against oil and gas and now seeks
to be a champion for that industry.

2500748107
07:02:55.764 --> 07:02:57.671
I'd also like to point out that there

1067417299
07:02:57.672 --> 07:02:59.529
is a global oil price crash in 2014.

2479153456
07:02:59.530 --> 07:03:00.744
And what did we do?

723481175
07:03:00.745 --> 07:03:04.143
We implemented a policy of
maximum economic recovery.

615553218
07:03:04.144 --> 07:03:06.151
We cut taxes and we stemmed job losses,

3845028816
07:03:06.152 --> 07:03:08.108
the exact opposite of what this Labour

466529696
07:03:08.109 --> 07:03:10.015
government is doing in the North Sea,

567561929
07:03:10.016 --> 07:03:12.222
who are accelerating
the decline and seeing

2267156164
07:03:12.223 --> 07:03:14.698
thousands of people
being made independent.

2826644769
07:03:14.699 --> 07:03:17.004
It's frankly offensive,
Madam Deputy Speaker,

62626748
07:03:17.005 --> 07:03:20.616
to call the bill that is being
introduced and Energy Independence Bill.

2260912116
07:03:20.617 --> 07:03:23.493
Madam Deputy Speaker, it is
an energy dependent bill.

347197939
07:03:23.494 --> 07:03:27.190
More dependent on foreign
imports, more dependent on China,

1790744463
07:03:27.191 --> 07:03:28.896
more dependent on Norway for gas,

3366712122
07:03:28.897 --> 07:03:31.557
who are drilling it from
the very same sea that this

1461086282
07:03:31.558 --> 07:03:33.913
government is banning
Britain from exploiting.

1284975904
07:03:33.914 --> 07:03:35.844
It is insanity.

2110423805
07:03:35.844 --> 07:03:38.203
Once again, the Secretary
of State has put his

1851583696
07:03:38.204 --> 07:03:40.559
ideological fantasies
before what he is doing,

2584116685
07:03:40.561 --> 07:03:42.869
what is right for
the people of this country.

2989252613
07:03:42.870 --> 07:03:46.245
The only people who will be cheering
this on are those in Moscow,

2450841641
07:03:46.246 --> 07:03:49.497
Tehran and Beijing who, to
be fair, who, to be fair,

3330350478
07:03:49.498 --> 07:03:53.107
will probably themselves be incredulous,
unbelieving of their luck that

1896860279
07:03:54.192 --> 07:03:57.603
they have such useful idiots in
the form of this Labour government,

1498737702
07:03:57.604 --> 07:04:00.463
cheered on by the SNP with
their decade long presumption

3810279308
07:04:00.464 --> 07:04:02.871
against oil and gas,
and the Liberal Democrats,

1802965396
07:04:02.872 --> 07:04:05.580
who have a different position
depending on which part

1126146903
07:04:05.581 --> 07:04:07.991
of the country you happen
to be in at the time.

3970572505
07:04:07.992 --> 07:04:12.154
All, all choosing to make the UK poorer,

3621472414
07:04:12.155 --> 07:04:14.611
colder and more vulnerable
to outside influence.

4182798677
07:04:14.612 --> 07:04:16.016
Let us be absolutely clear.

1636443845
07:04:16.017 --> 07:04:18.324
The position of this
Labour government on oil

3461044904
07:04:18.325 --> 07:04:20.281
and gas is downright dangerous by now.

1745502244
07:04:20.282 --> 07:04:23.050
Proposing to legislate
a ban on all new licences,

3816198142
07:04:23.051 --> 07:04:25.558
this government might as
well be hanging a closed

520153694
07:04:25.559 --> 07:04:27.897
for business sign over the North Sea.

1690711984
07:04:27.897 --> 07:04:30.146
Madam Deputy Speaker, I and not just me do

2539803033
07:04:30.147 --> 07:04:32.943
not understand the logic of these actions.

3653789427
07:04:32.944 --> 07:04:34.898
The Secretary of State, his Ministers,

1671359794
07:04:35.192 --> 07:04:36.997
the current occupant of number ten,

547741386
07:04:36.998 --> 07:04:39.055
repeatedly tell us that oil and gas will

2555638266
07:04:39.056 --> 07:04:44.103
have a role in the UK for years to come.

1326440189
07:04:44.104 --> 07:04:44.906
They are right.

581761023
07:04:44.907 --> 07:04:47.718
Roughly 85% of the homes in
the UK rely on gas heating.

854060412
07:04:47.719 --> 07:04:52.355
Over 90% of vehicles in this in
the UK rely on fossil fuels to run,

2117325171
07:04:52.356 --> 07:04:54.213
so it is not going to end overnight.

1175224868
07:04:54.214 --> 07:04:57.774
But all this legislation will achieve
is that will become increasingly

517527977
07:04:57.775 --> 07:05:00.596
reliant on shipments from
abroad at higher cost,

2019356729
07:05:00.597 --> 07:05:04.797
with higher emissions
and fewer jobs here in Britain.

415697791
07:05:04.798 --> 07:05:06.753
Madam Deputy Speaker, I and colleagues

2200741822
07:05:06.754 --> 07:05:08.509
like the Leader of the Opposition,

975311553
07:05:08.510 --> 07:05:10.215
the Secretary of State for energy

925828867
07:05:10.216 --> 07:05:12.223
and others have come to this House time

165590954
07:05:12.224 --> 07:05:14.180
and time again to highlight the damage

921390261
07:05:14.181 --> 07:05:16.035
this government's approach is having

2868659307
07:05:16.036 --> 07:05:19.547
to communities in and around Aberdeen
and the north east of Scotland.

2607314544
07:05:19.548 --> 07:05:22.008
I am always willing to
give way to my right hon.

4011879924
07:05:22.009 --> 07:05:25.571
>> Friend the Secretary of State
claims he is leading a moral crusade,

3827993351
07:05:25.572 --> 07:05:27.879
but we know he is simply
exporting emissions.

3459601310
07:05:27.880 --> 07:05:29.887
It's like saying, Lord, I will not sin,

1636638772
07:05:29.888 --> 07:05:32.498
but I'm quite happy for
people to sin on my behalf.

904965632
07:05:32.499 --> 07:05:32.799
Yeah.

1065449598
07:05:32.800 --> 07:05:33.703
>> The right hon.

1618814859
07:05:33.704 --> 07:05:35.257
Gentleman is absolutely right.

2093713536
07:05:35.258 --> 07:05:37.764
We are exporting emissions,
we're exporting jobs,

3818651634
07:05:37.765 --> 07:05:41.226
and we're having and it's having
a detrimental impact on our economy

378699451
07:05:41.227 --> 07:05:44.387
and communities up and down
the length of this United Kingdom,

425774950
07:05:44.388 --> 07:05:46.445
not least in the north east of Scotland.

843897630
07:05:46.446 --> 07:05:48.003
I see it every time I go home.

141526603
07:05:48.004 --> 07:05:51.992
1000 jobs are going to be lost every
month under this Labour government.

3117727533
07:05:51.993 --> 07:05:56.494
£50 billion of investment lost
under this Labour government.

1103389832
07:05:56.495 --> 07:05:59.353
Pubs, restaurants, shops closing
up in the Granite City.

2528040661
07:05:59.354 --> 07:06:00.857
Under this Labour government,

1930809525
07:06:00.858 --> 07:06:03.115
the impact is being felt
across the country.

3562213073
07:06:03.116 --> 07:06:06.529
This is true, but it is in Aberdeen,
in the north east of Scotland,

610265910
07:06:06.530 --> 07:06:07.985
that the pain is most acute.

788523605
07:06:07.986 --> 07:06:09.691
I'm always delighted to give way.

3223063948
07:06:09.692 --> 07:06:10.495
>> I thank the.

2296938786
07:06:10.496 --> 07:06:13.959
>> Shadow Ministers for giving way
and I wonder if he could help me.

2378364606
07:06:13.960 --> 07:06:16.216
I don't understand why
the Labour government

351192877
07:06:16.217 --> 07:06:18.324
think there's a need to ban new licences,

2742739174
07:06:18.325 --> 07:06:21.987
because they keep telling us that
there's nothing left in the North Sea.

1732591324
07:06:21.988 --> 07:06:25.549
If they think there's nothing left
there, why are we banning ourselves

2042102008
07:06:25.550 --> 07:06:28.459
from looking for anything that
might not be there anyway?

372787712
07:06:28.460 --> 07:06:28.911
>> Well.

2749462294
07:06:28.912 --> 07:06:30.669
>> Is it better than I ever could?

275850259
07:06:30.670 --> 07:06:31.923
She is absolutely right.

3240747747
07:06:31.924 --> 07:06:33.427
It is completely nonsensical.

1699768139
07:06:33.428 --> 07:06:36.487
In Aberdeen, there will be
a referendum on this government's

3023291934
07:06:36.488 --> 07:06:39.148
approach to the North Sea
in just a few short weeks.

549812998
07:06:39.149 --> 07:06:41.157
On the 18th of June, the people of what

2779063398
07:06:41.158 --> 07:06:42.913
was until recently the oil capital

556324034
07:06:42.914 --> 07:06:46.125
of Europe will have their say on
how they view this government,

2713556223
07:06:46.126 --> 07:06:48.533
how they feel this
government has treated them,

240727336
07:06:48.534 --> 07:06:50.792
and the industry of which
they are so proud.

1819982594
07:06:50.793 --> 07:06:53.956
But it is not just the production
of oil and gas that is being

3680880796
07:06:53.957 --> 07:06:56.663
driven into extinction by
this government's policies.

3074431936
07:06:56.664 --> 07:06:59.373
Nor is it just Aberdeen
that's being affected by this

67333810
07:06:59.374 --> 07:07:01.878
government's anti-growth
anti- business policies.

3463100835
07:07:01.879 --> 07:07:03.982
Lindsay Mossmorran, Grangemouth, Denbigh,

3590569782
07:07:03.983 --> 07:07:06.487
Pembrokeshire Glassworks
and Metalworks Potteries

467620767
07:07:06.488 --> 07:07:08.592
refineries chemical plants heavy industry

65591172
07:07:08.593 --> 07:07:10.600
is being crushed by the cost of energy.

185955103
07:07:10.601 --> 07:07:12.607
Yet rather than trying to prevent this,

22012390
07:07:12.608 --> 07:07:16.167
this Labour government is only
interested in accelerating its decline.

3358304620
07:07:16.168 --> 07:07:18.573
Madam Deputy Speaker,
the government's headlong

677579426
07:07:18.574 --> 07:07:20.780
rush to renewables may
be well intentioned,

3021584985
07:07:20.781 --> 07:07:22.888
but it is utterly bereft of common sense.

1146749452
07:07:22.889 --> 07:07:25.747
This Labour government is
rushing towards a power system

2317443279
07:07:25.748 --> 07:07:28.206
that depends on the weather
rather than on firm,

4261755830
07:07:28.207 --> 07:07:30.563
reliable base loads,
exposing us to blackouts,

3994691001
07:07:30.564 --> 07:07:33.223
just as they saw in
the Iberian Peninsula last year.

2652277488
07:07:33.224 --> 07:07:36.733
Avoiding such blackouts and providing
that energy baseload is exactly

1825347266
07:07:36.734 --> 07:07:39.594
why the roll out of new nuclear
is an absolute priority.

1887385670
07:07:39.595 --> 07:07:41.903
I am pleased that there
is consensus on this,

1030052199
07:07:41.904 --> 07:07:44.360
and the government recognises
the important role

117291803
07:07:44.361 --> 07:07:46.518
that nuclear has in our future energy mix.

1434492348
07:07:46.519 --> 07:07:50.182
That being said, and as I have said
before in this House, Madam Speaker.

1342565792
07:07:50.183 --> 07:07:52.940
Sadly, this government's
ambition for nuclear pales in

1134672800
07:07:52.941 --> 07:07:55.796
comparison to that of ours
when we were in government.

258397854
07:07:55.797 --> 07:07:57.903
Their failure, their failure to commit to

1540944575
07:07:57.904 --> 07:08:00.060
a third gigawatt scale reactor in Anglesey

4238034842
07:08:00.061 --> 07:08:03.474
is a huge disappointment not just
for us on this side of the House,

2820929074
07:08:03.475 --> 07:08:05.834
but for industry and
the people on Ynys Mon to

4012773434
07:08:05.835 --> 07:08:08.243
the roll out of small
modular reactors is good,

2799582219
07:08:08.244 --> 07:08:11.751
yes, but it curtails the possibility
of gigawatt scale at Ynys Mon.

560024370
07:08:11.752 --> 07:08:12.905
A cynic might suggest.

3242291588
07:08:12.906 --> 07:08:16.417
Madam Speaker, the decision was made
to rush out this announcement in

2574998695
07:08:16.418 --> 07:08:19.828
some desperate and hasty attempt
to salvage the Welsh Labour Party.

470313352
07:08:19.829 --> 07:08:21.585
It's safe to say that that failed.

2110344651
07:08:21.586 --> 07:08:24.995
But back to ambition decommissioning
the UK stockpile of plutonium.

3642209539
07:08:24.996 --> 07:08:27.603
The selection of only one
small modular technology,

1620833640
07:08:27.604 --> 07:08:29.761
the refusal to follow our ambition of 24GW

1772109460
07:08:29.762 --> 07:08:32.810
of new nuclear is just not good enough.

3952204177
07:08:32.811 --> 07:08:33.915
Yes, I will give way.

2734205229
07:08:33.916 --> 07:08:37.450
>> It's about his party's ambition
for new nuclear in this country.

1941095928
07:08:37.451 --> 07:08:41.399
Can he remind the House how
many new nuclear plants

3898050790
07:08:41.400 --> 07:08:44.008
his party opened during
the course of their tenure?

338064656
07:08:44.009 --> 07:08:44.410
>> Yes.

178890324
07:08:44.411 --> 07:08:45.546
>> I could learn.

3125399528
07:08:45.547 --> 07:08:47.755
I could run through
the list as the shadow,

3173602935
07:08:47.756 --> 07:08:50.546
as the Ministers has heard
me do on multiple times.

858152866
07:08:50.547 --> 07:08:53.357
What we did achieve in office
when it comes to nuclear,

2905153711
07:08:53.358 --> 07:08:56.800
I would like to remind him that
the Labour Party, the Labour Party,

593856167
07:08:56.801 --> 07:08:59.626
have never opened one
nuclear power plant in all

151232310
07:08:59.627 --> 07:09:02.186
the years that they have
been in office, a record.

3480461404
07:09:02.187 --> 07:09:06.152
They're probably going to continue
over the next three years.

957393706
07:09:06.153 --> 07:09:09.052
Madam Deputy Speaker, this act of national

878360864
07:09:09.053 --> 07:09:10.709
self-harm has to come to an end.

2978460906
07:09:10.710 --> 07:09:14.323
There is only one party that has
a plan to cut bills, support industry,

4052328771
07:09:14.324 --> 07:09:17.050
protect jobs and make
Britain energy secure.

4210204880
07:09:17.051 --> 07:09:18.755
Energy costs are stalling growth.

1788361645
07:09:18.756 --> 07:09:20.797
No one deindustrialised in the country

812703645
07:09:20.798 --> 07:09:23.004
and weighing down on
family and businesses.

16868890
07:09:23.005 --> 07:09:25.765
That is why Britain needs
a serious plan to cut bills.

727526872
07:09:25.766 --> 07:09:28.022
And with the Conservatives
cheap power plan,

3529876152
07:09:28.023 --> 07:09:31.385
that is exactly what Britain would
get a £200 cut to energy bills.

3202932329
07:09:31.386 --> 07:09:33.248
This could be delivered right now.

3774655285
07:09:33.249 --> 07:09:33.449
Mr.

3387068995
07:09:33.450 --> 07:09:36.157
speaker, if this government
prioritises the people of

3375508928
07:09:36.158 --> 07:09:38.864
this country rather than
wacky, unrealistic ideology.

3285524868
07:09:38.865 --> 07:09:42.860
But we would not stop there,
Madam Deputy Speaker.

212678322
07:09:42.861 --> 07:09:44.918
We would go much further and much faster

382761731
07:09:44.919 --> 07:09:46.724
to make this country energy secure,

1127805534
07:09:46.725 --> 07:09:47.978
to protect British jobs,

3908573359
07:09:47.979 --> 07:09:51.289
to grow tax revenue and welcome
billions of pounds of investment.

2018613211
07:09:51.290 --> 07:09:54.552
We would tell the world that
the North Sea is open for business.

481423594
07:09:54.553 --> 07:09:58.554
Our Get Britain drilling Bill would
end Labour's ban on new licences to

2039712055
07:09:58.555 --> 07:10:02.165
unlock the gargantuan supply of
opportunity that lies beneath our seas.

2606033594
07:10:02.166 --> 07:10:02.768
I will not.

2543083307
07:10:02.769 --> 07:10:05.328
We would back our world
class oil and gas industry

1705851652
07:10:05.329 --> 07:10:07.034
by scrapping the ban on exporting

3203285383
07:10:07.035 --> 07:10:10.696
technologies and welcome the £5 billion
worth of exports that we create.

3206422665
07:10:10.697 --> 07:10:11.902
I am sorry, I will not.

4127116293
07:10:11.903 --> 07:10:14.760
The North Sea Transition
Authority would be rechristened

3588653558
07:10:14.761 --> 07:10:17.670
the North Sea Authority
and tasked with one noble mission

1150042473
07:10:17.671 --> 07:10:20.330
to maximise North Sea oil
and gas drilling and raise

780334351
07:10:20.331 --> 07:10:22.839
billions more in tax cuts
for the British people.

2583061552
07:10:22.840 --> 07:10:24.695
And of course, Madam Deputy Speaker,

3359069193
07:10:24.696 --> 07:10:26.701
we conservatives would scrap the energy

1531129753
07:10:26.702 --> 07:10:28.658
profits levy the anvil around the neck

398318494
07:10:28.659 --> 07:10:31.568
of the industry that Labour
extended and increased as one

1826193238
07:10:31.569 --> 07:10:34.377
of their first acts in
government because a profitable,

183874958
07:10:34.378 --> 07:10:37.735
attractive, investable North Sea
would strengthen public services,

1537930871
07:10:37.736 --> 07:10:40.393
strengthen our energy security
and grow our economy,

1472016259
07:10:40.394 --> 07:10:42.148
making Britain a stronger country.

2847638790
07:10:42.149 --> 07:10:45.108
And if members agree with that, if hon.

4124786127
07:10:45.109 --> 07:10:47.717
Members agree with us that
a brighter, more secure,

3434040269
07:10:47.718 --> 07:10:49.522
more prosperous future is possible,

3838085877
07:10:49.523 --> 07:10:51.732
if you fight for it,
then I would urge hon.

2582034681
07:10:51.733 --> 07:10:53.889
Members to vote for our amendment tonight.

575022013
07:10:53.890 --> 07:10:56.397
>> I call the Ministers
Ministers Michael Shanks.

2961634855
07:10:56.398 --> 07:10:56.799
>> Yes.

3330866033
07:10:56.800 --> 07:10:58.605
>> Thank you, Madam Deputy Speaker.

82287786
07:10:58.606 --> 07:11:02.365
>> It is a privilege to close this
debate on the Gracious Speech,

2255044144
07:11:02.366 --> 07:11:05.148
and it has been a pleasure
to sit here all afternoon

1985597290
07:11:05.149 --> 07:11:08.260
and listen to all of
the contributions and what turned out to

1500422327
07:11:08.261 --> 07:11:11.271
be a far more wide ranging
debate than just energy policy.

2477524551
07:11:11.272 --> 07:11:13.560
And I thank all members for that.

3322279509
07:11:13.561 --> 07:11:15.819
I will respond to a few
specific points that

3669780385
07:11:15.820 --> 07:11:17.877
were raised in the debate in due course,

596794771
07:11:17.878 --> 07:11:20.939
but just to single out a few
contributions from my own side.

2817707319
07:11:20.940 --> 07:11:22.094
First of all, the hon.

2089404254
07:11:22.095 --> 07:11:24.350
Member for Chesterfield
was absolutely right

2004906342
07:11:24.351 --> 07:11:26.158
in his speech in a number of areas,

1975678748
07:11:26.159 --> 07:11:29.169
but one in particular that we
should be very cautious about

2763925117
07:11:29.170 --> 07:11:31.878
taking any advice from
the Shadow Secretary of State,

2920811280
07:11:31.879 --> 07:11:36.102
lest she changes her mind, as she has
done so often in this policy area.

2053318828
07:11:36.103 --> 07:11:36.504
My hon.

800272914
07:11:36.505 --> 07:11:39.703
Friend for Cramlington
and Killingworth spoke quite,

148510684
07:11:39.704 --> 07:11:43.316
quite rightly about her pride in
Blythe and the workers who work there.

2107272571
07:11:43.317 --> 07:11:46.078
I was really pleased to be
there just a few months ago

3241497925
07:11:46.079 --> 07:11:49.122
to celebrate the 25th
birthday of offshore wind,

2270318874
07:11:49.123 --> 07:11:52.711
which of course was started
in Blythe 25 years ago.

2549369124
07:11:52.712 --> 07:11:53.113
My hon.

3599417945
07:11:53.114 --> 07:11:57.402
Friend for Luton South, for
Scarborough and Whitby.

1159847699
07:11:57.403 --> 07:11:58.505
For Bournemouth West.

269473082
07:11:59.196 --> 07:12:01.352
For East Thanet, for Heywood and Middleton

1404460810
07:12:01.353 --> 07:12:03.357
North all made important contributions.

1230022597
07:12:03.358 --> 07:12:03.960
And my hon.

3008988011
07:12:03.961 --> 07:12:07.072
Friend for Na h-Eileanan an Iar,
who I had the great pleasure

4081017524
07:12:07.073 --> 07:12:10.130
of joining in Stornoway just
recently, rightly congratulate,

730960645
07:12:10.131 --> 07:12:12.439
and I put on the record
my congratulations to

1682623946
07:12:12.440 --> 07:12:15.151
Donald McKinnon MSP on
his fantastic election

2840009238
07:12:15.152 --> 07:12:17.751
as the member of the Scottish Parliament

1979869865
07:12:17.752 --> 07:12:19.458
for the Western Isles and my hon.

1012080795
07:12:19.459 --> 07:12:21.414
Friend the Member for Bournemouth West

199859090
07:12:21.415 --> 07:12:23.271
gave a fantastic sales pitch for her

947242689
07:12:23.272 --> 07:12:27.155
community and the role that it's
playing in the clean power transition,

1714948606
07:12:27.156 --> 07:12:29.262
but also the Dorset Clean Energy Cluster,

1929339592
07:12:29.263 --> 07:12:32.248
which I would be absolutely delighted

2850614733
07:12:32.249 --> 07:12:34.156
to visit at some point in the future.

449819180
07:12:34.157 --> 07:12:36.812
Now, honourable contribution
contributions from hon.

3472801979
07:12:36.813 --> 07:12:39.973
Members on all sides of the House
were were interesting today.

2699843795
07:12:39.974 --> 07:12:42.310
The consensus on nuclear in particular,

2499382027
07:12:42.311 --> 07:12:44.751
I welcome and is hugely important.

1689418261
07:12:44.752 --> 07:12:45.504
The right hon.

2468993452
07:12:45.505 --> 07:12:49.052
Gentleman from South
Holland and the Deepings

685186725
07:12:49.053 --> 07:12:50.507
gave a wide ranging lecture,

3637355259
07:12:50.508 --> 07:12:52.613
an important conversation on the economy.

2657669574
07:12:52.614 --> 07:12:55.405
But actually I completely
agree with his points

1714087398
07:12:55.406 --> 07:12:57.314
on skills and the need for us to have

3647578893
07:12:57.315 --> 07:12:59.472
some balance in how we approach the future

2253306557
07:12:59.473 --> 07:13:01.378
of skills development in the country,

3819591335
07:13:01.379 --> 07:13:03.536
so that we have the skilled workforce that

3161468197
07:13:03.537 --> 07:13:05.446
we need to do all that we want to do.

4197294450
07:13:05.447 --> 07:13:05.898
The hon.

359660019
07:13:06.201 --> 07:13:08.107
Gentleman from the Isle of Wight East

1452936881
07:13:08.108 --> 07:13:09.913
gave a bizarre argument, I thought,

2060677249
07:13:09.914 --> 07:13:13.377
in which he said that the last
government was both at the same time.

260112042
07:13:13.378 --> 07:13:16.510
I don't think he's in his
place, but at the same time

286820726
07:13:16.511 --> 07:13:18.818
did a fantastic job
and did everything right,

3236414987
07:13:18.819 --> 07:13:23.053
but that we should now do none of
the things they did into the future,

3570637711
07:13:23.054 --> 07:13:24.809
which was a slightly odd argument.

1748115990
07:13:25.200 --> 07:13:27.455
But nevertheless,
the shadow Ministers stole

4111572605
07:13:27.456 --> 07:13:31.062
my thunder with the speech for the hon.

1918101460
07:13:31.063 --> 07:13:35.599
Gentleman from Homerton and Sidmouth.

1500661954
07:13:35.600 --> 07:13:38.158
But actually it was
the intervention from the hon.

1222370095
07:13:38.159 --> 07:13:40.966
Member for Tunbridge Wells
that I particularly enjoyed,

2335205360
07:13:40.967 --> 07:13:42.320
where he essentially said,

997732065
07:13:42.321 --> 07:13:44.278
nobody really likes any of us and it's

686784829
07:13:44.279 --> 07:13:46.186
all the fault of first past the post.

3748939653
07:13:46.187 --> 07:13:47.741
That was a great contribution.

3700896971
07:13:47.742 --> 07:13:51.607
I do want to just single out
the contribution from the right hon.

1549500019
07:13:51.608 --> 07:13:56.105
Gentleman from Westmorland and Lonsdale,
who gave an excellent speech,

444971203
07:13:56.106 --> 07:13:58.561
but in particular emphasised
absolutely rightly,

3118877249
07:13:58.562 --> 07:14:01.121
that Britain is not broken,
but we must be better.

2328810779
07:14:01.122 --> 07:14:04.234
And I think that was a really
important charge for all of us.

2607857736
07:14:04.235 --> 07:14:06.910
This debate showed today
that the whole House agrees

4136355764
07:14:06.911 --> 07:14:09.807
on the need to strengthen
our energy security.

1968020276
07:14:09.808 --> 07:14:13.871
As we respond to the second fossil
fuel shock in less than five years,

3376828299
07:14:13.872 --> 07:14:16.432
where we are going to make
just a bit of progress.

440779035
07:14:16.433 --> 07:14:18.492
But where we diverge is on how we do it.

2768711516
07:14:18.493 --> 07:14:21.904
For this side of the House,
the overriding lesson from both Russias

1591921878
07:14:21.905 --> 07:14:25.361
invasion of Ukraine and from
the present crisis in the Middle East

3430024986
07:14:25.362 --> 07:14:27.921
is that every day we spend
exposed to fossil fuels

2890197224
07:14:27.922 --> 07:14:31.412
we can never control is
another day of insecurity,

3029996246
07:14:31.413 --> 07:14:33.658
of being buffeted by conflicts.

3833504318
07:14:33.659 --> 07:14:35.704
We had no part in starting.

3136373092
07:14:35.705 --> 07:14:39.102
Of working people opening their
energy bills and finding

3367616198
07:14:39.103 --> 07:14:42.015
the cost of someone
else's war of Britain's

888684825
07:14:42.016 --> 07:14:46.006
future being held back by
global market in which

3140535772
07:14:46.007 --> 07:14:48.014
we are and will always be price takers.

3795156169
07:14:48.015 --> 07:14:50.523
Now the opposition say
that they too have learned

2902607242
07:14:50.524 --> 07:14:52.731
a lesson from the second
fossil fuel shock.

437034079
07:14:52.732 --> 07:14:54.336
They have studied the evidence.

2160561641
07:14:54.337 --> 07:14:57.095
They have weighed up
the options and their conclusion,

2583836561
07:14:57.096 --> 07:15:00.055
their amendment to this Gracious
Speech is that the answer

2352788596
07:15:00.206 --> 07:15:02.765
to a fossil fuel crisis
lies in more fossil fuels?

1678073024
07:15:02.766 --> 07:15:05.075
Now, I would like to
give credit where I can,

2169935027
07:15:05.076 --> 07:15:07.484
Madam Deputy Speaker,
so I will give them this.

577678078
07:15:07.485 --> 07:15:10.697
It takes a particular kind of
courage to stand up in this House

1012450975
07:15:10.698 --> 07:15:13.715
at this time and make that
argument with a straight face.

3915027110
07:15:13.716 --> 07:15:14.317
The Tories.

3944720804
07:15:14.318 --> 07:15:15.454
I will give way.

472978191
07:15:15.455 --> 07:15:17.411
>> Grateful to the Secretary of State.

103045342
07:15:17.412 --> 07:15:20.306
He will know that Scotland
within the United

2045374455
07:15:22.204 --> 07:15:23.809
Kingdom has almost all the oil.

1919811551
07:15:23.810 --> 07:15:26.258
We have the vast majority of the gas.

2600740439
07:15:26.259 --> 07:15:31.208
We have the most onshore
renewables and the most hydro.

3207932842
07:15:31.209 --> 07:15:36.109
And yet, under his watch, his
constituents and mine in Scotland

1306637139
07:15:36.110 --> 07:15:39.861
pay the highest electricity bills
anywhere on these islands.

3706690792
07:15:39.862 --> 07:15:41.768
What does he say to our constituents?

801249826
07:15:41.769 --> 07:15:42.472
>> I have to.

1050578211
07:15:42.473 --> 07:15:45.860
>> Say is that his party's
plan for independence

958728701
07:15:45.861 --> 07:15:48.569
and for energy was
the flimsiest of flimsy documents,

4212490341
07:15:48.570 --> 07:15:51.730
which had no plan for how
independence would bring down bills.

713181552
07:15:51.731 --> 07:15:53.537
Because the truth of the matter is,

2392399367
07:15:53.538 --> 07:15:55.693
independence would tear apart any argument

3009298051
07:15:55.694 --> 07:15:57.901
of energy security
and would drive up bills

2323782178
07:15:57.902 --> 07:15:59.606
for people right across Scotland.

200367376
07:15:59.607 --> 07:16:01.413
And that is why people rejected it.

1251197147
07:16:01.414 --> 07:16:04.253
Ten years ago in that referendum,
the Tories and their

3535204827
07:16:04.254 --> 07:16:07.908
former friends and colleagues
now sitting in reform,

2432715889
07:16:07.909 --> 07:16:11.814
want to solve a dependence problem
by becoming even more dependent.

2855004126
07:16:12.160 --> 07:16:13.314
Well, as my right hon.

3293768984
07:16:13.315 --> 07:16:15.554
Friend the Secretary of State,

4032669737
07:16:15.555 --> 07:16:18.267
I am going to make a bit of
progress as my right hon.

804300347
07:16:18.268 --> 07:16:20.674
Friend the Secretary of
State outlined earlier,

2246133881
07:16:20.675 --> 07:16:22.431
we will not be taking this course.

2341731166
07:16:22.432 --> 07:16:25.242
This is the moment to end our
reliance on fossil fuels,

2951374551
07:16:26.205 --> 07:16:27.809
to electrify the wider economy,

3940934803
07:16:27.810 --> 07:16:31.020
to speed up our transition to
clean, secure, home grown energy,

1603776037
07:16:31.204 --> 07:16:33.159
which does give us energy sovereignty.

636657908
07:16:33.160 --> 07:16:35.116
That is the road to national security.

2269641366
07:16:35.117 --> 07:16:37.174
And along the way, we seize the economic

3563473131
07:16:37.175 --> 07:16:41.006
opportunity of the 21st century 400 000

1251062737
07:16:41.007 --> 07:16:42.963
extra good energy jobs and billions of

208044911
07:16:44.204 --> 07:16:46.009
pounds in investment by 2030 alone.

380148519
07:16:46.010 --> 07:16:48.006
And I will give Ministers.

484565026
07:16:48.007 --> 07:16:51.015
>> I wonder whether he would
agree to meet with me

2722424287
07:16:51.016 --> 07:16:54.956
and the Member for
Bridlington and the Wolds,

3954798762
07:16:54.957 --> 07:16:58.608
because the attic gas
storage site in my hon.

1579495548
07:16:58.609 --> 07:17:00.564
Friend's constituency is 47 years old.

219402633
07:17:00.565 --> 07:17:03.754
It's nearing end of life,
and it's a critically

2638756122
07:17:03.755 --> 07:17:06.010
important part of our
energy infrastructure.

1001541422
07:17:06.205 --> 07:17:09.957
Does he have plans to ensure that
our gas storage is maintained,

160787529
07:17:09.958 --> 07:17:13.768
and will meet with my colleague
and myself to discuss this issue?

2836736417
07:17:13.769 --> 07:17:16.629
>> Well, we are consulting on
the future of gas storage.

1756825327
07:17:16.630 --> 07:17:18.738
I'm always I've made it my policy to meet

539029048
07:17:18.739 --> 07:17:20.546
every MP who wants to meet with me.

3239429696
07:17:20.547 --> 07:17:22.152
And of course, I've always had.

2040901161
07:17:22.153 --> 07:17:23.256
I've always, even in.

1138079303
07:17:23.257 --> 07:17:25.759
The shadow Ministers says I've always had

1393550344
07:17:25.760 --> 07:17:27.665
very good conversations with the hon.

830045262
07:17:27.666 --> 07:17:28.216
Gentleman.

162708970
07:17:28.217 --> 07:17:32.556
So he's in the wrong party.

3126942147
07:17:32.557 --> 07:17:33.711
They all hate him now.

2909425198
07:17:33.712 --> 07:17:37.311
Now is also, Madam Deputy Speaker,
not the time to look away

832134820
07:17:37.312 --> 07:17:40.661
from the biggest long term
threat we face climate change,

2144989507
07:17:42.206 --> 07:17:44.163
a threat that we can no longer ignore.

3573735042
07:17:44.164 --> 07:17:46.623
And so we build the energy
system of the future.

2995464152
07:17:46.624 --> 07:17:48.512
Now, since we came into power,

810784760
07:17:48.513 --> 07:17:51.069
we've had two record breaking
renewables auctions.

3117388322
07:17:51.070 --> 07:17:54.530
After the catastrophic failure of
AR five under the last government,

4021616266
07:17:54.531 --> 07:17:58.207
and despite the shadow Secretary of
State's advice to cancel AR seven,

2662985252
07:17:58.208 --> 07:18:02.260
we have secured clean home-grown power for

3236080600
07:18:02.261 --> 07:18:04.554
the equivalent of 23 million homes.

3749010704
07:18:04.555 --> 07:18:06.962
Power that, since
the Middle East crisis began,

3440397325
07:18:07.204 --> 07:18:10.859
is saving this country millions
of pounds every single

1940519054
07:18:10.860 --> 07:18:12.969
day in gas that we no longer have to buy.

3360404362
07:18:14.268 --> 07:18:15.472
But good is not enough.

9347163
07:18:15.473 --> 07:18:18.317
We are determined to
go further and faster.

4074543051
07:18:18.318 --> 07:18:22.210
That is why we are bringing forward
the next auction round to July.

969111662
07:18:22.211 --> 07:18:25.664
And it is why the Energy
Independence Bill will accelerate

128370902
07:18:26.208 --> 07:18:28.765
the build out of grid
infrastructure by reforming,

2599157447
07:18:28.766 --> 07:18:30.721
planning and getting clean power built

3861675822
07:18:30.722 --> 07:18:34.817
at the speed that this moment demands.

2115688905
07:18:34.818 --> 07:18:36.874
And then on nuclear, the biggest nuclear

3651989485
07:18:36.875 --> 07:18:38.780
building programme in half a century,

802348399
07:18:38.781 --> 07:18:43.557
not vague promises that never
materialised for 14 years,

3426646738
07:18:43.558 --> 07:18:46.065
or endless rounds of
consultation that the shadow

3259477056
07:18:46.066 --> 07:18:48.958
Ministers loves to tell us about so much.

1562041612
07:18:48.959 --> 07:18:50.563
But actual nuclear being built.

3871214725
07:18:51.208 --> 07:18:53.465
And so with the nuclear
regulation bill that

4047415378
07:18:53.466 --> 07:18:57.112
is genuinely pro-nuclear and pro nature,

4141196659
07:18:57.113 --> 07:19:00.662
we will cut costs and timeframes without

1029384927
07:19:00.663 --> 07:19:02.517
cutting corners on safety regulation

2076473963
07:19:02.518 --> 07:19:05.980
reform that the Tories now claim
they would have loved to have done,

3151988124
07:19:05.981 --> 07:19:08.841
but just never found the time
in 14 years in government.

957348710
07:19:08.842 --> 07:19:11.119
Well, we're going to
get it done because we

2761895200
07:19:11.120 --> 07:19:13.771
have to be honest about what we inherited,

3879697489
07:19:13.772 --> 07:19:20.261
the environmental impact assessment
for Sizewell C ran to 44,000

2589206534
07:19:21.204 --> 07:19:23.160
pages, and it still left nobody happy.

3394688647
07:19:23.161 --> 07:19:24.855
That is not caution.

30545087
07:19:24.856 --> 07:19:27.754
It is paralysis dressed up as paperwork.

1093732658
07:19:27.755 --> 07:19:31.760
This government will end it so that
we can get Britain building again

2577186319
07:19:31.761 --> 07:19:35.664
and deliver the energy independence
that people have waited for.

1651517091
07:19:35.665 --> 07:19:38.374
And as we build for
the future, Madam Deputy Speaker,

3018758544
07:19:39.204 --> 07:19:40.809
we also have to protect people.

4033893431
07:19:40.810 --> 07:19:43.016
Right now, 6 million
families are receiving

1675234419
07:19:43.017 --> 07:19:45.962
the expanded warm home discount,

3809084507
07:19:45.963 --> 07:19:47.518
a £15 billion Warm homes plan,

3074837709
07:19:47.519 --> 07:19:50.514
the largest upgrade programme
in British history.

4208000831
07:19:50.515 --> 07:19:52.824
And as a result of actions
that my right hon.

785640888
07:19:52.825 --> 07:19:54.931
Friend the Chancellor took in the Budget,

1729265388
07:19:54.932 --> 07:19:59.566
the price cap fell by £117 in April.

3844327967
07:19:59.567 --> 07:20:02.483
The energy I will give will.

3280656295
07:20:02.484 --> 07:20:03.035
>> People.

3119671791
07:20:03.036 --> 07:20:06.860
Right now my constituents are losing jobs.

1824732105
07:20:06.861 --> 07:20:09.118
Thousands of jobs every
few months are being

2415115927
07:20:09.119 --> 07:20:10.875
lost in the north east of Scotland

721700340
07:20:11.166 --> 07:20:16.263
because of the government's continuing
to keep the energy profits levy.

3043762450
07:20:16.264 --> 07:20:17.918
Labour's tax on Scotland's jobs.

2642233651
07:20:18.209 --> 07:20:22.011
Will the Ministers make
a commitment to move from the EPL to

2621413213
07:20:22.012 --> 07:20:25.310
the OGPM in order to protect
jobs from my constituents?

3281432785
07:20:25.311 --> 07:20:26.063
>> Yeah, yeah.

1698954050
07:20:26.064 --> 07:20:28.122
>> Well, I'll come on to the question of

1129524973
07:20:28.123 --> 07:20:30.131
jobs in the North Sea in just a moment,

2897940476
07:20:30.132 --> 07:20:32.591
because I've got a section
of my speech on that,

3575096721
07:20:32.592 --> 07:20:33.996
because it is so important.

298793412
07:20:33.997 --> 07:20:36.556
I do have to say I find it
absolutely incredulous.

2865744813
07:20:36.557 --> 07:20:38.714
I can almost understand it from the Tories

3423170813
07:20:38.715 --> 07:20:40.621
that at a moment of windfall profits,

3086175459
07:20:40.622 --> 07:20:42.680
a party would think it was the moment to

3143679974
07:20:42.681 --> 07:20:44.487
cut taxes on oil and gas companies.

91571201
07:20:44.488 --> 07:20:46.495
But now we've got a partnership here of

572632133
07:20:46.496 --> 07:20:48.252
the SNP and the Tories who believe

1723717962
07:20:48.253 --> 07:20:52.555
that now is the moment not to help
people with their energy bills,

1818090826
07:20:52.556 --> 07:20:55.165
but to cut the taxes for
for the biggest companies.

1594282450
07:20:55.166 --> 07:20:58.712
So I think that's an interesting
lesson that we've learned from this.

4175866950
07:20:58.713 --> 07:21:01.922
Madam Deputy Speaker, the Energy
Independence Bill is about how

4058880863
07:21:01.923 --> 07:21:04.834
we go further and on fuel
poverty, which a number of hon.

1370023021
07:21:06.209 --> 07:21:07.763
Members raised in this debate,

2061088939
07:21:07.764 --> 07:21:10.916
fuel poverty in this country
is not a misfortune.

2068178714
07:21:10.917 --> 07:21:11.770
It is a scandal.

399967047
07:21:12.168 --> 07:21:17.211
More than a third of school pupils
have told their teachers that

2019406776
07:21:17.212 --> 07:21:21.765
they are cold at home in one of
the world's largest economies.

580555732
07:21:21.766 --> 07:21:25.513
A third of children go
to school to get warm.

1337733476
07:21:25.514 --> 07:21:28.408
We must bring this to
an end with new minimum

2418089272
07:21:28.409 --> 07:21:30.413
energy efficiency standards for renters

299721503
07:21:30.414 --> 07:21:33.411
and new warm homes agency
to ensure that home grades

3201789103
07:21:33.412 --> 07:21:35.707
are not as they have been for too long,

1904140577
07:21:35.708 --> 07:21:37.414
the preserve of just the well off

4231366759
07:21:37.415 --> 07:21:40.059
and a strengthened Ofgem with the powers

691106503
07:21:40.060 --> 07:21:43.622
of a genuine consumer champion,
not just a regulator in name.

3231255030
07:21:43.623 --> 07:21:47.615
That is what fighting the corner of
working people actually looks like.

2801054677
07:21:47.616 --> 07:21:52.765
Now let me say something about
the people who power this country.

2562493805
07:21:52.766 --> 07:21:54.957
I speak at industry conferences regularly,

554617349
07:21:54.958 --> 07:21:59.069
and I always say about my
pride in the North Sea,

2947447359
07:21:59.070 --> 07:22:01.810
not as a Ministers reading from a brief,

1626532261
07:22:01.811 --> 07:22:05.612
but as someone who has friends
and families who work offshore,

1062717110
07:22:05.613 --> 07:22:07.671
and as a Scottish MP who knows more than

3789894401
07:22:07.672 --> 07:22:10.366
many about what the sector means,

3513735191
07:22:10.367 --> 07:22:12.614
it's people right now doing skilled,

4272596504
07:22:12.615 --> 07:22:16.507
dangerous and vital work, work
that this country has depended

1272443112
07:22:16.508 --> 07:22:20.558
on for decades and does not
get taken for granted.

3661659541
07:22:20.559 --> 07:22:23.558
And the question in front
of us, the question, well,

3056124334
07:22:23.559 --> 07:22:26.310
we're not actually,
and that's just nonsense.

876508714
07:22:26.311 --> 07:22:31.421
The question in front of us is how
we secure their long term future.

1807702954
07:22:32.208 --> 07:22:35.670
Now, the answer is not, as some of
the other benches have suggested,

1704637595
07:22:35.671 --> 07:22:38.764
to pretend that the North Sea is not

3769064206
07:22:38.765 --> 07:22:40.620
a maturing basin in natural decline.

3275063134
07:22:40.621 --> 07:22:45.762
It is not about nostalgia for
some new age of discovery.

3830621421
07:22:45.763 --> 07:22:51.061
We are neither a turn off
the taps party, nor nor a drill.

3034888219
07:22:51.062 --> 07:22:51.914
Every last drop.

991904307
07:22:51.915 --> 07:22:52.365
Neither.

2288389990
07:22:52.366 --> 07:22:53.769
Neither are credible plans.

3396952197
07:22:53.770 --> 07:22:56.727
And so we will introduce
transitional energy certificates,

1075936191
07:22:56.728 --> 07:22:58.483
as industry itself has called for,

507948198
07:22:58.484 --> 07:23:02.367
to enable tie backs and to manage
existing fields for their lifespan.

2427055080
07:23:02.368 --> 07:23:06.011
We will give the North Sea Transition
Authority, for the first time,

2763727250
07:23:06.012 --> 07:23:09.111
a statutory responsibility
to consider workers,

511331133
07:23:09.112 --> 07:23:12.724
communities and supply chains
and will launch a new Jobs North Sea Jobs

2777979917
07:23:12.725 --> 07:23:17.809
service to support people through
every stage of the transition.

3150671062
07:23:17.810 --> 07:23:20.518
Because this energy transition
only works if we bring

2810603111
07:23:20.519 --> 07:23:22.777
people with us on what
we are building next,

394868434
07:23:22.778 --> 07:23:24.483
and that is already taking shape.

2076398626
07:23:24.484 --> 07:23:25.488
I do not have time.

545152257
07:23:25.489 --> 07:23:26.040
I'm sorry.

3744360899
07:23:26.041 --> 07:23:27.545
That is already taking shape.

3809511216
07:23:27.546 --> 07:23:29.551
Whether it's nuclear engineers Ynys Mon

556753646
07:23:29.552 --> 07:23:31.456
following in their parents footsteps,

2088048580
07:23:31.457 --> 07:23:34.916
apprentices learning to weld in
the Aberdeen Energy Transition zone,

3179169954
07:23:34.917 --> 07:23:39.862
or wind turbine blades being forged
in Hull, tens of thousands of jobs,

1006728560
07:23:39.863 --> 07:23:44.471
record investment, real communities,
real wages and real future.

3668236094
07:23:44.472 --> 07:23:46.729
The North Sea made Britain
an energy nation.

3272949049
07:23:46.730 --> 07:23:50.114
This bill ensures that it will remain one.

1686757963
07:23:50.115 --> 07:23:51.217
Madam Deputy Speaker.

551170195
07:23:51.218 --> 07:23:53.124
Sometimes in the noise of this place,

827325083
07:23:54.212 --> 07:23:56.420
we lose sight of what
is actually at stake.

2441800953
07:23:56.421 --> 07:23:58.662
Half of Britain's recession since

340500689
07:23:58.663 --> 07:24:03.367
the 1970s caused by fossil fuel shocks.

2180746450
07:24:03.368 --> 07:24:06.264
Not bad luck, not acts of
God, but the predictable,

3551153547
07:24:06.265 --> 07:24:09.900
repeated consequence of building
our future on an energy

1184751738
07:24:09.901 --> 07:24:12.622
source that we can never
have control over.

2461950324
07:24:12.623 --> 07:24:16.319
And what we have heard today
is that parties opposite have

4220060500
07:24:16.320 --> 07:24:19.231
not only chosen to ignore what
is going on all around us,

2122782985
07:24:19.232 --> 07:24:24.019
but actively want us to go even
further, to risk even more,

4008524186
07:24:24.020 --> 07:24:28.114
to gamble with the futures of every
single one of our constituents.

3499154745
07:24:28.115 --> 07:24:32.973
The warning signs were
there in 1973, in 1979,

520882807
07:24:32.974 --> 07:24:34.914
in 2022, and they were ignored.

3130968299
07:24:34.915 --> 07:24:36.520
The warning signs are back now,

4248986809
07:24:36.521 --> 07:24:41.667
and it is right that we learn
the right lessons now.

4245918814
07:24:42.166 --> 07:24:44.373
Madam Deputy Speaker,
just a few weeks ago,

1202729511
07:24:44.374 --> 07:24:47.418
98% of our electricity
came from clean sources.

406236778
07:24:47.419 --> 07:24:52.420
It was for a small period
of time, I recognise it,

192588895
07:24:52.421 --> 07:24:55.280
but 98% of our electricity
came from low carbon sources.

1486420354
07:24:56.208 --> 07:24:58.414
This country, when it
commits to something,

1020673349
07:24:58.415 --> 07:25:01.367
is capable of achieving
extraordinary things.

1229638361
07:25:01.368 --> 07:25:04.060
This is not ideology.

2004065141
07:25:04.061 --> 07:25:07.868
It is the most basic duty of
government to protect the people

2930828762
07:25:07.869 --> 07:25:10.528
of this country from dangers
that we can see coming.

1285662497
07:25:10.529 --> 07:25:14.612
The energy bills contained within
this bill, within this King's Speech,

4114007420
07:25:14.613 --> 07:25:16.971
are the path to a stronger
future for Britain.

2845251157
07:25:17.212 --> 07:25:20.070
Energy security that no blockade
can threaten warm homes

2173818195
07:25:20.071 --> 07:25:23.709
for families that have gone
cold for far too long,

2828476722
07:25:23.710 --> 07:25:26.817
good jobs in communities that
have faced de-industrialisation

2846589757
07:25:26.818 --> 07:25:29.315
for decades because of
governments that just

2193222148
07:25:29.316 --> 07:25:32.362
did not care about industrial
strategy and a climate

2173993401
07:25:32.363 --> 07:25:34.771
that we can hand to our
children without shame.

410242023
07:25:34.772 --> 07:25:39.261
And I commend the King's
Speech to the House.

1311837701
07:25:39.262 --> 07:25:43.119
>> The question is that
the amendment be made,

704389520
07:25:43.120 --> 07:25:44.676
as many of that opinion say I.

3290525120
07:26:30.219 --> 07:26:30.520
>> I.

76212397
07:26:30.521 --> 07:26:30.972
>> Know.

2937809003
07:26:30.973 --> 07:26:31.675
>> The lobby.

1754130764
07:26:34.212 --> 07:26:35.918
>> Michael Shanks do you wish to.

1426092348
07:26:35.919 --> 07:26:38.817
Marvellous colleagues on the back benches.

1740607421
07:26:38.818 --> 07:26:41.772
No benches should be seated, Mr.

1075462831
07:26:41.773 --> 07:26:42.424
