709646820
08:00:03.911 --> 08:00:06.803
It seems the taxpayer will
bail out everything else,

887198959
08:00:06.804 --> 08:00:09.652
but not community impact.

2407555037
08:00:09.653 --> 08:00:13.160
>> So I think the community
impact and the mitigation are

948684847
08:00:13.161 --> 08:00:15.970
key to this project moving
forward in a successful way,

2585506357
08:00:15.971 --> 08:00:20.503
because that is the that
is how trust can be

331378487
08:00:20.504 --> 08:00:23.900
restored and the breakdown in community

587844424
08:00:23.901 --> 08:00:26.852
faith in this project and a trustworthy

350709763
08:00:26.853 --> 08:00:28.607
relationship has been broken down.

1888768549
08:00:28.608 --> 08:00:30.817
And I think that is
the best way to restore

120021648
08:00:30.818 --> 08:00:32.574
it and making sure that our roads,

2341481501
08:00:32.575 --> 08:00:35.434
if there are hundreds of lorries
passing over our roads,

2719095238
08:00:35.435 --> 08:00:38.195
that all of us have the ability
to fix those potholes,

1936782601
08:00:38.196 --> 08:00:39.199
to fix those roads,

2909567415
08:00:39.200 --> 08:00:43.061
to make sure that areas that
are being blighted by HS2,

3209639083
08:00:43.062 --> 08:00:44.615
there's compensation for that.

1268442309
08:00:44.616 --> 08:00:47.374
Those communities, whether
it be parks or green spaces

1725355953
08:00:47.375 --> 08:00:50.655
or extra available funding
for our infrastructure,

3261574454
08:00:50.656 --> 08:00:56.156
I think that is a fair and reasonable
request that we're all making,

3483045286
08:00:56.157 --> 08:00:59.858
so that this can be something
that everyone can benefit from,

1370951743
08:00:59.859 --> 08:01:03.209
not just all of us who have
it sort of forced through our

374058960
08:01:06.252 --> 08:01:08.807
constituencies with absolutely
zero benefit point.

2527326597
08:01:08.808 --> 08:01:09.058
Yes.

117918756
08:01:09.254 --> 08:01:12.811
>> I know, incredibly lovely
when everybody can get in.

1200651375
08:01:12.812 --> 08:01:14.618
This debate has to conclude at 746.

3115151937
08:01:14.619 --> 08:01:15.422
It is her time.

2906147397
08:01:15.423 --> 08:01:17.502
But you may want to consider giving some

3394409643
08:01:17.503 --> 08:01:19.209
time to the Ministers at the end.

3566270167
08:01:19.210 --> 08:01:22.407
>> David Simmonds madam,
I'm incredibly grateful to

698407004
08:01:22.408 --> 08:01:24.915
my constituency Labour for
giving way once again.

3332039741
08:01:24.916 --> 08:01:26.120
Does she agree with me?

360929284
08:01:26.121 --> 08:01:28.479
A positive that could
come out of this process

1150454713
08:01:28.480 --> 08:01:32.103
is if the work which she
has been trenchantly

1665524153
08:01:32.104 --> 08:01:34.602
doing to secure an upgrade to the status

3372636449
08:01:34.603 --> 08:01:36.308
of the Cole Valley Regional Park,

420307170
08:01:36.309 --> 08:01:38.668
moving it to a position
where it enjoys a high

3163312742
08:01:39.253 --> 08:01:41.208
degree of planning protection would be

4037233359
08:01:41.209 --> 08:01:43.814
a significant win for
my constituents and for

1594500771
08:01:43.815 --> 08:01:45.870
hers and for other members constituents.

3625768192
08:01:45.871 --> 08:01:49.281
And perhaps that is something where
the Ministers, in her response,

3899835707
08:01:49.282 --> 08:01:51.840
might consider putting
a little bit of pressure on

33785616
08:01:51.841 --> 08:01:54.600
the rest of government to
ensure that that is secured.

3695613400
08:01:54.601 --> 08:01:57.911
So there is a positive benefit
that future generations can enjoy.

2887919417
08:01:57.912 --> 08:02:01.121
>> While protecting the Colne
Valley Regional Park is something

696802621
08:02:01.122 --> 08:02:03.832
that we have from across
this House that we all share

577508508
08:02:03.833 --> 08:02:07.093
in wanting that extra protection
and to mitigate both the impact

1989792053
08:02:07.094 --> 08:02:09.752
of HS2 and all of the other
infrastructure projects.

3941111683
08:02:09.753 --> 08:02:11.709
And just to give one poignant example,

4290255262
08:02:13.208 --> 08:02:15.868
and the reason I called this
debate today is a very,

3545846330
08:02:18.252 --> 08:02:23.706
very difficult HS2 example of one
of my constituents, Luke Oldfield,

2344758027
08:02:23.707 --> 08:02:29.661
who has been struggling against HS2
for 12 years in a dispute with HS2.

2252666797
08:02:29.662 --> 08:02:32.406
And yes, that is 12 years.

2203981109
08:02:32.407 --> 08:02:32.607
Mr.

1081545303
08:02:32.608 --> 08:02:36.805
Oldfield has a home
recording studio business

2819426052
08:02:36.806 --> 08:02:39.113
that predated the white
elephant that is HS2.

934257529
08:02:39.114 --> 08:02:42.658
From the onset, he raised concerns
over the impact of construction

2024837658
08:02:42.659 --> 08:02:46.103
and future rail noise on his home
and recording studio business,

3417630885
08:02:46.104 --> 08:02:49.956
although he secured assurances that
HS2 would address noise concerns.

3787405937
08:02:49.957 --> 08:02:52.705
In his view, monitoring methods failed to

2287314707
08:02:52.706 --> 08:02:56.053
properly capture the noise affecting

313861922
08:02:56.054 --> 08:02:58.754
his studio and that HS2 later privately

1153843150
08:02:58.755 --> 08:03:00.510
accepted there would be an impact.

1207209390
08:03:00.511 --> 08:03:03.805
The only viable solution identified has

1715312945
08:03:03.806 --> 08:03:06.164
been to construct a new replacement

3344415121
08:03:06.165 --> 08:03:10.108
studio and despite years and years
of design, work and cost assessment,

1058672981
08:03:10.109 --> 08:03:14.662
and the Department of Transport
has repeatedly delayed progress

3925615164
08:03:14.663 --> 08:03:18.855
and pushed back on cost,
what is clear is that Mr.

4153433811
08:03:18.856 --> 08:03:21.703
Oldfield and I am sure
he is not alone on this,

1219829839
08:03:21.704 --> 08:03:25.064
is a victim of a national infrastructure
project that doesn't care

126668121
08:03:25.065 --> 08:03:28.507
and has not been subject to
sufficient independent oversight.

1637884836
08:03:28.508 --> 08:03:31.561
It will soon be too late,
so the government must act.

1550343912
08:03:31.562 --> 08:03:35.173
I would be grateful, therefore,
if the Ministers could confirm in their

643916670
08:03:35.174 --> 08:03:39.908
reply tonight that they will
urgently take up the case of Mr.

2627228346
08:03:39.909 --> 08:03:44.702
Oldfield with me and secure final
and just resolution for the building

3149722115
08:03:44.703 --> 08:03:47.514
of the new studio so he can
carry on with his business,

645798456
08:03:47.515 --> 08:03:51.976
that they will urgently set out
a timeline for the final resolution

1484465995
08:03:51.977 --> 08:03:54.584
of all disputes outstanding
alongside the HS2 line.

363029219
08:03:54.585 --> 08:03:58.563
So my constituents
and others across this House can

1462454837
08:03:58.564 --> 08:04:00.957
finally put the nightmare
of HS2 behind them.

1993262059
08:04:00.958 --> 08:04:04.111
HS2 is a project that
should never have been,

1907552521
08:04:04.112 --> 08:04:06.610
but now we must act to bring the nightmare

4228684621
08:04:06.611 --> 08:04:08.707
to an end for people like Mr.

3842864906
08:04:08.708 --> 08:04:09.208
Oldfield.

192363850
08:04:09.209 --> 08:04:12.763
I urge the Ministers to do just that.

2911830679
08:04:12.764 --> 08:04:13.315
Thank you.

3508264492
08:04:13.316 --> 08:04:13.616
Yeah.

2025758583
08:04:13.617 --> 08:04:16.809
>> Lilian Greenwood Ministers.

2720458177
08:04:16.810 --> 08:04:18.615
>> Thank you, Madam Deputy Speaker.

3911297358
08:04:18.616 --> 08:04:20.312
I'm grateful to the hon.

68534028
08:04:20.313 --> 08:04:23.304
Member for Beaconsfield
for securing this debate

3075500505
08:04:23.305 --> 08:04:26.655
and indeed for
the contributions of other hon.

4071326193
08:04:26.656 --> 08:04:27.508
Friends and hon.

708999856
08:04:27.509 --> 08:04:27.959
Members.

976177091
08:04:27.960 --> 08:04:30.569
I will try to address
the points that she's raised,

2306823819
08:04:30.570 --> 08:04:32.456
she and others have raised.

1227274235
08:04:32.457 --> 08:04:34.865
I want to begin by fully
recognising the change

178336617
08:04:34.866 --> 08:04:38.708
and upheaval that major
infrastructure projects like

13705383
08:04:38.709 --> 08:04:42.362
HS2 bring to the communities
they pass to, I pass through,

2735551725
08:04:42.363 --> 08:04:46.167
I understand the concerns raised by hon.

3154945447
08:04:46.168 --> 08:04:49.110
Members on behalf of their
constituents, as my right hon.

2389078893
08:04:49.111 --> 08:04:54.003
Friend the Member for Swindon South
set out to the House earlier today.

3832954609
08:04:54.004 --> 08:04:57.659
Taxpayers, passengers
and communities along the route

4249723121
08:04:57.660 --> 08:05:00.319
have been let down by years
of mismanagement on HS2.

1432416851
08:05:00.320 --> 08:05:03.411
The failures of the past
mean that HS2 will now

1428676492
08:05:03.412 --> 08:05:05.569
cost more and take longer to be delivered.

329610329
08:05:05.570 --> 08:05:08.010
And the most important
thing that we can do

4091239904
08:05:08.011 --> 08:05:10.402
for communities now is to get a grip on

836019987
08:05:10.403 --> 08:05:12.511
the programme so that the job can be done

2526443961
08:05:12.512 --> 08:05:14.919
and the disruption brought to an end.

322355401
08:05:14.920 --> 08:05:16.876
Over the past year, the government has

2346447651
08:05:16.877 --> 08:05:18.807
been working closely on a full reset

1150893215
08:05:18.808 --> 08:05:23.809
of HS2 to bring effective oversight
and start rebuilding public trust.

805328000
08:05:23.810 --> 08:05:26.959
And whilst HS2 has faced
significant challenges,

3324354787
08:05:26.960 --> 08:05:29.058
this government has been clear that

3420243315
08:05:29.059 --> 08:05:31.908
infrastructure development is the heart of

4262106992
08:05:31.909 --> 08:05:33.863
its strategic missions and priorities.

2834810698
08:05:35.256 --> 08:05:40.711
It will deliver significant benefits
once delivered and I think those.

4209638719
08:05:40.712 --> 08:05:42.811
Whilst those benefits are undeniable,

1024535113
08:05:42.812 --> 08:05:47.010
we know that they come at the cost of
disruption caused by construction.

3528167474
08:05:47.011 --> 08:05:51.552
We have to do right by the residents
who are impacted through a range

1458704419
08:05:51.553 --> 08:05:55.103
of programmes made available to
them, and I appreciate that.

2592908624
08:05:55.104 --> 08:05:58.863
Right now, HS2 construction is at its peak

1730287471
08:05:58.864 --> 08:06:00.569
in many areas and so regrettably,

2414146144
08:06:00.570 --> 08:06:03.358
is the level of disruption
that does include

2554907353
08:06:03.359 --> 08:06:05.711
things like road closures and lorry

2525496269
08:06:05.712 --> 08:06:08.559
movements and other
visible and audible signs

1637128943
08:06:08.560 --> 08:06:12.016
of construction in affected areas.

3960617288
08:06:12.017 --> 08:06:13.422
And she and indeed the hon.

2329854264
08:06:13.423 --> 08:06:17.792
Member for Buckinghamshire,
I forget his constituency title,

4200639332
08:06:19.259 --> 08:06:22.761
mentioned the damage done
to done to the highways.

956381418
08:06:22.762 --> 08:06:24.970
And of course HS2 has
put in place measures

2393860445
08:06:25.256 --> 08:06:27.211
to address that with the establishment

1368211949
08:06:27.212 --> 08:06:30.865
of a highway deterioration fund
to resolve some of those issues,

3185895740
08:06:32.256 --> 08:06:34.313
and it should be done quickly and easily

1304078819
08:06:37.256 --> 08:06:38.959
through funding that's available.

1428366970
08:06:38.960 --> 08:06:41.814
But inevitably there will
be some unwelcome impacts

1377029646
08:06:41.815 --> 08:06:45.069
on local people when you
have major projects,

615295146
08:06:45.070 --> 08:06:47.528
and I know that the Rail
Ministers is determined

297968944
08:06:47.529 --> 08:06:50.359
to make sure that HS2 limited does

3711521067
08:06:50.360 --> 08:06:53.257
its utmost to ensure
that impacts are reduced

2886516535
08:06:53.258 --> 08:06:56.756
as much as is reasonably possible.

447632862
08:06:56.757 --> 08:06:59.710
HS2 limited must be a good
neighbour to affected

316581073
08:06:59.711 --> 08:07:01.766
communities and treat them with respect,

616178598
08:07:03.260 --> 08:07:07.458
even if that has not always been
the people's experience of residents

3103291970
08:07:07.459 --> 08:07:10.412
who constituent Who members
here are representing.

3822654710
08:07:10.413 --> 08:07:13.017
They should listen to
local concerns and be

1766115387
08:07:13.018 --> 08:07:15.809
accountable for their
actions at all times,

2476288458
08:07:15.810 --> 08:07:17.715
and we expect communities affected by

3531311134
08:07:17.716 --> 08:07:19.622
the construction of the railway to be

2771747778
08:07:19.623 --> 08:07:23.212
at the heart of HS2
Limited's delivery plans,

1843271761
08:07:23.213 --> 08:07:24.669
and I know that both my hon.

3155455869
08:07:24.670 --> 08:07:29.916
Friend, the Rail Ministers
and Mike Brown, the chairman of HS2,

2077240461
08:07:29.917 --> 08:07:32.324
are taking a personal
interest in these issues.

455832481
08:07:32.325 --> 08:07:35.335
They want to ensure that residents
who we know have endured

3350335345
08:07:35.336 --> 08:07:38.060
sometimes very lengthy
periods of disruption,

1081308617
08:07:38.061 --> 08:07:41.719
are treated with fairness
and respect and that issues around

3831245027
08:07:43.212 --> 08:07:45.768
compensation are resolved
as promptly as possible.

3507070570
08:07:45.769 --> 08:07:50.559
And indeed, we want to see HS2 limited
leaving a positive legacy through

1599559486
08:07:50.560 --> 08:07:54.522
for communities such as through
the community and business funds,

633715704
08:07:55.260 --> 08:07:57.265
which have already provided millions of

3497766707
08:07:57.266 --> 08:08:00.609
pounds in support of local projects,

2730374679
08:08:00.610 --> 08:08:04.661
from sports clubs to
children's play facilities.

1299820796
08:08:04.662 --> 08:08:05.314
Now the hon.

409188107
08:08:05.315 --> 08:08:08.559
Lady raised the specific case
of one of her constituents,

3924377144
08:08:08.560 --> 08:08:11.772
who we know runs a music
studio, and his experiences.

1820475664
08:08:12.255 --> 08:08:16.413
My officials have briefed me on this
situation and I appreciate that.

934092889
08:08:16.414 --> 08:08:20.565
It's been a very long standing case
and a difficult one to resolve.

49880358
08:08:20.566 --> 08:08:23.712
I am pleased to hear that
based on these discussions,

1409532517
08:08:25.260 --> 08:08:28.320
HS2 limited and her constituent
are on a path to resolution.

3543913615
08:08:28.321 --> 08:08:32.315
My department is committed to resolving
this situation whilst ensuring

4021556707
08:08:32.316 --> 08:08:37.962
value for money for the taxpayer
and fairness for her constituents.

2361877054
08:08:37.963 --> 08:08:41.659
The long term solution that HS2 limited
is focussed on is facilitating

3485451667
08:08:41.660 --> 08:08:44.319
and funding an alternative studio in

327116173
08:08:44.320 --> 08:08:46.760
the grounds of her constituents property.

3197827308
08:08:46.761 --> 08:08:50.016
I appreciate that this is
taking some time and there

2492156551
08:08:50.017 --> 08:08:52.861
may be a difference in
expectations between HS2

2895187154
08:08:52.862 --> 08:08:56.107
limited and her constituent
as to what constitutes

2188731430
08:08:56.108 --> 08:09:00.106
a reasonable replacement
of the existing studio.

2069196278
08:09:00.107 --> 08:09:02.757
However, we are committed
to doing the right

1367346522
08:09:02.758 --> 08:09:04.513
thing and delivering this at pace,

414530564
08:09:04.514 --> 08:09:08.025
and I'm aware that there's a further
on site meeting planned shortly.

3059437080
08:09:08.026 --> 08:09:10.922
I'm hopeful that an agreement
on the way forward

1773105955
08:09:10.923 --> 08:09:13.029
will soon be reached, and alongside this,

3170680057
08:09:13.260 --> 08:09:18.359
I understand that HS2 limited has
made further commitments in recent

654920662
08:09:18.360 --> 08:09:22.467
weeks to carry out any vibration
causing works earlier in the day,

2396616700
08:09:22.468 --> 08:09:24.827
in order to avoid
the times that would be most

1742887840
08:09:24.828 --> 08:09:28.613
disruptive to her constituents business.

4096919749
08:09:28.614 --> 08:09:32.717
Frankly, I have great sympathy
with the constituent in question.

916943546
08:09:33.255 --> 08:09:36.111
Disruptive works have continued
longer than anticipated,

3868230724
08:09:36.112 --> 08:09:39.473
and this has obviously taken longer
to resolve than we would wish,

3583581318
08:09:39.474 --> 08:09:44.366
and we hope to find resolutions that would

2735614938
08:09:44.367 --> 08:09:45.971
expedite this in further cases.

2542981540
08:09:45.972 --> 08:09:50.556
I just want to turn to more
general concerns about

3895948891
08:09:50.557 --> 08:09:52.761
compliance with
undertakings and assurance.

3409987832
08:09:54.256 --> 08:09:56.713
The Secretary of State
takes compliance with HS2

2292144633
08:09:57.263 --> 08:09:59.467
undertakings
and assurances very seriously.

2474141980
08:09:59.468 --> 08:10:02.855
There are rigorous structures
in place to manage compliance,

1162452251
08:10:02.856 --> 08:10:05.406
and its performance is
monitored closely by

3974373964
08:10:05.407 --> 08:10:07.764
the department and
the vast majority of cases.

3074819870
08:10:07.765 --> 08:10:09.068
Compliance has been good.

2533756622
08:10:09.069 --> 08:10:14.014
Out of nearly 5000 undertakings
and assurances on HS2

2249004685
08:10:14.015 --> 08:10:17.217
compliance has fallen short
in less than 1% of cases.

1324907471
08:10:17.218 --> 08:10:20.465
However, that is 1% to too many.

3013150757
08:10:20.466 --> 08:10:23.718
But the department does
remain confident that people

1377494620
08:10:23.719 --> 08:10:29.149
can rely on the commitments
that were made to them,

1599218064
08:10:29.150 --> 08:10:32.922
and those commitments and assurances
are given by the Secretary

3051094570
08:10:32.923 --> 08:10:36.717
of State to Parliament
during the HS2 Bill process.

2166550145
08:10:38.256 --> 08:10:40.212
And that's why HS2 limited delivery of

204739501
08:10:40.213 --> 08:10:42.618
them is overseen by our department,

2238421417
08:10:42.619 --> 08:10:45.258
and why the Secretary
of State is ultimately

975878250
08:10:45.259 --> 08:10:48.007
answerable to Parliament in these matters.

3675461179
08:10:48.008 --> 08:10:52.911
I'm really regretful that
we have very limited

2664848894
08:10:52.912 --> 08:10:54.667
time to to answer these questions.

1635030354
08:10:56.257 --> 08:10:58.315
I just want to assure her and other hon.

1369821738
08:10:58.316 --> 08:11:02.616
Members that there are layers
of independent scrutiny.

1724894607
08:11:02.617 --> 08:11:07.166
So HS2 limited is held to account
by the Secretary of State,

210814883
08:11:07.167 --> 08:11:10.711
who has that independent
statutory appeal function

3092831664
08:11:10.712 --> 08:11:12.667
between HS2 limited and other parties.

553230026
08:11:13.256 --> 08:11:15.313
And it's notable, I think, that there is

50239418
08:11:15.314 --> 08:11:17.118
only one assurance compliance case,

3649458792
08:11:17.119 --> 08:11:18.223
the one that the hon.

2778933582
08:11:20.260 --> 08:11:24.057
Member refers to, that's been
escalated beyond the department.

2353109820
08:11:24.058 --> 08:11:27.011
To the speaker As
the representative of Parliament,

2140612303
08:11:27.012 --> 08:11:28.768
we need to ensure that these cases

56112370
08:11:28.769 --> 08:11:30.775
are dealt with and dealt with properly,

713482921
08:11:30.776 --> 08:11:34.911
